text: We had been driving around for some time, on a weekday last week.  This was our last time in town, as we had sold our home in Alton.  So, after going to 3 different restaurants and finding that they are closed for various reasons, we decided we would come here.  WOW,  Seriously, everything happens for a reason, and WOW.   We were maybe one of the first patrons in the restaurant upon opening.  The ambiance is lovely.  We were greeted warmly initially, and the warmness continued throughout our visit.  As I said prior, the ambiance is lovely, the decor is SO just want to take it home.  The service was impeccable, our waitress was attentive, friendly, knowledgeable, and smiley.  OMG. The food.  THE FOOD!!!!  We had their summer special .  Holy COW, were they fantastic!  Entrees were   seafood shrimp Alfredo and our friend and I had the steak.  Honestly, you cannot go wrong with anything that you order from Tony's.  Top notch, old school dining experience, which is RARE.

name: All In Shipping
categories: Shipping Centers, Local Services
text: I love this little local business. They have everything I could ever need for local and long distance shipping along with a pleasant attitude that makes me a loyal customer. From boxes, to mailboxes, making keys, these guys have a great business that keeps people coming through the door.

name: K-9 Groom Room
categories: Pet Groomers, Pet Sitting, Pets, Pet Services

categories: Plumbing, Home Services
text: I have an AHS warranty. These guys were sent out. Spent all of 8 minutes tryi g to up lugged. Then told me I needed to put a clean out opening down stair in my finished basement bathroom. Which of course wouldn't be covered by my warranty. Called Roto Rooter, they came out had my drain unclogged in less than 15 minutes. Don't wastes your time or money. name: Heitz Optical
categories: Eyewear & Opticians, Sporting Goods, Shopping, Medical Supplies, Laser Eye Surgery/Lasik, Optometrists, Health & Medical, Outdoor Gear
text:
So thankful we discovered Heitz Optical.  What a great place!  The staff is friendly and very knowledgable about the eyewear they sell.  The Drs. are amazing too.  They are always punctual, and that is important to me. 

 One time I could not get to the office before they closed, and Drew took my contacts and put them in his mail box so I could get them from there on my way home from a meeting in STL.  Now that is customer service! 

We will always use Heitz Optical.

name: Chew Doin Fried Chicken & Ramen
categories: Restaurants, Chicken Shop, Ramen, Japanese
text:
I would give it 3.5 stars if Yelp allows me. 
I ordered the Steak Ramen and the Chicken ramen and a nashville fried chicken.
The Nashville Fried Chicken is so so delicious. It came with cole slaw, pickles, buns and 2 pieces of chicken. The chicken is moist, the skin is crispy is well-seasoned. The cole slaw goes really well with the spiciness of the chicken. 
Ramen: I would not say this is authentic ramen. Does not mean it is not good. It's just Asian-infused and more Westernized. Both steak ramen and chicken ramen are flavorful. The only thing I had to rate them down because they are both way too salty. I had to pour out all the broth in the bowl, put hot water in twice and it was still salty. 

I would definitely come back for Nashville Fried Chicken. Maybe will give Ramen another chance.

name: Ron & Jo's Firearms & Sporting Supplies
categories: Guns & Ammo, Sporting Goods, Shopping
text: Hands down the worst customer service every single time I've been there. They all act like they're better than their customers (if you can actually get one of them to speak to you at all) and condescend to you from start to finish. They are an absolute last resort for anything. Last straw was today when I stood in line for 30 minutes just to be able to go past the entrance and stand there for another almost 15 minutes while they all looked right at me and walked right past. Absolute trash.

name: Best Bridal Prices
categories: Shopping, Bridal
text:
After I found "the dress" at a local bridal boutique, I still wanted to do some price matching to see if I could get a better deal, as I had already raised the amount I was willing to spend for my wedding dress in order to get what I really wanted. I came across bestbridalprices.com but was skeptical about buying online due to horror stories I've read about. I did some research on the company and the designer of my dress (Sottero & Midgeley by Maggie Sottero) and found that the website was a "premier authorized dealer". The website is linked to the physical store called Frew's Bridal in Alton, IL. 

The price was the best that I found anywhere in the Chicago area by at least $400, not to mention they were running a deal to get a free veil up to $100 and free shoes up to $50 and free shipping (although there are restrictions on the designers to choose from). A pretty good deal that can save a decent amount of money! The ordering process was fairly easy as well, although I didn't have an area to provide comments or specify a hollow to hem size, which would have been nice since the dress fits perfectly except the length is way too long. The shipping was way faster than estimated!!! I ordered March 31st and it wasn't scheduled to be delivered until July, but it came at the beginning of June!! I know these have a lot to do with the designer, but the dress goes to the store first to be checked before being shipped to the customer, so still great turn-around time. When I received the dress, there were 2 small areas where the stitching was loose. I called the store in the required timeframe and they didn't hesitate to let me return it to have it fixed by the designer. I declined, opting to have my seamstress fix it when she shortens the dress, since it was very small fixes and my parents were visiting soon and I really wanted my mom to see the dress since it would be the only chance before the wedding next year. 

I have 2 complaints. First, the veil was delivered in a round plastic container and it was kind of folded in, so I'm going to have to mold it to shape to my head or it will be sticking out every which way. I wish they would ship them in a container where the whole thing can lay somewhat flat. Second, the shoes I ordered were 1/2 size too small (my big toes hung over the edge a bit). I tried to exchange them since I didn't wear them anywhere and they were still in the packaging in perfect condition, but they wouldn't do it. I even took extra time looking at similar shoes and sizes to try to get it right the first time, but you can never 100% get it right with different brands. I think this was completely unreasonable and stupid - so make sure to pick the right size. At least they were free, but I wouldn't order the right size from them since I don't want to chance that those could possibly still be the wrong size and not be able to exchange or return them.

Overall, great company to work with minus the whole shoe debacle.

text: Overall good experience from the from the front desk, to the tech who evaluated our dog and finally to the veterinarian who gave our dog the nose to tail exam. I highly recommend this place to anyone who needs veterinarian care.

categories: Restaurants, Salad, Soup, Sandwiches
text: Great Sammich!. I have never been here before and up until I saw the sign, had never heard of the place. This is a very clean establishment and the staff was very attentive, friendly, and eager to serve. The sub was amazing! I had the Bucky and was extremely satisfied with what I experienced from the first bite to the last. Fresh made with fresh ingredients. I also had a cup of chicken noodle which was just as tastey. If you are looking for the same old subway, this is not the place for you. Do yourself a favor and try a real sandwich served by the friendly staff at Subliminal.

name: My Vintage Addiction
categories: Antiques, Shopping
text:
My Vintage Addiction is a one-of-a-kind shop.  If you are a child of the 70s, you'll feel very nostalgic as you browse their ever-changing selection of hand-picked items.  They also sell handmade items from local artists, which is a huge plus!

My husband and I drive from Arnold, MO to visit - definitely worth the drive. 

Plus Courtney (owner) is super-sweet!

name: The TOCO Shop
categories: Fashion, Local Services, Community Service/Non-Profit, Shopping, Thrift Stores, Used, Vintage & Consignment
text:
The prices are great.  They even do bag sales twice a year to clear out their inventory.  They are also set up to help local people with the money that is made.

The not as great things is that they are pretty small (so less stuff), amd their hours are pretty limited (not open on Mondays and I think they close around 6pm otherwise).  However, it is clean and my favorite thrift store around, and who I donate to.

name: Ashley HomeStore

name: Super 8 by Wyndham Pontoon Beach IL/St. Louis MO Area
categories: Hotels & Travel, Event Planning & Services, Hotels
text:
Inexpensive, but needs some improvement.

Being one of the cheapest Wyndham hotels in the St. Louis area, I thought I'd give this Super 8 a shot. 

Checking in was fine, but as soon as I got to the stairwell, I noticed a very musty smell. The second floor hallway wreaked of smoke, even though smoking was supposedly not allowed. 

The room gave mixed impressions. The bed was nice, but the closest power outlet was literally attached to the wall with a piece of scotch tape. I tried plugging my phone in for a charge and it kept falling out. 

Checkout was very slow. Usually Wyndham properties allow express checkout, but not here. After waiting for about 15 minutes, the lady at the desk prints my receipt, only to walk away and say she'll be right back. I guess she went to check that the room was left in good enough condition to return the security deposit. Either way, it was one of the slowest checkouts I've ever had. 

If you're looking for a budget stay and won't mind a few of the issues listed above, then you may be fine staying here for a night.

text: Hands down, one of the BEST steak places around! The atmosphere- an "adult" restaurant, with "adult" servers! No screaming, crying children. Light music, great service, great food. Very relaxing dinner! Have never had a bad meal and drinks are great too!!!

name: U.s. Post Office
categories: Post Offices, Public Services & Government
text: This post office is one of the worst.  The employees are worse than indifferent.  It always seems to be short on personnel and those who are there are slow and make it obvious they couldn't care less about customer service.  Instead, their demeanor seems to say they are doing you a favor by allowing you to do business there.  It is always out of numbers, which allows for line jumping and other confusion. There is only one worker that stands out in this office.  Her name is Pam.  I don't know her personally but she is the only one that displays a level of professionalism and good service.

name: HCI Alternatives
categories: Cannabis Dispensaries, Health & Medical, Cannabis Clinics, Shopping
text:
After going over to,"Cracker Barrell" in Troy,IL today for lunch,we made a little trip to Collinsville,IL to check out,"HCI Alternatives" , our new Medical Marijuanna Dispensary for the
Medical Marijuanna Pilot Program here in IL.
  As I eagerly await my,"Illinois Medical Marijuanna  Card" here in southern IL. (It takes 2-3 months to get your card back from the state of IL) I'm educating myself about everything I need to know 
as a pt./client of this most worthy pilot program.
  HCI opened up both in Collinsville & Springfield,Il dispensaries after medical marijuanna was approved by the voters of our state.
   I'm very much impressed w/ their set-up thus far, & look forward to becoming a regular client.

text:
Nice, clean place, good Mexican food but not great

Bar does not have the same choices that Las Tres Marias had, but it is OK.  I need to sample a few more items before I write a thorough review, but so far the food was good, but not great.  Prices are OK.
I prefer Lafanda's in Edwardsville for this price range.
I also think their menu is just too big.  Cut down on the menu, offer less choices but do the things you do top notch.

name: Martin Glass Company
categories: Contractors, Shopping, Kitchen & Bath, Building Supplies, Windshield Installation & Repair, Home & Garden, Home Decor, Plumbing, Automotive, Glass & Mirrors, Auto Glass Services, Home Services
text: While I was pleased that they were able to come replace my windshield at my place of employment, and they did a good job, the workers also left my car unlocked and the driver-side window rolled down, which I didn't discover until the end of the day.  So my car sat totally vulnerable to thieves for hours.  Thank goodness nothing appeared to have been stolen.  I definitely won't be using Martin Glass again.

name: Post Pack & Ship
categories: Packing Services, Shipping Centers, Local Services, Home Services
text: Exceptional service, friendly and caring staff and owners, hometown type atmosphere and business, delivered with a true expertise in knowledge. A family who runs their business the way I tried to run mine for over twenty years, with professionalism while still making you feel as though you were one of the family. I wouldn't go anywhere else.

name: The Green Solution
categories: Shopping, Health & Medical, Cannabis Clinics, Cannabis Dispensaries

name: U.S. Bank Branch
categories: Financial Services, Real Estate, Home Services, Banks & Credit Unions, Mortgage Brokers, Financial Advising
text: I opened an account for personal checking account with free ATM card almost 5 months ago.  2 months in a row got charged $57.90 for the "ability" to use my ATM card which I just got in the mail last Saturday!  The only charge I am supposed to have is $6.95/mo for maintenance fees. I just got my checks today!  Also, since opening it until last week (almost 5 months later) I have not been able to log on online, make deposits, or even use my account because all I was given when I opened the account was a handshake and a brochure with a post it with a bad online login password & ID stuck to it.  I have called and even talked to the agent that did setup & no answers except "they are in the mail" & that they can't fix online or tell me my account info so I can use teller until they come.  Seriously?  How do they expect happy customers when they can't use their money?!  Everyone else kept sending me back to original agent even though I explained situation.  It was only resolved after the items finally arrived and someone took pity on me and helped.  Still, I have these bogus charges for a total of $115.80 that has been taken from my account for which there has still been no explanation or refund for.

name: Auffenberg Mazda
categories: Car Dealers, Auto Repair, Auto Parts & Supplies, Automotive
text: I took my AutoTrader Trade-In Marketplace price quote here, and they refuse to honor it (or even offer a price at all).  If they are this hard to deal with when I'm trying to use a program they are participating in, I'm not going to find out how they are when negotiating a price to buy a car.  I frequently buy and sell cars, but I won't be coming to the Auffenburg dealerships for my next car.  I also won't be bothering with AutoTrader's Trade-In program either.  One good part - the staff was friendly and made time to look at the Trade-In offer certificate.

text:
I give it a 2; 1 point for being open 24 hours and another point for not being a chain restaurant.  The food was typical to something you could order at denny's/waffle house, but probably grimier.  

But, I have to say, with a couple of drinks in me and every other restaurant kitchen closed within walking distance from main street in Belleville, the food tasted pretty good!  I had a waffle with syrup; good enough to please me in this moment of hunger.

Service was not friendly, but I wasn't expecting much.  Go there if you are completely out of options and are under the influence.  I know for me, otherwise, I wouldn't have liked it!

categories: Mexican, Restaurants
text:
Poor service but it depends entirely on which waiter.  We've gone there often and the food is better than average (with one exception see below) and had good service, but this trip, it was almost 10 minutes to even get a waiter to come by and give chips and salsa and get drink order (I was 1 minute from just getting up and leaving).  The food came for the 3 of us, but not a plate in sight to eat off of when we clearly stated in the beginning that we were sharing the 3 dishes.  Watching him with other tables, he was clearly only paying attention as it came time to leave a tip, but not at other times during the meal.  That being said, we have been happy with other wait staff on other visits.

The Shrimp Nachos were a huge disappointment, the limp nachos and less than generous amount of shrimp were buried under a large amount of lettuce.  I've never seen lettuce on nachos.

We'll be back, but we will watch which waiter serves us.

name: MassageLuXe
categories: Day Spas, Skin Care, Massage, Beauty & Spas
text: So impressed with the facility. So clean and just so organized and the staff was so professional and super courteous. For a mommy of 3 this was truly a one hour getaway for me!! I LOVED IT! I loved it so much that I joined the membership program and guess what the first month was only $10!!!  AMAZING!!!  My masseuse was Roy and he did so outstanding working out all the kinks outta my neck and back!! Cant wait to go back for my next message/facial. Oh and with the membership you get to use their waterbed massager thingy literally every day and I don't doubt their facility so I know they sanitize that bed.

name: Edwardsville Endodontics
categories: Endodontists, Health & Medical, Dentists
text: Dr Etcheson is such a caring doctor. He is extremely careful to make sure his patients are completely comfortable.

name: Midwest Appliance & Repair
categories: Local Services, Appliances & Repair, Home & Garden, Appliances, Shopping
text:
Last year we bought a washing machine from Dale, the owner, and were so happy with the condition of the machine, service (delivered next day and for free and old washer was hauled away), and price, that we recently went back to buy a dishwasher, electric range, and fridge. 

We totally recommend that you shop Midwest first and you will find Dale offers an good selection of appliances at a price that can't be beat. His delivery and install guys are great too and were careful of our floors and walls when hauling away old stuff and bringing in the new.

name: Service Protection Direct
categories: Automotive, Auto Repair
text:
Hello Yelp users,

I wanted to share the information I searched about this company on Ripoff.com and USA.gov. As many of you did, I received their mail today (July 26, 2014) and something raised a big red flag on my mind as soon as I read their letter - no company logo, too many words in bold and italic. I became curious and googled the company's address and found some nasty information that should impact your decision. I posted a snapshot of their letter for your reference.

* RELATED REPORTS
- Palm Beach County Consumer Affairs Division (latest dispute record on Feb 20 2014) http://www.pbcgov.com/pubsafety/consumer/asps/BusinessInformationReport.asp?hrfBusSeq=800492&hrfBusName=Service%20Protection%20Direct&hrfProductSeq=0

- Ripoff report#1: http://www.ripoffreport.com/r/Marathon-Administrative/Select-StateProvince/Marathon-Administrative-Service-Protection-Direct-RIPOFF-DONT-BE-A-FOOL-AND-FALL-FOR-T-1124176

text: Came in on a Saturday night at 630 and even though they were a bit busy, we got a table immediately. The wait staff was prompt and we ordered a appetizer sampler and a large pizza. The pizza isn't greasy and was delicious, it has a sweet tasting tomato base. The owner was walking around and stopped to talk with us. He explained that they make all their food is made by hand and they use fresh ingredients. You can tell. Not badly priced, 4 drinks, large speciality pizza, and the appetizer was 48.00 not too bad in my book. We will definitely be back. I'm looking forward to trying the deep dish next time.

name: Dizzy Dugout Cards, Comics & Games
categories: Shopping, Tabletop Games, Books, Mags, Music & Video, Hobby Shops, Comic Books
text:
This place is a hoarders dream. Be careful, or you might trip over one of the hundreds of items strewn on the floor. If you have any allergies or possess any form of claustrophobia stay far away, as this place is dusty, dark and cramped. Additionally, unless you are dealing with the middle-aged gentleman (appearing to be the manager, who was outgoing and helpful) expect to receive the same sub-par service I have received on my various trips to this place. Want to see something under the counter? Good luck: the counters are so cluttered with junk it's nearly impossible to see what's being shown. 

They do have some of their card collections catalogued, but with as unorganized as the store is, do not expect it to be up to date. 

I would try other places first if you can. They need a liquidation company or the guy from CNBC's "the profit" to come in and give them a hand.

text:
Went on Saturday Aug 23, 2014. 

They are a little higher price than the other.   First tray wasn't wiped down thoroughly, second was slightly damp. 

Second.   They didn't have shredded  lettuce for tacos.    Husband prefers that to eat with salad.

Third the waitress was working quite a few tables, where there was another waitress who was waiting very few tables and was barely doing that.

Now recall this was a Saturday night, so it was quite busy.     

We even asked if our waitress if they were over worked and she stated just me.

The lady who was waiting on us was so overwhelmed that she ended up quitting.

My husband mentioned that the one lady wasn't doing anything and the other was over worked, she basically said that the just started at 5 pm.   

Granted people might have less tables if they worked longer, however the difference in amount of tables were greatly different and she basically was dismissive of my husband.     Since she walked off.

Oh and the person who was supposed to take over her tables never got us anything else to drink.

So I had to drink from my husband's glass.

We will never go back to this location.  

Been to plenty across the nation, some are good and some aren't, and this was the worse as for customer service.

name: Illinois Division of Motor Vehicles
categories: Public Services & Government, Departments of Motor Vehicles
text:
I went here yesterday to get my drivers license and today to get my plates and registration. I drove down here from Pontoon Beach/Granite City (25 minute drive), because the DMV in Granite and in Edwardsville both have a lot of horrible reviews on google. Each time I went there, and signed in, I was promptly helped by a competent and clear person. The entire process was pretty painless. The place seemed well organized and the staff seemed interested in doing a good job, and helping things flow along. When new people came in, someone would check on whether they had signed in and were at the right window. The personalities of the people who helped me varied a bit, one guy was pretty low key and reserved, a woman was bubbly and cheerful, etc. But everyone was polite and respectful. 

There is a LOT of documentation you need to bring if you move from out of state and want to get a license in Illinois. Includes proof of SS#, Identification, two documents proving Illinois residence, and another proof. I brought a SS card, Drivers License, a bank statement and a bill both sent to my current IL address and that was sufficient. But you need to check carefully the website to make sure you bring the right things for whatever you want to get done. If you want to get your Illinois plates, don't forget your title (forgot that the first time - needed to go back). If you don't have the right documentation, there is not much they can do for you. The good news is that they know what is needed and are willing to explain it to you clearly and politely, and once you have what you need, they do everything with you.

After they filled in the required paperwork on their computers, they printed it out for me to check. There were minor errors at some times (e.g., one person got the county of Granite City wrong) so I 'm glad they were very patient about this and glad that I checked carefully. 

The drivers test on the computer is kind of a joke how easy it is. Questions sort of seemed like "is it okay to drive while intoxicated"? or asking you to identify a stop sign. But it was sort of fun to review these basic things. 

When you get your license, they ask you if you want to be registered to vote. This is a nice touch and I appreciated getting these done at once. 

Going to the DMV is certainly not a highlight of anyone's life, but at this office, at least, the experience was pleasant enough and I felt like state dollars weren't going to waste. 

One more thing: based on the pictures everywhere, the current Secretary of State kinda looks like OJ Simpson!

categories: Home Services, Baby Gear & Furniture, Furniture Stores, Home & Garden, Shopping, Local Flavor, Interior Design
text:
I just rolled into Chesterfield, MO and was told by a friend to check out Mueller's. Although it's a good 35 minute drive I decided to have some trust and  check it out. I was not disappointed.

Rebekah greeted me with open arms and showed me around to all the different areas for the things I was looking for. I needed furniture within the next three days delivered and as long as I was okay with taking a floor model they promised to get it to me two days later (which they did). The prices were great and Mueller's is very good with haggling and throwing in perks.

I ended up getting three bedroom sets, a dining room table, kitchen table and living room set delivered to me in two days. The delivery guys were great and polite and stayed in contact with me so that I knew the precise time that they would arrive (perfect for those who need to do errands in the interim). 

I will definitely go back to Mueller's for more furniture in the future!

Hers is perfect but mine has 6 lines in the staff instead of 5. It looks fine but it pisses me off every time I look at it  because the notes BFF are not the same if the staff has 6  lines. What pisses me off even more is that I drew and approved the sketch so I know that it had the correct number of lines on it. Like I said, my friend's is fine. Waste of money.

name: Aroy Thai
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Caters': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'Corkage': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': None, 'valet': False}", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': None, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}", 'BYOB': 'False'}
categories: Thai, Restaurants
text:
Better than any of the Thai I have tried in or around downtown St Louis or Grand!

I'll gladly make the trek from south city to O'Fallon to get this delicious, superior and value Thai.

Having been twice, I am ashamed to admit that I am addicted to their Drunken Noodles so I have had that each visit, albeit once chicken and once pork.

The appetizers are delicious.  Have tried the spring rolls, chicken satay and chicken pot-stickers and they were all satisfying.

The waiter/waitress will ask you what level you want your heat if you get a spicy dish.  They ask you on a scale of 1 to 4.  First visit I asked for 3 and the dish was very nice.  Last visit I went 4 and while it was definitely a "sinus opening experience" the food is pleasantly hot without any of the ill side-effects later on...if you know what I mean.

The menu has over 100 items on it and while some of the other reviews complain of the vegetables being "not fresh" I can only compare Aroy with the pricey city Thai I've had in/around St Louis and I put Aroy equal of better with HUGE portion sizes at very reasonable prices.

Each visit I have found the service to be attentive and available.  Once during Saturday lunch rush and another post-lunch afternoon.

Walk-in takeout service seemed very quick for those I observed on my visits.

I've been to Thailand a few times and while you'll never beat home-cooked Thai with exported fare, I have nothing bad to say about Aroy Thai.  It's where I'll be taking my out-of-town guests and where I'll go for takeout when the urge hits. 

Looking forward to my next visit to explore more of their menu choices...unless those Drunken Noodles get me again!

text: My coworkers and I have decided that we are going to do a bakery crawl every Wednesday. This week crawl for me at A Little Taste of Heaven. This place is right off of Main St in Edwardsville, IL. This is a grab and go place. Parking lot across the street. The bakery boasts chairs but only in their front window. The owners greet the customers and it is a quick grab and go. Today we tried the cookies, They had four different kinds in the case, and after I got my order and man walked in and asked for the cookies that they were famous for, just my luck they were coming out of the oven. They are a triple(yes triple) chocolate cookie. I selected the Blueberry Almond cookie, it was chocked full of blueberries, I almost did not feel guilty eating it because it had two super foods (blueberry and almonds). We also got the chocolate chip, this was a little crusty, I am sure it would be a good dunking cookie, but I only dunk basketballs not cookies. Finally we got the oatmeal raisin. It was a nice cookie, but I think my recipe is better. The place lives up to its name... Bonus, they do sell coffee to go...No almond milk though.

name: Wood Bakery
categories: Donuts, Restaurants, Food, Bakeries
text:
Surprise to see so many 5 stars.  I went in with high expectations and was sadly disappointed.  I gave this place two visits just in case the first time was just an off day. 
Allow me to explain!  Heading out for work, I had a craving for donuts. I typically do not eat sweets so early but chocolate glazed sounded good. Read good reviews and had to see for myself. Well, place is nothing  spectacular.   I was expecting full racks, shelves and trays stacked with goodies and glass display cabinets filled with cakes of all sorts. What I saw, instead, were half empty racks, table of cookies had few selections and atmosphere did not have the great aroma of a fresh bakery. And to top it off, my cashier very young lady was not that friendly. Did not even make eye contact as she accepted my payment.  Like I said, maybe just an off day! 
So I return another day. And, this time it was in the afternoon. Did not see another customer so I figured quick service. Well, three employees were there talking fairly loud. One acknowledged my presence and gave me a greeting. She had to get through two other employees deep in their loud conversation. The lady taking my order had to asked me twice what I said.  She would apologize for not hearing me the first time as she also apologized for the loud noise coming from the other two.  I got my order and went on my way. 
The donuts are ok.  I could buy from grocery store and be just as satisfied. I would visit again just to try other items. I do support local family businesses so give this place a try.

name: Value City Furniture
categories: Home Decor, Home & Garden, Mattresses, Furniture Stores, Shopping
text:
You think Value City, you think cheap value, right? Wrong! 

Think Rothman prices with Ashley Furniture pieces. Not a Broyhill in sight. 

Negatives:
- Entertainment centers and TV stand selection is small, and over priced selection.
-Their "Clearance" section is laughable and not much of a sale. No one is going to pay $299 for a nicked up coffee table that was originally $350. Go lower. 
- Sectionals by themselves average around $1,000 by brands I've never heard of. 
- The staff hangs out like a clique chatting in the middle of the store rather than helping customers. 
-Dining sets are nothing special and overpriced as well. I've seen the same selection everywhere else at a lower price. 
-5% military discount? Ooooh you're going to knock $20 off my sofa! 

Only Positive:
-They have a few modern pieces. 

Overall:

I think they're high for low quality-mediocre furniture. Shop around town. Or if you do find something you must have here, wait for a holiday sale.

text:
This is going to be a very mixed review. Last time we went it was pizza & wings. Tonight we went and it brand new menu. Lots of burgers, sandwiches, sliders, flatbread and pitas. 
Pros: Loved sweet hot wings, main reason for visit delicious! Also our waiter Jacob was complete professional and I dare said best waiter I've ever had.
Now the bad...
Cons: I ordered the Fried chicken sliders and it was a chicken nugget on a bun twice it's size. Also both types of fries were unseasoned. Also no children's menu. 

The manager did come over at end of meal to see how we liked everything and mentioned the lunch buffet has items on it (like the pulled pork which is amazing) that is not on the menu to get people in the door during their slow time. My husband and I were puzzled by this because we see buffets as way of sampling menu and then come back and order pulled pork sandwich at dinner time but that is what she explained.

All in all we will be back for the wings and possibly lunch buffet.

name: Massage Envy - O'Fallon-IL
categories: Massage, Health & Medical, Skin Care, Day Spas, Massage Therapy, Beauty & Spas
text: Horrible experience. Do not get involved. Inconsistent therapists. I became a member, I tried booking my appts online, they didn't respond to me. When I called, their lame excuse was "if there's no space available we may or may not call you back." The "quiet room" is  joke, people on their cell phones, rules not enforced. Last appt I had my therapist was 10 minutes late, he didn't seem to appreciate return clientele even though I tip more than 20%. When my 6 mos was up my credit card was expired so I naturally just quit making payments. I just wasn't going to go back even though I had 3 massages left. Well I got a notice from a collection agency, apparently the account "rolls over," now they're saying I owe them $180 for nothing AND I can't cancel or use the credits I legitimately paid for since my account is in "bad standing." These people are thieves I do not recommend getting involved with them. I called and spoke with the manager Lori  who had the audacity to tell me I "had to understand their point of view" and if "I chose to be difficult" she wouldn't help me. So basically they expect me to pay them $60 so I can use the credits I paid for and cancel, which since I'm canceling I have to use within 30 days. My advice: spend your money with an independent/self employed therapist who appreciates your business and will be paid well for their services. This place screws their clientele AND therapists. If they keep treating people like this they will be out if business soon.

text:
Ok I was traveling through and it caught me eye so I tried it! When I went to post this I saw there are mixed reviews; people love it or hate it! It may be what you order. I tried the PIG sandwich and it was amazing! The twisted taters were freaking great and everything was ultra hot; I loved that! Now I went through around 11:15am. Also got a concrete and threw a coozie around it and it was still cold and not melted by the time I finished the meal.

I did not try the brisket, and I can tell you from my travels and dining experiences that brisket is an art to prepare well and often bbq places dry it out too much. I can also tell you this; look at my reviews I travel the US extensively with work and especially the mid and Deep South and I eat at lots of bbq places. The sandwich I had today was one of the best ever I have had. It was a little fatty, but one of the meats on it is pork belly, duh that will be fatty. I like a little fat not loaded but a little for flavor and juiciness. The portion was huge. I will be back and I would try it if you are looking for something local

name: Bobeck's Sports Bar & Grill
categories: Nightlife, Bars, American (Traditional), Restaurants
text:
This was our last stop on the way home. The waitress greeted us, with menu in hand and drink special. Half the party decided on the 6 beers for $15. We also ordered a margarita and glass of white zin. We informed the waitress that we just wanted to have drinks and watch the basketball games. Fine, she would check on us from time to time. We decided that we need some food. We ordered wings, smothered buffalo chips and the new pretzels stiks. Much to our delight the pretzels stiks were from Gus's Pretzels. The wings had just the right amount of seasoning and spice, to be tasteful but not over powering. Finally, the smothered buffalo chips. I thought the buffalo was a little strong, but the rest of the party enjoyed them. 

This is a fun place. The restrooms were clean, except they had an extremely loud hand dryer.

name: Olive Oils & More
categories: Specialty Food, Olive Oil, Food
text: Olive Oils and More-  This  mother/ son team are versed not only on the quality difference in their products, but also in matching specific oils, vinegars and other culinary ingredients with the dishes you intend to create.  Understanding and sharing the alchemy that is created when selecting and matching the perfect ingredients, whether oils, vinegars,  is where they  differentiate themselves. It's encouraged to slurp!  oils Strippaggio is the term used to describe the slurping employed by an olive oil taster after taking an oil sample into his or her mouth. This technique allows a complete sensory experience of the oil compared to just sipping the oil.  So slurp away at this family run business.  You will also discover amazing pastas, and don't forget to return your used bottles.

name: Gateway Center
categories: Event Planning & Services, Venues & Event Spaces
text:
I go to a lot of cons, and thus, have experienced a lot of Convention Centres. I went here for the 2007 NASFiC which was also Archon for the year and was simply unimpressed with the space. It's sad because I really would have liked it. 

The first thing is that it's located in the middle of freakin' nowhere from the point of view of someone who isn't from around those parts. It's about 30 minutes out of town, with no direct way to get there except for SuperShuttle, which costs a ton. A Taxi will run you 'OH MY GOD!" and if you try to take the lightrail you're a fool. Just a fool. 

Now, once you're there, there's everything you need to keep yourself from experience too much of the world outside the convention center area. There are varying levels of restaurant within walking distance and a dozen or so hotels. I stayed at the Drury Inn. There's a Mexican place, whcih is OK, and there's a White Castle, which I put a hurt on the first day I was there. There's a lovely Rudy Tuesday, and after years of seeing their commercials in a state that has no Ruby Tuesday, I was glad to get to see one in person. 

The real problem is the Convention Centre itself. The rooms are weirdly set-up and I had a real problem finding the rooms where the various programmes were. The signage was poor and at a couple of points it seemed to indicate that the same room was in two different places. The thing could handle a good-sized con, but it also had some serious bottlenecks that you don't have to deal with at the best CCs.

name: Collinsville Aqua Park
categories: Water Parks, Active Life, Amusement Parks
text:
Working for a teen camp, you have to find things for teenagers to do.  What better way to cool off than at a water park.  Add to it, a long bus ride on the hottest day of the summer (or so it would seem).

The park is located in Collinsville, and conveniently located near 55/70 and 255, so it is a bit of a drive, if you aren't from the area, but who doesn't like a road trip?

Splash City is open 11 am-7pm.  If you arrive after 4pm, you get $5 off your admission!  Prices start at $13 for children and $16 for adults.  These are for non Collinsville residents.  

Now for the attractions.  There is this wave machine called "Flow Rider" in which you get up on a surfboard.  That was way cool!  Monsoon Mountain is the bucket attraction that pours water on you, and there are water slides as well.  

They have concession if you get hungry and there is a store, in case you need a new swimsuit or more sunscreen.  

What better way to beat the heat!

name: Mello Freeze

text: I've been seeing Dr Darin for 2 years now, and wow what a difference in the way I feel! Doc is awesome, very knowledgeable, but explains everything in a way that makes sense. The staff is ahhhhh-mazing too! Honestly it's like a 2nd home! During this pandemic, they have taken all the necessary precautions. The facility is pristine and social distance is practiced. Your spine is in great hands with Darin Chiropractic!

text: I have been a fan of Chateau La Vin for a few years. It has been fun to watch the place evolve. At first it was more of a wine store with only a few tables. Now it has been transformed into a wine bar. He offers cheese and crackers and people order from the local restaurants and some of them even deliver. He had two guys playing music. He offers so many different wines and is willing to share his knowledge. My friend is a beer drinker and he has a nice variety for them as well. He does have a few tables out in front. This is a great place.....

name: Hampton Inn & Suites St. Louis-Edwardsville
categories: Hotels & Travel, Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Venues & Event Spaces
text:
Settled just outside of the busy city, this hotel is located just off the highway, yet is secluded enough for a quiet stay. 

We stayed here overnight during a cross-country trek and the staff, facility and overall stay was perfect. The fitness area had adequate machines for exercise, and the pool and hot tub were a nice was to relax after a long day on the road. 

Being a Hilton Honors member, I look forward to the comforts of the Hilton chains- like home away from home.

name: Tiger Plumbing Heating Air Conditioning & Electrical Services
categories: Professional Services, Heating & Air Conditioning/HVAC, Home Services, Electricians, Plumbing
text:
We bought the membership program for plumbing, electrical and air conditioning. They would come out periodically to check, but it was only just an excuse to try to sell us new and unnecessary parts. 

After calling to cancel the $35 per month charge, I was told I had to send a written request by email or regular mail, and it would take 30 days for it to be cancelled. Of course that means they get another payment out of me. 

30 days?  Sleezeballs.

name: MERS Goodwill
categories: Shopping, Local Services, Community Service/Non-Profit, Thrift Stores
text:
This is what I would consider a fast-paced Goodwill. If you don't move quickly, you likely won't find much.
That being said, I have spent many a slow evening looking through the clothing racks and scoring on items like a Tory Burch cardigan, new Kut from the Kloth jeans, and more. But this is not the norm, it is the exception. Thrill of the hunt!
The housewares, furniture, and shoes are pretty run-of-the-mill. I rarely find anything.
DO NOT GO ON THE WEEKENDS. It is a madhouse. Parents do not watch their children and I don't know if the workers say anything. 
If I could rate the finds at this store, it would be 3/5. Mostly mall brands (huh, is that a mall across the street?) and occasionally higher-end items.
All in all, it's a good place to hunt, but don't be surprised if you leave empty-handed.

name: Mississippi Mud Pottery
categories: Home & Garden, Shopping, Home Decor, Arts & Crafts
text: Wonderful store with beautiful work!  The talented and friendly artists have it to where you can watch them work in the shop; always a treat to see artists demo. Variety of pottery is strong for daily use as well as display with unique designs.  Definitely worth stopping in while in the area.

name: Walmart Supercenter
categories: Shopping, Department Stores, Drugstores, Grocery, Discount Store, Pharmacy, Food, Fashion, Electronics, Health & Medical
text: This Walmart has appallingly bad reviews and a low rating. I'm giving them a pass. It's Walmart you guys. Are you expecting white glove service? I'm not. It serves its purpose. That doesn't mean you shouldn't wipe down your cart really well with those sanitizing wipes by the door and try not to touch anything you don't have to touch. You should!

name: Safelite AutoGlass
categories: Windshield Installation & Repair, Body Shops, Auto Glass Services, Automotive, Auto Repair
text: Excellent service. Got me in quickly. Was told you may not even be able to see where the chip was but my concern was that it not spread. You can barely see where the chip was in the windshield and so far it has held up. Staff is courteous. They will come to you if necessary. No complaints

name: LaRosa's Flowers
categories: Party Supplies, Shopping, Flowers & Gifts, Florists, Gift Shops, Party & Event Planning, Event Planning & Services, Baby Gear & Furniture
text: I bought a floral arrangement for a funeral.  I needed it in kind of a hurry.  They got it there early, it was very affordable and was the best looking one there.  Unlike most arrangements I have purchased from photos online, though never here, this one looked better in person than it did on the picture on the website.  The staff was friendly and polite and the flowers were wonderful.

name: Country Hearth Inn & Suites Edwardsville St. Louis
categories: Hotels & Travel, Hotels, Event Planning & Services
text: I have to say you get MORE for what you pay! This hotel is clean and organized. The staff are very respectful and responsive! ALSO breakfast was excellent!! OMG eggs, sausage, waffles, OJ, you name it!

name: Michael Murphy, OD
address: 4933 Benchmark Centre Dr, Ste D, Vision Care Associates
categories: Optometrists, Health & Medical
text:
I had been looking for a regular office I could use for my whole family. You can book appointments online any they provide text reminders for upcoming appointments (really convenient).  Dr. Mike offers the type of personalized care that is hard to find from the chain vision stores. He worked well with the kids and provided explanations of the evaluations and the results. 

I really enjoyed discussing the difference between the different brands of contacts that are out there and why his office chose the brand they use now. He was never condescending and was patient when working with the kids. I will return again and would recommend to anyone looking for a good eye doctor.

name: Nailhaus
categories: Beauty & Spas, Nail Salons
text: The service here is terrible. After a fill in my nail and the acrylic cracked in half there he used the blade. I called up there and the man who answered said they'll fix it. Once I got there they tried to charge me 10 to fix something that was their fault. Then the man at station 5 caught an attitude because I wouldn't let him pull my broken nail off that was still connected to my skin. He then told me he wasn't fixing my nail.

name: Allergy, Asthma & Immunology Center
categories: Health & Medical, Allergists, Doctors, Immunodermatologists, Internal Medicine
text: The staff her have the biggest most caring hearts. They truly care about people

name: Two Men and a Truck St. Louis East
categories: Home Services, Movers, Shopping, Packing Services, Packing Supplies
text:
Helping my friend move across the river from IL to the STL side. No hurry to move all at once,  but wanted to move the big stuff all at one time and have it done seamlessly! 

Tony & Courtney arrived at 9:00 on the dot (said B/T 9-10) and were ready to go! To expedite things, I had sectional couch disassembled as well as bed and most everything ready as possible.  They came in with clean blankets, wrapped everything then followed that up with shrink wrap to each article taken into the truck. 

They were both most professional in appearance, experience, attitude, manners, correspondence and work ethic. Had the truck loaded in almost no time (very efficient), and were punctual in arriving at new residence as well.  Unloading was just as easy and could not have expected anything more from these two gentlemen. 

Lost count of the number of times they offered to move a specific item to exact location and set things a certain way. That has not been my experience with moving companies in the past. 

Based on phone conversation when scheduling the appointment, the quote was spot on regarding the time it would take, if not less. 

It is worth a bit extra in saved time and piece of mind by hiring professionals (if within budget), versus renting a truck and utilizing friends..  

This was the first time using this company and glad we did! 

Thank you!

text: I attended a comedy show on 8/12 with Johnny Behner as the headliner! This was my first time at this specific comedy club. The atmosphere was stunning with painted portraits of comedians throughout the walls. The service was excellent, and the food/drinks were not overpriced. The owner spoke to the audience, and he was gracious, humble, and hilarious! This is a gem in Southern Illinois. Johnny Behner was incredibly funny and natural. He interacted with the crowd in a sweet/charming manner. I highly recommend taking in a show at Hey Guys! It's a great venue with awesome and inspiring talent!

name: The Blonde Salon & Spa
categories: Community Service/Non-Profit, Local Services, Nail Salons, Makeup Artists, Beauty & Spas, Day Spas, Bridal, Tutoring Centers, Education, Hair Salons, Massage, Shopping, Specialty Schools
text:
I am from WA state and was in town visiting my sister the week of Thanksgiving. She scheduled us hair appointments with Ally W.  I was very nervous because I hadn't colored my hair in 7 years(it was just a very boring brown color) ;) I have hard water and didn't want my water to change the colors. I explained to her kind of what I wanted (blonde highlights) then told her about my hard water. She said she had a plan for me and would love to do caramel since my water is so hard. I let her do what she thought was best (usually I wouldn't), but she seemed to know what she was talking about and was VERY VERY confident in her job. I trusted her and walked out of the salon feeling fabulous. She did such an amazing job and I have never gotten so many compliments on my hair.  I love the confidence that she had and she was so personable. If I lived closer I would go back in a heartbeat. The next time I come and visit I will definitely be making another appointment with her. Thank you again Ally. 
Carrie

name: Kelly's Limousine Service
categories: Transportation, Party Bus Rentals, Event Planning & Services, Hotels & Travel, Airport Shuttles, Limos
text:
Very disappointed and NOT RECOMMENDED!
We rented a limo for a bachelor party on Friday December 27th. 
The day I booked the rental they charged my debit card $100 deposit. 
I received a confirmation via email with pick up address and confirmed via email. 
The driver was to pick us up at 830PM.  At 9PM I started calling the main number I booked the reservation through.  I talked to a guy who said he would call me right back he had to find the driver.  After 20 minutes i called back.  No answer. 
I then navigated through the entire phone tree by pressing numerous prompts and finally got an emergency number.  I called that number and got Pam. She said she would find the driver.  Again the same story.  She called back 10 minutes later and said they had to cancel, could not find the driver!  How does a company not know where their drivers are?  How can a company just decide to cancel one hour after they are supposed to be there?  There was no apology in her voice.  Just sorry had to cancel.  Kellys was sure quick to take my $100 out of my account the day I booked. But NOT customer service oriented to cancel before I had to call them! 
Never again and I tell everyone not to use Kellys in Belleville IL! 
They could have offered to maybe provide a few hours of free drive time for the local wedding etc. Something to make up for the inconvenience.  But I guess they have so much business they did not care!

Chicken was good but salad that came with lunch was full of water and premade. Server never refilled my drink and had to be tracked down. Twice. Tables were not full. Place was empty.

name: Best Friends Animal Hospital & Pet Resort
categories: Veterinarians, Pet Sitting, Pets, Pet Services
text: It is hard to find a good reptile vet. This hospital has the best herp vet we have ever been to, and we do know our herp vets! We have had Tibby our turtle for over 10 years, he is a part of our family!  I highly recommend Dr. Craig. It is evident he is extremely passionate about exotic animals care, and he is especially knowledgable about reptiles and amphibs. He spent a great deal of time talking to us and explaining things, and he even followed up our visit with a personal email after he had done some research. How awesome is that?! We will take Tibby back to him for our yearly check-ups and are so glad he is in our neighborhood!

attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Caters': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'Alcohol': "'full_bar'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}"}
categories: American (Traditional), Seafood, Restaurants
text:
I have been reading different reviews on Yelp just to see what people have to say about different places. Yelp seems to be a place where anyone can say anything about every business. After reading some of the reviews just about Joes I am horrified. I have eaten here several times and loved the food and the service. 

Don't go to a place where the staff dance and sing if you don't like that sort of thing. That seems to be YOUR problem. Not Joes. The food is delicious and yes, the staff is made up of young people. Who do you expect to be waiting on you....your tax attorney? 

I have found everything delightful every time I have eaten here. I am sure I don't understand why the internet has become a place where anyone can just desparage any business for the most ridiculous things. 

People go out of their way to leave lengthy reviews about business' ....on and on about every single detail....my god get a LIFE! Do you have nothing else to do? Seems today everything is a drama! Oh, I went to xyz...let me now destroy them on the internet when I get home.  

I love Joes Crab Shack and I will go back as often as possible. I did not find the prices to be outrageous or the service bad....I think the place is fun and has great food. I am always happy to be able to have some down time and enjoy a good meal with my family and Joes is a favorite of mine.

name: Bank of America Financial Center
categories: Financial Services, Mortgage Brokers, Home Services, Real Estate, Banks & Credit Unions
text: Ok for bank lost 2 power of attorney's at this branch could do military banking but would call Texas. Staff not very friendly or helpf.

name: The Ice Cream Heaven
categories: Food, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt
text: We ordered from the grumpy guy at the counter, who was repeatedly impatient with my indecisive toddlers. Once they did make up their minds and I told him their order, he said there was no way they could handle that order. If I'm paying, and that's what they want, then MAKE it! When I slightly modified their orders, he still didn't want to make them. We ended up walking away with no ice cream. We will not be going back. I'm guessing this grouch could end up costing them the business...

name: Spring Valley Dental Group
categories: Cosmetic Dentists, General Dentistry, Health & Medical, Periodontists, Dentists
text: Very friendly and helpful staff. The dentists are very professional. Clean office and modern equipment. I feel like I'm an actual patient here and not a dollar sign.

text: Firehouse is one of my go to places. This new location  is right near my house. The staff here is friendly and doesn't rush you even if they are busy. I like all of their toasty subs so I can't recommend just one. If you're tired of the boring subs from from Subway you should give Firehouse a try. You will love it and this new location.

name: Fresh & Green Carpet Cleaning
categories: Local Services, Carpet Cleaning
text: David was very polite & professional , did a great job cleaning our carpet and bringing it back to life !!! House smells clean now .

name: Super 8 by Wyndham Collinsville St. Louis
address: 2 Gateway Dr., 11 Miles NE of St Louis
categories: Event Planning & Services, Hotels & Travel, Hotels
text: We came into town for a wedding and o my stayed one night. For the price, this was a pretty decent hotel. The staff was very friendly. We were able to get a late check-out with no trouble. Everything inside the room was pretty clean (they forgot to dump one of the trash cans out; no big deal). They had a lot of amenities (iron, ironing board, hangers, microwave, TV, mini fridge). They supplied plenty of linens. Everything was nice. We'd stay again.

name: Rapid Fire Sandwiches & Treats
categories: Sandwiches, Restaurants, Burgers
text:
The burger was outstanding! I only wish I had bought 2 cause it was so good. The fries were great as well and there were plenty of them. 
The atmosphere here is very welcoming and the young man working here is very nice and attentive. He visits several times to make sure we have everything we need which is appreciated.

text: We drove about 5 miles from the interstate into this Subway location in Maryville, IL just to receive one of the worst service I have ever had. The second we walked in, the girl behind the counter 'greeted' us with the driest, unenthusiastic 'welcome' ever, as dry as the Sahara desert. Next, the same girl started to ask our orders, as we started to make our orders, she kept walking back and forth into the back room trying to get other stuff, and almost like we are such an inconvenience for her! Lastly, when she started to put my daughter's sub together, she just slapped everything on a sub and flung that sub on a toaster tray that made everything on it spill everywhere and that's when I said something - she gave me a look and never apologized for her demeanor. I wish I can give 'no star' for this location because it is not worth it. If you are looking for a Subway location in the Troy/Maryville location - NEVER go to this location!

text:
We went looking for a new stove and visited the usual big places.  We couldn't find what we wanted and decided to try Mark's.  I'm so glad we did!  They had just what we wanted and gave us a great deal.  Our sales person was very knowledgeable, way more the the big places.  He took awesome care of us and it was delivered within a few days!  I love my new stove!  If you are in need of appliances, I highly recommend Mark's.

The repair guy came back today and fixed the dishwasher.  Hopefully this is the last time for awhile.  So we have a happy ending!

categories: Shopping, Party & Event Planning, Florists, Gift Shops, Event Planning & Services, Flowers & Gifts, Wedding Planning
text: Fantastic experience! I own a flower shop so I am kind of a hard one to please when I send flowers to others but this shop did a GREAT job! They hit the nail on the head and delivered it quickly. THANK YOU :)

categories: Hotels, Restaurants, Diners, American (New), Hotels & Travel, American (Traditional), Event Planning & Services, Gastropubs
text:
This is probably the best restaurant I have ever eatin at that was inside a Holiday Inn, and actually one of the better ones I have been to period. I would normally give it 4 stars, but considering where it is, I think it deserves an extra star. Normally, holiday Inn restaurants are terrible places, and I avoid them, but it was late, and we were exhausted, so we gave it a chance. Bossman got the porkchop that was about 4 inches thick (no kidding) and I got the bourbon chicken. Both were excellent, and the pork wasn't tough, which was surprising Considering how big those chops were. 

A few things about Alton:

East Alton is a rusty old industry town, a place in its hay day made some awesome stuff. They still have Winchester making ammunition their and Olin Brass cranking out precision copper and brass alloys. unfortunately, my reason to go  there was to decommission some research equipment at the olin Brass Metals research Lab. Yeah, the bean counters shut down the research department. Stupid. I wonder what the heck is going to keep this country going in the future. 

Also, Alton was home to the worlds tallest man.

name: Dragon Palace

categories: Restaurants, Chinese
text:
Reading the reviews, I cannot agree with the others which tout the quality of the food. I had the dinner buffet and the food was mediocre at best. The selection was fine, though they do charge a higher price if you want crab legs. BTW- neither Easy Buffet nor Ginger Buffet charge extra for crab legs. The flavors were there, but the meats were dried out, concentrated, and fried foods soggy and tough as if the they hadn't been turned over in hours and were just sitting on the steam table.  

Service was very nice but slow, especially since there were only 3 tables going the whole time we were there.  I think they had him responsible for too many things other that waiting tables.  

There is a slim chance I'll come back since there are 3 other Chinese buffets in the area that I prefer over Dragon.  Perhaps if I do, there will be more guests to turn over the food and I can update my ratings.

name: Babies R Us
categories: Baby Gear & Furniture, Shopping
text: I bought a recliner/glider Sept 10 and was told it was on back order and I'd receive a call when it ready for store pick-up.  No problem, I was 18 weeks pregnant.  Picked up "my chair" Nov 5 and kept it in storage for 2 weeks until baby's room was painted.  Opened the box and it's the wrong chair, someone else's custom ordered chair.  The store told me my chair was still on back order and they didn't know why I received a call already for my (wrong) chair, they reordered my correct chair Nov 19, I was told it would take two weeks.  I called yesterday and was then told it would take 8-10 weeks!  I'm now 32 weeks pregnant and hope I get my chair before baby arrives.  I didn't realize ordering furniture here would be such a hassle.  The website says chair ships from warehouse in 15-20 business days, hell.... I've been waiting 14 weeks so far for a chair I've paid in full. My advice? Buy furniture elsewhere or buy before you even conceive because delivery takes that long.

text: This was our first time buying a car from Carmax (we had previously sold a car to a different Carmax). name: Burger King
categories: Fast Food, Restaurants, Burgers
text: Despite the website schedule in the building signage when I arrived about 25 minutes ago to get breakfast I was told at the drive-through that they would be closed for the next 20 minutes. This is supposed to be a 24 hour business... I will be calling the 1800 number to inquire about this.

name: Foley's Tavern
categories: Bars, Pubs, Nightlife
text:
Although known as an Irish Bar, the only thing Irish about this place is that my family was in here last night drinking them out alcohol. I am a firm believer that the venue is never as important as the company you are with, and this was definitely the case last night. You could have dropped off our crew in a cornfield last night and it would have been a blast.

So anyway, what do you say about this stinky bar.........shuffle board table, dart boards, golden tee, good juke box and plenty of cold beer. No food, no pomp and some rough looking characters that seem like they come daily and drink their fill. Two guys made a point to come try and start a fight with someone from our table throughout the evening, which was comical considering the collective sizes and temperaments.

End of the day, tread carefully at Foley's....its my kind of bar.

text: I'm a big fan of St Louis Bread Co, but the experience I had this morning was horrible. I stopped by the drive thru since l was on a tight schedule. With one person in front of me, it still took ten minutes to reach the window. I then was told the computer was down and being rebooted. Five minutes or so later, still nothing. Eventually another worker opens the window and says she's re-ringing the order but not charging me for the frozen mocha (I never ordered a frozen mocha). She finally found our sandwich, which I paid full price for. It was cold, hard, burnt, and made incorrectly... I didn't have time to complain since I was late and there were about 7 cars behind me by then. I'll never be going back to this location.

name: Tip Top Nails
categories: Beauty & Spas, Nail Salons
text:
I will never go back there again. I decided last minute to get a silkwrap instead of just a manicure. I'm not really a nail person, I get my nails done maybe once a month. I tried to explain to her how I wanted them done, which was kind of hard because of the language barrier. I don't like the fake plastic tip because they damage your real nail. I watched several Youtube videos on how a silkwrap was a better alternative. Anyway because I wanted a little length to my nails she was going to use the plastic tips. I told her no, and I explained to her why. She said so you want to use your own nail, I said yes. Long story short and $35 later I have a regular manicure. When I saw how short she was filing the nail (which was my own nails length), I asked her what she was doing. She stated this is how its done and there was nothing else she could do since I didn't want the tips. So even though I was unsatisfied with her service I tip her anyway. I guess she was unhappy with the tip and after she finished painting my nails, she had me dry them using the mini fan at her station. Normally they take you to the drying station. And I was supposed to receive another service, but she started work on someone else. By this time I'm livid; I grab my things and left. I was able to find another place to get my eye brows done (Brown Spa; which they did an excellent job and was very polite). I asked the tech about silkwraps and she confirmed what I though. She also told me she never goes to Tip Top Nails "they're terrible".
I was able to find the Youtube video, so I went back to Tip Top Nails and show it to her. She said they don't do it like that, and that if I showed her the video before she would have told me no. They refused to do my nails the way I wanted them, and refused to give me a refund.
I'm a stay at home mom so I don't get many days to myself, and it pisses me off that this chick messed up my day.
Save yourself some money and go to a different salon. The Tip Top Nail Salon in the Galleria Mall (Brentwood, MO) is so much better.

categories: Bars, American (Traditional), Restaurants, Dive Bars, Nightlife, Irish Pub
text:
A dive bar with a huge selection of whisky and draft beer. Headed out for an evening of Blues playoff hockey, Cards baseball and a UFC fight. McDill's had us covered!  Plenty of TV's and the staff were accommodating to everyone's watching needs. The bartenders were on point with drinks and food orders. 
Speaking of food, this menu has locally sourced items.  All bread and buns are specially made from the bakery across the street!  The onions, tomatoes and lettuce are purchased from the Collinsville farmers market.  I ordered the Irish burger!  A huge beef patty cooked to perfection and covered in Guinness soaked onions. The pulled pork was smoked in house and offered complex flavors.  The ribeye sandwich was delicious and HUGE!  So much food and drink and so little time. I'll be returning soon as I've heard great things about the reuben sandwich.

name: Advantage Maytag
categories: Contractors, Local Services, Shopping, Home & Garden, Home Services, Appliances & Repair, Appliances
text:
If I could give them a negative star I would. This company is the worst I have ever dealt with.  I recommend you not to even waist your time calling this company. We had a refrigerator break down, it ended up being a compressor. Called  Advantage Maytag on a Monday morning and they sent a technician out on Wednsday. We were charged $68.00 for the call out just to have them to tell us they would order a compressor for us and it would take two weeks or more for them to recieve it. We still have not heard anything back from them, I even tried to call them, but no one answered. 
Lucky for us, I followed my gut instinct and called Mr. Appliance a few days later and got the work done in a few days. In todays technological advanced world, what takes two weeks?  I understand if the refrigerator was ten years old or more, but this unit is only two years old and it is an LG. 
Anyways the compressor came in the next day from Mr. Appliance, the same one Advantage was saying two weeks.  Again, if you do business with this company, don't say you have not been warned.  I truly believe companies like this should just shut their doors, we do not have the time for their bad business practices.

I also got a coupon to come back for 20% off anything I have done in the salon which I will be redeeming later this month. I have been here for the Benefit Brow Bar as well which I HIGHLY RECOMMEND, if you want your brows to look amazing - it is the best place you can go . I trust them with my life.

name: ATI Physical Therapy
categories: Occupational Therapy, Rehabilitation Center, Doctors, Sports Medicine, Health & Medical, Physical Therapy
text:
Short summary:
This place overbooks to get as many patients in as possible. I did not get quality care and was often forgotten about while there for my four visits. In contrast I have had two very positive experiences with Performance Physical Therapy over the years. I can't say much about the other ATI therapists or ATI branches, but I know where I'm going from now on. 

Detail: 
Picked this place because of the convenient location. What a mistake that was. I went here for four visits before I decided it was not worth my time or money.  Red flags from the first visit. I worked with Jeff and Nicki. Both nice people, but unfortunately unable to give me enough time for care. They were usually juggling 3-4 patients at the same time slot, meaning I spent a lot of time waiting around for the next instructions. A couple other times, Jeff had phone calls double booked with my time, so I didn't even get to see him or get to ask questions. Yet they always made sure I got the laser treatment, which I suspect may have been another way to bill more $ from my insurance. On the other hand I'm now at Performance for the same issue. From day 1 I got 1 on 1 uninterrupted care from someone who took more time to evaluate and answer questions. I went to performance 2 yrs ago for a back issue and had the exact same kind of good experience. Definitely worth the longer drive.

text:
Product selection is good; however, when I attempted to return an unopened item with a receipt I was told I had to have an account with them in order to do so. The back of the receipt stated that only a receipt is needed for returns, but the store clerk and manager would not take the return unless I provided them with my name/address/email address. This is a highly unethical business practice. 

I did call the corporate customer service line and was told that I don't need an 'account' to return items, and that they would clarify the company's policy with the store. Whether or not they did so I can't say. 

I would caution any customers of this store to ascertain the return policy before making any purchases. There is no stated policy in the store specifying any requirements for returns outside of a receipt. 

I will not go back to this business.

name: Belleville Public Library
categories: Libraries, Public Services & Government
text:
I have read the reviews of other past raters, and am sorry for their past experience.  I on the other hand have had much help and felt welcome.  I have been going to this library every day for the past year.  Why?

I am a school bus driver, from the Randolph County area.  I drive 20 minutes from my house to the bus yard, then pick up a student (Special Ed), and drive this student to a special school in the Belleville area.

Because of the low pay and long distance drive, I made arrangements with my boss, who is also the owner of the bus company, that I can stay up there, that the Library is only 2 miles from the school, and I would have plenty to keep me occupied.

Since it would also save him fuel/maintenance costs (making 1 trip as opposed to 2 trips), he allowed me to do that.  They have been good to me.  Yes sometimes it gets a little loud, and it has become a 2nd home for the less fortunate, but it has many great reference materials.

It is an old building, but I view the architecture as a work of art.  The second floor has a huge ceiling, with giant windows.  It is nice and open.  Thier reference section has shrunk down as they are re-arranging thier book set-up.

They have undergone renovations, and changed thier computer policy.  Now visitors can get 3, 30 minute sessions online.  The computer system is now linked up to all of southern IL, from Cairo to Effingham. 

If you have a library card anywhere in the southern part of the state, even if you have a Carbondale, or Mt Vernon card, it is now good for checking any book out there.  You can also access the Online Catalog system, and access your library account, and even place items on order yourself, and the staff will even show you how to do that if you ask them.

I am writing this review upon my final visits, due to, as I will be driving to a different school starting next week, in a different area of the Metro East.  They all knew what I did as a bus driver and was supportive of my being there as well.

So I have had good experiences overall, and rate the place about a 4, because it is in a building of Historical Significance, the computer access policy, an awesome microfilm (of Belleville News Democrat - Back to 1930s) collection, and a great children's section as well.

name: Farm Fresh Milk Store

text:
Visited tonight for take-out.  16 bucks for the tutto du Mari, which had 6 small shrimp and a bunch of nasty canned clams, most of which were so mushed up I couldn't tell what they were.  No seasoning except salt and tons of pepper.  Sauce tasted like flour and water.  Salad was limp and soggy.  Bread was ok, but basically a giant unheated roll.  16 bucks for one bite of salad that I spat out, six small shrimp, a bite of bread, and 2 forkfuls of pasta.  The rest went into the trash.  If I hadn't gotten take-out, entire meal would have gone back.

Gooey butter cake was ok but not particularly fresh, and t-ravs were edible (but easy to get frozen so hard to mess up).  Hubby had the chicken portobello pasta and reported it bland but inoffensive.

name: Sprint Store
categories: IT Services & Computer Repair, Mobile Phones, Mobile Phone Accessories, Shopping, Electronics, Local Services, Telecommunications
text:
Bad experience.  I had been with ATT for 15 years.  No problem with ATT except I wanted unlimited everything.  Went in and explained I wanted a 64 gig iPhone 6.  No problem says the clerk.  He comes out of the back with a box, ports my number and hooks me up with a plan.  While he's doing this, I see on the box it says 16 gig not 64.  When I bring that to his attention, he says that was to get me on a plan and that more 64's were to be in at the end of the following week and I could trade it in then.  Needless to say, a month later and still no 64 gig.  The manager now tells me that since I am past my return period, they can do nothing for me.  This after almost daily calls or visits to the store.  
     All they wanted to do was have me walk out with a phone.  They don't care if it's what you want or not.  I have now made several calls to customer service and will continue to bad mouth this particular store to all who will listen.
     Make sure you walk out with what you want, because they will do nothing for you afterward.  Instead, go to Marshall Wireless in Collinsville.  They know customer service.

text:
Katy Perry, kissed a  girl and liked it. I had a McRib sandwich and didn't like it. 

The other day on my way to work without a lunch the morning DJ's were talking about the McRib and the limited availability. In all the years McRib has been offered, I have never tried it. With it's departure from the menu coming up soon and the positive spin one of the DJ's gave, I thought I'd try one for lunch. 

I ordered a McRib combo meal with a small french fry and small coke. Kevin the DJ, said he orders his without pickle and onions. I like pickles and onions, so I kept them on mine. I'm glad that I did, the bun along with the crisp pickles and onions were the best thing about the sandwich. The processed meat was tasteless, it was over sauced with a BBQ that was way to sweet. I thank my luck stars that I had an order of fries. I only wished I had upgraded to a larger size to fill the void left by a flavorless sandwich. 

This is a very clean and friendly McDonald's. I will not lower their star rating due to a seasonal sandwich that I did not enjoy. However, I would not recommend a McRib to anyone, not even my worst enemy.
