name: Monkey's Tree Service
categories: Tree Services, Home Services
text:
I think that I would have written a very different review two weeks ago than I would want to write now. I am also a fair person and I don't want to write an initial review that might hurt a nice young couple that is, quite frankly, up against "big business". With their current training, their actual performance, I am satisfied. Bobby and Renee are an interesting and dynamic young couple. They are the "american  dream".  The pricing was great, the actual "work day" was well executed and they did a fine job. The complaint and gap is in their follow-through. 

They started the job (trees and fence removal with post/concrete removal; as quoted) on or about 10 SEP.  They came and picked up the final debris (after MY removal of the fence-posts) on 28 SEP.   So, maybe it is a case of getting what you paid for but that does not benefit me or Monkey.

With the right training, right support and discipline in scheduling, we would use them again. The job is done, our house is safe and the property looks better and is better. We are happy... finally.

 Here is where I would like to depart from the actual review of Monkey's Tree Service and instead wax poetic about American Small Business and the "dream deferred".  

When we lived in Baltimore we got two different "home improvement" jobs done. Both of those events were single day, a stretch of a few hours actually, done well, done crisply and with no discussion.  Both of those jobs were done by larger companies that had hired (illegal or not, I don't know, didn't check) Spanish speaking labor.

One of the refrains we heard from our friends at Monkey was "our workers....fill in the blank".  They had challenges maintaining a work force to complete the jobs that  Bobby hustled to get for the company. 

 They are trying to grow, trying to be successful but are held back by a few things; a lack of strategic planning, a lack of basic HR skills, a lack of clear roles for the two leads of the company.  If I had the time and money I would like to give them an injection of capitol and some executive coaching which would allow them to turn that business around and really succeed. 

What, you say there is a Small Business Administration to do that sort of thing...not for 2 people companies with one truck!  If you care about these kind of things more than NFL protests...pay attention to what your prospective leaders are promising in terms of the "american dream" and making "america great"...and vote accordingly.

name: West End Bar & Restaurant
categories: Burgers, Sandwiches, Restaurants, Pizza
text: Found this place after a planned trip to Otts' tavern in Milstadt  Ill. for fish.  For some reason Otts is closed on Sundays now.  Fish was not as good as Otts fish but other food items were pretty fair.  Service was ok and friendly.  On a positive note, the beer they serve is ice cold.

name: Hertz Rent A Car
categories: Hotels & Travel, Car Rental
text: We won't be using this Hertz location again.  Although they are located close to our home, the staff are uncaring, I felt that we were bothering them when we were picking up the rental.  One time when we picked up a rental, the inside of the car smelled like an ashtray.  We refused the car and ended up having to ride with a friend instead.  This last time, they gave us a car that wasn't even washed.  At least the car looked clean and smelled clean on the inside.  The employee was saying something about the person who washes the car the evening before, but I stopped listening because they were not going to wash it.  The car had a faulty tire sensor, indicating a low tire pressure when the tire was not low; I purchased a tire gauge to check the pressure.  When I told the employee when I returned the car, he said that that doesn't sound right.  Again, didn't seem to care.  If renting a car here, don't expect any support.

name: La Quinta by Wyndham Pontoon Beach
categories: Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Hotels & Travel
text: Staff greeted us and made us feel welcome upon arrival and had our room ready early for check in.  Elevator was out of service which was inconvenient but provided an opportunity for exercise. Indoor pool was clean as was the fitness room. Guest room was clean at first sight but when a quarter rolled under the bed I wish I hadn't gone after it.  Lots of food and debris scattered under there!  Beds were comfy and AC worked great.  Easy drive to downtown St Louis.  Breakfast was hot and had a nice variety with eggs, sausage, biscuits and gravy in addition to all the cold items and waffles

name: Mungo's
attributes: {'WiFi': "u'free'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsBitcoin': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2'}
categories: Italian, Restaurants, Steakhouses, Salad
text: Fantastic food, service, and atmosphere. The Mungo's salad is excellent. You have to get the olive oil dip for the bread as an appetizer - good blend of Italian seasonings and cheeses. I love the lasagna; my wife loves the pasta pesce (seafood pasta - if you don't like a little spicy heat, just ask them to eliminate or go easy on the red pepper...not a problem). By the way, don't let the strip mall exterior affect you; the inside is very nice - I also hear they are moving close to the O'Fallon 15 movie theater soon. Bella Milano can't compare to Mungo's.

name: Baymont Inn & Suites
categories: Hotels, Hotels & Travel, Event Planning & Services
text: Clean, good specials on a king suite, quiet, good parking and far enough from the interstate for peace and quiet

name: Appliance Discounters - Fairview Heights
categories: Kitchen & Bath, Appliances & Repair, Local Services, Appliances, Home & Garden, Shopping
text: Where ALL of your flooring dreams come true.  The store manager at the Fairview Heights Floor Trader is incredible...if you need help ask for Cleveland.  He will assist you in any way!  The store has a huge selection of carpets, hardwood floors, and much more! You really can't go wrong at The Floor Trader.

name: Jan's Hallmark Shop
categories: Shopping, Cards & Stationery, Arts & Crafts, Flowers & Gifts, Gift Shops, Event Planning & Services
text:
They used to offer complementary gift wrapping came here for that.  You bought their wrap and they wrapped it.  When they stopped doing that I stopped coming here.  

Got a 5.99 Mother's Day card? Really!?!

I am going to start going to the dollar store for cards.  

They also push like 4 things on you at the cash register.  Worse than hair braiders on a Jamaican beach.

name: Callahan's Corner
attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True'}

text:
We love to go to Callahan's to watch any sporting event. They have plenty of TVs to have every game that any sports fan wants to watch.  
They have a very wide variety of sandwiches on the menu but their burgers are great and you have several choices to top your burger with. 
They have several beers to chose from and a large selection of liquors for any mixed drink you desire.

name: Malcolm W. Martin Memorial Park
categories: Active Life, Parks
text: Malcolm W. Martin Memorial Park is defintaly a hidden gem! My brother wanted to go take pictures of the arch from a distance and he brought me here. He asked me if I've ever been before and of course I haven't. I discovered one of the largest fountains in the US here...I've always seen the fountain erupt from the interstate but never knew where it was exactly. Unfortunally we came here on the off peak time for it. Anyways, this place is very clean, grass is very green! Landscape is nice! Great layout and great view of the arch! There are also camera's on site so it does make it a little more safe to be here. I would deff. return here in the near future.

name: Lion's Choice

text:
The front line staff is still getting broken in. The food was hot and wonderful as I expect from a lions choice. The only thing was there was a lot of standing around at the front and the tables extremely needed attention. There were 2 clean tables when my family got there and not one time did any tables get wiped down while we were there. 

You can tell the staff is green and needs broken in a bit. I will be back. Hoping it gets better, not worse....

name: Jack Schmitt Chevrolet - Wood River
categories: Body Shops, Car Dealers, Automotive, Auto Repair, Used Car Dealers, Auto Parts & Supplies
text: Thanks again to the whole team at Jack Schmitt !!! 24 years working with them and still make me feel like I'm top priority !!!

name: Brevan's Patisserie
categories: Bakeries, Food
text: I've dropped in to Brevan's a few times now, and am finding it harder and harder to resist the urge to splurge. Everything I've tried has been great. The chocolate in their tarts is perfect. Their special Brendan chocolate mousse dome with peanut butter inside is  terrific. I finally tried their cheesecake yesterday. Some of the best I've had if you like it with a rich, dense consistency. I had the peanut butter cheesecake. What a treat! The only thing I've had that I wished was different was the chocolate croissant. It was good, but I like mine a bit more light and flakey. The inside was just a little dense that day. Having Brevan's in Edwardsville is a great addition. If only I could make it in to try one of the eclaires!

name: Healthy Home Pest Control & Services
categories: Local Services, Pest Control
text: They came out and cleaned my airducts Roman was nice and polite. Wow this made a difference in my heating and cooling cost. My allergies are so much better . I get this done once a year thank you Healthy Home

name: PetSmart
categories: Pet Stores, Pets, Pet Services, Pet Groomers, Pet Training
text: They have very good selections of different things for almost all pets although depending on the item things can get very expensive. If your pet needs a new toy I would still recommend coming here. It is right off of Frank Scott Parkway.

name: Auto Butler
categories: Car Wash, Automotive
text: . Nothing like a nice clean car on a sunny day thank you Auto Butler great job!!

name: Bodies Kneaded
categories: Beauty & Spas, Health & Medical, Reflexology, Massage Therapy, Massage
text: This is hands down the best place to get a massage.  The salon and spa are trendy.  They massage rooms are clean, quiet, and comfortable.  I recommend all of the girls on staff, I've been to most of them and they all do a great job.  Their prices are affordable.

name: Denny's
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True'}
categories: Restaurants, Breakfast & Brunch, Diners, American (Traditional)
text:
If I could give this particular location a 0 out of 5 stars, I would.

My Father and myself are on a 18-wheeler almost 24/7/365, minus when we are at either our home or a friend/family's home.  I would say it's months between when we have what most would see as a 'home cooked meal', due to how expensive truck stop restaurants are, and a lot of actual restaurants don't allow, or have room, for semi (18-wheeler) parking, so obviously, we are fairly often shoppers at Walmart and Sam's Club.

As I said, it's rare we eat in a sit down restaurant, so today, my Father decided, he wanted Denny's, and wanted it to go.  I even called this particular Denny's before we pulled into the parking lot, to see if it was possible to use our own to go dishes we had gotten extra from another Denny's.  At first the lady I spoke to said yes, so I came inside to make the order.

Once at the counter, after waiting roughly 10 minutes to even see a employee in there, someone finally asked what I needed.  I told her, and she seemed hesitant about putting the food in the containers, but agreed.  About a hour later, another woman came out and said her boss said the containers were 'dirty' and could not be used due to 'cross contamination'.

I would've understood if they had said that because they were outside containers, technically, they couldn't use them, but saying the containers were dirty was uncalled for.  The way the inside of Denny's was, now that was dirty.  I'm overlooking the snow, but their attitudes need a very good cleaning.

So for anyone thinking of coming here?  Avoid this place like the plague.  Only thing going good for them is their wifi, and Flying J has plenty of that to use.

name: Great Clips
categories: Hair Salons, Beauty & Spas
text: Terrible. The lady who cut my hair clearly had no idea what she was doing and was distracted half of the time she ended up cutting off wayyyyy too much of my hair before i could even say otherwise. Please do not go here.

name: Bindy's
categories: American (Traditional), Restaurants
text: Well me and my hubby ate there on Thursday for the steak night it was horrible and there waitresses was crap never eating here again !

name: Marco's Pizza
categories: Food Delivery Services, Pizza, Italian, Restaurants, Chicken Wings, Food
text: So we thought we'd give it a try. This was a BIG MISTAKE! First tried ordering online, gave it several valiant tries then had to call the store...oh the call . The obvious uninterested individual that answered was rude and told me no I could not have the online special but that I could?? Her only redeeming quality was that we  got the online price. A price which was quite a bit higher than their competitors. Now let's talk about our delivery driver...after handing my hubby a salad we didn't order, and receiving a generous tip, this man ASKED FOR A CIGARETTE!! I've never seen anything like that! My husband was not smoking at the time so I don't even know why he would think to ask! How rude and bizarre! And the pizza was not very good.

categories: Custom Cakes, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Desserts, Cupcakes, Food, Bakeries
text: Love me a good cupcake. I've never had Jilly's before so I'm going on the delightful flavors and reviews of others. I can't wait to try these cupcakes. Yum.

name: Drury Inn & Suites
categories: Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Hotels & Travel
text:
First time staying at a Drury and I absolutely loved it!! 

This place is pet friendly and the pet fee is only $15! 

Nice lobby, VERY nice eating area! We had their free breakfast and the variety was so big! I was surprised to see biscuits and gravy. Everything was delicious. Their eggs tasted like real eggs. Normally at hotels that have free breakfast, the eggs taste very instant. 

The room was extremely clean and the beds were comfy. The decor in the rooms could use an update, but it's not a big deal. 

Will definitely be back to this place if I'm ever in town.

Oh and they have military discount!

name: Joe K's
attributes: {'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': None, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': True, 'breakfast': True}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': None, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}"}
categories: Restaurants, Breakfast & Brunch, American (Traditional)
text:
I went for breakfast on a Sunday. I was dining alone so I sat at the counter. My order was taken quickly. . I ordered eggs Benedict, it doesn't come with any sides so I had to order hash browns on the side. I also ordered 2 pancakes since the pancake menu was so large, I assumed it was a point of pride for the restaurant. 

The eggs Benedict was good for a dinner, the english muffins were not toasted at all, but the eggs and the hollandaise sauce were good so I still count it as good. The hasbrowns had zero flavor at all. The portion was plentiful but they had no taste, even salt didn't help. The pancakes were good but this is where I have to really mark them down. FAKE Syrup, not real maple syrup. FAKE butter, they had some cheap off brand margarine. FAKE cream, some palm oil based off brand creamer. They also only had sweet and low and equal as sweeteners. 

In spite of sitting right in front of the coffee machine at the counter, I had to ask for a refill on my coffee. There is also no way the coffee they are brewing is Ronnoco. Ronnoco has a rich delicious flavor and a robust smell. This coffee had almost no flavor or scent, if they are brewing Ronnoco, then they are not making it with the proper amount.

I expect a mom and pop restaurant to serve real food. Real cream, real butter (hopefully whipped) and real maple syrup. The pancake prices aren't low enough to justify the "cost cutting" on the butter and syrup. Also it is still probably cheaper to buy the real stuff in bulk and package it in the store.

I gave it 3 stars instead of 2 because I think the basic food is decent. If I go back I will get an omelette and just drink water.

text:
Do not eat here if you are a vegetarian!  A few times I have ordered the Cheesy baked zitti with no meat only to find upon getting my food home that there was meat in the sauce.  This last time my wife asked for no meat and even checked the ticket and guess what there was meat.  Now I am forced to go back up there if I want to rectify the situation.  They should bring me the correct food.  Long story short I like the food but it is sad that the workers aren't more competent.  I won't eat there again.  
I imagine if you don't have any dietary restrictions it is a wonderful place to eat.

text: This is a small mom and pop type place. Its run by the sweetest couple. The food is inexpensive and delicious and the service was quick. This is mostly a breakfast type place but they do have a lunch menu with some sandwiches. This is a perfect place to add to our lunch rotation and I plan on going back for breakfast this weekend. They don't accept credit/debit cards though.

name: Beautiful Nail & Spa
categories: Beauty & Spas, Eyelash Service, Nail Salons
text: It was awful. I get my nails done every two weeks, I decided to try this place because the yelp review was 4 stars. What a mistake. This is one business that does not believe the customer is right. The other lady in the shop wasn't happy and she received different services than me. When he was about to put my acrylic on he didn't bother fixing the air bubbles from my last set. I had to address it to be fixed. Then I asked them to put another coat of no chip on and they refused to do so. I'm a paying customer.. If I want another coat it doesn't seem to be too much to ask. He told me my nails are supposed to be see through. Wow. The color I picked on the wheel of slim pickings for no chip was not the color I received on my nails. I would suggest updating the colors you are presenting if they aren't accurate! To top it off... My nails are still sticky, clearly he didn't seal them well enough with the polish remove when we were done!!! Never will I be back. I tried to stay respectful right till the end but this is just not customer service.

name: Relax Nail
categories: Nail Salons, Nail Technicians, Beauty & Spas, Hair Removal, Waxing
text: While visiting our daughter over the weekend, we decided on a family pedicure. We selected Relax Nails due to the previous review and feedback. The family consensus afterwards was "best pedicures EVER!" We opted for the deluxe (at a very reasonable price) and received the royal treatment. The additional touches of the collagen socks and hot stone massage were fantastic, and on top of it we enjoyed complimentary drinks while watching college football! I agree with the previous comment that this is a hidden gem; excellent value & customer service. Your feet will thank you for days!

name: St Elizabeth's Hospital
categories: Health & Medical, Hospitals
text: My father recently went here for left elbow and lower arm pain. He was told that he had to go the the hospital in an ambulance because he might be having a heart attack. He was told that blood pressure and chest x-rays were okay, but that he still needed to be taken by ambulance. My father absolutely did not want to take an ambulance, and explained that if they thought it was absolutely necessary his wife would drive him. He was then told that if he didn't follow orders, his insurance wouldn't have to cover his medical bills. He was frustrated, scared and embarrassed to be leaving in an ambulance for what he described as a minor lower arm/hand pain. Because of the diagnosis he received at this urgicare, the hospital put him through tests all day and made him spend the night. The next day he was finally seen by another physician in the hospital who quickly and easily diagnosed what the issue was. My father had a nerve in his elbow that was causing the pain. We're living in a time when health insurance prices are skyrocketing. This misdiagnosis is unacceptable and cost his insurance $16,000. He has medicare which means that taxpayers, you and I paid this bill.

name: Petco
categories: Pet Training, Pet Sitting, Pets, Pet Stores, Pet Groomers, Pet Services
text: I was disappointed to learn that the Petco near my house had closed, so I was very excited to find one in my neighborhood at work. I need some goldfish for my outside pond. They had a huge tank in the middle of the fish section. The attendant was very friendly and helpful. I told him that I was just going to put them in an outside fish pond. He suggested the 15 cent ones in case a few died, plus he grabbed only the gold ones so you could see them in the pond instead of the black ones. How cool was that???? I got to the front to check out, the attendant was pushing the rewards card, I said that I don't really buy much, she said it was free and if any of my friends or family wanted to use the card, I could give them the free stuff. Sure what the heck all of my children have dogs and I can buy them treats.... Great place, quick service, and great customer service.

text: New Korean restaurant.  We went there for dinner, had a couple of appetizers (Dragon & Monkey ball) and they were excellent. The meals ordered were Beef Bulgogi, and Chicken Bokum which were very authentic. They came with a house salad, Miso soup, and 5 different sides of Kimchi which were also house made and had great flavor. The salad was fresh and crisp with a great house made dressing. The Bulgogi was nicely marinated and not overly sweet like some places. The Bokum had a great level of spice and flavor. The customer service was outstanding and they have a real passion for their food and customer's satisfaction. I would definitely recommend this restaurant to family & friends!

categories: Antiques, Auction Houses, Venues & Event Spaces, Event Planning & Services, Shopping
text: I made the huge mistake of coming here hungover. Let me tell you from first hand experience that listening to the auctioneers sell items for three hours is not a good idea. This place is what it is, a building used for auctions, events, weddings, etc. It has a huge gravel parking lot to accommodate parking. The inside it spacious but very outdated. Overall it's a great place for an auction but I would not host a wedding or anything nice/trendy here. Also, if you are going here for an auction they accept checks and cash only but there is a gas station up the road with an ATM.

name: Men's Wearhouse
categories: Shopping, Fashion, Men's Clothing, Formal Wear, Shoe Stores, Plus Size Fashion, Bespoke Clothing
text:
I stopped in here the other day because of the buy one suit get one for $100 promotion. I've shopped here a couple times before and probably the single reason I haven't shopped here more are their prices. I think the trick is to shop their sales and avoid the place if you are going to pay full price. 

Leo helped me out and was very attentive and knowledgeable. He helped me try on a half dozen or so suits trying to find something I liked. After finding a couple suites I liked he also paired me up with a shirt and tie for the suit I didn't have anything else to go with it. 

Being a fairly skinny guy I took the liberty of having the suites altered a bit so they fit me better, as well as having the hems on the pants done. Here is my one beef with The Men's Warehouse. They sell unhemmed pants that cost from about $70 on up, then they charge you $12 to hem them. I have no problem paying to take in my suit jackets, but if I've paid $90 for a pair of unhemmed pants hitting me with a $12 alteration fee to hem them is a low blow in my opinion. The only good thing is that if they have made an alteration, they will make additional alterations on that seam free of charge. So if you get your pants taken in a bit then gain some weight, they will let them out so that you can still get into them. 

The buy one suit get one for $100 was really great as their suits were about $100 off regular price anyway, so it was almost a buy one get one free. I ended up paying about $420 for two extra long suits. The alterations cost me close to $100 which was a bit excessive in my opinion, but I don't have stuff altered all that often so perhaps that is about right. 

Being a tall, skinny guy I can always count on the Men's Warehouse to have something that will fit me, which is generally a challenge at other places. I'll continue to shop here when they have sales, otherwise I think I will shop elsewhere.

name: Willard's Formal Wear & Tailor Shop
categories: Fashion, Sewing & Alterations, Local Services, Men's Clothing, Shopping
text: Absolutely the most awful experience for a bride. My sister-in-law opened up her dress bag two hours before the wedding to find that her dress was not finished. The lace had been cut across the bottom and was pinned all the way around. They also forgot the bustle. In addition, when they shortened the sleeves there were more buttons than loops to fasten them. I can't put into words the distress they put her through. I will be telling everyone I know in order to save them from such heartache and disappointment. In the end, they had the audacity to blame the bride. It seems that their idea of a finished dress is different from the rest of America. After reading the reviews, it's obvious that this is how they do business. If only she would have read these first. Lesson learned to the entire bridal party and everyone we can tell.

name: Drury Inn St. Louis Collinsville
categories: Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Hotels & Travel
text: This was my first time staying in a Drury Inn, and I was convinced to do so by fellow Yelper's review saying, "I wasn't sure what to expect, and the name Drury suggests dreary, but this is anything but." It really is a clean, comfortable hotel, and for those of you TRAVELING WITH A DOG, IT'S A TERRIFIC OPTION. Nancy at the reservation desk was so friendly she could practically be working for the Human Society.  The hotel was extremely clean, and although I was too lazy to get breakfast, my partner said it was, as other reviews claimed, very good.  The four-star rating is for a bathroom a little more worn than the rest of the room. But that shouldn't discourage you from a great stay.

name: NEC Technology Repair
categories: Local Services, Electronics Repair, IT Services & Computer Repair
text:
Dryer GE is under an extended service warranty with Lowes. Dryer breaks down warranty still effective service company NEC shows up to REPAIR with no parts whatsoever driving a passenger car. Diagnosis the problem says he'll order the parts have to reschedule when the parts come in between five and seven days. I decide I'll try to get the parts myself and find somebody to fix the dryer as we can't wait another week to have the service. When I called to get the part number from NEC I am told "you will void your warranty we will report you to Lowes" I never It's on the service I just wanted to see if I can get it done faster. After finding I couldn't get the parts as easily as I thought I called NEC and was told by text: Hello. Your ticket is closed with us. You informed us you were going to order your own parts and we contacted Lowe's with the report. Thank you. Have a nice day. :)"
Avoid this company like they are Covid silent super spreaders. I wouldn't want them back in my house. Filing a complaint with the Missouri Attorney GeneralYep consumer Fraud section

categories: Car Rental, Hotels & Travel

name: 17th Street Bar & Grill
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'Caters': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}"}
categories: Barbeque, Restaurants
text:
I'd been meaning to hit this location for a couple years, but after seeing them on Food Feuds with chef Michael Symon (who I am totally crushing on), it kicked my butt to get there.

I LOVE Pappy's, but I'm pretty close to love with 17th Street.  The ribs were indeed amazing.  The meat did not not fall off the bone, because that would be WRONG, people!  But they did bite cleanly and the crunchy edge was absolutely delicious, with a touch of sweetness.  I just wanted to suck on the bones after the meat was gone.  The brisket was moist and really good also. 

For the sides, I tried the baked beans which I enjoyed.  They were tangy-tomato-ey and I thought it was a nice touch that they used different types of beans together.  The mac and cheese was solid, if not outstanding.  The fries were seasoned and done well.  

This location is really big with several different rooms.  Our server did a good job of being attentive without being overbearing. When it came to dessert, they were out of several items since they make evertying in-house, so when it's gone, you're out of luck.  I tried the bread pudding which was sooooooo dense, it felt like it was just sitting on top of all the deliciousness in my belly.  And I was really disappointed that they used Cool Whip instead of real whipped cream.  Yuck.

All in all, 17th Street is definitely worth the drive, which isn't really that far, and I can't wait to get back and try more of the menu.

categories: Donuts, Food, Bakeries, Custom Cakes
text: This place is always clean, staff nice and friendly. There is far more than just cakes here. While I've never tried the cupcakes, I've tried just about everything else and it's all delicious! Donuts, cookies, tons of variety in pastries. It is a smaller shop and you can make custom orders that come from the main bakery from there. Due to its proximity to the high school, I would not visit right before or after school lets out in the afternoon, lots of parents and kids clog the parking lot. (This is not their fault, that pkg lot has been that way forever)

name: Danny's Brushless Car Wash
categories: Auto Detailing, Car Wash, Automotive
text: Staff was friendly. My car was extremely dirty (I live in a small country-like town, I drive back roads a lot). I bought the $8.95 car wash. There were still small spots still on my car however, it looked A LOT better than before. For $8.95 with free vacuuming, you can't beat that price. The vacuums are incredibly powerful.

text: My wife and I's love affair with Chipotle continues in Fairview Heights. Same amazing Chipotle as the others but they do tend to skimp on the rice, however, if you just ask them for more rice they are happy to accomidate. They recently raised their prices and axed the military discount which kind of sucks but nothing could make Qdoba better than Chipotle!

name: McDonald's
attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'"}
categories: Food, Burgers, Restaurants, Coffee & Tea, Fast Food
text:
I ordered thru the mobile app and decided to have it delivered to my car. The order went thru without issue, and I pulled into the parking lot and the designated spot for pickup.
I noted there was another car waiting when I pulled in. The drive thru was very busy, so I felt my decision was the best one. 
I waited nearly 10 minutes and neither I nor the other car were served. The drive thru continued to be busy. I also saw several cars were pulled up into waiting areas. 
Another 5 minutes rolled around and I noted the other cars that were asked to pull up were gone. Furthermore, the drive thru was slowing down, and both of us in the delivery pickup were still without food.
Finally, at 20 minutes, the other car was serviced. I heard the young lady apologize, and say they were swamped.
At this point, I was ready to go into the restaurant. I decided to give a few more minutes, expecting my order. By thos time the drive thru had cleared out. 
Soon enough our food was delivered. It was fresh and the fries were hot. The crew member was duly apologetic, using the same reason given the other customer ("We were swamped").
I will be hard pressed to do this again at this location. I have used it at the Bethalto store, and was promptly serviced. I considered calling management concerning my experience, but assumed that if manager was on duty, this behavior was approved.

name: Ahne's Bakery
categories: Restaurants, Bakeries, Food
text: Love the place.  Reminds me of the old time bakeries from my childhood in the 50s.  Everything good there.  Everyone nice there.  Pastries are the best. Pies excellent.  They close early.

name: Regis Salon
address: 136 Saint Clair Sq, Saint Clair Square
categories: Hair Salons, Beauty & Spas
text: I went here for to get my hair highlighted and lowlights and it looks like nothing I asked for.... I felt rushed the whole time I was there. I wish the stylish took more of her time on me and stopped worrying about what the other stylist we doing.

name: Coyote's Ranch Grill & Saloon
categories: American (Traditional), Restaurants
text:
The 6:10 show for Avengers was sold out, so we had time to kill. Our friend who wanted to go to Coyote's couldn't remember the name, because the place is masquerading as Ranch and Grill, with Saloon and Bar thrown in. We need something we can type into Google Maps here.

Everything was littered with spelling errors. From the very sign on the building ("Coyotes" with no apostrophe) to the chalkboard with drink specials ("Captin Morgan") to literally every page of the menu ("Bluberry" muffins, "Ceaser" salad, "Rueben" sandwich), my group spent most of our conversation mocking the appalling lack of proofreading. Those little red squiggly lines in MS Publisher aren't just for decoration, guys.

On the note of decoration, the design looks like it was fished out of the bargain bin at Hobby Lobby. There were two pairs of leather chaps on the wall, and ugly metal sconces that weren't even lit. We had time to spend staring at the décor, because it took an hour to get our main courses.

I'd eaten dinner at home, but I didn't want to sit there just drinking water. I ordered a mudslide and nachos. Both of them were absolutely atrocious. 

The $6 alleged mudslide was a mixture of generic, soft-serve chocolate ice cream (right out of a bad Chinese buffet) and off-brand syrup (I could tell it wasn't Hershey's or anything higher quality because of the distinct flavor of plastic). I had two of my friends taste it, and none of us could detect even the faintest hint of Kahlua or Bailey's, which are the most basic ingredients required for the drink.

The $7 "Tri-color Nacho Chips with Spicy Queso Dip" involved about thirty sparse chips (I counted) arranged on a melamine plate that'd been under a heat lamp. What self-respecting Tex-Mex restaurant charges this much (or anything) for a bunch of bland tortilla chips from a bag? It'd be gracious to say that the taste was on par with the sort of nacho cheese I got from my high school cafeteria, because I remember actually enjoying that stuff at the time. 

The cheese glop was very obviously served from a Costco-style container, and had no amount of spice to it. The chef apologized to us later, explaining that he was training new hires and they'd made it wrong, and produced a second plate of nachos as we were trying to leave. They were every bit as bad, except now they had a few pieces of jalapeño and bell pepper diced in there. He also had the gall to insist that they'd made it all from scratch--in which case, I'd love to know where they're getting the red and blue cornmeal, and exactly how they're preparing chemically flavored cheese product right in the kitchen. It was so gross, I was nauseous for hours afterward.

My friends weren't faring any better; annoyed, I asked to try their food. It was all terrible. One girl paid $7 for a 7" DIY personal pizza that she could've gotten for a dollar from a gas station, topped with pineapple chunks that were clearly from a can. Another friend paid $8 for a 12" pizza, which makes zero sense. The pricing structure is completely off. Another girl had a pulled pork sandwich that she took two bites of and refused a to-go container for, probably because it was a scoop of lukewarm pork on burnt bread, served with freezerburnt fries that I'd bet were Ore-Ida or the equivalent. 

The only good thing was the beer my boyfriend ordered, because it's hard to screw that up. Our server was all right; she was doing her best with what the kitchen gave her to work with. She was friendly, but couldn't tell us what the drink special of the day was (consistently rotated Monday through Friday, per the website). A friend asked what the applesauce shots were made with. The server and the bartender didn't know--they apparently had to call the head bartender to find out how they'd been prepared. I wonder what they'd do if the shots were actually selling and they had to make more?

The manager came out to speak with us about our experience, and decided to lecture me about the definition of the word "queso," and that since it just means "cheese," it's somehow excusable to serve that slop and call it dip. I speak Spanish--I don't need this speech. She also insisted that it wasn't microwaved, they used heat lamps. Oh boy! If you made your chips yourself as you claim, they'd be hot from a deep fryer, and wouldn't need to warm them under a lamp for god knows how long.

My mudslide and nachos were both comped, but unfortunately most of our party paid for food they hardly touched. Extraordinarily bad customer service, and this was from the manager.

The website and menu include tons of photos stolen from Google Images. We spent a while looking for the sliders on the back page, which aren't even for sale. Hint: don't show pictures of happy customers that are not yours, in a restaurant that's not yours, with a chef preparing pasta dishes you don't serve.

If I wanted to spend $7 on industrial-bagged nachos with reheated cheese, I would've bought them at the movie theater.

name: Starbucks
categories: Coffee & Tea, Food
text: Never been inside but the drive thru staff are always pleasant and apologetic if they are busy. Great customer service for sure!

name: Beall Mansion An Elegant Bed & Breakfast
categories: Public Services & Government, Venues & Event Spaces, Bed & Breakfast, Hotels & Travel, Hotels, Event Planning & Services, Landmarks & Historical Buildings, Arts & Entertainment, Museums, Wedding Chapels
text:
That first room pictured with a queen four-post bed is the room my husband and I stayed in.  The bed was comfortable; we slept like babies.  The blackout curtains helped us sleep well into the morning.
All previous reviewers' comments about Jim, the chocolate bar (note: the pictures on Yelp do not do it justice; we're talking a bureau top FULL of various chocolates), and the attention to detail are spot on.  Though we wanted to getaway from the cares of this world, having a TV in the room playing classical music was quite a nice, elegant addition that transported us back to the Victorian era.
If you're trying to decide which package to spring for, I'd suggest going for one that includes breakfast in bed.  Jean, who made our breakfast, had me get into bed before placing my breakfast tray over my lap.  The breakfast comes complete with an appetizer, entree, dessert, and palate cleansing liquor.
We biked from St. Louis (30 mi) to enjoy the elegance of the Beall Mansion and it was well worth the painful (for me), hot ride to enjoy such opulence!

name: Mokka Cafe
attributes: {'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': True, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Caters': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
categories: Restaurants, Cafes, Coffee & Tea, Food
text:
I went to Mokka this morning to eat breakfast.  Walked in to no greeting, the woman behind the counter just ignored me standing at the counter until I said excuse me.  Then went through the odd sequence of ordering off of one of the two menu books located at the counter.  Finally ordered food.

I order an omelet which arrived small, cold, and thrown together as if assembled by a toddler.  More ingredients were outside the omlet, rather than inside.  The plates were chipped, we had to ask for silverware, butter, jelly, and napkins.  

I will never eat here again.  Food was poor, service was worse, and they have the gall to ask you for a tip before any of the described negligence has an opportunity to occur.

text: I do not like this place. First, their alcohol selection sucks. Second, they forget to charge us for drinks but tell us our tab. After we pay and go outside, the bartender come out, so glad we stuck around, and tells us we owe more on our tab. If we didn't stick around, they would have been just fine. Then, before they close, we are sitting outside waiting for our Uber and they turn off the lights and the heater. Pretty much a final, forget you and we don't give a crap about our guests. That's fine. That's the first and last time I'll ever go there.

text:
Conveniently located right off the highway, we stopped here simply based on location and price-point. 

Our server was a super cute young girl with a contagious smile and great demeanor. The bearded cook smiled back at me while I was up front waiting to pay, that was pleasant.

The food is A-OK. You get what you pay for. BUT... the restrooms needed cleaning. The serving area was, actually, quite gross. Ok, it's true, the entire place is in need of a serious deep clean.

name: Watershed Nature Center
categories: Educational Services, Elementary Schools, Recreation Centers, Education, Specialty Schools, Local Services, Local Flavor, Community Service/Non-Profit, Active Life, Parks
text: Watershed Nature Center is a beautiful nature reserve located in the heart of my town.  It is a wonderful place to go for a run, have a picnic, take the kids for a family walk, or just to sit and enjoy the beauty and peace of nature.  I take pride that there is a nature reserve in my town and that people in my community take the time to appreciate the nature and beauty of it all.

name: Country Inn & Suites
categories: Hotels & Travel, Event Planning & Services, Hotels
text: We rented three rooms in June 2016.  The room was well furnished but was not clean.  I saw dirt and hairs in each corner of the bathroom.  The shower was grungy.  On the positive side, I found the breakfast to be one of the best when compared to similar chains.  The rates were slightly better than the other hotels in the area.

text: Red Robin is basically fast food, but it's high quality. We visit once a year for a family birthday gathering with a huge party (15), and they always accommodate us. Many restaurants don't know how to handle such a large group, but Red Robin does well every time. They have a few long table areas that we can all sit at and the food is usually very quick and still hot. Being a french fry connoisseur, I love unlimited french fries, and they usually keep them flowing!

name: Subway
categories: Restaurants, Sandwiches, Fast Food
text: HORRIBLE!!  GO TO ANOTHER SUBWAY NOT THIS ONE!  It's like they have no idea how to make the special sandwiches.  Ordered the ultimate garlic cheesey meatball sub -- have had it at 2 other Subway shops and love it -- but this was the 2nd AND LAST time for this location.  There's hardly ANY cheese, fewer meatballs and light sauce.  It's so noisy in the restaurant no one can hear or they just don't want to hear ...

text: Dive with great breakfast and lunch menu. Most foods are made from scratch. Daily specials are all the comfort food you could need. Everything from Hungarian Stew to Stuffed Cabbage. Stuffed Pork Steaks to Salmon Patties. The owner and front of the house Michael will now you and your family by your third visit.

name: First Stop Bake Shop
categories: Pizza, Sandwiches, Donuts, Restaurants, Food, Bakeries
text: So happy to hear about this place. My family tried it today and their treats are simply wonderful. We had the key lime pie, chocolate croissant, cinnamon roll and these raspberry cream pastries. All delicious and not overly sweet...just right! Not much seating but we just popped our hatch and all ate outside. The owners were wonderful. We are looking forward to many more visits.

name: Best Western Plus Parkway Hotel
categories: Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Hotels & Travel
text: I will never go here again. I am a BW rewards member but this specific one I won't be back to. They have a no smoking policy. However if you are on the floor or in the vicinity of where the smoke was coming from , the manager will go by her nose and if they GUESS it was you they take your 150 deposit. Even if it truly wasn't you. Even claimed it was ashes in the room when I asked to see , I COULDNT BECAUSE IT WAS A LIE. Bottom line they had to blame someone for it without a actual investigation , they picked me and it wasn't right.. there are two others who I have never had this problem with at all.. their procedure is different! I wouldn't recommend staying here AT ALL. If your local you need 150cash deposit on top of the price for the room... there is another on college ave where they do things totally different. Go to them.!

name: Atrium Hotel & Conference Center
categories: Event Planning & Services, Hotels & Travel, Venues & Event Spaces, Party & Event Planning, Hotels
text: I had a wonderful experience staying here Memorial day weekend. First of all the layout of the hotel is very modern. It's located in a nice part of town. After driving all through the night I was  delighted to find a friendly staff that had me checked in almost instantly. My sleeping experience was above average in their bed. Room was immaculate and my TV was much larger than what I am accustomed to in most hotels. The hotel is a relatively short drive from St. Louis, so if you're looking to stay at a place with big city comfort at small town prices this is a solid option. I was very impressed with the value and quality of my entire stay, not to mention the breakfast buffet is game changer. I'll be back next time I roll through town.

name: Premium Cleaners
categories: Local Services, Dry Cleaning & Laundry, Laundry Services
text:
They do an ok job. If they just do what we asked them to do. No crease no starch. How hard is that to do?? They lost my jeans this go round. 
The price not bad until the add starch that doubles the price.

name: The Weeping Willow Tea Room
categories: Soup, Restaurants, Food, Tea Rooms, Breakfast & Brunch, Sandwiches
text: Sorry unable to snap a photo of the food it was that dang good! The woman who owns this restaurant are freakishly fantastic at what they do. I haven't had this good of simple comfort food from the East Coast, NM since I was on the East Coast. I will definitely be going back here again. The lobster soup is so creamy and thick and the tomato basil grilled cheese sandwich is sinfully good.

name: Southern Illinois Associates
categories: Doctors, Psychiatrists, Counseling & Mental Health, Health & Medical
text: Office staff very rude, jamie has absolutely no idea what she is prescribing.  She sits ar her desk and goes hmmmm.....or will prescribe you something that main side effect causes anxiety and that why I was there.

text: The weird thing about this McDonald's is they have large signs explaining that you can only use their Internet for 15 minutes or they will kick you out. I'd say either they have a problem with moochers or they are extremely busy. I'd guess the former.  The sweet chili chicken McWrap is pretty tasty...probably not good for you, but tasty.

name: Circle K
categories: Food, Gas Stations, Convenience Stores, Automotive
text:
I think I walked into heaven! This new location is well lit, even the shelves. The polar pop station has a fancy 4 panel tv screen display. It had a nice variety of soft drinks to choose from, both Pepsi and Coke products. There is even a tea station that you can drink hot or iced. The Froster has slushed soft drinks. There are only four flavors to choose from, but there are caffeine-free options.

The fast snack section has pork egg rolls, hot dogs & nachos. You can even top your hot dogs and nachos with free chili, cheese & even queso blanco (white cheese)!!!

The walk-in cooler has your staples like milk and eggs for they "quick trip" to the store. The BEER CAVE is amazing. If it wasn't so cold, I would want to pull up a recliner and tv and just hang out.

name: Holiday Inn Hotel Alton - Lewis & Clark Trail Site
categories: Venues & Event Spaces, Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Hotels & Travel
text: Needs an upgrade which I heard is happening. The AC unit was incredibly loud. As it cycled on and off every 20 minutes, it rattled us out of our beds. Free buffet breakfast was nice with our kids. Great location from the soccer tournament . Bar service was slow. Pool is typical size for budget hotel. Pool tables and ping pong are nice amenities .

name: D.S. Vespers Sports Pub and Eatery

text: This is one crazy busy place. It can be your one stop shop, movie=check, drinks-check, food= check, laser tag= check, watch the game=check. We stopped in after running a 5k. The parking lot was very full, we had to drive around for a bit before we found an open spot. Once inside, we secured an open table, but getting a server proved to be hard to find than the parking spot. I cant really say that many good things about the service, but the food made up for it. Highly recommended to shop here.

name: Verizon
categories: Shopping, Electronics, Internet Service Providers, Home Services, Professional Services, Mobile Phones
text: If only I could rate with a negative star. Terrible customer service! Sales person lied right to out faces to get us to sign a contact. Shady, and when we went to try to speak to them about it, they only suggested that we have an early termination fee. I've been with them for twenty years, and that means nothing to them. Very disappointed and totally taken advantage of.

name: Bridal Parlour
categories: Bridal, Shopping
text: Although I didn't end up finding "the dress" here, I found some of the most beautiful delicate and boutique-styled gowns I have seen. The intimate one-in-one experience with Heather was unbeatable. If you want a stress free, relaxed, and super fun environment (not to mention the entire place to yourself) PLUS a wonderful collection of unique dresses, do yourself a favor and just GO.

name: Nettie B's
categories: Restaurants, Seafood, Southern
text:
I went here today because I read the reviews from
Facebook. The atmosphere inside the restaurant was nice. I ordered a shrimp po boy & fries. I must say this was one of the best po boy sandwiches I've ever had. My food was made to order & it was fresh & hot. I will definitely go back to this restaurant.

name: Stumpy's Spirits
categories: Distilleries, Food
text: I have been wanting to check out this local gem. Finally we made the short drive off of Route 3 and found the distillery. It is nestled on the owners family farm. He proudly told us during the tour that his whiskey is made similar to those in KY on the Bourbon trail, they use water feed springs that run under the property to make their "spirits". During the tour we were walked through the process of making the whiskey and vodka. After the tour we stopped in the tasting room/gift shop. We sampled their Pecan Pie Whiskey, their Honey Whiskey and my favorite the Unbroken Vodka. All distilled on their property. A special that they had was a free t-shirt with a bottle purchase. So you will be fashionable and drunk.... This place is worth the stop, and you can take a bottle home to sip at your leisure.

name: Dollar Tree
categories: Discount Store, Shopping
text: Love it because I can get so many things that I need for a one time occasion and I don't feel bad when I toss it the next day :D

name: Belleville Animal Clinic
categories: Pet Stores, Pet Services, Pet Groomers, Veterinarians, Pets
text: If not for the attention and care of the staff and Vets my 13 year old lab would not be walking.  They got him within half hour of my phone call.  The vet put him of a cocktail of meds and recommended laser therapy. I honestly thought he would not be coming home with us since he collapsed and his back legs would not work.  I go In every couple of weeks to get his meds refilled and they are friendly and caring.   The vet has even called to check on him.

name: Meineke Car Care Center
categories: Oil Change Stations, Automotive, Auto Repair, Tires
text: Ever since my brother could no longer change my vehicles oil, I've been looking for a place to take my vehicles. Meineke has been nothing but the perfect replacement for my brother to me. The wait times are short and they're always friendly there, not to mention every 5th oil change is free. Trust me I called around and for a basic oil most places were like $30 or more but not at Meineke. Meineke's basic oil change is only $19.95 and that includes a synthetic blend oil not just standard oil. I highly recommend Meineke for your oil changes.

name: Starbucks
categories: Coffee & Tea, Food
text: This location is convenient and closer to the college in town as well as avoiding the busy shopping centers where the other Starbucks is located. So far every encounter with the staff has been a good one. The tables have charging stations on them, only wish they had more tables but a Starbucks can only be so spacious.

name: Sleep Inn
categories: Hotels & Travel, Hotels, Event Planning & Services
text: Very clean and friendly staff. The lobby is always well decorated and smells amazing any time of day. The rooms are a bit cramped unless you get an end room. Beds are very comfy, showers hot and full of water pressure, and the pool is indoors so always open. The breakfast is run of the mill - eggs, cereal, waffles, etc. nothing special. Some rooms have a jacuzzi hot tub which are amazing and the main reason I keep coming back. That and the fact I've never seen a bug here.

name: Edwardsville Public Library
categories: Libraries, Festivals, Arts & Entertainment, Local Flavor, Public Services & Government
text:
There are 5 things that are great about Edwardsville, Illinois and this is clearly one of their hidden crown jewels.

Quiet, free wifi, excellent official reference librarian, you could do scientific research, book reports, or just plain ask for help.  An entire basement floor dedicated to children's books, story time, reading clubs for children and even computer rentals for adult and children.  It is a pillar of the community.  The route 66 festival is held annually among many events.  You can walk to downtown main street.  librarians will even call you when books are due!

Basket weaving, exhibits, stuff for the family have been here in the past.  I really like the large windows that let in light and soft leather chairs.

If you get hungry, you can walk to Wasabi Sushi, Sacred Grounds, Walgreens, CVS.. even Pizza.

name: Elegant Brides
categories: Fashion, Shopping, Bridal, Formal Wear
text:
The ladies here are incredibly helpful. They genuinely wanted to make sure I got exactly what I wanted. And I did. 
I came in open to ANY dress with a few details I was particular on. They worked with me fine tuning my vision and I ordered the most beautiful Maggie Sottero gown I could have dreamed up. 
Highly recommended.

name: McDonald's
categories: Fast Food, Coffee & Tea, Burgers, Food, Restaurants
text:
Went through drive through on a Sunday at 12:44.

Ordered a Big Mac combo, 3 sausage McMuffins, and a fruit and yogurt parfait.

Asked to pull forward to wait for food, it took all but 20 minutes to get food brought out. Meanwhile at least 10 cars got their food and left.

I don't know if it is pure incompetence or if they just can't do both breakfast and lunch at the same time but 20 minutes is a little ridiculous.

name: Starbucks
categories: Coffee & Tea, Food
text: Proably one of the best place to go and eat or drink in Edwardsville. I have only been here for 2 and a  half days and Ive been here twice already. Workers are friendly and my drinks have been delish!

name: Planet Fitness - Fairview Heights
categories: Trainers, Gyms, Tanning, Beauty & Spas, Active Life, Fitness & Instruction
text:
Ended up cancelling my membership here after my contract ran out because this place is gross. Thankfully I had access to another gym most of the time so I wasn't always forced to go here. 

The staff were always friendly, they never really spoke to me because they are usually at the front desk eating, but they also didn't do anything rude so I suppose that is good. 

However this place needs a serious clean up. The women's locker room smells like sewage, raw sewage. A hand dryer and a toilet stall have been broken for over a year with "out of order" signs on them -- apparently not ever going to be repaired. There is mold all over the floor in the bathroom area as well. 

The bulbs in the tanning beds haven't been changed in who knows how long, probably years, so if you are paying extra to tan it is a waste of money. 

The equipment isn't terrible and this place is cheap but if you can afford it I highly recommend going elsewhere just for hygiene purposes.

categories: Caterers, Event Planning & Services, Restaurants, Fast Food, Mexican
text:
I finally had a chance to try Qdoba.  I'll preface this by letting you all know I am a Chipotle addict.

So... I got the chicken queso burrito.  Rice and black beans were similar to C.  The chicken was good but not as good as C and in general it looked to me like the meats were higher quality and fresher at C.  Lots of sauces to choose from, I got pico, the one with corn, and the "next to hottest" - they were all good.  Guac, sour cream, and cheese all good.  The queso sauce was really tasty and I enjoyed it but I also know it pumped up the fat/calorie content (which is already high enough in burritos like these).  

I have to say overall I really liked it pretty much as much as C except the meat quality.  I will definitely go back bc it is closer than C but if given the choice... it's still C.

Oh, chips were good - had a good flavor and I think I do like them better than C's bc C's have gotten super salty in the last couple years.

name: Beloman
categories: Plumbing, Home Services, Air Duct Cleaning, Pest Control, Home & Garden, Professional Services, Advertising, Metal Fabricators, Kitchen & Bath, Shopping, Heating & Air Conditioning/HVAC, Contractors, Local Services
text:
Having an air conditioner break is never fun: it's a substantial unexpected expense and usually comes at a time where the need for cooling and humidity reduction is the greatest. Also, it's a substantial expense!

That said, what should a person expect? If a repair job by a handyman is selected, then one gets what one pays for. If a person opts in favor of an established company selling quality products, the expectation it that a job should be done professionally and in a reasonable time-frame, and that the customer should feel good about both the hardware quality and workmanship. Describing the expectation is important because BELOMAN exceeded it in almost every regard.

1) They use Carrier systems, which was the brand of condenser I replaced. Not only are the new units much nicer (despite not being top-of-the-line or anything fancy), but the coil inside my house is MUCH nicer. The original home manufacturer used a generic coil on the inside, which is the only kind I'd ever seen, so the complete Carrier system was nicer than my expectations.

2) When they arrived to do the install, there were two complications: that the unit wouldn't fit on the house-bracket (so it needed the ground plate) and that the nice inside coil was a bit wider and needed custom transitions to fit properly. No problem for BELOMAN! They had the common base on-hand, and metal workers took measurements, coming back from their shop with perfectly sized adapters to complete the professional installation.

3) My home has two furnaces, so I was quoted two days to complete the installation (two A/Cs onto existing furnaces). Additionally, I was informed that the personnel could not complete the outdoor soldering and electrical work if there were thunderstorms. Knowing that storms were predicted for the second installation day, two extra people arrived in the morning to accelerate the installation! This all-hands-on-deck approach (including someone who I overheard mentioning that he could only help for an hour before he had to be at another appointment) was truly exceptional. I'm sure don't always have capacity to do that, but to know that they will when they can.

4) As my air conditioning was failing, I had researched many methods to try and keep my house cooler. This left me with several questions about how best to use the new system moving forward. They took ample time to answer them and look at various ducts about which I had questions. They did not, at any point, seem rushed or bothered by taking the time to help me. In addition, they provided thoughtful responses that made me appreciate their time and knowledge (and they still finished ahead of schedule)!

5) The person who came to the house also did a great job listening to my needs and designing a solution that would accommodate.

6) On top of all this, they were genuinely nice people. They were mindful of my dog when coming in and out of the house (petting him even), and even asked about the project I was working on in my garage. 

Together, all this made me feel that the whole team really was invested in me, my home, and of course my air conditioning. I don't know if there's anything else they could have done to make the experience more enjoyable. I would recommend them to anyone who wants a quality job, done right, the first time, by great professionals.

name: Tri-City Speedway
categories: Active Life, Racing Experience
text:
Took advantage of a groupon back in November and set up a technician 6 month incentive with the payout being held at Tri-City Speedway and a package to the Kenny Wallace Dirt Track Racing Experience.  

From the moment we arrived, the ladies in the check in trailer were extremely helpful and added to the overall experience.  They took us back to give us the run down of rules, and explain how to drive the car.  What to do and how to do it.  Even if you have never been in a race car, they will give you more than enough information to make you comfortable getting in and running.

It was a very hot day, but we all got in our fire suits, picked out a helmet and got pictures taken by the car we were going to drive.  They stuffed ear pieces in the helmets and we were walked through every lap by a team member in the stands.  He helped with lap traffic and reminding you to be smooth and controlled when drifting through a corner.  I have done several racing schools, Michigan, Gateway, but never ran on dirt.  I have to tell you, it is a totally different experience.  

It was a great time, and all my technicians that won were extremely happy with the program. I would love to do it again, and we may have to set up a little contest for one of my other stores so they can get the same experience.  Its a great team building event, no matter what your business is.  You should give it a try!

text: Two visits now and I am thrilled about the place and the folks who own it as well as the staff.  The cheese/meat plate I had was great.  The wines were nice as well.  Being a serious wine enthusiast for twenty five years I often look for a broad offering of interesting wines, but starting a place that features wine in a beer town might be suited to starting with a modest offering and growing with the clientele's feedback and hopefully a knowledgeable distributor (or two or three..).  Hemingway's is a fantastic departure from chains and sports pubs and beer halls.

name: Happy Hop Home Brew & Gourmet
categories: Breweries, Food, Shopping, Brewing Supplies
text: I made a day of it, literally, and headed to downtown Belleville to check out Dave's Homebrewing and get what I needed to make my 5 Hoppiness Wheat IPA. Everything I needed was there and easy to find. I liked that they kept their malts in bulk, and you could ask for any amount, and they would either bag it up for you or run it through the mill. Very friendly staff and I would go again, even though it is out of the way for me. They did tell me that they will ship anything for a flat rate, so that could be a option to save me the drive.

name: Hollywood Show Club
attributes: {'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '3', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}"}
categories: Nightlife, Adult Entertainment
text:
I came with a group of 6 girls. We were visiting our friend who strips here. They wouldnt even let us in the door because we didn't have a male escort. They said we needed 1 male per 1 female. I've never heard of another strip club having this rule. We found a party bus in the parking lot full of males, enough to escort us all. Security came and said all of us females needed to leave because those "were not our dates". I guess my money isn't as good as theirs? Although I was planning on buying drinks and paying for dances. VERY RUDE. No wonder they have 10 cars In the lot compared to Larry Flint's 60+ cars. Save yourself the trouble. What type of business turns away ten paying customers? 

Oh and also, the party bus we met told the bouncer to shove it and went down the road was well. Way better clubs in the area.

text: Came here for Sunday brunch with my family, LOVED IT! The crab cake Benedict was fantastic. I tried the meat lovers omelet and that is what I'll be getting next time. Finished brunch off with carrot cake. Great experience, great service, great food. Kind of fancy but it was a nice treat. Most definitely will return.

name: Pirtles Famous Ice Cream
categories: Food, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt
text:
No seating. Ice cream was freezer burned. Very expensive for the quality. No toppings are offered outside of Reece's or Snickers so I'm not sure where the pictures of the layered sundaes are coming from. 

Very, very disappointed in this visit compared to the other ice cream parlors in the area.

name: Dawn Corwin Creative Photography
categories: Event Planning & Services, Session Photography, Photographers, Event Photography
text: We love the work they do; however, after your shoot the customer service is lacking severely. You wait 3+ months for your pictures after spending $2,000+. We have them a second chance and After having a discussion that this is not the norm the same thing happens. They prioritize new customers over taking care of the ones they owe pictures too. The same excuses presented. Then when you get your pictures there are things missing. We were warned about this after our first mishap but like the other reviewers gave a second chance just to have the same thing happen. Again, they do great work and if you can wait 3+ months for your stuff then this is the place for you. If not heed the warnings.

attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'Corkage': 'True', 'BYOB': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Ambience': "{u'divey': None, u'hipster': None, u'casual': True, u'touristy': None, u'trendy': None, u'intimate': None, u'romantic': None, u'classy': None, u'upscale': None}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
categories: Pizza, Italian, Restaurants
text:
Nice outdoor dining area brought us here. Plenty of space between tables, and umbrellas for shade. Waitress was masked and polite. Those are all positives.

Unfortunately, the food and service were more of a mixed bag. Somehow, they ran out of Coke. And, in general, the service was very slow. My cod sandwich was pretty good (the fish part), but the bun was burnt. Meanwhile, the fries were a soggy mess -- the most disappointing part of the meal. They were oily and soft throughout.

Overall, there are many Waterloo restaurants superior to Frederico's.

categories: Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Restaurants, Burgers, Food, Fast Food
text: This is an older DQ so not as nice looking as a newer DQ building.  What it does have is good service and best DQ food I have eaten.  So do not come for the decor, but all the things that make this a local traditional favorite.

text: Had a great time at the Obar Cafe!  Very friendly atmosphere. Great brunch food selection. There were also options for adult beverages as well.  Will definitely be back.

name: Hokkaido Seafood Buffet and Grill
attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': True, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'Caters': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}"}
categories: Buffets, Seafood, Chinese, Restaurants
text:
When it comes to good Chinese buffets in the metro east area your choices have been pretty much limited to Ginger, until now. Hokkaido opened recently in the old Ryan's Steakhouse location and they have done some extensive renovations to the interior. Overall the selection is great, traditional Asian inspired food, American, large desert bar, and a hibachi station. The food is great, probably one of the best Asian buffet in the St.Louis area. The food was fresh and the chicken was moist and tender, nothing was dried or tasted like it was sitting out for a long time. 

Prices are fair, lunch was about 25 for two with drinks. A little bit more expensive than some of the other choices like Ginger, however the food was much better and that more than makes up for the difference. Trust me if you are considering between the two I would choose Hokkaido any day over Ginger, and I used to love Ginger. 

For those in Missouri Hokkaido also has a location in North County, more specifically Florissant, MO off North Highway 67. I haven't been to this location yet however I would assume that the quality is the same..

categories: American (New), Restaurants, Bakeries, Food, Breakfast & Brunch
text: We passed this last weekend and couldn't wait to come back and try it.  Cute place!  Maybe they are trying to compete with Cracker Barrel.  Fun lil general store area inside and a nice bakery, complete with ice cream and coffee selections!  They've only been open 3 weeks and people are still learning their places. The hostess was friendly and welcoming and our server Kelly, was perfect for us.  A fun gal, with a little spitfire.  We had the breakfast, just FYI, only served until 10:30.  Simple selections.  Hubs and I both had their hash brown casserole, similar to a Strata, a baked, sliced cheese covered, mile high concoction with eggs, potatoes, sausage and onions, side of toast. I also ordered a side of the breakfast gravy, for dipping, ya know.  Everything was pretty good. The lunch and dinner menu looked good as well. All you can eat fried chicken on Wednesday and Sunday!  After our meal, we stopped by the store and the bakery!  Everything was wonderful!  Look forward to going back again!

name: Winchester Place Apartments
categories: Real Estate, Apartments, Home Services
text:
I lived here for a year and enjoyed the pool and quick response to any repairs/issues needed. The apartment complex was quite, never had any issues with others in the building. I moved out because there were better, newly remolded apartments in the area for a much lesser price. Winchester did want to raise the rent over $200 and also had integrated this new rent payment site online that residents were forced to pay through. The processing fee was almost $20. NO WAY! 

The location is nice, the grounds keeping is nice. But the apartments do need some renovation for the pricing. They are all carpet with outdated kitchen appliances and cabinets. If you want a loft apartment, you'll have to get a apartment on the 3rd floor. And let me tell you those are a lot of steps...which was a tiring hike up uneven placed stairs everyday that I never seemed to get use too. 

I wouldn't rent there again or recommend it just because the interior of the apartments aren't up to date. And because of all the steep steps to climb if you want a loft style apartment.

name: Brent Bergheger Chrysler Dodge Jeep Ram
categories: Oil Change Stations, Car Dealers, Automotive, Auto Repair
text: If I was not pressed for time, I would have taken my car  to another Chrysler dealership. It took them 2 weeks to fix a minor issue with my car. They never once called me to give me a estimate or even let me know my car was ready for pick.  They however, did a great job repairing my vehicle. Thats the only reason I gave them 3 stars instead of 1. The customer service was terrible!    Didn't even get a thank you back from the grumpy old man who was upset he had to get up from his desk to cash me out. This place will not see another penny of mine.  Recommend anyone interested in taking their vehicle to this place think twice.  The Auffenberg dealerships in O'fallon are definitely worth the 10 mile drive.
