categories: Restaurants, Mexican
text:
9/10 authenticity!
10/10 cleanliness (cleanest authentic Mexican restaurant I've ever been to)
10/10 on customer service

Think of it as a more authentic version of chipotle, but with a better price.  

The tacos are great and NO CHARGE for guacamole, or any topping for that matter.  The burritos are just as big as Chipotle's, but with more meat/less filler.  The drinks are authentic too.  I like the Agua de Jamaica (hibiscus tea) but my kids get the jarritos Mexican sodas.  If you want tacos or burritos, this is your place; if you're looking for a larger menu, hit Fairmont city, but you'll drive farther and pay more.

name: American Nails
categories: Beauty & Spas, Nail Salons
text: This is a good place for a pedi! The owner is always there and she remembers you! They always talk to you instead of exclusively to themselves and try to remember your preferences. My whole family comes here! And they have good prices for services!

name: Don's Hardware
categories: Shopping, Home & Garden, Hardware Stores
text: Wonderful staff. Just packed with knowledge and parts too. The parts people are genuinely helpful and interested in seeing to it that I get the right parts and even parts that I hadn't thought of. It's that kind of experience that turns a once thought junk appliance into a reliable one for years to come.

name: Great Clips
categories: Hair Salons, Beauty & Spas
text:
As simple and basic a haircut may be, for some reason it can be hard to find a place where the people are decent and they don't screw up. For me that place is this Great Clips.

I've been coming here for the past 2 years for my monthly haircut (my hair grows fast). I don't have a favorite stylist I just go with who is available, and I have never had a bad experience. The stylist are nice, quick, and professional.

I really like how they save your preferences in their computer. It eliminates explaining what you want, there doesn't seem to be any confusion, and they confirm what you want before they begin.

I don't need a flashy salon, just a place that gets the job done. This place can do that, and they won't hurt your wallet either.

name: Valvoline Instant Oil Change
categories: Automotive, Auto Repair, Oil Change Stations
text: Great place to have your car serviced.  I was very impressed with the friendly service.  The guys all seemed very knowledgeable. They were training a gentleman today and they treated him  respect.  Carla does a fantastic job supervising the crew.  She worked very hard.  I will always bring my vehicles here for a thorough service!!  Very positive exoerience!!

text: This place is a hidden gem!  They have a variety of items on the menu and the food is great. It did not take long at all- even during the lunch rush!  Large portions and it's cheap too!  The gyro was amazing. I can't wait to try the Reuben soup when I go back.

name: Tin Rooster
categories: American (Traditional), Restaurants, Food, Breakfast & Brunch, Bakeries
text: If you think free hotel breakfasts are awesome, you'll love the buffet, except here you'll pay $8.99 for it. Powdered eggs, dried out potatoes, sausage and ham sitting in a 1/2" deep pan of oil, undercooked pancakes and mediocre biscuits and gravy. The ice tea was good. The service was decent and the price is cheap. We won't be back for breakfast. I'm leery to try the regular menu for dinner but we'll likely give it a shot to see if it's any better.

name: Bin 51 Wine & Spirits
categories: Beer, Wine & Spirits, Food
text:
One of the best smaller wine stores I've run across, coast to coast. Well curated selection, knowledgable and patient folks there to help you out... And best of all you can pick a bottle, sit at the bar, and for (I think) a $6 corkage fee, have them serve it to you there. They also have some selections by the glass. 

You can order outside food for delivery there, and Cleveland-Heath (quite excellent in their own right) is literally next door. Still, might be fun if Bin 51 had a few snacks available... or perhaps even a cheese/meat/cracker tray... 

That notwithstanding, the wine selection is robust for a store of its size, and well thought out... and you can drink it there for much less dough than you'd pay for a bottle of the same stuff at a restaurant. Go for it!

categories: American (Traditional), Event Planning & Services, Breakfast & Brunch, Caterers, Comfort Food, Southern, Restaurants, American (New)
text:
First of all, I would like to say that this place has great food items on their menu and they are quite delicious.  I enjoy coming here for lunch or dinner because of the delicious food.  I do not, however, enjoy the service which saddens me terribly because like I said, I love their food and their pecan pies during the fall.

Every experience I have had here has been disappointing when it comes to the service.  I have been to the one in Caseyville, and Troy but I have been to this location the most.  Regardless of the location, I get the same low quality type of service.  The waitresses always seem very lethargic, stressed out, rushed, and not very friendly.  I have been there during different hours of the day, including times when they aren't busy and yet I have never had a server who actually looked like they even remotely have any interest in serving their clients.  Unfortunately, these horrible experiences have been embedded inside my head that sometimes, even when I feel like going there for their food, the memories of bad service holds me back and instead takes me somewhere else.  

To the food, I love the cracker barrel sampler but I have also had their country fried steak and they were all good.  For the price, you're really getting a great bargain and they give you three sides of a long list of sides which is really awesome because you can try out different things.  

I also have to mention that this place does have a great feel to it for dinning and the food that they serve compliments the atmosphere.  I definitely commend them for doing a great job on that part.  However, in an overall rating, I would give the service a 1-star and the food a 3-star.

name: Club Fitness - O'Fallon
categories: Active Life, Gyms, Fitness & Instruction, Trainers
text:
I really like this gym. Its new but they work hard to keep it clean. There are many choices in equipment and classes. Plus the place is 24 hours! 
I wish it had a place to swim but the sauna and infrared massage kind of compensate. And for the cost I feel it is well worth it.

name: The Wildey Theatre

text: I had my wedding ceremony at the Wildey November 7th 2015. I cannot express to you enough how GREAT my experience was. Janel took care of my every question without hesitation. She helped me every step of the way. When I arrived her staff was so accomodating. They spoke over walkie talkies to help organize and shuffle people around, and to make sure music and timing was perfect. I didn't have to worry about a single thing. Janel went above and beyond, she even helped manage a few rocky family situations without hesitation! If you are looking into the Wildey for your wedding. I highly suggest it!

name: Granite City Urgent Care Walk In Clinic
categories: Medical Centers, Walk-in Clinics, Urgent Care, Health & Medical
text: This has got to be the most ill-practiced staff I've ever come across. You can tell they all have no fucking clue what the hell is going on. I was told over the phone that they can do physicals INCLUDING IMMUNIZATIONS and then when I get here, after I've already paid ofcourse, they then tell me they can not. And whoever the "doctor" was had absolutely no professionalism and was a literal joke. I would absolutely NEVER recommend this place to ANYONE.

name: T-Mobile
categories: Shopping, Mobile Phones, Telecommunications, Mobile Phone Accessories, Electronics, Local Services, IT Services & Computer Repair
text: Long-time TMobile customer (about 10 years), and I recently had a major issue with my cell phone. Despite how frustrating it was to not have a phone for a couple of days, I got my phone replaced twice in a week and the employees here were patient, kind, & knowledgeable. Thank you especially to Aaron & Brandon for your awesome customer service!

name: Express Medical Care
categories: Health & Medical, Urgent Care
text: They did a great job of caring for me and even helped me find a primary care provider.  Their staff is efficient, thorough, friendly and knowledgable.  I'm glad they are right up the street if I need them.

text: Absolutely love that I can order online and that they deliver! I got the broccoli & cheese soup and the Mediterranean veggie sandwich and both were really good, as always. I love their specialty coffees and smoothies, as well as the bagel and bread selections. I will definitely continue to go here.

name: Dobbs Tire & Auto Centers
categories: Automotive, Oil Change Stations, Tires, Auto Repair
text:
The worst interaction with an auto repair institution. DO NOT! I repeat, do not Interact and/or do business with one of the pseudo managers Ron. I'm not sure what happened to him as a young man but he is not equipped to make rational and/or ethical decisions as an adult. Before going to this Dobb's location to get a quote, I had already received a quote from another mechanic. So to be clear, I already knew what was wrong with my vehicle and I explained to Ron that I simply just needed a quote for the issues that had already been diagnosed from the previous mechanic. No big deal, right? Apparently not! Upon retrieving my vehicle from Dobb's, Ron informs me that I am being charged $129 for an estimate. At no point did Ron explain or tell me that I would be charged $129 for a simple quote. Again, I already knew what was wrong with my vehicle, I was simply price shopping. After over an hour of arguing (which Ron was extremely rude, unprofessional and spoke to me as if I was a neighbor he didn't care or have any respect for) Ron finally agreed to lower to charge to $100. At this point he also told me that him as well as the other mechanics would have to cover the $29 "discount" I received. Now c'mon.. Really, Ron? You guys had to cover "my bill"? Another drop of untruth in a waterfall of lies, Ronnie. I paid the $100 and left with my faith in humanity once again shaken. This is simply a warning to my fellow road warriors. BUYER BEWARE! If anyone (this includes you Ron, or any representative from the Dobb's company) would like to call me I am leaving my personal phone number. I will be glad to further share my experience, give advice, recommend legitimate/honest mechanics or welcome a full refund. Thank you and don't forget to wear your seatbelt! 618-882-0047

UPDATED 2/3/18

A store supervisor reached out to me and was extremely apologetic about my experience. I was issued a check for $150 to reimburse the original $100 they charged me plus $50 for my experience. The store supervisor was very professional and I wish he was the individual I had originally encountered the day I originally visit the Shiloh Dobb's location. Thank you.

name: Stone Falls Dental Care
categories: Periodontists, Dentists, General Dentistry, Cosmetic Dentists, Health & Medical
text: This is absolutely a five-star establishment. I've seen nothing but professionalism from this place in the last few years. When I got military orders and needed a last-minute dental exam, they slipped me in -which was a benefit to me, my family, and my unit. Additionally as I was leaving from that appointment I heard them singing happy birthday to their receptionist. They seem like a very patient-centered dental office AND a pleasant workplace.

text:
The service was great. 

The restaurant was decorated very cute . Very much in theme to what the restaurant was serving.  

The BBQ was okay . I say this because the brisket was really dry . Taste very good but the dryness took away from the flavor. The sauces were fair, hot sauce had a mild heat , sweet had good flavor , mustard tasted just like yellow mustard :(.  The onion rings were good , my husband loved the mushrooms with horseradish . I did try my husbands pulled pork sandwich and it was really good .

name: East Town Donuts
categories: Donuts, Food
text: The donuts are decent if you don't mind waiting your whole morning. Even with an online offer I had to wait over an hour after the time it should have been ready to get them. They were very understaffed or overextended. They even forgot items for my order.

name: Target
categories: Home & Garden, Shopping, Grocery, Drugstores, Fashion, Department Stores, Food, Electronics, Furniture Stores
text: I love this Target. I get my prescriptions filled here and I come daily for my #Shopkick points and always leave with a good deal! You can never beat using coupons on items you get gift cards for! Love it!

name: Safelite AutoGlass
categories: Automotive, Auto Glass Services, Windshield Installation & Repair, Body Shops
text: My recent visit to safelite in Alton was one of the best automotive experiences I've had. The technician, Curtis, is the man. He will take care if you! He did a great job on my window repair!

text: I ate there for the first time.  The menu is a bit long with a lot of different items.  I had the lunch special a sandwich, fries ad a drink.  The iced tea was brewed and very good, the ruben was very tasty with lots of meat and kraut, the fries were very good done and hot.  The waitress was very helpful and polite.  I belive I have found an other good place to eat.

name: Best Western O'Fallon Hotel
categories: Hotels & Travel, Event Planning & Services, Hotels
text: Wish I could give zero stars. I'm pretty confident the floors have never been vacuumed or mopped. We stayed for a week and I started noting stains on the tile in common areas just to see if they were still there the next day (they were there the entire week). Dishes were left over night in the breakfast area with old dried food on them.  This place was beyond dirty, but the worst of it all was someone used a master key to enter our room and steal items. Not only was our room broken into, but other rooms on our floor were broken into on the same day, and expensive electronic items were stolen. The police came and were able to check the electronic key card reader on the door and noticed a master key that hadn't been used in over a month was used to access the rooms. The police also mentioned that they've had multiple complaints on Best Western. This was hands down my worst hotel experience, and I will never stay at another Best Western again because of it. Please take my warning and stay away. Stay anywhere but this place.

name: CPR Cell Phone Repair Fairview Heights
categories: Shopping, Local Services, IT Services & Computer Repair, Telecommunications, Mobile Phones, Mobile Phone Repair, Electronics Repair
text: We dropped off a cell phone with a cracked screen.  Was told that it would be ready the next day, it was not - but no big deal it is easy to fall behind.  When we did pick it up we did not notice that the screen shows white light around the bottom edge where the screen was not glued down all the way.  Took it back and they kept it another 4 or 5 hours then gave it back to us.  The next day the screen popped up again in the exact same spot, however, this time it developed a small crack starting in that corner (obviously glass does not bend well!) - took it back and they told me that they would give me the labor to fix it again free and a 10% discount on the screen (about 14.00 off of a 140.00 screen) - they absolutely refused to take ANY responsibility for the screen not being repaired correctly the first time.  I would avoid them.

text: Great place. Great atmosphere and great bartenders. The siding and exterior is so beautiful. Extremely professionally done. I want that guy to side my house. The interior is top notch and it is a fun place no matter what time or day.

name: Green Mount Lakes
categories: Apartments, Home Services, Real Estate
text:
This place was great...until we moved out!  We were super excited at the chance to live here, and it was an added perk that we only had a $24 deposit due to me being in grad school still.   The community was decent, apart from the kids that parents let run rampant.  And the staff was decent the majority of the time. 

 A month before our lease was up, we received a $100 late fee charge.  When I went to the office to see what it was for, as we were NEVER late on our rent.  Andree originally told me it was because I never paid the second half of my pet deposit ($300 total.)  When I told her I knew for a fact that was wrong, she quickly changed her tune to that it was because part of our rent was late.....in MARCH.  When I asked her why it took so long (it was now October), she didn't have an answer for me. So we sucked it up and paid the stupid late fee knowing it wasn't late.  THEN a few weeks after moving out, we received a charge of $125 listed as "pet cleaning".  I personally steam cleaned the floors AND knew that there was still a pet deposit of $150 (the other $150 was supposedly nonrefundable).  My boyfriend called several times to discuss the matter, and was always given the run around and promised a return call.  THEN yesterday we received a letter indicating they had turned us over to collections.  I simply believe that these people were out to get more money from us due to the fact that we didn't have a full deposit during move-in since I received the "student special".  I will NEVER recommend this place to anyone.  Beware.

name: The Happy Bakery
categories: Food, Restaurants, Vegetarian, Custom Cakes, Specialty Food, Vegan, Cupcakes, Bakeries
text: Recently exploring a vegan lifestyle so we came to check out the Happy Bakery....let me tell you that the bakery items we sampled were delicious! I guess they have new selections throughout the week... today we tried the savory bacon cheddar garlic scone! Delicious! My friend tried the cinnamon chip scone, and two other kinds of tasty muffins. Also, very good!!Highlights:  a large selection of freshly baked goods, complimentary coffee today, friendly counter service, and a we were able to enjoy our items on the sunny patio! The real kicker is that entire bakery is vegan! A shiny gem for the metro east!

name: Domino's Pizza
categories: Sandwiches, Pizza, Chicken Wings, Restaurants
text: First of all, I do not normally make reviews on franchise restaurants, because you know what you're getting for the most part. However, I use yelp often for restaurant locations/address and I noticed the terrible (2) 1-star reviews. This almost deterred me from going here, but it's the closest to our home. I decided to give it a try. The young man who took the order was so nice! The order was correct and everything was just as expected from an inexpensive franchise pizza joint.

name: R & R Transportation Service
categories: Hotels & Travel, Transportation, Airport Shuttles, Taxis
text: R&R helped me so much back in the winter of 2016 when there was a awful ice storm. My car was in the shop and I needed to pick up my son from daycare. The roads were so bad that there were cars stopped all over the place. I was afraid R&R was going to cancel on me because of the awful conditions but the owner didn't. Royce pulled through to pick me up and took me to my son. I'll always be grateful for what Royce did that night for my son and I.

name: Dill's Floral Haven
categories: Flowers & Gifts, Party & Event Planning, Gift Shops, Shopping, Wedding Planning, Event Planning & Services, Florists, Floral Designers
text: We used Dill's for our wedding.  We had to switch florists at the last second, so I chose Dill's only because of its website and customer testimonials.  I wasn't disappointed.  We worked with Amanda who was very friendly and helpful and created beautiful bouquets.  If I ever need a florist again, I will definitely go to Dill's.

name: Moody-Longacre Park
categories: Active Life, Parks, Playgrounds
text:
Wonderful turf play area for kids, beautiful pond and lots of kids activities.

Many places for gatherings, very large sand volleyball courts.

text: This place is ok. I've been here once and I ordered the bbq sliders (3 pretty much regular sized buns). Way too much food for one person. If I liked the slider I would've only ate one and the salad. The salad was also huge! I only ate two bites of my slider bc it straight up tasted like breakfast meat (too much maple). I don't eat pizza but I'd be willing to give this place one more shot. I liked the salad I ordered.

name: The Sports Academy
categories: Active Life, Venues & Event Spaces, Event Planning & Services, Fitness & Instruction, Soccer
text: This place was good for a rainy day so the kids could burn some energy but I wouldn't really be interested in doing a party here or anything. Only $3 a kid to play in the jungle gym so that was nice. There where wires exposed from a ride that bothered me because we had small kids with us and they could really use some cleaning under the play area.

All in all, a pretty good place to eat.  Burgers are good, as well!

name: Jimmy John's
categories: Sandwiches, Food, Food Delivery Services, Restaurants, Delis, Fast Food
text: I am a fan of Jimmy John's.  Their sandwiches are very tasty.  This particular store is well maintained and clean.  My only issue with this store is they usually have the music up so loud it is hard to carry on a conversation.

text:
Always reliable food here. We are big fans of the spinach artichoke dip and cheeseburger egg rolls. Both are delicious ! For meals last time I had the chicken tender basket with fries, can't really go wrong there (minus the calories !) my son had the surf and turf and he loved his steak and the shrimp. My daughter had the three cheese chicken cavatini and it was a huge portion. She enjoyed it also.

Only reason not to rate it higher was the waiter was not the best. A little slow all the way around and they weren't super busy.  But not terrible either just not a five star experience on the service end.

categories: Mexican, Restaurants
text:
$7.99 lunch buffet. Not bad. The manager (owner?) seemed very nice. Service was good. Food... ehhh... I didn't hate it but didn't love it either. I did, however, really like how everything on the buffet line seemed fresh (especially the salad bar ingredients and salsa). The line also had more to offer than other local Mex buffets (Zapatas and Casa Azteca). As we were leaving, the owner told us that they do not have their liquor license yet so "next time we come in, bring whatever you like to drink and we'll get it set up for you." -- which was nice.

Overall, may go back just to support but would probably stick with other mex restaurants in the area.

-- oh. Also... the rice had potatoes in it, which was different but nice.

name: Animal Emergency Center
categories: Veterinarians, Pet Services, Emergency Pet Hospital, Pets
text: The staff is amazingly caring and sincere. I was confident my pups received the best possible care and would recommend them to anyone in needs of ER services!!

name: Bard & Didriksen Pediatrics
categories: Pediatricians, Health & Medical, Doctors
text:
After asking many of our friends who already had kids who is the best pediatrician in the Metro-East we decided to see Dr. Nauman at Bard & Didriksen Pediatrics.  We are very glad we did.  Dr. Nauman and the staff are awesome.  They always listen and are more than willing to answer any questions (even those from an over-reactive new parent).

The one thing I really like about this office besides that great staff is they have separate waiting rooms for well patients and those that are sick.  No more sitting in a room full of sick people when you are there for a check-up.  

I highly recommend Bard & Didriksen Pediatrics!

categories: Dentists, Health & Medical, General Dentistry, Cosmetic Dentists, Orthodontists, Endodontists
text:
So this doc had my tooth pulled out and he was very forceful on my lower jaw. I'm having this major swelling now after the procedure and have to see an oral surgeon to have it fixed. 
I'll not choose here for any of my future dental work.

name: Relleke Farms
categories: Pumpkin Patches, Food, Shopping, Farmers Market, Home & Garden
text:
Great place to spend a weekend in October with your family!  There is so much to do here my family comes back every weekend!   

They have various food vendors from River Fish, Funnel Cakes, Corn Dogs, BBQ, Fried Chicken and Mexican!  You will not go home hungry!

They keep the kiddie busy with rides, hayrides, a petting zoo and much more.  

Check their website for the weekends that the firetrucks come out, or the pumpkin smasher. 

Don't forget to stock up on pumpkins while you are down here, the Relleke Family works hard to make sure there is plenty for everyone.

name: C And C Food For Your Soul
attributes: {'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}

text: C&C for your Soul is definitely good for my soul!The chef and owner is there cooking and supervising each order. She has a open area kitchen where you can see her and her staff prepare your meal with fresh ingredients. I have been here two times and she has not disappointed. Today, I had catfish fillets with homemade mac and cheese and spaghetti with homemade meat sauce. I could eat her home cooked entrees daily. Do yourself a favor and try this new restaurant. The customer service, cleanliness, and fast service adds to the great tasting food.

name: La-Z-Boy Furniture Galleries
categories: Home & Garden, Home Decor, Home Services, Furniture Stores, Interior Design, Shopping
text: I was very impressed with the way the entire staff helped me. Pascha gave me all of her attention for well over 2 hours, Lawrence was attentive as well and steered me toward what I was looking for. And Chris (?) was helpful in offering discounts and accomodating my budget. The furniture is beautiful and well made and I was made to feel comfortable and like I was the only one in the store. It was a great experience.

text: When l walked in, the display in front of me had the same brand same box same wreath as Walmart has for $7.99. At Home price was $14.00. First impression was cheap stuff at inflated prices. Some of there other things were neat.  Big selection of rugs.

text: I have just recently discovered this place and find that I crave it often.  So far I have only sampled the calzones, salads and sandwiches. The pizza comes highly reccomended by several people in Belleville. Very polite staff and quick service. The chicken ultimate calzone is huge and delicious. Order it for dinner and you'll have leftovers for lunch! The pastas and wings are next on my list. I'm sure I'll have more raves to share as soon as I try them.

name: St Clair Bowl
categories: Arts & Entertainment, Leisure Centers, Active Life, Party & Event Planning, Event Planning & Services, Sporting Goods, Restaurants, American (New), Arcades, Bowling, Shopping
text:
I came here after a late lunch with a friend. We decided to go bowling because it's something we both enjoy and don't do very often. Since we were in Fairview, we came here. I had been here a couple of times since I was on the bowling team in high school. The alley is average and a little outdated, but the lanes, balls, and seating areas were fine for us. 

We went to the counter and we were not treated kindly. We ask said we wanted to get a lane and the lady only said "bowl fast, were cleaning the lanes in 20 minutes." Like I said spending time in alleys before, I understood this. So, we said we would just want one game. I guess there must have been some miscommunication, but she was extremely rude and began yelling at us. After confusion was taken care of and she understood it was one game for each of us and on the same lane, she said I will put you away from the oiler to you have more time. Then, she put us only a few lanes away from where the oiler began so I don't understand what she was thinking? We were rushed in our one game. This would not have seemed so bad if it weren't for the terrible service we received at the counter. 

Since we felt our time together had been cut short, we decided to be goofy and go to the arcade. I got cash out from the atm and got $10 worth of coins. I immediately regretted my decision. 80% of the machines took my tokens without working and the change back didn't work. Then, most did not even give out tickets. When we tried to tell someone, no one was at the counter. 

Overall, what we thought would be a relaxing afternoon turned out to be a terrible lesson.@

name: Community Kindness Resale Shoppe
categories: Shopping, Thrift Stores
text: This a great thrift shop, well organized and prices are clearly marked. If you're looking for furniture there is a whole warehouse next to the main store just for their furniture and bigger items so be sure to ask. I will say that I wasn't thrilled to find that they were selling a several years expired car seat on my last visit there and didn't seem concerned about it; car seats should not be resold, but especially not expired ones.

name: Gateway Regional Medical Center
categories: Health & Medical, Medical Centers, Sleep Specialists
text: Place is a joke and the nurses are lazy especially the ones in kettler. Every elevator is out of order. Just drive a little further to Anderson hospital.

categories: Coffee & Tea, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Food
text: The owner of this place is doing a great job! The staff are always happy and polite. Their menu is very extensive. I recommend reading it online if you've never been. Sooo many options. My favorite thing at Shivers are the coffee offerings. Try an affogato if you love coffee and have a sweet tooth!

name: MedExpress Urgent Care
categories: Health & Medical, Walk-in Clinics, Medical Centers, Doctors, Urgent Care
text: Came in to get checked and it was 20 mins till close and was in and out like if nothing was wrong with me.

name: Hooch & Sixteen's
categories: Bars, Nightlife
text: Great tacos and best hand mixed Bloody Mary in town!

name: European Wax Center
categories: Waxing, Hair Removal, Skin Care, Beauty & Spas
text: If you usually break out from getting your eyebrows waxed then definitely DO NOT go here. I'm so broken out in every spot she put the wax around my eyebrows. I'm assuming it's the kind of wax they use because I have never broken out this bad from going to a salon. The lady that did mine did a fine job I'm just writing this so people with sensitive skin will avoid the pain of being so broken out afterwards. Definitely not worth it!

name: Centennial Park
categories: Hiking, Parks, Active Life
text: This is a nice retreat nestled in a corner of Swansea. This is not a big park, but it is beautiful. It is like walking through a fairy tale forest. Shady with tree canopies overhead, wooden bridge, and a stream. I will be back with my fave walking Buddy.

name: Ruler Foods
categories: Food, Grocery
text: I don't buy much from the store just wanted to say that the cashier made my day. Not often are people so funny and nice it seems and this cashier was hilarious we bounced off of each other's jokes and after the 6th day of rain I really needed something to laugh about. I will be going back just for that very reason good customer service

categories: American (Traditional), Bars, Nightlife, Restaurants, Sports Bars
text: The food tastes like yesterday's food. My husband got the meatloaf and it was way over cooked and looked old. I had the horseshoe (how can you mess that up!) and the fries were soggy and not hot, the kidney beans in the chili topping were overpowering, there was only one hamburger patty, (but two slices of bread) there was hardly any cheese and none of it tasted like it was cooked within the past hour. They served those two entrees first and then we waited about 10 min before my son got his chicken ranch sandwich with the same old fries. The waitress even brought out a new plate of fries for him (we had said nothing) and said his looked "soggy." I couldn't eat my horseshoe, so I ordered some onion rings. They were very good. When we were almost finished, the waitress asked how everything was. I told her the onion rings were great, but the horseshoe, not so much. She made no mention of any adjustments, and for that matter, made no apologies. Needless to say, we won't be going back anytime soon.

name: United States Post Office
categories: Public Services & Government, Post Offices
text: Sometimes, the line is too long. And I wish the clerks would smile more. But, for most of my shipping needs, the USPS still offers the best value, and this is the best one around.

text:
I'm giving them 4 stars, because they shine a little brighter than some of the other Quick Service restaurants in the area. 

We've been there twice in the last 2 weeks - right when the lobby is closing (but the drive thru is still open). They were attentitive, friendly, and accomodating. Even though they had put the condiment station away, they cheerfully got us little containers of pickles and peppers. The Regular roast beef is very good and was cooked to order. Also, love the waffle fries.

name: Strange Folk Festival
categories: Festivals, Arts & Entertainment
text:
I don't know why I've never been to this festival until this year. Maybe the very strange promotional art? I thought it was going to be very hippie, and it was in a way, but it brought out a lot of people...and not all of them were hippies. I do love the idea though: arts and crafts through upcycled material...how much cooler is that?

Getting there is somewhat of a pain because Highway 50 narrows down to one lane each way when you get close to the park. Add to that Oktoberfests galore, and you have a very nice recipe for "traffic jam". Everyone parks everywhere, but surprisingly enough, parking wasn't that big of a deal. It is really a family thing too. They have arts and crafts for the kids, indie bands playing, lots of picnic tables set up with the usual assortment of fair foods, an alpaca petting zoo, and of course, Girl Scouts selling cookies. 

But the booths themselves are the showcase, and the media is quite varied, even though I heard a booth owner complain, "It is so hard nowadays to be original." She was selling wire jewelry, so I guess I can see her point. And really, my favorite booths are really the unique ones like Beqi Clothing and Newberry Furniture. The Newberrys repurpose old wood for new stuff...their current thing consists of Adirondack chairs made from an old barn. And Beqi takes vintage clothing and changes it all around..she has quite the gift. The whole thing is pretty big, and it really does impress me that there are so many craftsters in the area.

text: I live in the area.  I love to have breakfast out on some Saturday's. It's awesome to have Homestyle breakfast that you don't have to make at home. Lol! They have great dinners also. I love the atmosphere and the staff. It's all around vibe.

name: Towneplace Suites
categories: Hotels & Travel, Event Planning & Services, Hotels
text: I've stayed here a few times since this location opened earlier this year.  Rooms are still stylish and comfortable. Great working ac. Nice spacious showers. They provide breakfast and my only complaint is they always serve fried egg with cracked pepper and turkey sausage. Can't we get scrambled or omelette like the other do? Provide a variety of egg so if guest is there more than one night they actually can have variety of egg during their stay.

name: Leisure World Health Club
categories: Gyms, Health & Medical, Saunas, Trainers, Active Life, Swimming Pools, Fitness & Instruction
text:
Not too much to say, this is your typical health club. Cardio Machines, Free Weights, Pool, etc basically everything you would expect from a regular health club. The employees working the front desk are always friendly.

I would rate this higher however I had some bad experiences in the past, the pool has basically become a place for kids to play. If you are a swimmer, do not go during family nights, Tues & Thursday.

name: Sushi Tatsu
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'Caters': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'beer_and_wine'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'DogsAllowed': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}"}
categories: Sushi Bars, Food, Restaurants
text:
I came here with my boyfriend on our way back to central Illinois from St. Louis. This had the best reviews in the St. Louis area, so I was a little put off by the exterior: right next to a car dealership, one car in the parking lot, adjoined to a jewelry store, and one dim window.

The inside is nothing special either. Dimly lit, minimal decor, obviously converted from some kind of diner.

Service was great until we were ready to pay and then it took about 20 minutes.

Miso soup had good flavor, but was pretty bare bones with very little tofu or seaweed in it. Ginger dressing salad was very tasty, but didn't have much of a ginger flavor.

We ordered the Dragon Roll, Volcano, and another one I can't think of. Presentation was pretty. The rolls are good sized, but most of it is due to a thick layer of rice. The inside of the rolls was bland and didn't appear to have half the ingredients listed on the menu.

As an avid sushi eater originally from Chicago, I'd say this place is nothing special. The ambiance and sushi are average, at best. What little fish I could taste didn't taste very fresh. But the free pineapple dessert was a welcomed surprise. I'd say despite reviews, there's is probably a better place closer to St. Louis.

text: Great christmas lights. We also love the laser light shows, I recommend seeing both. They have the one with classical christmas music and then one with more updated music. The wreaths are amazing as is the tree display. The buffet at the restaurant on the other hand is slow and gross. Service couldn't possibly be any slower. Small food selection. The food was bland, whatever the roast beef was, was old, it had a fishy green tint to it. The chicken had very little meat to it. The mashed potatoes were fine. The upside was a pasta station where you choose what you want in it and that was okay, the veggies were fresh but the chicken for that tasted prepackaged frozen. Like I said go for the lights skip the food.

name: Auffenberg Nissan
categories: Automotive, Car Dealers, Auto Repair
text: Stopped here just looking and had a great experience. Auffenberg Nissan has a ton of cars to look at and the salesman Mark Chapman was awesome. He showed me 3 different cars and spent the extra time in making sure I was getting what I needed. When we found the right one we went inside and the price was already marked down well below what I was expecting to pay which was nice to not have to spend 3 hours going back and forth and getting in and out of finance was also faster than expected. Mark spent all the time necessary making sure that I knew how to work my new Nissan and thought it was nice that he offered for me to come back anytime if there was something that I didn't understand on the car and he would help me out. If your looking for a new car you cant go wrong here. A++

name: LKQ Pick Your Part - Washington Park
categories: Car Dealers, Recycling Center, Local Services, Junkyards, Shopping, Auto Repair, Hardware Stores, Tires, Automotive, Auto Parts & Supplies, Home & Garden
text:
I am a DIY type of person and it comes in handy when funds are tight. My 2010 Kia has had the original battery and people are shocked it still has enough juice to start up. I was told I need to replace the battery before the winter and today I decided to look into doing that. Battery for my Kia start at $145, which is not in my budget. However I remembered there's a pick n pull in Washington Park, IL not too far from me. It's located right off I 64, pass the 2 strip clubs. 

Now my normal DIY has nothing to do with cars. But I'm confident I can do this.... It's only a battery right!?! Right!? 

Going in there is a $2 entrance fee however you don't have to pull the battery from the cars so you don't have to pay the fee. The battery's are not located in the lot but in the main area. There's also a book with cars makes and models so to you get the correct battery. The cashier was helpful in letting me know that. I found the battery in the book But not on the table. There was another cashier who came over to help me. Said they had it in the back, he got it for me and rung me out. Battery was $52.99 and if I brought my original battery back for them to dispose of I would get $11 back. 

So I'm 5'4, cute lil thang with my sunglasses and handy dandy toolbox walking out to my car with this battery. I could only imagine the thoughts of all these men. I was successful with changing out my battery and got my $11 back. All without breaking my nails but I did get a little dirty. 

At the end of the day... If I have a auto DIY... Yes I will come back!

name: Michelle's Massage Therapy
categories: Day Spas, Nail Salons, Massage, Skin Care, Chiropractors, Massage Therapy, Health & Medical, Reflexology, Beauty & Spas, Waxing, Hair Removal
text: My fiancée and I went here just this evening for a 90 minute couples massage. We had Michelle and Amy; I can only speak of Amy but my fiancée said Michelle was amazing. I absolutely recommend Amy for any type of massage you'd want. Her strong dexterous fingers unwound my entire body and made my week. I'll be seeing her again as soon as I can.

name: Best Western Premier Alton-St. Louis Area Hotel
categories: Hotels & Travel, Event Planning & Services, Hotels
text: We had a short stop at this hotel, but it was long enough for us to be very impressed! First, the rooms were very big and clean. The hotel has just been renovated and the niceness shows. The staff member who checked us in was very quick and helpful. There's a nice restaurant/bar attached to this hotel, which is nice for a cocktail or beer or meal after a long day's travel. The breakfast buffet was fantastic - hot and cold options, plus there is an actual wait staff that waits on your table to make sure you've got fresh coffee and drinks at all times. It's a nice touch. We definitely recommend!

name: World's Largest Catsup Bottle
categories: Local Flavor, Landmarks & Historical Buildings, Public Services & Government
text: The new owners are cleaning up the building and exterior. Nice job with the lighted Santa over Christmas too.

name: LensCrafters
categories: Ophthalmologists, Doctors, Health & Medical, Optometrists, Shopping, Eyewear & Opticians
text: I saw Dr Reed for a problem. She was remarkably helpful, taking time to make me aware of other issues I had but hadn't realized there were possible solutions. She took time and explained my eye health. Lorrane was wonderful too. Very professional. I felt well cared for. I consider this my eyecare home. I would not hesitate to recommend them.

name: A to Z Pediatrics
categories: Pediatricians, Doctors, Health & Medical
text: Terrible customer service. The medical staff is okay but we transferred to a new pediatrician after just a couple of experiences with the office staff. Even obtaining your own child's records feels punitive and like they are doing you a favor. For $15.

name: Eaker's Family Barber Shop
categories: Beauty & Spas, Barbers
text: Family owned...old school from the barber chairs to the phone.  Cash only.  Friendly and worth a shave and haircut.  Will definitely visit when I'm in town!

text: We've been eating here since they converted it from a Wendy's.  Recently, they removed all the promotional artwork on the windows and it really helped to class-up the place.  They have also updated the dining room furniture.  Waitstaff is very good.  Drinks are excellent.  We always try the items advertised on the walls instead of ordering off the menu.  Today, we both had the Guaco Tacos.  Three steak tacos served with onion, guacamole, and a little lettuce.  Gee, there were sure good and we will order them again on our next visit.

The only thing that got me is that if you wanted to have a certain flavor butter, a little cup would cost you .79 cents. One last thing is some low music would have been nice and they could put the TV to use instead of displaying a screen saver of  fresh brewed coffee. Other than that the food was pretty good.

categories: Lounges, Restaurants, Nightlife, American (New), Bars
text: This was my first visit to Bossanova and I am in love. The bartender was friendly. She offered the drink menu which was two pages of martini's. They have taken the 007 theme and the martini' are named after characters in the movie, it was fun to read the menu. I knew that I had to drive so I stuck with wine. We ordered from the appetizer menu, they have a dip with olive oil, feta cheese and kalamato olives served with chiabatta bread. It was delightful, a healthier version of the appetizer. The place must be popular amongst the locals because people just kept pouring through the door. The bad part is no outside seating and it does not open until 4 o'clock. This is a must stop when you are in Alton.

name: Coffee Mill Cafe
categories: Food, Coffee & Tea
text: Love having a local coffee shop in Millstadt! Their selection of flavoured syrups is awesome, and they frequently offer special flavoured lattes and frappes. As a cold brew fan I find theirs tastes more like iced coffee because it's a bit strong -- medium roasted beans might yield smoother flavour. Still, it is reasonably priced and I love having that option: I've always found a great selection of donuts, and they are locally made and delicious. I hope they start offering cookies and brownies to go along with the great coffee. Owner and staff are very nice and friendly, and the café is spotless. 5 stars all around

name: Enterprise Rent-A-Car
categories: Car Rental, Hotels & Travel
text: Terrible customer service. No cars available during previously scheduled appointment. Offered me a van or a dirty car as best option after waiting for an hour.

text: The food was great, menu needs refining as you shouldn't have to ask questions about what it is you're getting.  My server should not have assumed that just because I asked about what came with the country fried steak that I wanted it, I was asking what came with it.  I had to ask the hostess when she passed to seat another customer where my waitress was and she showed up five minutes later, she also walked past my table four times and where I was seated she came from behind me and didn't stop once until she returned with my check...  Food...five stars, service...1, averaged it at 3.

attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': None, 'trendy': None, 'upscale': False, 'classy': None, 'casual': True}", 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'HappyHour': 'True', 'DogsAllowed': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'"}
categories: Restaurants, Sushi Bars
text: This place has been hit or miss but with not a lot to choose from on this side of the river, it's good. I've been to the Wasabi in St. Louis and they are always great, this one seems to fall off a bit. The sushi at times isn't wrapped very well and falls apart which Makes it hard with chopsticks but there have been other times when it was perfectly good and tasty. It's hard to judge because it seems to be the luck of the draw here. They also have some good options if sushi isn't your thing but you're with someone who has to have it. The Dragon Rolls are Awesome when made right. Overall the service has been good and the food tastes great for where your at. It's a nice option on this side of the river but if you're willing to drive, go to the one on Washington Ave. in St. Louis.

name: Bean Tree Cafe

categories: Restaurants, Coffee & Tea, Coffee Roasteries, Breakfast & Brunch, Food, Cafes
text:
Wonderful little local cafe that my parents took me to before we went to the Christmas tree farm nearby. Between 5 of us, we all had something different. I got the BLT, which was delicious and perfectly sized. My niece got the regular French toast, which she shared with me and was also very good. 

The owners were super friendly and were talking to all the tables, welcoming everyone to the restaurant.

name: Wacky Warriors Paintball
categories: Social Clubs, Arts & Entertainment, Outdoor Gear, Sporting Goods, Paintball, Shopping, Active Life, Amusement Parks
text:
My son was invited to a birthday party there and the dads came along and participated as well. We all had a blast, the kids and the dads. It was just awesome. To an expand, I would like my party there if anyone would ask. 

The fields were great and diverse, the stuff was very friendly and helpful. We could not ask for a better service and the price was great. 

I look forward to going back there. Hopefully soon.

name: American Cleaners
categories: Dry Cleaning & Laundry, Laundry Services, Local Services
text: Went here recently for my third (and possibly last) time. I've gone out the door chuckling to myself each time at how incredibly poor their customer service is. Just dropped off some shirts to be cleaned. I wasn't expecting a life-long friendship with the woman at the counter,  just a professional and courteous exchange about my shirts. Instead it felt like an interrogation by the Major Case Squad. Short, one-word questions and answers from a person who apparently hasn't smiled in the past thirty years. It was obvious that she was "bothered" by my presence. I saw a Now Hiring sign among the many others that adorn the entrance. A quick note to the owner/manager who seems to follow these comments on Yelp - please raise your standards on those future new employees. They are the first and last impressions made on your customers. They make or break your business. Choose them wisely and train them well.

name: Taco Bell

text:
This Taco Bell is located near downtown Granite City. The food here is typically good, but over the last couple of months they have made mistakes while completing our drive through orders. 

I recommend double checking your order before pulling out of the parking lot.

name: Scott Air Force Commissary
categories: Grocery, Shopping, Food, Discount Store
text: Super packed on weekends! Commissary is a great place for groceries. You can find the same/almost better deals as a regular grocery store. If anything you're saving on some groceries by 10+ cents or so. Some stuff is still expensive without being on sale. There are some groceries there that you can't find anywhere else which is nice too! I would avoid weekends as it can be a disaster. PS: you can use coupons here too like any other grocery store.

name: Xclusive Auto Sound & Security
categories: Auto Glass Services, Automotive, Car Stereo Installation, Home Services, Home Window Tinting
text: Just got my car tinted at Xclusive two days ago, what a great experience!  Very professional, not like some of these other shady tint places around here.  They called the night before to confirm my appointment and to see if I would be dropping off the car or waiting for it.  Dropped the car off and picked it back up after work.  Quality of work was amazing, car looked great and I didn't see any flaws whatsoever.  Highly recommend Xclusive for any tinting needs!

name: Subway
categories: Restaurants, Sandwiches, Fast Food
text:
Great service and great subs, the perfect combination! The service at The Fairview Heights Subway has always been friendly and prompt. I enjoy stopping in this Subway to grab a sub for myself and a few for the family. 

The restaurant is clean there is usually plenty of places to sit.

name: Dierbergs Markets
categories: Fashion, Shopping, Department Stores, Drugstores, Food, Beer, Wine & Spirits, Flowers & Gifts, Grocery
text: Great store! I love it when I find clean and well stocked stores. They have just about everything here, even a ups store built in!

name: Hollywood Hair - Shiloh
categories: Beauty & Spas, Shopping, Makeup Artists, Bridal, Hair Salons
text: Oh man, where do I start?! This place is awesome. I saw Kaitlyn and she rescued my hair. She found the perfect hair color and cut that best suited me. I brought my 7 year old daughter for a cut and she loved it. They made her look and feel like a star. I highly recommend this place.

name: Custom Sounds & Tint
categories: Auto Glass Services, Car Window Tinting, Car Stereo Installation, Automotive, Auto Customization, Electronics, Shopping
text: I would definitely recommend the Alton location, the team was very helpful and professional and done in a timely manner. I had all new after market system installed in my truck. Cody the installer from the Alton location is the man. He went above and beyond to make my system slam. I'm so happy with my install.

name: Kohl's
categories: Women's Clothing, Men's Clothing, Fashion, Department Stores, Sports Wear, Sporting Goods, Toy Stores, Shopping, Shoe Stores
text:
I am a big fan of Kohl's.  They have a rather large selection of quality clothes and housewares.  Their prices are competitive with other retailers and often times you can get some really great deals.  

I've never been dissatisfied with the quality of clothes Kohl's offers.  The associates here are usually pretty helpful too.  You can beat that value.

name: Q-Nails & Tan
categories: Nail Salons, Beauty & Spas, Tanning
text: I walked in here to get a pedicure. They were not busy so I got right in. The service was just OK. Not friendly at all. The woman mumbled under her breath the entire time. My feet are in good shape so there shouldn't have been anything to complain about. On my big toes, she started the polish so far away from my cuticles, it looks like they were done 2 weeks ago. I had tipped her (she looked surprised) and left before I noticed. They had an opportunity to gain a new and loyal customer due to the proximity of the salon to where I live. Unfortunately, the service and atmosphere of this salon is a BIG NO.

text: The food is ok, but poor ownership when they tell you your food will be ready in 10-15 minutes so you go up there only to wait an hour...Ridiculous!!!

name: Kristen Cummings, DMD - All Grins 4 Kids
categories: Oral Surgeons, Pediatric Dentists, Health & Medical, Dentists
text:
I was very impressed with this place from the moment I walked in.  The front desk staff was more than welcoming.  There is a cute little nemo fish setup in the waiting area (what kid's dentist office doesn't have this these days?).  My three year old's first dentist appointment happened here with no hiccups.  She was uncomfortable at first for the teeth cleaning so instead of forcing her, they took a break and did the dental exam.  When it got back to the teeth cleaning she was more comfortable.  They have TV's above head to watch with cartoons on them.  My dentist office doesn't even offer that!

I would definitely recommend this place for infants, toddlers and other kiddos to come get there teeth cleaned here, great for a pediatric dentistry.

Keep your eyes peeled for the "treasure chest" that awaits your child at the end of there visit :)

name: Vive Yoga Studio
categories: Active Life, Fitness & Instruction, Yoga
text:
I first learned about this studio and the instructors just a few weeks ago. I had practiced yoga for 7 years but stopped for some time due to injury. I recently decided to start practicing again, and wanted to find both a great studio and great instructors. 

With Vive Yoga, I found both.

I contacted Vive via email to discuss private sessions to start, just so I could get back into the swing of things before taking a class. I wanted to make sure that I wasn't a disruption and that I could do all the poses. Alexis (co-owner) was very prompt in responding, discussing, and understanding my concerns. With that out of the way, she set up an appointment time for a private session.

When my appointment time came, Alexis was there and ready to go. Behind the desk they have bottled water for sale, a room to store your phone/shoes/keys, and the bathrooms. The studio is in the basement of a professional building and is laid out like a normal studio with plenty of room to practice. It's very clean and is enjoyable to practice in. They offer both yoga blocks and straps should you need them, and they have mats available too. Alexis quickly discussed the points I had mentioned in email and we were off. (It was nice that I didn't have to remind her, just confirm)

After years off from yoga, Alexis kept me working, and was doing a great job reminding me when to breath, gave me enough time to catch up when I was struggling, and offering modifiers. At the end of the session she sat and spoke with me about taking a few more private sessions and was empathetic and encouraging about my return. I signed up for a few more private sessions and she was truly wonderful about helping me return to Yoga.  After a few more private sessions, (I still have one left), we discussed that I was ready for a group class.

I attended the Monday night Vinyasa Flow class with Felice (co-owner). I hadn't done Vinyasa before, I had always practicing Hatha. Felice was a wonderful instructor and was very good about walking around to make sure everyone was doing the poses correctly. It was so nice to have an instructor provide a great work out and yet make the class light and fun, she has a great sense of humor. One thing I want to point out, Felice starts the class by asking if anyone is opposed to an assisted adjustment, and if you are, you simply raise your hand. Alexis doesn't do hands on, but will demo next to you. This is a truly great thing, and I wish more Yoga studios asked first. Keep that up! 

On Tuesday morning Alexis reached out to me to see how my first group class in years went, and to make sure I didn't have any questions/concerns, that's fantastic customer service!

I attended my second group class tonight with Alexis, Hatha this time and it was great. I will be returning for both Vinyasa Flow and Hatha classes (Nice that they switch up the day and evening classes so no matter your schedule, you get a choice). When I am back in shape, will be going to the Power Yoga class. There is also a Beginner class, but I haven't attended that one, and there is a children's class too. Oh, and they have lunch time Yoga once a week!

A couple other things to point out quickly; They have a really good Facebook/Website presence, so if you have questions or want to know what else is going on with the studio, it's a click away. They do also have a small section of tanks/yoga pants that they designed for sale and I have never heard them being pushy sales women like I have seen with some other studios. (They don't have shirts for men, but with our small demographic in Yoga, I'm NOT going to knock them for that, but I was told tonight they are looking into making a small batch for the guys). The prices of their classes are extremely competitive, so even people on a budget won't really have an excuse to skip class. To be fair, I do have to point out they are a new studio, so they may have a few quirts to work out in the system as time goes on, but I haven't seen any yet. 

My last point is my most important point. They are good ethical teachers! 

I have seen my fair share of yoga teachers that know the poses, and can lead a class, but they only really talk the talk. These women walk the walk. From their Facebook page alone you can see they are really interested in getting children involved in Yoga and helping people learn more about nutrition and health in general. They even lead classes' offsite that seem fun (I haven't attended one yet, but I've seen the photos). They are both very kind and encouraging with issues you may have. They are both Yogi's in mind, body, and soul. 

I can't recommend them enough, I did serious research regarding studios and instructors in the area and I am happy to say they not only met my high expectations, but bested them. They opened a few months ago, but they have really done a great job, looking forward to more time in the studio

Nice job Alexis and Felice, keep up the great work!

text: We went to Sybergs when it first opened because we have went to their other location in St Louis and loved their food and was excited that there was now one on the Illinois side of the river and out experience was above average and the food was good but the service was the only reason for not being 5 star. I love eating wings but hate the sauce being on the wings and I asked for the sauce to be but on the side twice and after about 45 minutes of waiting they come out with sauce all over them. Now usually the server would ask if you would like them to make another order without but we didn't get that option. It was just put on the table and that was kind of that. We have not been back to this location but would consider it again down the road.  Like I said food was great just wish the service was better.

name: Xtreme Paintball Park
categories: Active Life, Paintball, Laser Tag, Summer Camps
text: What a great experience. I am afraid you guys got this 37 year old hooked now. Wife won't be happy with my next few amazon purchases. Tim was an outstanding host/ref and I was very impressed with the course options. I will definitely be visiting again.

name: Family Sportsplex
categories: Arts & Entertainment, Active Life, Stadiums & Arenas, Sports Clubs
text: Family friendly complex with lots to do! It's down the street from where some family lives and is very convenient. Clean facility and friendly staff

name: Alpine Shop
categories: Outdoor Gear, Sporting Goods, Shopping, Bikes, Sports Wear, Fashion
text: If you live in the St. Louis area and are into knives do yourself a favor and stop in this shop.  GP Knives is by far the best knife shop I've ever been in.  They stock all the major brands from any price range $20 and up.  The sales staff are very knowledgeable and friendly.  If you don't live near by, check them out online and buy a knife from them.  You won't regret it.

text: Tickets were pretty cheap!!! However, the volume was WAY too loud. It was fine during the movie since I was seeing Insurgent, but they need to adjust the volume next time.

Obviously the manager isn't familiar with the term "quality control." If I could fire her, I would.

name: Car-X Tire & Auto
categories: Automotive, Auto Repair, Tires, Transmission Repair, Oil Change Stations
text: The average price in the area is between 80-90 per labor hour and I was charged 105 an hour to fix a window regulator on a Honda. It was my first time using my warranty I had on the car but the warranty company said the hour rate was $20-30 more than average so that had to come out of my pocket. Unless my car can fly after this fix, I don't see why it's $30 over priced per hour. UPDATE: I ONLY WENT TO THEM BECAUSE THEY ARE CLOSE TO MY HOUSE AND THEY SAID IT WOULD BE DONE BY CLOSE OF BUSINESS YESTERDAY AND THEY STILL HAVENT STARTED FIXING IT. PAYING MORE MONEY, WAITING LONGER. UPDATE: Final bill $430 to replace a window motor and it took 24 hours

name: Star Clipper
categories: Books, Mags, Music & Video, Comic Books, Shopping
text: Pretty good selection of new comics and lots of trades. Impressed with the selection of small press books. I'm glad it wasn't overrun with kids and their magic cards and what not. Staff was nice and checked in with me to make sure I was ok. Didn't feel like I had invaded someone territory which was nice.

name: Rich's Record and Audio Emporium
categories: Electronics, Local Services, Electronics Repair, Shopping, Books, Mags, Music & Video, Vinyl Records
text:
My husband and I made special trip there on our anniversary to get a vintage system refurbished and but a new system.  We were very excited, and try to spurt local businesses rather than order a new system online.  

Imagine our surprise when we were completely ignored for over half an hour, not even acknowledged when we walked in, so that he could chat someone else up,  who was clearly not even interested.  The owner couldn't even ask the other person to excuse him long enoygh to greet us. 

The last straw was when the other gentleman said "oh, I was just walking up the street and thought I'd look around" edging his way to the door and the owner STILL kept talking him up and ignoring us!! Done. I'll find some other small business to shop at.

name: Sleep Number
categories: Home Decor, Furniture Stores, Home & Garden, Mattresses, Shopping
text: Dont buy a sleep number. The numbers on the pump dont show up. I have only had my sleep number 3yrs and hardly ever adjust it, but you cant tell what number you are on. I called them and they want 100.00 to replace it when it has hardly ever been used. They obviously sell junk. That doesnt hold up over time!!

name: Schiappa's
attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True'}
categories: Pizza, Chicken Wings, Restaurants, Italian
text:
We found this place when we flipped on the GPS on our phone.  Looking for something close by and it popped up.  Not something easy to see from the freeway but there is a sign before the exit.

I had a pizza which was good.  My daughter had ravioli and she liked them.  My husband ate the special, a buffalo chicken stromboli.  It came with a salad & he really liked the dressing.  We ordered hot wings which were THE BEST HOT WINGS I have ever had.  They were large (I hate little wings!), definitely hot but not vinegar-y.  They left my lips tingling but no tears.  Perfect amount of spice.

The thing that makes this place stand out is their 40" pizza.  It is the size of a table.  They have to cut a slit in their doors leading to the back room to bring the thing out!  They have a pizza challenge which has only been accomplished twice.  Their 36" pizza to be eaten by 3 people in 1/2 hour.  I can eat some pizza but after those awesome wings, I had a hard time killing 1/2 of a 14" pizza.

It was really good.  I will have to try a pasta dish next time I come thru St. Louis.

name: Treo Salon
categories: Hair Salons, Beauty & Spas
text: Hannah did an awesome job and helped my first experience at treo be a great one. I have curly hair and normally keep it short and went in for an even shorter cut. I love it, she did a good job styling it and gave me a relaxing wash. I will definitely be returning in the future.

name: Sunset Ford of Waterloo
categories: Auto Parts & Supplies, Car Dealers, Automotive, Auto Repair
text:
After 2+ years of looking for just the right truck, we found it at Sunset Ford of Waterloo. Kudos to Mark Springer, Manager for hiring Julian Henson, a top notch Closer, that's right, Closer! 

Unlike other salesmen at the countless dealerships whom we met over the past two years, Julian hopped in the back seat like one of the family.  During our test drive, Julian and Kent talked about the various trucks they both have had throughout their driving years, while at the same time, never missing a beat answering all of my important questions, such as "what's this knob do", "where's the USB port", "where do I control the temperature on my side", and many more. It was as though we were at a family reunion, and these two cousins who hadn't seen each other for years, were catching up on old times! I'm so grateful for Julian. 

Julian is a down to earth young man who honestly cared that what we were looking at, is what we really wanted. Julian went the extra mile to ensure we drove away without any regrets. 

Julian, being new to Waterloo, helped pass the time while we waited for Bill, by asking about the different golf courses, fishing holes, and local events. Together, we googled Ann Briar, Mystic Oaks, Acorns, Trapper Falls, as well as the local nightlife uptown. Yes Waterloo has come a long way since I moved here in 1969, and Julian Henson is a wonderful, welcome addition to our town. 

Bill Rolfus reviewed with Kent all options available (which ones would be good for us and which ones not so good); and within minutes...Kent was the proud owner of a 2013 Ford truck...FINALLY!!!

If you are looking for someone to help you find the truck or car of your dreams, go see Julian Henson at Sunset Ford of Waterloo, and tell him Pam and Kent said "Hi"!

name: Orange Leaf Frozen Yogurt
categories: Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Desserts, Do-It-Yourself Food, Food
text:
step in the door and you will be amazed to find out that you just made the best descision of your life!!! this place is awesome has roughly around 14 flavors and always getting new ones, the wedding cake is my fav, i have to agree with other reviews that they don't have the best location/size/seating for the amount of buisiness they draw... i have went there on weekend nights and had to stand before because it was so crowded!

if your looking for a healthy desert option where you can choose how much you want which is a great benifit and only pay 44 cents an ounce then visit orange leaf, you won't be dissapointed

name: Wilke Window & Door
categories: Home Services, Building Supplies, Windows Installation, Door Sales/Installation
text: They were not willing to do a quote for a custom door! The only way they would even consider helping would be if I paid to have it installed as well as paid to have a steel frame removed from the concrete foundation and a new one installed. Way to upsell customers.

categories: Bars, Sports Bars, Nightlife, Restaurants, Burgers, Steakhouses, American (Traditional), Chicken Wings, Fast Food
text:
Went there on a Saturday mid May about 4pm.  Should have known when we saw it was not busy at all by the looks of the parking lot.  Getting inside, we were seated right away, but noticed two tables near us were not cleared or cleaned.  It stayed that way for over half an hour.  We went there because Applebees was running a special this month on Dos Equis beer.  The add said they offered both the lager and amber.  The waitress took our drink order and had no idea of the amber one, saying they only had one tap beer of Dos Equis and it was the lager.  I said ok and she went to get it, returning with out saying they were out.  How do you run out on a Saturday afternoon when your promoting that beer.  We should have just left, but we didn't.
We completed the order and don't get me wrong, the server was nice but never saw a hint of a manager and other than the server, no one acknowledged us as there.  The food came out, and it was one of their specials with steak and shrimp.  I'm not a food snob but the shrimp was tasteless.  I ordered the steak medium and should have ordered rare, as it came out well.  I just didn't want to waste anymore time there so I just kept the steak.  The server did ask if the food was alright.  It told her it was ok and not medium, but was not going to have her refire another.
Just very disappointed in this Applebees and was the worst one yet.  Usually we get pretty good food, but it's been a long while since we have gone to this one....now I know why.

text: What a great find! My wife and I just had lunch there and loved everything about it. The restaurant is very clean, the service was great, and the food was amazing. The waitresses were very friendly and attentive. As soon as we sat down they took our drink and appetizer order. We had the fried yucca and loved it. My wife ordered the Cuban sandwich and had the steak sandwich. Both were very authentic and great tasting. The owner is very friendly and seems very proud of his restaurant. If you are looking for a great lunch place, this is it. We will definitely be back.

name: Auffenberg Ford Belleville
categories: Auto Repair, Car Dealers, Automotive
text: We made an appt to come and look at 06 F150 for a Saturday at 1:30. At 1 someone called to verify we were still coming to look at said truck. I said we were on our way. She said she would see us shortly. We get to the lot and a man walks up to us and asks if he could help us. I said "yes we have an appt at 1:30 to look st an 06 For F150". He says "Oh yea, that's been sold". I asked why the person that called at 1 didn't tell me that so we didn't waste our time coming down there. We live an hour away and wasted time and gas going there. He said the paperwork was still in process the money just hadn't come through yet but the guy wasn't going to back out. He then says "we don't have any other trucks in that price range either. Check back often though". Never offered any explanation or even to help us find another vehicle. I know they have multiple lots in other towns. Figured he could've checked that inventory or something. He just walked off to go smoke with another salesman. I called to complain because the truck still showed available on their website 2 days later. The first lady I talked to heard all of this and said she was making a note of what happened and was going to put me on hold then She transferred me to someone else who I had to explain everything to AGAIN. She said the sales staff wouldn't be in until 9am and she would have someone call me back asap. No one called. At all. The truck wasstill showing for sale again the next day. I'm not sure what's going on at the Belleville location but I wasn't treated like a customer should be treated and am very unhappy with how everything went down. The salesman was rude and when I wanted to talk to someone about it, no one wants to take the time to call me back. I contacted them 2 days in a row and was told both times someone would get back to me and no one ever did. Guess my buying and driving needs will have to met somewhere else.

name: Lashley Animal Hospital
categories: Pets, Veterinarians, Pet Services
text: If you need a Vet, this is the best!   Dr. Lashley is a very caring,  compassionate person!  Also very truthful about what he can do and what percentage of the time it would help.   He does not do procedures just to make a buck but to help the pets!  Been going to him for over 30 years and would not go anywhere else!  He is the best!

name: Lake House
categories: American (Traditional), Restaurants
text: Loved their beer selection! Hospitality was amazing!Server Laurie and hostess Jerry were so fun! Loved Brussel sprouts, serving portions were very good!  Prices on the fish Friday nite specials were very good! The band and dance floor were a surprise good time. I can't wait to come back to the area and go here again!

name: Edwardsville Auto
categories: Auto Repair, Automotive
text:
I was so happy with this shop after my first visit. They identified and fixed the mystery noise I was hearing, but can't any shop do this? I had to come back a second time because the caliper they replaced at that first visit was a bad one and drained all my brake fluid. Shame on me for giving them a third chance after that for a similar problem, which actually was not resolved when the car was returned to me.
I recently had to have my car looked at again and something was nagging at me about this shop, so I went elsewhere. Only to find out there were a few things (brakes, spark plugs) that had been "fixed" but now needed repair again (still? Because of their work? hard to say.) I will not be going back. Beware.

name: Rural King
categories: Hardware Stores, Food, Grocery, Shopping, Nurseries & Gardening, Home & Garden, Sporting Goods, Farming Equipment
text: This was my first time in this location....Love to support small businesses but I would much rather go to Home Depot, Lowes, or Menards. The staff here was not welcoming at all! The customers in the store were a lot more friendly vs staff. Coming here looking for some potting soil and grass seeds....I felt out of place lol. The place smells really old and it's junkie inside. Very plain. This location use to be an old value city and before that grandpa's....interior still looks the same from many moons ago!

name: Hudson Jewelers
categories: Jewelry, Shopping
text: I've bought lots of jewelry from Hudson's. They have a large selection of both men's and women's jewelry have great customer service and are always willing to order what you are looking for it they don't have it in stock. My wife had her wedding ring reset last year and couldn't be happier. I would have given 5 stars but on my most recent trip (which I was wearing some old shorts and t-shirts) one of the ladies was more interested in talking with some family members than helping me. She asked someone else to help me and that person was excellent.

If this place was closer I would be here all the time.  I stumbled upon it by accident and it was a GREAT find.  

It was a late mid afternoon and I was the only customer.  I had a difficult time choosing the coffee flavor and menu item.  SO many good choices!  I got the Barista.  I didn't have room for desert so I will have to go back!
