name: Buhl's Auto Repair
categories: Oil Change Stations, Auto Repair, Automotive, Body Shops
text:
My grandson broke down in Lebanon this past Saturday afternoon on his way visit my wife and I in Springfield. 

On way to Lebanon to see what I could do, I found Buhl's on Yelp. I called and they told us to bring the car right over. 

In less than 5 minutes they diagnosed a bad idler and immediately order the part from a local supplier. The supplier delivered the wrong part in about 20 minutes. He immediately went back and came back with the right part. 15 minutes later (after their normal closing time) the car was fixed and we were given a fair price. This could have a long and costly day, it wasn't bad. We enjoyed a great conversation with the office lady and time passed quickly. They gave us a student discount for my grandson. Thanks to the great people at Buhls.

name: Cassens and Sons
categories: Car Rental, Car Dealers, Hotels & Travel, Automotive, Auto Repair
text: It is interesting to see that you have removed the ability of customerd to comment on facebook when they do not recommend your facility.  Can you explain to me what being the third owner of a vechicle has to do with the fact that the vechicle has a warranty?  I would be careful saying you couldn't find anything wrong because someone else might have been able to get the job done where you were unable.  So now the concern is if Cassens and Sons, through your incompetence, are unable to diagnose a vechicle then you run the customer off when they start asking for things to be documented.  You make it sound like you gave me a choice to come back or not.  You most defiantly did NOT give me an option to return.  When I asked that my repair order be documented, Mike Hasamer threw my keys down on the table and explained to me that he was "not going to sit there and write a book with me".  He also explained that he was not being paid to put in my comments.  Sounds to me like when a customer requests documentation it makes Cassens uncomfortable.  I think what people would be interested to know is why me not purchasing a vechicle from you and me being the third owner has anything to do with me bringing a vechicle to you under warranty.  You were unable to accurately diagnose a problem!  There was a defect and I will elaborate on that at a later time.  It's important not to paint a picture that there was no problem when in fact there was.  Had you removed the shaft and checked the u joints you would have found that they were locked up.  Now, not only do you disregard a customers request to dig a little deeper into an issue, we see your staffs inability as well as the  Chrysler tech advisor Shanes inability to correctly identify a u joint locked up.  I'm an engineer not a mechanic but u joints are extremely easy to tell if they are locked up.  Face it, you didn't want to take the time to correctly identify the problem and it was easier to tell me to leave!  I would not recommend Cassens and Sons services or Mike Hasamears ability to care for you and your concerns about your car.  Buyer Beware!!!!!!

name: Dobbs Tire & Auto Centers
categories: Auto Repair, Oil Change Stations, Tires, Automotive
text:
Use your valet key, and lock up everything. 

Because of perceived trickery, it's been a year or two since my last visit, but I needed a leaking tire fixed and they're close to me. Ugh. 

I drive a company leased car, and most shops see this as a blank check to do whatever they want without my approval, so I'm always on guard. Today the price and service was good, but what irked me enough to write about was when I signed the papers to leave. Papers signed and they hand me a fleet driver info booklet I keep in my glove box. I was obviously perplexed, so Greg quickly interjected he needed some additional info from it. 
I was sitting in the waiting room, and they never asked me any questions or where to find this book they "needed". BTW, all the pertinent fleet info was on the card I gave Greg when I checked in. The booklet has nothing more they need, it's info for the driver. 

I'm pissed that they snooped my car while I waited patiently. 

I'm convinced they were looking at my fleet maintenance records to see what else they could convince the fleet co to pay for. 

Arrogant snoopy crooks!

categories: Fast Food, Restaurants, Food
text: We got a carry out order of pulled pork from Cafe Agape, and we were pretty impressed. Lots of food and good, quality, FRESH flavor and ingredients. The only thing is, clean it up, folks. The outside is littered with equipment. I understand needing and using it, but move it to the side or at least make the drive up seem presentable. My fiance went in to get the meat and said the inside looked like someone's yard sale exploded. Luckily, I don't judge a place based on the looks/atmosphere, but there IS something to be said for organization and cleanliness when you're serving food. I've heard pretty good things about the rest of the daily specials, but I'm not sure I'll get my fiance back--even as good at the pulled pork was.

text: My boyfriend and I live right down the street from here, and we always try to come in every week or so. We both love beer and I love that the selection changes fairly often so I can always try something new. The atmosphere is really fun and laid back and sometimes they'll have bands play. It's never so loud that you can't talk but it does get busy sometimes (however, you'll always get served quickly). I don't mind paying a little extra for beer, especially when it's one I won't have anywhere else. The staff is very knowledgeable of the selection. Sure, they don't make food here, but you're always welcome to bring some in from elsewhere. I've never had any complaints, and we keep coming back as much as we can afford! :)

name: Meineke Car Care Center
categories: Tires, Automotive, Oil Change Stations, Auto Repair
text: Wow.  I took my daughter's car in for an oil change while she was out of town.  I had an advertisement flyer and figured if they were good I would bring the other vehicle in.  The ad said it was a five quart oil change, check the fluids, tires and air filters.  I was not interested in any upsales and told him no thank you.  One of the things he tried to upsale to me was air filters.  The air filters were changed the day before.  I just needed the twenty dollar oil change.   He took my car in and in no time at all I had the car back. I  Paid the man and I went home.  The man behind the counter said it was his shop so I assumed he would be more friendly.  He wasn't.  It has been a few days now and the car keeps dinging.  My daughter lifted the hood and checked her fluids.  She was almost out of brake fluid.  Guess they did not check the fluids.  I contacted meineke's headquarters and filed a complaint, their shops are franchised companies owned by an individual.

name: Baymont by Wyndham O'Fallon St. Louis Area
categories: Hotels, Event Planning & Services, Hotels & Travel
text:
I rarely every complain, but this property was HORRIBLE.  So much so, I made a list of everything that was wrong during our stay:

1)  The sign out front didn't even say Baymont, but WOWHOTEL
2)  The room smelled terrible.  When telling the front desk we were told that "all the rooms have a smell to them now"
3)  The elevator was broken
4)  No drain stoppers in either the bath tub or the sink, when asking the front desk for them, was told, "we don't have any"
5)  Large amount of dust/drywall dust covering the lower portion of the door in the bathroom
6)  Room was not cleaned while we were here even though we left the room Saturday morning at 9:15 AM and didn't return until 6pm
7)  Waffle mix was not properly prepared and would not make a waffle
8)  Doors to the rooms do not slow down before closing, so they slam shut usless someone closes them manually
9)  No hangers in the closet, front desk unable to provide any
10)  When using the room phone to dial the front desk, it continues to ring even after connecting with the front desk
11)  Wi-Fi stopped working after the first night and front desk said that there was nothing they could do and the reason they gave was because "a lot of people must be using it"
12)  Two dead cockroaches in bathroom
13)  Unable to turn the heater in the room on because it set the fire alarm off snd produced a burning smell.  When alerting the front desk, was told, "We will add it to the list."

This was, from start to finish, one of the worst hotel properties I have stayed at.  Nothing worked, the rooms smelled, and it should not have been operational if the construction being done was this much of a detriment to the operation of the hotel.

name: China Star Restaurant
categories: Restaurants, Chinese
text: I ordered a sweet and sour chicken dinner special and it was by far the WORST I've ever had! It was so gross that I took two bites, and threw it away. The restaurant was absolutely disgusting and it looked like they had never cleaned. Will never go back.

name: Rally's
categories: Restaurants, Fast Food, Burgers
text:
I loved this place when I was a little kid.  I thought the two drive-thrus was totally novel and fun.  I used to get excited about which one my mom would drive through.  It was so much fun to drive all the way to Rally's to get curly fries and a big juicy, loaded burger. 

Now that I am older and wiser, I have come to realize, Rally's is a little bit gross, just like all fast food really, two drive-thru windows isn't really novel, and the burgers aren't that good, juicy or loaded, they are just really REALLY big.  

Rally's has some of the most annoying jingle music of any commercial on local television as well.  I often get that "You gotta eat" song stuck in my head.  It's very annoying.  Rally's has a fairly limited menu (standard burger, fries, and chicken sandwich of most fast food restaurants) and really, it's not as cheap as the advertisements seem to lead you to believe.

I know it's fast food and I shouldn't be too judgmental, but with the advant of places like Qdoba and Noodles and Co, I suppose my expectations of fast food restaurants has gone up over the years.  For fast food, Rally's isn't horrible, it's just ordinary.  Although, their curly fries are still killer.

name: Park Place Dental Group
categories: Orthodontists, Dentists, General Dentistry, Health & Medical, Cosmetic Dentists, Periodontists, Pediatric Dentists, Oral Surgeons
text: Dr. Shelton and his staff at Park Place Dental Group are top notch.   The office is inviting and calm and the staff are extremely friendly. They have a gaming area to keep the kids content before their appointments. Our dental hygienists were gentle and thorough. Thank you Park Place Dental. I will recommend you without a doubt.

text: Second time trying to eat here and while I thought it couldn't be worse than the first I was wrong. Their version of cleaning the tables is simply taking the plates away. They do not wipe them off. There is no sign that says seat yourself or wait to be seated so you kind of stand there like an idiot for a few minutes before just seating yourself. We waited 25 minutes with no food order taken or drink order or even a waitress acknowledging our existence. The worse part is that there were 5 other tables in there before us that didn't even have a drink on their table either. I'm sure their food is great but good luck even getting to try it.

name: House of Chiu
attributes: {'WiFi': "'no'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'Caters': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'True'}
categories: Chinese, Restaurants
text:
This has been my absolute favorite place to eat since I can remember. I've had countless birthday dinners and lunch dates here. It's a small family business. I watched the owners' children grow up. When I walk in, the owners ask me how life in California is. Every time I come home to Belleville, I make sure to visit (and chow down) at lease once. When my parents visit me in LA, they ask the owners to make a special batch of their extraordinary Lo Mein Noodles to bring out to me. 

Things to know: 
-Lunch Buffet (I think it's about $6 now?) It's small, but it features all of their best recipes, and there's always plenty to fill you up. If you come in for the buffet and the food looks like it's been sitting there for too long, they will make a fresh batch just for you. It's not like a normal Chinese Buffet where there are 8 buffet tables, with everything you can think of including sushi and pizza. They put a lot of thought and care into their small buffet, and I've never found another one like it. Somehow, even their simple vanilla ice cream is incredible. Sort of salty-sweet. 
-There is NO DINNER BUFFET, but you can eat in or take out large portions of any of their many scrumptious dishes.

text: We love Gruchala's. Their breakfast,  fish Fridays and chicken Sundays are the best! You're in for a real treat when they have german potato salad - homade and oh so good!! On top of that, cold, cheap beer, laid back/homey atmosphere,  extremely friendly staff and great service.

name: Tammy Nail
categories: Nail Salons, Beauty & Spas
text: Where do I start... no one even spoke to my gf and I when we walked in. We got seated for an 11am appointment at 11:25 and that was after asking. The guy who did my friend's pedi didn't say one single word to her, literally not one. Her pedi was 15 minutes long, no exaggeration. The girl who did my pedi cut my cuticles repeatedly even after I said ow several times. They are not clean, nothing was sanitized, even the bowl I had my feet in with water felt slimy and dirty... bottom line, terrible service all around and definitely do NOT recommend! Don't go here!

name: Hampton Inn & Suites St. Louis/Alton
categories: Hotels & Travel, Hotels, Event Planning & Services
text:
As a Diamond member I tried to use points for my stay at this property.  When I went to book on-line the only rooms available were handicapped or accessible rooms.  Not needing this type of service I explained I didn't want to stay in this room in case someone would need it for their accessible needs.  Can I use my points to book a regular room as I have done for the last 10 years?  That was not option and I could only use my points for the accessible room.  

How inconsiderate and disappointing that this Hilton property would stoop to this level!!

name: Illinois American Water Company
categories: Local Services, Water Delivery
text:
1. Jan. 4 A tech came out to change the meter.  Could only detach 1 side.  He told me he had set up an appointment tor the next day for someone else to come out to do it.
2. Jan. 5 No one came, no one called
3. 1 week later I called the service number.  No one knew anything.  Said they'd check into it.  Never heard back from them.
4.  Called again on March 2.  No one could read the original tech's writing.  Said they didn't know what the problem was, but would set up an appointment
5. March 3. I got a call from Illinois American who said the problem with the meter was our fault and we would have to arrange for a plumber to fix it.  I called the Alton service number again and they still didn't know what the problem was.
6. March 4  Received a letter dated March 1 that the meter needed to be changed and to call for an appointment.  Waited a week to call so that I could calm down from their gross incompetency.
7.  Called  and made an appointment.  Tech came out about March 23.  Spent a few  minutes with the meter.  Went out to his truck to get a larger wrench and came back in and changed the water meter. Said " Right tool for the right job.  Some of these young, inexperienced guys are afraid they'll break something."  Took less than 10 minutes and was apologetic for the water company.
8,  April 8  Got another letter from  Illinois American saying the meter needed to be changed or water would be turned off in 10 days.  Too stupid to know they've already changed it.  My husband will call on Monday.  If they turn off our water we will sue them and I will report them to the Illinois Department on Aging.  Already have it bookmarked for inappropriately turning off the water on my elderly mother.

text:
I've been comparing Indian restaurants in the area and the Taj on the other side of town is better. I had been avoiding this place mostly because the building was weird. I finally gave it a try recently. It was not good! The chicken tikka masala sauce tasted like chef boyardee with chicken. Yuck. The texture and flavor was way off. The samosas were ok...a bit mushier inside than they should be. The aloo gobi had too much sauce and the flavor was also off. 

I wanted to like this place because it's closer to my house. It's also cheap! I will say the kheer was ok but usually kheer has pistachios.

Anyway, I consider myself to be a half way decent critic when it comes to Indian food. I just moved here from San Francisco. SF has tons of great Indian restaurants.

Pretty good food.  Salsa is on the spicy side.  I ordered the chicken chimi and it was good, but there wasn't enough cheese sauce and there was no guac on the plate.  Big bummer.
This restaurant gets four stars because of the atmosphere.  There were workers sitting at the bar on laptops and it felt more like a living room than a restaurant.  Waitress was nice enough, but gruff.  Probably won't return because there are so many GREAT Mexican restaurants in the area.

name: Newbold BMW
categories: Auto Repair, Auto Parts & Supplies, Automotive, Car Dealers
text: When we thought it was time for a new car, we shopped around a bit but in the end decided to stay with BMW.  And Newbold BMW is where we've traded before.  We hooked up with Rich, the salesman who had sold us our last car, in mid-December & Rich helped us decide on the model, found the car we ended up buying before it even hit the USA shores and managed to get it to us before Christmas!  And Carlos helped us learn all the great new technology before we left the dealership and followed up the next week to see if we had any questions (which we did and he had us come back to resolve those question).  Great experience overall & we are enjoying our new car!

name: Sears
categories: Department Stores, Shopping, Fashion
text:
Angelique, manager in Jewelry / Makeup was phenomenal.  She went the extra mile & made me feel special when I checked out.  She answered all of my questions and made me want to come back & shop!  She also was dressed very stylishly and her makeup was beautiful. Definitely a "Sears Model" if I ever saw one!!!  
I also had the sweetest lady (in her 50's?) who was organizing the clearance racks and she helped me find a few PERFECT dresses in my size.  It was my first time at this Sears, and I was really surprised at their focus on personal attention!  Thank you & I will be back!!!

name: Five Star Learning Center
categories: Child Care & Day Care, Local Services
text:
Before our baby was born we checked out several day cares to ensure the best fit for our family.  As soon as I walked into Five Star Learning Center I knew this was the place.  The staff here are great.  During our first visit we noticed all of the staff had smiles on their faces. All of the kids seemed happy too.  This visit was a surprise visit so I know it wasn't staged.  To top it all off, they were the cheapest day care we had visited.

FSLC offers more services than most other day cares.  They offer 24 hour care for those parents that work shifts.  They also offer a "Parent's Night Out" one Saturday each month.  This consist of child care from 6 pm to midnight to allow parents to go out and have fun by themselves.  This is really nice for those parents that may not have a close family support system and just need a night to themselves. 

Our son has been going to Five Star Learning Center for over a month now and I still feel the same way.  I know our son is getting the proper care and attention he needs.  He comes home happy every day and is hitting his milestones.  I feel he is treated just as if he were one of their own.  I am truly amazed by this place after hearing horror stories of day cares.

name: Christone Enterprises
categories: Real Estate, Home Services, Property Management
text:
Heads up! I would not advise anyone to sign a Property Management Contract with Christone Enterprise LLC. They will not take onus if your property is destroyed. Even though they approved the applicant(s). They do not check on your property but will collect their management fee each month. Applicants rental history, I believe, was not check prior to moving into my home. Applicants had a prior eviction, bankruptcy, serious delinquencies, and child support collections. Ask yourself if you would have allowed these applicants to rent your home.

I would not recommend this company to manage someone property!!!!!!

name: Breadeaux Pizza
categories: Pizza, Restaurants, Italian
text:
We did a bike ride in Millstadt today and Breadux pizza was a sponsor. I am not sure what that meant because we did not receive any kind of discount. They had a lunch buffet with a salad buffet. They only offer Pepsi products. They have beer on tap but no wine. The salad bar had four different types of salad dressing. It was clean and had many options to chose from: black olives, eggs, sunflower seeds, two kinds of cheeses, and peppers. They had deep dish and thin crust options on the lunch buffet. The server kept coming around and cleaning the tables off, for some reason this made me think that they did not have enough plates for everyone. 

Pizza was good, service was great.

name: Tee Time Lawn Care
categories: Pest Control, Irrigation, Home Services, Local Services, Landscaping, Tree Services, Lawn Services
text: We had Tee Time for about 9 years. I was never satisfied with their service but my spouse didn't want to change until it finally became intolerable. First, they call all the time to sell new services. Second, their employees claim to have extensive lawn care experience and knowledge, but in many conversations with them over the years they continually show this is not the case. Example (two of many), they tried to sell me grub control for $600 after I had completed grub control myself and knew there had been no grubs for at least a year. They tried to tell me grubs were the reason my lawn was turning brown! It was late summer, over 100 degrees for several days and I don't water. My lawn was going dormant, not being eaten by grubs! Next example, they tried to sell me lime service for several hundred dollars to adjust the pH of my lawn. I asked if they had done a soil test and the person at my front door didn't know what that was or why he would want to apply lime or why a soil test is important.  The office then called me in response to this conversation and told me a soil test isn't required in this state but their tech "could tell" my lawn needed lime. He didn't know what pH is or what the relationship to lime is, so how could he know if my lawn needed lime? It's important to note I had already done a soil test through my local extension and my pH was fine. Third, they spray indiscriminately on windy days. On several occasions I witnessed TeeTime spraying in 30 mph winds to include spraying of herbicide on my trees. One year I lost 5 healthy trees during perfect growing weather within days after witnessing one of these indiscriminate spray incidents.  All the weeds inside the drip line of these trees were dead within a day or two of this incident and the trees quickly followed. TeeTime essentially blew me off and said there was no way their people would spray on my trees and they wouldn't spray in 30 mph winds. I wish I had taken a photo. Fourth, they are not supposed to apply fertilizer, weed killer, etc within a certain distance of gardens growing edible plants. We discussed this before we contracted with them. Yet I repeatedly caught them applying these chemicals right up to the edge of my 30x30 foot vegetable garden with fruits and vegetables clearly visible! And I could go on and on. Over a period of 9 years I have found Tee Time to be overly focused on sales, not knowledgeable about lawn care, and downright negligent in their application practices, which is a byproduct of poor training. I do not recommend this company!

name: Uncle John’s RRR Bar
categories: Arcades, Pool Halls, Bars, Arts & Entertainment, Nightlife
text: First: BRING CASH!  Had the original flat burger. I'd say it was the best smash style burger I've had. Bun is toasted, burger is fresh and juicy. They don't ask you how "done" you want your burger. Don't fret, they make it perfect. The crispy edge of the burger extends out from around the bun, there is no 'where's the beef' moment. Fries are crisp and not a floppy/soggy one in the bunch. I'll agree with a previous review, you'll be dreaming about and thinking about when you're going to get it again.

name: Horseshoe Lake Animal Hospital
categories: Pets, Pet Services, Veterinarians, Pet Groomers, Pet Sitting
text:
The staff and vets here provide great care for my dogs and cat.  They offer wellness packages and a yearly service that includes free regularly-scheduled vet visits and discounted emergency-scheduled vet visits.

I initially became a client here because one of the vets that used to work with horses but doesn't anymore was willing to come to my barn when my horse went down.  I credit Dr. Ervin for saving my horse's life.  Soon after, we moved all of our other animals (dogs and cat) over to Horseshoe Lake Animal Hospital.  Now all of my animals get the best care.

name: Dream Dentist
categories: Cosmetic Dentists, General Dentistry, Orthodontists, Health & Medical, Dentists
text: I have nothing but rave reviews for Dr. Sarah and her staff . I've had crowns ( 4 or 5 ) a bridge. A cracked wisdom tooth pulled. No pain !!!! My teeth look fantastic. My visits are absolutely fantastic. Been going to her for close to 6 years, I believe.  5 stars across the board

name: Reed Hair Design
categories: Makeup Artists, Beauty & Spas, Hair Salons, Massage
text: Love this salon! Amy and Danielle were able to squeeze me in last minute for a blowout on a busy Saturday morning. They were so accommodating and a pleasure to spend time with. Danielle's blowout was perfect. I left there feeling like a million bucks. I left with not only a beautifully coiffed head of hair, but a bottle of sweet smelling product that I can't wait to use! I highly recommend this salon.

categories: Eyewear & Opticians, Optometrists, Shopping, Health & Medical

name: Bowman Dental Group
categories: Pediatric Dentists, Cosmetic Dentists, Dentists, General Dentistry, Health & Medical
text: I am still in extreme pain from a routine cleaning, which I have NEVER experienced before other than the usual tenderness. It has been over 24 hours and I still can not eat even soft foods like breads without being in pain. I'm on an applesauce and cottage cheese diet for the next few days after just a routine annual cleaning! They found no cavities which was great but the whole experience was an absolute nightmare!!! I was staring at the ceiling and telling myself that I was on a tropical island sipping on a frosty drink as she used the ultrasonic tool to clean my teeth. She had to use the sucking tool and water to wash out the blood in my mouth 3 times while she simply flossed my mouth! My gums never bleed when I floss at home! I really don't recommend this office especially for children, they will fear the dentist for the rest of their lives after this kind of experience! I am calling them shortly to report this pain level and the problems I now have that I didn't have before. They answered most of my questions but I could have used an explanation for their answers. The actual dentist, Dr. Bowman, was incredibly kind but the hygenist got an attitude when I told her that I was in a lot of pain from the cleaning. I felt WAY worse when I left. I would never visit them again and was very disappointed. Inflicting this amount of pain and destruction on a patient's mouth is completely unprofessional and uncalled for in a dental practice!

name: Walgreens
categories: Food, Drugstores, Convenience Stores, Beauty & Spas, Cosmetics & Beauty Supply, Shopping
text: If I could give them no stars I would. Upon not being greeted, Kimberly at the photo desk was rude and slow, can't even flip through photos with her ridiculous long fingernails, and after some debate FINALLY agreed to getting the most up to date android cord so that I could actually patronize them. Then proceeded to go in the back with the manager, Amanda, where they were both speaking badly about me! The room they were in was not at all sound proof and was EASILY heard from where I was still at at the photo booth trying to buy 5 freaking pics of my late grandfather. This is not the first poor experience, they also held my dad prescription bc they didn't have it and wouldn't let me take it back to get his ANTISEIZURE meds somewhere else. Another time I had to search for an employee who I found grab assing w a coworker to help and he replied "guess I'll start on it now,"(referring to printing my pics) I WAS THE ONLY PERSON IN THE STORE. They have no sense of urgency, helpfulness or just plain decent customer service. Really really terrible experience every time I go in there. Trust me, go down to CVS instead, THEY may actually smile at you.

name: Walgreens
categories: Shopping, Convenience Stores, Photography Stores & Services, Food, Cosmetics & Beauty Supply, Beauty & Spas, Drugstores
text: The employees at this Walgreens are friendly and efficient. If the line at the register lengthens, they usually open a second register up front, or call you to the cosmetics or camera counter.  The items I'm searching for are almost always in stock. I like being able to manage prescriptions for my entire family on the Walgreens website, including processing refills, and e-mail notifications. I've had prints made from underwater film cameras, and the job was completed quickly and done well. It's also one of the best places in E'ville to find a wide assortment of quality greeting cards.

name: Frame Saver Eyeglass Repair
categories: Eyewear & Opticians, Professional Services, Shopping, Appliances & Repair, Local Services
text:
Great place for eye glass repair!!!
Had a pair of very expensive $800 Silhouette glasses that are made of titanium that keep snapping in half. 
First the ear piece then the nose piece.  
Neither Silhouette or Clarkson Eye Care would stand behind their product. 
I brought them to Jackie, she repaired them at a fraction of the cost Silhouette and Clarkson wanted to charge me for new parts on their crappy made product.
I highly recommend this place!!!

name: Target
categories: Department Stores, Personal Shopping, Shopping, Electronics, Discount Store, Fashion, Home & Garden, Furniture Stores, Food, Grocery
text: I stopped in at Target today. It wasn't overly crowded. I was able to get in and out quickly. I took the recommendation of a Target employee and bought the wine that she had suggested and it is awesome. So glad that target employees are so helpful!

name: Young's Chop Suey
categories: Restaurants, Chinese
text: I'm sure you can imagine how few lunch choices there are in this town. Our favorite Chinese restaurant on our same block closed a couple of years ago and we've never found a suitable replacement until now. We ordered about 4-5 different things from Young's and we were all really satisfied with lunch. You clearly don't know my coworkers but it's nearly impossible to satisfy everyone at one place. I ordered 3 mini egg rolls and plain fried rice with extra onion. Everything was cooked perfectly, packed well, and still hot when it got to us. That's kind of a miracle in this neighborhood. Two complaints: 1. You need to have hot mustard in the little packets. 2. If you had a printed menu maybe we'd order more? DUH!

name: Coldwell Banker Brown, Realtors
categories: Real Estate Services, Real Estate Agents, Real Estate, Home Services
text: Absolutely one of the worst places you can rent from. Maintenance requests are handled by priority only and just recently they disconnected the maintenance phone line, as "too many people were calling it."  Their leases are written grossly in favor of the landlord, so please read the fine print as there are a few clauses in there that will end up costing you if you don't question them.   They absolutely will try to bully you and charge you for things you aren't responsible for.  So very pleased with my new property management firm and ecstatic I was able to end my relationship with Brown Realtors.

text:
For a hot dog this place was really good, i didn't think too expensive at all either.  me and my wife, and the bill was just around $10  we didn't get the old time soda pop tho, maybe next time, i would definitely come back here and recommend to friends.  i got the polish sausage with kraut and onions it was a little spicy but really good, they have an option to grill whatever you want (it would make the sausage more spicy to grill it)

the one thing i would suggest to the company would be to maybe give some chips with the dog, just because it seemed like no one was getting them, they were a little pricey, and off to the side so some people didn't even notice them. i just think if people tried them and fell in love with them then you're more likely to sell the whole bags of them... when 1oz bag is $1.01 after tax. 3oz was $3 and it was a small bag for chips, they even had a $7 bag that looked about the size of a regular bag of chips

text: This location is fabulous! It's clean and it always seems like everyone is willing to help you out here! I recommend giving this place a try for all of your cannabis needs!

attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': None, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': None, 'classy': None, 'casual': None}", 'WheelchairAccessible': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': None, 'street': None, 'validated': None, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'HasTV': 'True'}
categories: Pizza, Restaurants, Sandwiches, Salad
text:
I count myself blessed to have born in the St. Louis Metropolitan area for one reason: Imo's Pizza. 
I now live in California, and I have yet to find a pizza that is anything like Imo's...the thin crust, the cheesy cheesy tomato sauce...my mouth is watering just thinking about it. 
Every time I'm home, I make it a priority to get Imo's at least once. 

I'm from West Belleville, so I've always ordered from this location. I've never had any reason to complain.

name: Domino's Pizza
categories: Restaurants, Chicken Wings, Sandwiches, Pizza
text: This place petty much ruined my life . Here i am 5 months pregnant and I have the dumb idea to ask them to put the word boy on a large pepperoni pizza to deliver to my mother in laws house for a gender reveal because they love pizza . & of course food is my only thought these days . They say they can do it and I thanked them and hung up . Three hours later the pizza arrives at their house . Three hours ...... it was a regular pepperoni pizza and my mother in law is wonder what am I doing ordering her a pizza . I called them to tell them and they said they couldn't figure it out and I told them they should have called and let me know and I would have just got it refunded . Yes my hormones were high but at the same time I could not get over the fact that they did that . I asked to speak to the manager and the girl said she was the manager. I explained why I was upset and she said " so did the crust not have garlic on it " I couldn't believe that she didn't understand a word I said . Then I find out later that she is not the manager and they don't have one and they can't do anything . I wish I could have sat outside for two months straight and picketed ! I was so frustrated . Never go here also every time you ever order it will be cold and late.  I hope it just a down

text: I had a Bloody Mary and it was pretty good even though it wasn't listed as a Specialty.  I ordered 2 appetizers, stuffed mushrooms and bacon wrapped jalapeño poppers.  Both were tasty, but not necessary out of this world.  The bartenders was helpful and friendly, the decor - top notch.  Definitely not a cheap place.

name: Randall's Wines & Spirits Co
categories: Food, Furniture Stores, Shopping, Beer, Wine & Spirits, Home & Garden
text: This is easily the cleanest and most well organized liquor store I have ever been to. They have a huge variety of liquor and beer and it is all set up in a well so that it is easy to find. There were three registers working at one time, and they seem to need it because there were quite a few people in the store. They didn't have the one particular beer I was looking for, but it allowed me to try some more local brews. They seemed to carry everything from one brewery. I particularly liked Two Hop IPA.

name: Menards
categories: Hardware Stores, Shopping, Home & Garden
text: If you're looking for anything you can find if at Menards! I first discovered Menards whenever I was living in Chicago! I never knew what the place was until I actually went in. I'm happy that they opened one in ofallon! It's a very nice store that has almost everything you need...even food. Yes kind of weird that they sell food, pet stuff, etc...my only downfall about this location that I think is kind of strange is the checkout. It's just completely different and very weird. That for sure!

name: Jacks 66 Auto Repair
categories: Automotive, Auto Repair, Tires
text: The owner and staff are very friendly. I've taken my car in twice now (battery replaced and belts replaced) and they did a great job taking care of my car. They were not sneaky about anything (like most mechanics who just wanna rip an unsuspecting female off). Getting your car fixed is  expensive but at least these guys don't try to rip you off. That in itself is worth five stars.

name: NTB-National Tire & Battery
categories: Oil Change Stations, Automotive, Auto Repair, Tires
text:
I will say that they did fix it right but the estimated price vs actual price was a little off by $75 but they did knock off $23 so I can't complain to much. They attempted to make it right so I won't say my overall experience was bad.  

The wait was what took forever over 5 hours. That's a little long.

name: Big Mama's Bbq Express
attributes: {'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': None, 'validated': False, 'lot': None, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{u'breakfast': None, u'brunch': False, u'lunch': True, u'dinner': True, u'latenight': None, u'dessert': None}", 'Ambience': "{u'divey': False, u'hipster': False, u'casual': None, u'touristy': False, u'trendy': None, u'intimate': None, u'romantic': False, u'classy': False, u'upscale': False}"}
categories: Restaurants, Barbeque
text:
I am not from here and so it was quite a mystery to me what Snoot and Cooter are. Where I'm from Cooter means something decidedly different. So I was curious, and I got the snoot and chicken wings combo. The wings were fine (suuuuuper deep fried). Needless to say, the snoot qualifies as one of the grossest things I have ever tried to consume. And I eat plenty of crazy food. For the randos like me trying something new, snoot is basically a sheet of deep fried pig fat. Imagine taking a layer of pork rinds, pressing them together and frying a second time just to be sure they are extra crispy. I got the buffalo wing sauce which was slathered on the wings and the snoot. But this didn't hide a somewhat rancid smell that emanated from the snoot. No wonder obesity is high in southern Illinois...

Service was cordial - took about 10 minutes to get the food. Seating is limited and not that comfortable (stools and a few tables). Only drinks I saw were fountain soda (no sweet or unsweet tea, no lemonade). Everything is a la carte (all sides must be purchased separate except for slices of white bread), which I didn't really like. Got the mashed sweet potato - didn't realize this is basically a dessert - loaded with sugar and cinnamon. Do not recommend unless you want to eat pie filling with your snoot.....

(For any locals who like snoot or sweetened sweet potato - I'm sorry I'll try to work on it)

name: Belleville Pancake House

text: The food was good.  The place was clean. The service was good. This was our first time and we had patty sausage, eggs, French toast, biscuits and gravy, and the potatoes.   None of it was greasy and it was actually good.  I would not go to this place for the coffee.  It wasn't terrible but I have a thing for coffee so it might be pleasing to the average coffee drinker. But the rest of our visit was good. Give it try. It was well worth our visit.  Pleasant atmosphere.

name: Apple Cleaners
categories: Local Services, Dry Cleaning & Laundry, Laundry Services, Sewing & Alterations
text:
We usually go to another dry cleaners but decided to give Apple a try. The lobby is very clean and air conditioned! (Compared to 2 other places in town, this is a bonus!).

For some reason, like most dry cleaners, they seem to relish posting a half-dozen signs telling the customers all the bad things that will befall them if they don't do exactly as expected by the business. Signs kind of set a negative tone. We're not the enemy, we are the customers!

I'm probably being generous with the 3 stars; but the service was not as bad as mentioned by others and the clothes appear to be clean. My biggest complaint was the price: 2 short-sleeve casual men's shirts, 1 woman's casual blouse, 1 woman's khaki capri's. Cost? With tax; almost $24. That equates to almost $6 per piece of clothing. Yikes!

name: JOANN Fabrics & Crafts
categories: Home Decor, Shopping, Fabric Stores, Art Supplies, Arts & Crafts, Home & Garden
text: As an out of town visitor, I spent about an hour in this store.  The store is clean, well organized and the staff were all very friendly to me.

Service

Food

I Highly recommend the Unch's Bacon Wrapped Double Cheeseburger.

name: Gateway Fun Park
categories: Active Life, Arcades, Batting Cages, Arts & Entertainment, Mini Golf, Amusement Parks
text: A bit of a rundown place but my husband and I had fun wasting a couple hours on mini golf and the go karts. Prices were good and it was very close to our hotel. Don't come here expecting a beautiful well taken care of golf course - you won't get it. Regardless of the looks you will still have a good time!

name: Walmart Supercenter

name: Little Caesars Pizza
categories: Restaurants, Pizza

name: Four Paws Animal Hospital
categories: Veterinarians, Pets
text: Four Paws Animal Hospital is lucky to have Dr. Bedard! She went above and beyond in helping us get our pets to Germany for our military move. We were in a bind since the base vet was unavailable the week we needed to get the International Pet Health Certificate. Dr. Bedard examined our pets and made sure the USDA paperwork was correct before I headed to Springfield to get it endorsed.  I can't thank her enough for her attention to detail, the phone calls, the faxes and especially her time. I highly recommend her to anyone looking for a caring vet!

This place is right across the street from North End Park which also happens to be our (Belleville Rowdies) rugby pitch. Excellent patio out back with tons of greenery surrounding a centered fireplace. Not sure how often the fireplace gets used but it looks cool.
Inside is filled with tons of old knick-knacks from years past. Its a cool place to just sit and have a beer and soak in all of the scene. Plenty of locals. Kinda divey. Most importantly, ice cold STAG on tap here. Can't go wrong with a place like that. No food served, but a decent stop for a beer or cocktail for happy hour.

attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsBitcoin': 'False', 'HairSpecializesIn': "{'straightperms': False, 'coloring': False, 'extensions': False, 'africanamerican': True, 'curly': True, 'kids': True, 'perms': False, 'asian': True}", 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}"}

text: Had a truly bad experience here.  The young lady who cut my hair was definitely not engaged in doing so.  I was the next person in line and she sorted magazines for 5 minutes before taking me back.  She did less than nothing to make me feel welcomed and appreciated.  I paid for a shampoo and she asked me, "You don't want a shampoo, do you?"  At this point, I felt like she had tolerated my existence  for long enogh and said no.  She did remove that from my bill.  There are other places to cut my hair and I intend to find one. Avoid this establishment!

name: Econo Lodge Inn & Suites
categories: Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Hotels & Travel
text: Do not come here. Do not book on any hotel sites. We booked at 8 pm arrived at 2 am for our reservation and were told our room was given away because we did not show up by 4. (Physically impossible) the concierge rudely offered us the lobby couches and told us absolutely no refunds. Pathetic. Would leave zero stars if possible.

categories: Race Tracks, Active Life, Bars, Sports Bars, Arts & Entertainment, Nightlife, Tours, Stadiums & Arenas, Parks, Horse Racing, Hotels & Travel
text:
So...Fairmount is my once a year guilty pleasure. A group of us usually head out on a Friday for "Party at the Park." $13 gets you in for the night and this includes an all you can eat buffet which is really just a fantastically fried food feast. The food is pretty artery clogging gross and every single minute I spend enjoy it I hate myself a little more BUT what doesn't taste good fried? Really? So i fill my plate with all kinds of fried goodness and try not to look down at my plate to survey the damage as I indulge. They also have $1 bud products (bottles) and pretty cheap mixed drinks all night. 

I am not a big gambler and my strategy is to pick a horse with a name I like and put down the minimum bet which is $2. Sometimes (not often) this works for me and it is pretty exciting when you see your horse cross the finish line first. It does get super crowded so if you want any shot at sitting down you have to get there early. 

From the fried food to the fabulous people watching this is definitely an experience and I am sure we will continue our once a year tradition.

name: Green Forest Vapor Shop
categories: Vape Shops, Shopping, Tobacco Shops, Electronics
text: I only use this place because it's close. The salespersons don't know anything without looking online and they're snobby. They acted like I was a loser because of the mod I had, and I literally bought it from the guy I was talking to. A year earlier he said it was top of the line and I'd never need another one, now he's never seen that before and "whoever" sold it to me was ripping me off. Well thanks for the heads up that you're a crap salesman. Overall they have good products, but they're overpriced. If you're going here, know what you're looking for ahead of time.

name: Caffe' Avanti

categories: Restaurants, Coffee & Tea, Food, Sandwiches
text: Caffe Avanti is a nice little bistro near downtown Edwardsville.  I had the meatball sandwich with chips and salsa.  It was wonderful.  The bread was soft and the sauce was just right.  My wife also enjoyed her buffalo chicken wrap.  If you are looking for something that is quick and not fried then this the place.

name: Lewis and Clark Confluence Tower
categories: Landmarks & Historical Buildings, Local Flavor, Public Services & Government
text:
And on a clear day...
On that clear day...
You can see forever...
And ever... And ever...
And ever more!

When you get to the top level of the Lewis and Clark Confluence Tower and burst in to song singing, On A Clear Day You Can See Forever, I can tell you, you will not be the first. All those tower guides have heard it before, it's not that original. However, I do think my rendition was note worthy.

I've been twice, I had to do a re-visit because on the first it was an overcast day. 
It was amazing how far I could see when a few clouds were removed from blocking my view. Each time, our tour guide was knowledgeable about the history of the area and Lewis and Clark. Our first guide on the cloudy day was witty and put his own spin on the presentation of information. The second guide sounded like a rehearsed tour guide, but you still get the info you need. 

It's a great outing for a family or a couple who just wants an adventure up the River Road.

name: TAJ Nail Bar
categories: Beauty & Spas, Waxing, Nail Salons, Hair Removal, Nail Technicians
text: I went here on a friends recommendation and her instructions were "don't have anything planned after this appointment because you'll be late. They really take their time." I absolutely loved it here! It's very clean and I love that the majority of their utensils are single use! I picked the aroma therapy pedicure and I got to watch him make the scrubs he was going to be using. And he gave the best leg/foot massage EVER. I think that with the service they give you their prices are extremely reasonable! I walked out happy with every penny I spent. They made my birthday that much better. THANK YOU!

name: Lucky Dog Barks and Recreation
categories: Pets, Dog Walkers, Pet Services, Pet Boarding, Pet Sitting
text: Only place I trust with my puppies! I love the wed cam service! I am able to watch Timber and Nova play all day! The staff is super nice and accommodating. I recommend them to everyone I know!

name: Walgreens
categories: Food, Cosmetics & Beauty Supply, Drugstores, Convenience Stores, Photography Stores & Services, Shopping, Beauty & Spas
text: I feel like I could be a secret shopper at Walgreens. I love that all of their stores are truly laid out in the same pattern. I have never had a rude or impatient worker at Walgreens. I stop at a Walgreens every week. Their sale ad is the first thing I read in my weekend paper.

name: Whisker Bones Supply
categories: Pet Services, Pet Photography, Pets, Pet Stores, Pet Groomers
text: Staff is very friendly, they even have our pups some treats when we were there! They have a lot of homemade items that are very cute. Small shop but they have a lot of great stuff! Even things for the home, I'll definitely be going back.

name: Labcorp
categories: Laboratory Testing, Diagnostic Services, Health & Medical
text: Very caring and compassionate team of ladies. I had a lot of blood to be taken and they were very knowledgeable and helpful. I had three very attentive staff members who all waited after closing to take care of me. They showed they really did care.

name: CPR Cell Phone Repair Glen Carbon
categories: Mobile Phones, Local Services, Electronics Repair, Shopping, IT Services & Computer Repair, Telecommunications, Mobile Phone Repair
text: My phone took a bath and I frantically came into the shop an hour before they closed. The new owner was so sweet, accommodating and informative. He fixed my phone within minutes and it was free ! Green mobile wanted to charge me $50 just to look at it. It's extra to fix it. All my phone needed was a simple fix ( who knew!? I thought I needed a new phone ) and I'm so so so happy I took it in to CPR. He was a life saver and a money saver. Thanks so much for your kindness ! I will send my friends here ! Thanks for having longer hours too!

text: I normally like this place because it's near my house. The 2 girls that were working there today (Friday, May 25) weren't very polite. I ordered a large chicken bacon artichoke pizza. I was charged $14.25. They had a sign up for that same pizza for $12, so I asked them why I was charged $14, one girl said "you have to mention that in order to get it for $12." How am I supposed to know that?! Even when my pizza was done, the girl didn't bother to say thank you. Going to the O' Fallon, IL location will be out of the way, but I think I'll have to start going there again. I'm so disappointed with today's visit!

name: Artistry On Cakes
categories: Bakeries, Food
text: I wanted to find someone to make a 3 dimensional cake for my dad's 60th birthday and Nancy came through for us! She made a beautiful 3-D semi truck resembling the truck that my father drives for work. Nancy was fabulous to work with and they delivered the cake on the sly for a surprise party too!  And, her prices are very reasonable, especially compared to other local companies who compete on the Food Network!!

name: Fringe
categories: Hair Salons, Beauty & Spas
text: I rarely get my hair cut because I feel like it never ends up the way I want. I decided to try Fringe because I wanted a change. I made an appointment with April and she totally listened to what I was thinking and gave me her ideas before she ever started. She was super helpful and did a great job. I will definitely be going back!

name: Hucks
categories: Food, Grocery, Automotive, Convenience Stores, Gas Stations
text: What a dump. Old pumps where you can't read the screen. No paper towels or cleaner in containers out by pumps.  Many dusty items on shelves. Inside is old and outdated.  My kids even refuse to get slushies from there.  This place needs an overhaul something fierce.

name: Foppe Automotive
categories: Oil Change Stations, Automotive, Auto Repair
text: Outstanding experience.  Replaced struts, spark plugs, and fluids on a Toyota Camry.  Very professional and liked out he saved the parts so I could see what was replaced and what the old parts looked like.  I like the smaller operation versus taking to the dealer.  I felt he was fair on price which the value exceeded the cost.  I will recommend Foppe automotive.

The only thing that would have made this sweet spot a 5 star hit would have been some tunes playing outside while relaxing with a sweet treat!

text: My wife bought me a gift certificate for their services....I have called and left multiple messages over the past month and have received no phone calls back. We are contacting the credit card company to report. Stay far away from this "company".  Very disappointed

name: Dobbs Tire & Auto Centers
categories: Tires, Automotive, Auto Repair, Oil Change Stations
text: These guys are great!! Granted I only needed wiper blades! But these guys & girls run out and install them in seconds!! Friendly too! Even with my Chicago Blackhawks Plates!!

name: Reconditioned Appliance
categories: Appliances, Home & Garden, Shopping
text:
RUN DO NOT WALK AWAY FROM THIS COMPANY!!!
I bought a used refrigerator from this company on 9/14/2017. After a few days the refrigerator started making a loud noise. The company sent out a repair man who said the condenser was bad and that he could tone down the noise but could not get rid of it completely. I told them that was unacceptable and we needed them to replace the refrigerator. They sent another one out. The freezer had no shelves even though there was a place for the shelves. There were 2 missing crisper drawer, & the metal bars on the door of the refrigerator were bent and about to break. The company told me that they would send out the shelves for the freezer and the two missing crisper drawers. This was approximately Oct. 6 2017, Said we would have them by the following Tuesday or Wednesday. Spoke with them on Columbus day and they promised again to have them there by Oct 10th or 11th. Again they did not show up. Although I cannot make complaints for other people, I have spoken to a couple of people who had the same experience. They give you the run around until you finally give up. I paid $125.00 for a refrigerator that work and had the necessary shelving. This company sold me a refrigerator that worked for 2 days. Every since then they have been giving me the run around. They have my money and I have a large box the cools but does not have the interior shelving. They have my money and I have a large piece of junk.

name: Motomart Convenience Stores
categories: Food, Convenience Stores, Gas Stations, Automotive
text:
I come in here a lot, because I go by it all of the time.  They have a TV in the check out line that can zombify some patrons.  

They have a Milk and a Coffee club card where you get free product after so many purchases.

text: Unfortunately I have been to this restaurant a number of times with a group of friend and for the life of me can't figure out why they want to go. Last night our group (10 of us) had reservations at 5:30 pm. We were all on time. We immediately order. Before we had finished our salads our main dishes were served. They never ask if we wanted any more to drink or even if we wanted desserts. They gave us our bills, took our money and we were out of there by 6:25 pm. We were rushed all the way through dinner. I had a pizza again and it was the worst I have ever had there. The group can go back but we (spouse) will never step foot into this establishment again. Just too many restaurants in Edwardsville other than Sugo's.

text: What a value! Joe's Asian is a great option for those looking for a lunch option on base.Expect to wait a few minutes in line to order but they have your food out fast. This is a mainly Filipino based food place but they also have some hibachi options, nachos, wings, and more. The quality and convenience are great for what you get. I highly recommend going on Wednesdays for the $7.50 Chicken pancit, chicken adobo, and lumpia special!

name: Honey Baked Ham Company
categories: Cafes, Caterers, Event Planning & Services, Sandwiches, Meat Shops, Specialty Food, Restaurants, Delis, Food
text: Stopped by here on Veterans Day for a freebie meal. WOW!!! doesn't even cover how good their food is, while it's full meal deal for free I'm definitely a returning customer in the future for regular lunch or dinner meals here to take to work with me. Can't say enough on how good quality this food is.

name: Springers Creek Winery
categories: Beer, Wine & Spirits, Wineries, Arts & Entertainment, Food
text: Wonderful ambiance, generous and charismatic owners, amazing wine.  I could not think of a single thing to make my experience more enjoyable

name: Lewis & Clark State Historic Site
categories: Public Services & Government, Landmarks & Historical Buildings
text: Really nice museum!! Very rich in information. A great idea to bring kids in a school field trip. ALL Staff members were knowledgeable and super friendly.

name: Illinois Department of Motor Vehicles
categories: Bars, Nightlife, Departments of Motor Vehicles, Public Services & Government, Local Services
text: I am late with this review and shame on me. I recently moved and I needed to change my address. I arrived at 8:30 on a Friday before a holiday weekend. The place was full, but they had 5 people behind the counter and they were hustling. I was prepared to wait for awhile. I was only sitting in my chair for around 15 minutes. and they called my number. I just needed to change my address and I was unsure what items I needed to make it happen. The clerk was very helpful and she even asked if I want to register to vote while I was changing my address. For it being a holiday weekend, the place packed full of people and she was very pleasant, thorough and made my experience easy. I know that the DMV gets a bad rep but this place was great.

name: Hometown Dental
categories: General Dentistry, Health & Medical, Dentists
text: Need more stars!!! Best dentist I have ever seen. They are so friendly and made me feel so welcome -as if they already knew me. They go over prices before your visit and Dr Woody did my cleaning himself! He fixed some fillings that were previously done very lazily at Green Mount family dentistry.  Dr. Woody sat and educated me on my X-Rays using a big screen television.  This made me feel very confident before we even started.  HomeTown Dental obviously cares about quality work and excellent customer service!

name: PetSmart
categories: Pet Services, Pet Groomers, Pets, Pet Sitting, Pet Training, Pet Stores
text: Took our toy poodle for first time grooming today, Shannon did a great job with him, he was a little matted since it was a first groom and she took the time and was very cautious with him being new to it all....we will definitely  go back!

name: Red Robin Gourmet Burgers and Brews

text: We really do like red Robin. They have a huge selection of different burger types, nice sweet potato fries and pretty good service. Overall it's one of our local favorites and we tend to go here when we're looking for a good burger and good service. It may not be gourmet cuisine but it typically fits the bill.

name: Arby's
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True'}

text: They have really good sandwiches that are well prepared.  I had an order for 6 people all with different picky orders.  They were 100% accurate and the people working here were very pleasant.

name: National Great Rivers Museum
categories: Museums, Arts & Entertainment
text: This is a small museum that is very nice & modern with a lot packed into its space.  Very accessible for people of all ages from small children to disabled/seniors, which impressed me.  I wish I'd read the other reviews prior to our visit as I didn't realize it was possible to go onto the actual dam adjacent to the museum; that would have been cool!  For a small museum I felt that I learned a lot about the Mississippi and other great rivers, without much effort.  Although it was just a tiny exhibit box, my favorite was seeing shells that were once used to make mother-of-pearl buttons.  They offered quite a bit of info on water conservation and on the river commerce & culture of the past, and a good deal of respect to engineers and lawmakers who created the dam and improved river travel immensely.

name: Domino's Pizza

text: I haven't been here in almost a decade! I've heard dominos made an improvement in their pizza's. I have to agree but I still don't care for them. We had a stuffed bacon and jalapeño with cheese bread. It was ok. Very doughy and was cold when received. We also ordered a pizza it was overly salty but the tomato sauce has definitely changed. It's an average pizza joint because my nephews will eat them :)

name: Exactime Watch & Clock
categories: Local Services, Clock Repair, Shopping, Watch Repair, Watches
text: great place.  They know there stuff.  I have had them work and clean on a number of my high end watches and i will continue to go back.  Also Steve helped me with some hard to find watch battery's for my bow sight one time.  he had them in stock when no one did.

name: Schnucks Belleville E
categories: Bakeries, Drugstores, Shopping, Flowers & Gifts, Florists, Food, Grocery
text: On Saturday, February 11, at about 10:30am, my Mom went to the deli to see about getting a couple meat trays.  When asked the girl was very rude about it and said they needed a 24 hour advance notice. Now I use to work for Schnucks deli and I can tell you this, if I ever refused a deli tray, I would have been written up. Not only were there 2 employees present, the store was NOT BUSY! My Mom tried to explain,, that we did not know that a family friend was going to pass away this am. So Mom left and went to Shop and Save. Lost more than one customer today.

name: Walton's Ice Cream and More
categories: Food, Burgers, Restaurants, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt
text: Don't let the sign fool you. I promise it's there. Walton's ice cream is a great addition to the main drag. Lots of soft serve options for adults and kids alike. I had the salted caramel truffle concrete which was fantastic. My kids got basic chocolate and vanilla. A number of kids got the vanilla soft serve with rainbow flavoring added. It was very cool and everyone was happy. If you are in the area definitely stop by and enjoy the great ice cream and friendly service.

name: Old Navy
categories: Children's Clothing, Fashion, Shopping, Women's Clothing, Men's Clothing
text: If you are looking for cheap clothes, this is the place to go. I usually go to Old Navy when I need to find something that I will wear only a few times. Their prices are pretty cheap as well as the quality.

name: Gateway National Golf Links
categories: Active Life, Golf
text:
Great views of the skyline!
Fairways smooth like carpet!
Greens are firm but, receptive!
Staff is friendly, helpful, & informative!

text:
My wife and I had a double date the other night and really wanted try tavern. Well it was a good choice. The wait staff was great. Always made sure we had drinks and everything we needed. 
The menus where just printed off from the computer and stapled together but to me that was the only thing bad about the place. There were to many things that sounded great on the menu which is a good thing I think.  It is a bit pricey but for the food it's not that bad. My wife and I go over to St. Louis all the time for a place like this. It was great not to have to this time. 

We will be going back for sure.

name: Mastermind Vodka
categories: Distilleries, Beer, Wine & Spirits, Food
text: This was our first time and the tour was fantastic. The tour leaders great, but if you are lucky enough to get a tour with a great group of people and led by the founder then you have hit the jackpot. These folks care about their product and it shows. They support their communities, they produce an excellent product at a great price, are locally owned and locally supplied and they deserve your support. Ask about the Groupon upgrade, if you like great premium vodka you will be glad you did.

name: Pier 1
categories: Shopping, Department Stores, Candle Stores, Fashion, Furniture Stores, Home Decor, Home & Garden
text: The employees at this location are by far the most welcoming and helpful people with outstanding customer service skills.  Missy searched for and held an item for us that was not available near us.  Hannah and Kat were helpful, too, with finding us a box for our large purchase, and putting paper around it to protect it.  We live in St. Louis, but would travel here to shop if we can!  The store was clean and laid out nicely, with enough room to walk between aisles without being fearful of knocking things over.  The staff was knew the merchandise and where it was located in the store, too.  Great job!

text: I left my wallet and the video shows the hostess picking it up. Then she takes it to the host stand where there is no camera instead of giving it to a manager like she is suppose to. I got my wallet back minus $300.

name: Schnucks Edwardsville
categories: Florists, Grocery, Shopping, Drugstores, Bakeries, Flowers & Gifts, Food
text:
This is really a nice schnucks.  It seems like the schnucks on the IL side are known for one thing of another.  The one in belleville by SWIC had a great seafood department, the one in Swansea has a better than average deli, the one in Fairview has a pretty good meat department.  This one has a nice produce selection. 

In st. Louis the one on the hill specializes in Italian items. 

I wish they all were of equal caliber in all of their departments.  

The store is big and clean.  They also have the cooking section where they sample the menus and have the ingredients conveniently located.

name: Ramada Fairview Heights, Il
categories: Hotels & Travel, Event Planning & Services, Hotels
text:
We stayed here one night in order to be close to St. Louis while still out a bit.  It is a great location as it is only 30 minutes from downtown St. Louis.  The Metralink is not that far away either, if you want to take public transportation into St. Louis.

The Lobby is clean and updated and the front desk staff were very friendly.  There is a comedy club and a TGI Fridays attached to the hotel and you get a discount for both places with your room key, so that is really cool.   There is a free breakfast, but it is nothing to really brag about.  Free wifi was good and there is pleanty of free parking.

As for the actual room, I was disappointed.  Our room on the 4th floor is in need of updating.  The bathroom tub wouldn't drain, so I reported that when we checked out.  For the rate that we got (Expedia unpublished rate $55.00 including tax) it was worth the money.  Had I paid more, I would not have been very happy.

attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'HasTV': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'DriveThru': 'False'}
categories: American (New), Burgers, American (Traditional), Breakfast & Brunch, Restaurants
text:
Service:  Great. 
Facility: still sub-par

This IHOP re-opened a few days ago after "voluntarily" closing down for two months to make health code related repairs.  Building is cold, not sure the heat is on.  Overheard staff say a pipe had froze over night and they had no water and that the owner was aware (for several hours).  However; no plumber was on site.  Eventually I heard a staff member say that they were going to close for the day due to no water.  

Not sure a manager was on duty.  I hardly ate my food but no one asked if anything was wrong with the food.  Did I mention the syrup on the table was frozen?  Frozen.  I went to pour the full bottle of strawberry syrup on my pancakes...and nothing came out.  The server noticed and then gave me some heated up syrup in a paper cup.  

I thought that since the heat was most likely off and no water that maybe my meal would be comp'd or offered a discount?  I wasn't really expecting a free meal (food was good...was too cold in the building), but the offer would have gone a long way. Staff is working the best they can with what they got.  With that said, I'm pretty sure doors shouldn't have opened  today with no water.

I had expected significant changes to the interior, but was surprised that very few changes were made.

This is the last visit I'll make to this IHOP until they tear it down and build a new one.

categories: Restaurants, Bars, Sports Bars, American (New), Nightlife
text:
I think this place is a great addition to the metro east! The concept is really fun, we've had a great time both times that we've gone. 

The bar food is good! We've tried the fried shrimp, chicken wings with the Thai chili glaze, the burger, and our absolute favorite, the nachos. All were so good, but man those nachos were the perfect Friday night bar snack *heart eyes*. 

Even with the good food, the drink specials alone make this place worth trying! On Friday nights they have $5 32 oz strawberry margaritas & on Saturdays $5 32 oz long islands- YUM. They are strooong, and so good! 

It's so nice having a place like this on the IL side. I'm excited to see how this place continues to grow!

name: Jan's Hallmark Shop
categories: Event Planning & Services, Arts & Crafts, Cards & Stationery, Gift Shops, Shopping, Flowers & Gifts
text: I will never be patronizing this hallmark ever again. I was horrified to learn that while my husband had run an errand for me to pick up wrapping tissue and paper during the holiday season after picking our young son from school, was turned away from their store bathroom in what I would call a potty emergency. After pleading with the sales clerk, he was directed to the Mexican restaurant next door. They weren't buying tacos, we were buying Christmas paper. Indignation doesn't begin to express how I feel about the poor judgement and treatment they were subjected to. Class act hallmark.

name: Corner Stone Dental
categories: Health & Medical, Dentists, Endodontists, General Dentistry, Cosmetic Dentists
text: I haven't been there in a few years, but the assistants and everyone else is nice. I had Dr. Wilson and my very first appt (back when he had the old office on Lincoln ave) he asked me if I wanted braces. My teeth are perfectly fine-- in fact, I get complimented on them all of the time, even back then. Therefore, I assumed that he's either a perfectionist or needs money. The past few times, he's had to put fillings in my mouth and both times were unpleasant as I don't think I had any anesthesia. Not fun AT ALL.

text: Staff is friendly and attentive! Cheese dip was delicious!! We ordered the mix fajitas. They were wonderful. You get a large portion and prices are good. Everything tasted fresh. We'll be returning customers for sure!

name: Shannon's Kitchen Company
categories: Food, Restaurants, Food Delivery Services, Soup, Salad, American (Traditional)
text: Great little eatery. Small menu but good quality. The owners are just fantastic and dedicated to serving you. Right outside the base and I would come again!

name: Gateway Grizzlies
categories: Arts & Entertainment, Professional Sports Teams, Stadiums & Arenas, Party & Event Planning, Event Planning & Services
text:
Even if you're not into sports, the food makes a trip to see the Gateway Grizzlies totally worth it.  I *love* the krispy kreme burger ($5).  It was the perfect size to be filling and satisfyingly sweet and savory, without inducing a heart attack.  The burger patty is about the size of a McD's cheeseburger, then there's a piece of cheddar, two slices of bacon and 2 halves of a krispy kreme donut as the bun.  The same concession stand by the kids playground also has great philly cheesesteak nachos ($6) and fries ($3.50).  The nachos have a generous amount of chips, shredded steak, grilled onions, and white cheese sauce.  For those wanting an adult beverage other than beer, they also have good frozen drinks.  I had some type of frozen mango drink that was very good.  

We rented a picnic table for a group.  For $36, you get a reserved picnic table and 6 tickets, and it's right by the kid's play area and food concessions.  Definitely a fun, cheap night out!

text: Well, it seems sad that I'm the first to give this place a review that's more than 2 stars. I've always loved going to the one near me (in Glen Carbon), but unfortunately the place closed a while back. So now I gotta go to the 'other G.C.' to get my Pizza World on. I always go during the lunch buffet, and I've never really had any problems. You gotta admire their diversity in toppings, especially what they put on the buffet! They always ask the customers for any pizzas they want on there. I've tried many, and again, no problem. Their dessert pizza is really good as well.

name: Westview Wine Cellar
attributes: {'Caters': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Alcohol': "u'beer_and_wine'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2'}

text: We have gone here a few times and enjoyed the atmosphere and wine. Most staff is friendly except for one female bartender who seems to hate her job but we overlooked her in the past. Tonight she was extremely rude and we will never go back! She came around spraying Fabulosa cleaner (not a disinfectant ) on table tops. The smell was overpowering and my wife commented on this within earshot. She went back and was laughing about it with someone behind bar. When she once again came to clean more tables my wife asked her not to and she told her tables had to be disinfected. My wife told her she would have to refund money if she continued and she rudely replied no way. Fabulosa does not disinfect it only cleans and how can you enjoy wine if you are eating cleaner. Will never subject myself to one as rude as she was. This review was somehow removed so I am reporting.

name: FedEx Office Print & Ship Center
categories: Signmaking, Professional Services, Printing Services, Local Services, Couriers & Delivery Services, Shipping Centers
text: The absolute worst service that I have ever experienced in my life, Rhonda and Steven. Management is not to be found he or she hides from any issues and is a complete coward. They make up policy to cover up their lies and mistakes and laziness. They checked in four of my packages only to leave them behind the counter, 5 days later I walked in the store to deliver another package and recognize my packages and when I asked the wallflower behind the counter she said they were headed back as unclaimed and that I would have to buy them at auction in San Francisco from FedEx. They would not allow me to take the packages because apparently once they are marked unclaimed then I can't take them. I had to have the Police Department intervene to get my Packages back. it took two hours of my life, 2500 dollars in goods and all of my patience. I would encourage anyone that represents this company to call me and I won't hold my breath. Avoid this place like the plague.
