categories: Restaurants, Bistros
text:
Good to see new restaurants in Maryville. I had the cod sandwich with mashed potatoes. The bread was somewhat tough for a dish sandwich but the cod was excellent. The garlic mashed potatoes were a bit cold and needed some spices but they had a lot of potential. My wife had the steak and Swiss with fries. The steak sandwich was really good but could use some au jus, it was kind of dry. The fries were hot and fresh. 

The bistro also has a great beer selection with about 10 draughts and 40 or so bottles. I had a 6 row wheat and a Magic Hat #9. The place is open until 1am during the week and 2am on weekends. Pretty good overall, will definitely try again.

name: Smoothie King
categories: Food, Health Markets, Juice Bars & Smoothies, Specialty Food
text:
I made the sad mistake of going here, one which I will not make again. I was on my way to chipotle in search of a remotely healthy meal after my workout. As I pulled up at 8:55pm the "open" sign was off and they were turning the lights off. Sighing, I drove across the street to smoothie king where the open light was still shining. I thought, surely something remotely healthy can be found here.

I walked in to the death glare of two high school looking girls. One rolled her eyes and shouted to the back, "hey we need a blender back" while the other said "I'm gonna turn the light off cause WE'RE CLOSED". I should've turned around and left right then and there. Pardon me for providing you with my business a few minutes before closing.

So I hurried to pick something after being asked 3 times what I wanted within 90 seconds. I settled for a smoothie that had "meal replacement" next to it, thinking it would be the best option for a high protein, low calorie meal. After they begrudgingly made my smoothie and handed it over (additional glares free of charge) I took one sip. Wait no, I'm still sucking on the straw... 3 minutes later, still sucking. It is so thick I can't drink it.

I give it the drive home to thin out. Then I open the lid, it's literally smoothie smush on the rocks. So I decide to look up the nutritional info to see if the effort is worth the while. And let me tell you what I found: OVER 150 CARBS IN ONE FREAKING CUP OF OVERPRICED BLENDED FRUIT AND ICE. I threw it away and made some broccoli. I didn't realize that "meal replacement" meant it could replace the #4 meal at McDonalds. 

Needless to say, the overwhelmingly friendly customer service, high quality and reasonably priced HEALTH CONSCIOUS smoothie left me yearning for more.

name: Sears Auto Center
categories: Automotive, Tires, Auto Repair, Oil Change Stations
text:
Still an amazing five stars!

Two weeks ago, I was driving to work and was at like 65 mph when my car started making this scratching kind of sound at the front. No sputtering, blocking, rumbling noises...just a weird scratchy sound. I got to work, consulted Google, and called my friend who's a mechanic about all the dreaded possibilities it could be. He told me to stick with diagnosing people and he would take a look at it if I ever decided to come up to Chicago. (If you don't see the humor and irony in this, you don't know me very well.).

Fast forward. So I really wasn't as worried because the noise never happened again and my car needed some maintenance anyway so I was planning on bringing it in sometime this month. But today, I started my car down the street and looked in the rearview mirror to see this trail of fluid. Condensation? Fluid leak? I don't know. I'm not a car doctor. But coupled that to the weird scratching noise that may have indicated power steering or braking problems (thanks, Google!), I was worried enough to drive back home and call Sears. I mean, I drive fast, but I'm not THAT stupid; last thing I want is the steering out at 80 mph. 

The conversation went like this (and yes, I do sound stupid):
Me: Hey, so I might have a leak. I'm not sure. There's a trail of fluid down my street.
Mechanic: Ok. What color is it?
Me: Uh, I'm not sure. It just looks wet. But I popped my hood and this container that has pink stuff looks low?
Mechanic: Hm. Well, just bring it in. We'll look at it. 
Me: Like right now?
Mechanic: Yep. 

So I get there, and there's like four other cars in the bay, but they put my car in right away. They take a look and tell me everything is a-ok, but that it's time for my oil change and the power steering fluid is a little low. No leaking though. OH, and that pink stuff is supposed to be at that level because it's coolant and circulates. I mean, who would have thought?! ;) 

So thanks, guys, for not laughing at me. And thanks for getting me in right away. And thanks for being all right with me running out in the bay in flip flops asking  where the coolant level should be and what other weirdo containers I need to look at if I ever need to do something like this again (which I feel like is the equivalent of coming into the OR in flip flops). I'm sure I'll be back with more car symptoms in tow.

text: After 10 hours on the road the last thing you want to deal with is trouble with your hotel room. We checked in online so that we could run right by the desk to get some much needed rest. The desk had a wait for it being late at night. The individuals behind the desk were very professional and calm dealing with a disgruntled customer. When we got to the room we found our toilet wouldn't flush. I told the front desk manager and he came right down to take a look. They offered a new room but we had already settled in and needed rest. I commend the staff of this location for holding true to their brand and doing there best to make sure the customers are satisfied with the location.  Asside from the small issue with the toilet the shower heads could do with an upgrade.  Great place to stop on a road trip.

text:
For Saturday lunch during a miraculous weekend in Illinois.

We both ordered a beer and a pizza.

I forgot what toppings she got on her pizza, but it was a hit!

I got Italian sausage on this "personal pan pizza" which was huge!!!

It's served on a cookie sheet. Does that tell you how big it is?

Plus it comes with a salad. And the salad was served on a plate. I cannot say how grateful I was for getting a salad served on a plate, so I could toss it appropriately! Bleu cheese dressing was so lovely.

After having eaten all the salad, I couldn't eat too much pizza, but it was delicious.

And we had a discussion about what cheeses were on this pizza. We decided there was some cheddar in the mix. Nonetheless, it was marvelous.

I checked out with an $11 tab for all that, and took enough pizza home for one or two meals!

text:

categories: Nightlife, American (Traditional), Restaurants, Pubs, Bars, Fish & Chips
text:
Saw the write-up in the Belleville newspaper yesterday and decided to give Spike's a try with my wife.  Spike's has a very nice deck out front that would be enjoyable on a cool evening.  All the parking is out back and we had no trouble finding a space.  Our server was a very nice young lady.  She was wearing knee-high boots which had to be uncomfortable for her at some point.  There is free WiFi which worked well (open network).  We sat next to one of the HDTVs which had an excellent picture.  I ordered a Bud LIght (very cold) on tap and my wife ordered a Diet Coke.  The menu has a fair amount of variety.  Walls are decorated with jerseys from local sports teams.  I ordered the fish tacos (featured in the Belleville newspaper review) and my wife ordered the Deluxe Calzone.  It took a while for the food to arrive.  Both entrees were served hot.  All food was served in plastic baskets lined with paper.  The biggest challenge to eating the two items is fluid management.  The Deluxe Calzone was particularly juicy.  When my wife cut it open, it kinda ran all over the inside of the basket and pooled at the bottom with no place to escape.  Near as we could tell, it was from the tomatoes in the calzone.  The crust got very damp and fell apart.  My wife finished it with a knife and fork.  It was well nigh impossible to pick up.  The fish tacos were a much better choice, but they also had a bit of an excess fluid problem, but not as much as the Deluxe Calzone.  The diner must race to finish the tacos before the soft taco wraps fall apart from moisture.  The tacos were well-seasoned and had melted cheese inside.  The fish were solid tenderloins and were very tasty.  When the server came to present the bill, my wife brought up the problem with the calzone and how it might have been better served on some kind of plate so it would drain better.  She said simply that everything was served in a basket.

The fish tacos were apparently really popular.  The cook came out of the kitchen and announced to our server that they were out of fish and would not have more until the owner came back tomorrow with more.  Now, if I were in food management, I would get what I needed that night to keep serving the fish tacos -- particularly since they were a featured item in the newspaper.

We're up in the air about returning to Spike's.  I think they are trying fairly hard and are deserving of your consideration.

name: Synergy Health Care Solutions
categories: Doctors, Physical Therapy, Naturopathic/Holistic, Pain Management, Chiropractors, Health & Medical
text:
I feel a need to revise my review, 7.30.19, the person that was in the office is no longer there and things are good for me at the chiropractic office at this location. I feel keeping your patients informed of any changes is important.  So a good front desk staff is crucial. 

I have been going there with my family for awhile now.  Dr. Hall is really awesome about helping me with adjustments due to my migraines.  He is a really good doctor as well as a caring person. 
 
Dr. Hall called me today, 8.15.19, and things are better now. I understand this place does accept walk-ins as well as appointments.  I also understand this office does not offer family or student discounts now.

They close this office at 6PM. 

I have called Brandy/Office Manager to explain this rude behavior to her today, 7.30.19, and she responded with a reply here, I have not spoken to her.

name: American Nails
categories: Beauty & Spas, Nail Salons
text: Love this place...it doesn't matter which nail tech you get they are all fantastic.  The ladies always try to wok you in.  I called right before closing one day and they said to come on up and three nail techs stayed late to work on my nails!

name: Best Wash Laundromat
categories: Laundromat, Local Services, Laundry Services
text: My husband and son went here last night it was clean very nice. Very nice employee s attendines. Nice worker's period  every one is so nice. My husband wears a back brace the worker helped him. Nice he gave him a tip. He. Deserve s that.  Thank you.  Best wash you are wonderful we will be back

name: Super 8 by Wyndham Troy IL/St. Louis Area
categories: Event Planning & Services, Hotels & Travel, Hotels
text:
We booked this hotel on Hotels.com based on the good recents reviews and the reasonable price. We were pleasantly surprised. The front desk lady was nice and helpful. The room was spacious, with newly updated bed, headboard, new dressers, TV stand and flat screen TV. The bed is nice and comfy as well. I was especially happy that they have PBS channel, because this means my son will be able to watch some kids shows in the morning while we pack - this was great since many hotels we've stayed before did not have PBS or anything suitable for young kids on TV.

The one star missing was for the older, thin towels they provided. They also only have paper cups in the room which was not the best when I wanted to make a cup of tea by boiling water in the microwave. And the indoor pool although seemed nice, they don't open until 10am, then check-out time is 11am so there's not much time for us to enjoy the pool. The wifi was ok, it stayed on to the most part, only dropped out on me twice and then it worked the rest of the night. Overall this has been a very nice stay. We'll rebook this hotel if we were ever in the area again.

name: Gateway Classic Cars
categories: Car Dealers, Automotive
text: Beware.  Consignment cars that look good in pics but run like crap- if at all.  Expect to put A LOT of money into any of their cars to make it a dream car.  Otherwise - A nightmare.  $5000 later.

She's a perfectionist who is not afraid to ask her fellow stylists their opinions if she needs to. Everyone seems to help everyone out and there is a no tipping policy. In addition to being a full service salon they have a boutique full  of original gift ideas, clothing,  jewelery, etc.. name: Firestone Complete Auto Care
categories: Automotive, Oil Change Stations, Tires, Auto Repair, Auto Parts & Supplies
text: Brandon, manager of Firestone at 922 Loughborough, MO 63111 saw me on the side of the road with a flat tire on 8/28/15.  He literally stopped, asked if I needed help, and I said yes- as I felt I was absolutely was in crisis, because my husband was so far away.  Brandon immediately put my spare on, and followed me to the local gas station, and filled the spare's pressure up to appropriate amount (I didn't know it was low & didn't have money on me).  I'm newer to the area and asked where he recommended me to go for help.  He recommended my local Firestone, Fairview Heights, IL and EVEN called to help me get my information in their system.  When my husband showed up, we wanted to pay Brandon for all his help, but he wouldn't take any money.  I was in a crisis & he saved me.  Then the next morning, Fairview Heights treated me with the utmost respect and gave Outstanding customer service.  I was really impressed with the whole experience from beginning to end.  Thank you, Brandon; and thank you Firestone.  I plan on choosing you for my automotive needs.

name: Heroic Adventures
categories: Books, Mags, Music & Video, Comic Books, Toy Stores, Shopping, Hobby Shops
text: I was greeted when I walked in the door and asked if I needed any help. The graphic novels I called for earlier were there waiting for me despite the fact that never shopped there before. After I paid for those they asked me if there's anything else I could help me with. They showed me some other collectibles I expressed an interest in. When I was finished with that asked me if they could help me with anything else. You couldn't ask for any more, outstanding customer service just outstanding. The previous reviews were left when it was under a different owner. Can't go wrong shopping here.

name: Four Muddy Paws
categories: Pet Stores, Pet Groomers, Pets, Pet Services
text:
The last time I was in here I asked the cashier a question about the strongest dog chew toys they had. Before she could answer, she took a phone call. 

I waited a long time for her to be available to help me. I tried looking around, but the store is pretty small and I felt awkward walking in circles and waiting. I found that most of their products are pretty overpriced and nothing too unique. After what felt like a long time, I finally just left the store, empty-handed.

I'd love to shop locally for my dogs toys and food, but this place just isn't for me.

text: Had a broken rear flange on my muffler. Brought it in at 8 in the morning. Technician looked at and said he could weld it back together cheaper than replacing the entire muffler. Had it done in less than an hour for a hundred dollars. Quick, cheap and efficient.

name: Little Caesars Pizza
categories: Restaurants, Pizza
text: Is Little Caesars the best pizza? NO.  Is Little Caesars the worst pizza?  NO But they do offer pretty good pizza that is always ready.  So if on a Friday night you finally decide at 8 pm you want pizza and your wife wants chicken noodle soup, you can make your way in to the supermarket to get the soup and walk into Little Caesars to get a pizza in less than 5 minutes.  I got a pizza, crazy bread and sauce for under 9 bucks!  You can't beat that.  I spent more on two cans of soup and a six pack.

text:
Do NOT go here. Worst pedicure I'ver ever had anywhere!
Older woman with a very nasty attitude, barely worked on my
feet, especially my heels at ALL. She was so slap dash, my feet didn't even feel like I had a pedicure. The experience was so uncomfortable. The negative vibes she was giving off were that she was angry she had to do the pedicure. This was my first time here and my last!

categories: Steakhouses, Restaurants
text:
I took my wife out for a steak dinner a few nights ago. We had two appetizers, a (cheaper) bottle of wine, two steak dinners, and a piece of cheesecake.

Food Quality: B+
Food Quantity: B
Cleanliness: B-
Design & Decor: C
Noise Level: C+
Staff Friendliness: A
Server Food & Beverage Knowledge: B

OVERALL GRADE: B  (I wouldn't eat here again but not because of the food or service)

PROS: Very friendly waitress, server, and hostess; not crowded, seated us 30 mins early; Excellent outdoor nature scenery; excellent stuffed mushroom appetizer; got in and out very quickly 

CONS: Not the ambiance we were looking for. I know it is an "old school" steakhouse, but we were the youngest people there by 20 years -- everyone else appeared retired. The steaks weren't bad but they weren't great; I've done better on my Big Green Egg. They charge St. Louis-style prices without the excitement and energy...environment was a big let down.

We won't be going here again, not because of poor service or substandard food, but because there are at least 5 steakhouses of superior quality in St. Louis, which is where we live anyway.

name: Gentlemen Cuts
categories: Men's Hair Salons, Hair Salons, Beauty & Spas
text:
Walked in with my two boys on the off chance of maybe getting an appointment.  Well they had three and all three of us got our haircuts that day.  

Atmosphere was amazing and service was amazing.  My boys are very particular about their hair and they got exactly what they asked for.  We're were all very satisfied with the work done.  I recommend Gentleman's Cuts to anyone that's looking for a great haircut.  

They are very reasonably priced as well.  I've paid close to $60 for some haircuts in the past but none of them even came close to the one I got at the Gentleman's Cuts.

name: Schorr Lake Vineyard
categories: Food, Wineries, Arts & Entertainment
text: Schorr Lake Vineyards is my new favorite vineyard that is close to St. Louis. It is small and has that small town friendliness that one expects. We went on a lazy Sunday and had most of the place to ourselves. Saturdays are apparently much busier. It has lots of seating and tables for a smaller place but it is not crowded too tightly together. It has a nice 7-acre vineyard that also includes a number of rows of big, beautiful blackberries. It has a small shop with various wine-related gifts and some food items, but you are welcome to bring a picnic basket as well - which is always important to us. We've evolved into avoiding those wineries that no longer allow us to bring in our own cheese. After all, we are there for their wine, not their food. Which brings me to the most important aspect of this place. The red wines and the blackberry wines (including the port) are phenomenal!  I love dry, velvety reds with deep flavors. My girlfriend loves sweet wines. Here we get them both. Seriously, this is probably the best Chambourcin I've ever had and one of the best Norton's (Cynthiana) that I've had. My girlfriend is not a port drinker, but bought multiple bottles of the blackberry port and the blackberry wine to take home. All in all, a great place!

name: Meineke Car Care Center
categories: Automotive, Oil Change Stations, Auto Repair, Wheel & Rim Repair, Tires
text: This place was so much better when they were at the old location. Same friendly faces always on top of things.   Since they have moved to the new location I never see the same guy twice at the front desk when my oil is changed. The guys at the front desk seem unsure of the computer system.  The guys changing oil don't have uniform shirts on the young guys have T-shirt or wife beater tank. The one young guy was smoking in the garage talking to the other guy doing my oil.  Just seems to be getting worse.  Sad. I have been coming to Meineke in Troy for many years.  Think it's time to change. Uhhggg

name: Mike's Automotive
categories: Automotive, Auto Repair, Oil Change Stations, Auto Parts & Supplies, Tires
text: Just wanted to give them a thank you for taking care of not just our cars but my family and friends. It is great to know you can trust them to take good care of you. Our Grand Caravan that we bought new from Cassens has given us some difficult times in the last year. When it broke down last year I hobbled in and was crying they were rude and gave me an appointment for 2 weeks later. I called Mikes and they said they would look at it as soon as I got there. They fixed it and I was on my way next day.  This week was frustrating with my car and Tom was so caring. Please consider them for your next auto need.  They take great care of their customers

name: Regal Nails
categories: Beauty & Spas, Nail Salons
text: Came here for a full set of acrylics with gel. I was seated right away and a gentleman came over to start. He immediately started the file and began to file my nails. The file was going very fast and soon became hot. He caught my cuticles twice which I understand is a risk of acrylics, but honestly he was just speeding through my nails and seemed not to care. He would grab my hands hard to pull them closer. He also accidentally glued two of my fingers together with the glue and then when i brought it to his attention, he just ripped my fingers apart which hurt a little. My nails look good, I'm happy with them. I'm just not a fan of the costumer service there. He was speeding through all of the process and got frustrated when I asked for a couple of the nails to be shorter. I don't think I'll get my nails done here again.

name: O'fallon Tire & Propane
categories: Tires, Automotive
text: I have been here twice for tire work and twice to have my propane tanks filled. In short, I will return. The man who owns the place is honest and does a great job. I highly recommend.

name: Cardinal Catastrophe Services
categories: Home Services, Roofing, Siding, Gutter Services
text:
I would like to take this opportunity to thank you for the wonderful job you did on installing our new roof.  The new roof gives the house a renewed character.  We also appreciated your outstanding professionalism.  This is hard to find anywhere these days.  

As a member of the local community I have security knowing you will be available if we have any issues in the future. 

You listened to our needs, gave us a reasonable quote, started the job on time, your crew worked dedicatedly, respected our property, and completed the job ahead of schedule.  And, you returned our calls, texts, and emails immediately.  There was no stress and no unforeseen surprises.  

Your guidance and patience working with our insurance company was much appreciated!

name: Chong's Oriental Market
categories: Grocery, Food
text: This store has closed. I know that I am not the only one that is so sad about this. I tried to call to see if it might still have something left this month, as I knew she said that she was closing due to personal reasons, last month. The phone number says no longer in service. I haven't driven down there, but I am assuming the doors have closed as she said they would. This has been my favorite Korean store for over eight years. I can't imagine going anywhere else. The selection was fantastic. I will miss the help that I got with cooking.

name: Newbold Toyota Scion
categories: Auto Parts & Supplies, Car Dealers, Automotive, Auto Repair
text: They squeezed me in for a last minute oil change and were super friendly. Free carwash with my oil change!! The waiting area was nice and clean, Starbucks Coffee machine, snack vending machines and a vintage 1978 Land cruiser to drool over. Only downside was a LONG wait (even for last minute).

name: Coffee Junction
categories: Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Coffee & Tea, Food
text:
The fro-yo is delicious and their breakfast sandwiches are pretty amazing as well.

I wish they had food items all day and night.

name: Joe's Pizza & Pasta
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'beer_and_wine'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'Caters': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'False'}
categories: Pizza, Italian, Restaurants
text: My hubby talked me into a Groupon for this place based on reviews. We're serious about good food and love finding great pizza. First off, we drove from just south of St. Louis to go. They're in a strip mall, kinda off the beaten path. But when we got there it was packed! We had to wait about 5-7 minutes for a table. We figured it was a good sign. We ordered fried pickles, a Chicago style deep dish with lots of meats, and a thin crust with pepperoni. The pickles were good, especially since I was wanting some. The pizzas came out and looked good. I found that there wasn't an abundance of toppings on the deep dish. The cruat was very doughy. I prefer it to be a little more crispy and buttery. The sauce is very sweet. A little too sweet for me. I only ate one slice of that one one square of the thin crust. Again, the sauce... Too sweet. The hubby and kids enjoyed it, but me? Not so much. I much prefer eating Chicago style deep dish at Pi in STL.

name: Bigelo's Bistro
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': True, 'casual': True}", 'Caters': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BYOBCorkage': "'no'"}
categories: Pizza, Restaurants, American (New), Sandwiches
text: I cannot express how much I love Bigelo's. Homemade ice cream, incredible pizzas, beer dinners, and delicious weekend specials! They always knock it out of the park. The Bigelo is my go-to sandwich these days - always amazing. Beer selection is ever changing and one of the best in town. The staff is always fantastic and friendly. I also love and appreciate the fact that this is one of if not the only restaurant in town that doesn't have a TV. Enjoy the food and your company. Bigelo's never disappoints.

name: Alton Cracker Factory
categories: Hotels & Travel, Event Planning & Services, Wedding Chapels, Bed & Breakfast, Guest Houses, Vacation Rentals, Hotels
text: This is a fairly new Bed and Breakfast in the Alton area. I was there for a small reception. There are three floors to the space. On the second floor, they have two suites which has two bedrooms and bath and with a full sized kitchen and living space. The second floor also has a studio space with a 1 bedroom option. Both the second and the third floor have a scenic view of the Mississippi river and the beautiful Alton bridge. The top floor has two bedrooms, two baths, huge kitchen and a pull out couch. This space can comfortable hold 60 to 70 people. Wifi is included. This would be a perfect place to watch fireworks or listen to a concert at Liberty Ampitheater.

name: Bert's Chuckwagon

name: Jack in the Box
attributes: {'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Caters': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'False'}
categories: Restaurants, Mexican, Tacos, Breakfast & Brunch, Fast Food, Burgers
text: I was in Alton visiting my husband for work and saw the jack in the box on my way into town and vowed to eat there before I left. The next day I excitedly went back to have some jack in the box. Now while I know they are not known for salads, I really wanted one so I proceeded to order a grilled chicken salad. From the outside the salad looked good, but once I got back to the hotel to eat it I was so disappointed. The chicken breast was very small and it was full of iceberg lettuce. There were a few cherry tomatoes and some cheese and carrots. That's it!! Such a disappointment. I will give them another chance but maybe try something else.

name: Lakeland Square Laundry
categories: Dry Cleaning & Laundry, Local Services, Laundry Services
text:
Machines were clean and many options were available, even though they were busy. Dryers were very fast. Clientele left me alone. There is a change machine, vending for laundry supplies and snacks, decent Chinese next door. The attendant was very nice in helping me figure out which machine to use, how many quarters they took and how to operate the machines. She also found dryers close together when my wash was finished. Cash only. No wi-fi. 

Four stars because they have a drop off laundry service and store the racks of clothes all over the laundromat making a sort of labyrinth out of the place.

text: I've never actually stepped foot into this place, so I can't write an authoritative review.  But - I catered a meal for 15 Chinese acrobats and crew from this place and the food was quite good.  A little greasy, perhaps, but overall I was pleased with the quality.  I was also extremely pleased with the value.   We had a mountain of food.   Great choice for big groups.  Just give them plenty of notice.

name: Carole Frew's Bridal & Tuxedo Shoppe
categories: Bridal, Shopping
text:
please don't go.  I wish I could give it no stars.

I am the mother of a 30 something bride who is smart and savvy.  We did our homework, had IN STOCK gowns on our phones, and made an appointment which we confirmed 30 minutes before we arrived.  We dressed properly and were polite.

They did not have our appointment (which we had JUST confirmed) in the computer.  At all.  The saleswoman then badgered my daughter about her nickname, scolded me ("shame on you!") for letting my daughter have a nickname, and she told me what she thought of my choice of my daughter's given name.

We just should have left then.  Within one minute the saleswoman offered to undercut the price of any gown we had seen anywhere else.  When I mentioned a specific gown and the price, she denied it existed and made funny noises about the price point.  Whatever.

There are NO 3500 gowns.  They have a second floor we were not allowed to go into.  They IGNORED the IN STOCK gowns we wanted to see.  The saleswoman kept telling my daughter she "KNEW" what my daughter wanted.  To be polite, my daughter tried on a gown the saleswoman suggested.  It was awful.  The saleswomen was surprised when she asked me if the bride had tried on any gowns anywhere and I said "of course".  My daughter came in prepared, with correct shoes and everything.  Including photos of IN STOCK gowns that we were not allowed to see.

When the saleswoman began reading texts my daughter was sending to me (brief comments about a couple gowns, reminders), that was IT.  We thanked them for their time and left.

text: Wish I could give it 0 stars but oh well. Absolute worst location I've been to. Which sucks with a 6 year old. Almost impossible to get what you order thru the drive thru. Orders messed up every time. And god forbid you dont check your order right there because if not forget about getting the issue resolved. All the employees are rude and don't give a crap about customer service. So i get on mcdonalds website to let them know, request a response from the owners association and nothing. Im guessing they dont care either. I dont know what Bill C. was thinking in his review. Must of had the wrong address.

categories: Dive Bars, Bars, Nightlife, Restaurants, American (New)
text:
Stagger Inn is one of my top 3 favorite bars of all time.

I don't think you can really call it a dive, cause the place is not that dirty and neither are the clientele. 

The crowd is always mixed, young and old. 

And the music is always good. Generally, Thursday through Saturday you'll find some great old timer rock bands playing classic covers while the middle aged women show that they still got it on the dance floor. 

Go. Have a beer. Sing along. Stagger home.

name: Custom Sounds - Fairview Heights
categories: Auto Customization, Mobile Phones, Automotive, Electronics, Car Stereo Installation, Auto Glass Services, Shopping
text: I was there yesterday for a small audio installation; a door speaker on my truck was rattling and buzzing. On Tuesday I dropped in and met with the manager, Adam. Adam recommended replacing both front-door speakers with Kenwoods, and gave me an appointment for 10 yesterday. They open at 10 but I was there at 9:30. Chris invited me in anyway, took my keys and showed me to the waiting room. 15 minutes later he said the installation was almost done. Total charge $177, sounds great, I was in and out the door almost before I knew it, and they treated me like I was spending $2,000. In the back of my truck I found the box from the Kenwoods, and my two old speakers. That's 5 stars in my book. If I need/want any car audio I will go there.

name: Fantasy Book
categories: Books, Mags, Music & Video, Shopping, Comic Books
text:
I've been coming to this comic shop ever since I was a kid. I remember when I was addicted to those Pokemon/ Yugioh cards and walking that three block excursion to buy just a few more booster packs. Ohh, those where the days haha. Anyways, they always have such a huge variety of comics, old and new, and that's not even to mention their playing card stock, Funko pops, and collectables. If they dont have what you want on their shelves they can easily order it as well. The staff is and has always been really helpful and actually pretty darn knowledgeable about the comics they're selling. I don't have anything negative to say about these guys, truly,  If anyone is looking for a comic store with a great vibe and stock, I reccomend stopping by-

I have been living out of town for almost 7 years and when ever I do come back to Belleville I almost make it a mission to stop by atleast once. Suprisingly, they still have me in their system after all these years too..

name: Performance Eyecare
categories: Health & Medical, Ophthalmologists, Doctors, Shopping, Optometrists, Eyewear & Opticians
text: I have been going to Dr. Massie since before he opened his own office. You cannot possibly ask for a more caring or thorough doctor. He takes the time to talk to you and see how things are going. You never feel rushed and he is always concerned that your questions are being answered. I went through a scary eye issue a few years back and he was amazing. After sending me to a specialist he called me to make sure that everything went OK and to make sure that I was OK. Everyone is the office is phenomenal and the selection of frames is amazing. I promise that if you give him a try you will never go anywhere else.

name: Laurie's Place
attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': True, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'very_loud'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Music': "{'dj': False, 'background_music': False, 'no_music': False, 'jukebox': True, 'live': True, 'video': False, 'karaoke': False}", 'CoatCheck': 'False', 'HappyHour': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BestNights': "{'monday': False, 'tuesday': False, 'friday': False, 'wednesday': False, 'thursday': False, 'sunday': True, 'saturday': True}", 'WiFi': "'no'"}
categories: Music Venues, Nightlife, Arts & Entertainment, Pubs, Bars
text: The food is really good at Laurie's. I'm an attorney in Edwardsville and this restaurant is famous with the lunch crowd. I really love their fried fish meal. And if you go close to St. Patrick's Day, they have a nice corn beef and cabbage meal. My advice is to arrive early. Like be there at 11:30 to order if you go with any group. If you get there early, you'll be eating within twenty minutes of your order. But, if you're there anytime after noon with a group, be prepared to wait more than an hour for your food. No joke. I think there is only one cook. Great food though--go early.

name: Germania Brew Haus

categories: Nightlife, Bars, Pretzels, Coffee & Tea, Beer Bar, German, Restaurants, Food, Juice Bars & Smoothies
text:
TL;DR: great coffee, great service, but uninteresting beer.

I think I've been here more days than not since they opened their doors, and I've loved this place ever since. It's only gotten better, with extended coffee hours (which I wish they'd extend further but I'd understand if it's not their thing), and of course the tap opening. I've yet to visit during tap hours, but my girlfriend said it was fantastic, and rather easy for someone who had never used a self-pour system before (so don't feel intimidated!). I plan to eventually come during tap hours, but as someone extremely familiar with craft beer, I've been uninterested in the brews they've had available so far. Because of this, I can't rightly give them a 5 star rating, but hopefully they'll expand on this area as they grow, and I'll find myself there passed 8pm.

name: Days Inn O'Fallon
categories: Hotels & Travel, Event Planning & Services, Hotels
text: GROSS!!!  Don't stay here!  I was moving to the area, and hotels.com told me this was the only location, that took pets.  IT'S NOT!  Drury Inn, which is much nicer does take pets, and it's right down the road.  Also, the hotel next door to this nasty hotel does too.  It was winter, and the windows were open for some of the rooms the whole time we were there (2 nights), and you could see the mattresses were upright too.  In the middle of the night, some girl was outside our room on her cell phone crying and screaming.  The room was in very poor shape, carpets were dirty & messy, and it needs to be updated.  The front desk staff as well as those partying in the lobby were sketchy as well.  Won't stay here again, guess I got what I paid for.

name: Dairy Queen Grill & Chill

name: Jimmy John's
categories: Food Delivery Services, Delis, Fast Food, Restaurants, Sandwiches, Food
text: I have a standing three-month appointment at a doctors office close by this particular location. I only get a sandwich from here once every three months. The last two times I have ordered a sandwich I have also ordered one for my husband. You cannot get more than one sandwich at a time correct. This seems to be a problem. If I just order one sandwich it's just fine, if I order two, the order is completely incorrect. Please try and work on this aspect of your business. Not everyone wants the same sandwich, you have to learn to try and make two different ones.  This used to just be a guilty pleasure that I would enjoy every few months, I will no longer enjoy it. Thank you for destroying my joy.

name: Take Care Clinic

name: Alton Hauntings
categories: Tours, Food Tours, Walking Tours, Hotels & Travel, Bus Tours, Local Flavor
text: Interesting tour which focuses on the history of Alton.  You get to go in a couple of cool places that you wouldn't ordinarily go in.  Wear comfy shoes and dress for the weather.  Fun tour!

name: Ron's Barber Shop
categories: Barbers, Beauty & Spas
text: Great small town barber shop.  Hot lather neck shave, reasonable prices, friendly staff. Highly recommended.

name: McDonald's
categories: Coffee & Tea, Fast Food, Restaurants, Burgers, Food
text: Came here for breakfast and had a good experience. The play area was great and deserves 5 stars. Food was the same as any other McD's. Gave 4 stars because it could have easily been a bit tidier but as we were leaving I saw an employee doing some wipe downs so maybe this is unusual.

name: Bob Brockland Buick GMC
categories: Automotive, Auto Repair, Tires, Car Dealers
text:
I decided to take my Lexus for body repair to this Buick location from a recommendation from family.
The car came out perfect! They used OEM parts resulting in perfect body panel alignment, with complete 100% perfect paint matching. 
Paul and John maintained excellent communication with me during the process, which was a quick one week turn around time.  No complaints at all and will for sure return.  Paul at service is also kinda cute, I hope he's single.

name: Munie Greencare Professionals
categories: Home Services, Adult Entertainment, Landscaping, Tree Services, Nightlife, Lawn Services, Professional Services, Irrigation
text: I'm happy with my yard and no worries with my services.  Last year they were late applying the last fertilizer. But I still use their services.

name: Kid Glasses
categories: Health & Medical, Optometrists, Eyewear & Opticians, Shopping
text:
Such a positive experiences with this business!!

I drove an hour from the St Louis area after my kids doctor said she had heard too-good-to-be-true rumors of a fantastic and cheap kids glasses place in Edwardsville. 

Over-the-top friendly & knowledgeable, I am so grateful to have this family-owned and run business to deliver outstanding customer service & walk me through buying kids glasses for the first time. And $79 a pair for indestructible kids glasses and $4 shipping?!?? At that unbelievable price, we were able to buy two pairs and not have to sweat about whether insurance is going to pick up any of it or not. 

I called twice with questions before driving to the store & both times Brian was super helpful and kind. Then when at the store, we found it to be comfortable and immaculate. And the staff was truly a God-send. Thrilled to tell my kid's doc that the rumors she heard are true.

name: Rcasa Tex-Mex Restaurant
categories: Restaurants, Tex-Mex
text: This place was great. Came here in between softball games and only had an hour and they got food out fast and with no mistakes. The chips and salsa were amazing as weel

name: Mike's iPhone Repair Service
categories: IT Services & Computer Repair, Mobile Phone Repair, Local Services, Professional Services, Electronics Repair
text: Mike was over the top in getting the job done in a professional, friendly, efficient, affordable manner. I contacted Mike for repair and within an hour, he met me. Mike had the phone completely fixed within an hour and a half. The screen had been shattered and some of the insides were showing when I presented the phone to him. In a short amount of time, Mike had it repaired and looking and working in perfect order! I highly recommend Mike! You will be pleased, not only with his service, but his fun, easy going personality! Thank you!

name: Schnucks Cahokia
categories: Food, Grocery
text: So rude! There was only one check stand open with a long line. A checker opened another lane and then took her fiends rather an the people who had been waiting. When we came over to the line, she didn't greet us and she just stared while we unloaded our cart. She never spoke one single word to us the whole time. At least the bagger was friendly. Prices are high as well. I'm never going to SCHMUCKS again.

categories: Gay Bars, Bars, Nightlife
text:
I went here for the first time a few weeks back, and had a great time! I was with my wife and a couple of friends, and just missed going upstairs for the drag show before they filled up, so we hung out downstairs until we were able to check it out. 

The atmosphere was a refreshing change from a regular bar. I say that, because everyone just felt so relaxed while there. Sure there were a lot of people, and that can get people charged up, but everyone was just kicking back and having a good time. In addition, I've heard the patio is great, so hopefully I'll get back when the weather is nicer.

When we got upstairs, the show was great. The girls did really well. I think several of them could be on their way to bigger and better places, but they all were great. 

If you are looking for a good night out, and tired of the Fast Eddies world, definitely give this place a shot. You will have fun!

name: Reiniger Jewelers
categories: Shopping, Watches, Jewelry
text: Fantastic staff extremely helpful. Prices not so sure of.  Went in for the 60% sale and felt I still over paid for what I purchased.  I might be so out of the loop though. But $1,000.00 for diamond chips. Seems to me overpriced.  Like it don't live it

name: iRestore Stl
categories: Home Services, Roofing, Damage Restoration, Gutter Services, Insurance, Home Inspectors, Financial Services, Siding
text: The crew showed up around 3pm to replace our roof, sunset was around 6pm. They did a whirl wind job of removing 2 layers of shingles and replacing the roof in a little over 3hours. I was told that  they would remove our old gutter gaurds and replace them when they were finished. When they were done, the edges looked wavy and the gaurds looked bent. So we had someone come replace the old gutter gaurds. The reason why the edges are wavy is because instead of removing the old gaurds, they nailed them down under the shingles. This made it almost impossible to remove them totally.  The gutter gaurd company did their best but couldn't get it all removed. So, I still have wavy edges. I wish I would have found someone else for our new roof.

name: Extended Stay America - St. Louis - O' Fallon, IL
categories: Apartments, Home Services, Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Real Estate, Hotels & Travel
text:
OMG they got fleas! This is a pet friendly hotel so be careful if you go the economical route and chose this hotel to save some money. Don't get me wrong, maybe the rest of their rooms were cleaned well and this room just so happened to have very stubborn fleas. But is it really worth being covered in bug bites all over your body? This hotel also allows smoking in certain rooms. I didn't think much of it at the time. Boy, was I regretting not paying attention to that! My room smelled smoky & my towels smelled like smoke. Imagine taking a shower and having to dry off your body with a smelly towel... As for the rest... polyester comforters, old school TV, room decor looks like it was stuck in the 80s... 

I will say, however, the people there have great customer service - Dana was apologetic and very empathetic to us. Such a kind person! But unfortunately, we still checked out early.

categories: American (New), Restaurants, Chicken Wings
text: I downloaded the app & placed a carry out order for 10 traditional mild wings, 10 bone out wings with honey barbecue & mango habanero sauces & large seasoned fries.  Upon arriving to pick up my order all the employees greeted me & welcomed me to the store. I quickly found out my order had not been received. In all fairness, the store has only been opened 1 week. The staff found the printout with my order & quickly began preparing the items. The manager apologized several times & comped my bill. Everyone was very nice. He offered me a beverage while I waited. They also gave me a free blue cheese dip. I normally don't like to try a restaurant that has recently opened & I was a bit concerned what the quality of the food was going to be after the mishap. I have to say everything was delish! The mango habanero was more spicy than I anticipated but excellent! The seasoned fries were also very good! I have to say the Blue Cheese dip tastes homemade!!! Everything was very good! I will be a regular!

name: Lewis & Clark Community College
categories: Middle Schools & High Schools, Elementary Schools, Colleges & Universities, Education
text:
==Service: 5 Star==
Students will have the best service here in this college. They have all the students need to complete their assignment even if you are home, students can access the library online. LC staffs are really friendly and they are willing to help student to achieve a better in their classes. 
There is a lot of campus activity if the student love this kind of thing. For sport they have almost have all of it.

There is some classes that are just offered in edwardsville campus. students are really force to go there and take their classes. 

-Tips:-
If you are struggling on writing, you can access the writing center in the library at the main building. They are very nice and friendly, and will help you a lot. I recommend the students go to the student success center because it is free and they will really help you a lot in your studies. be more active on activities so that will make students resume pretty.

==Atmosphere: 5 Star==
This place is so clean. One thing that is bothering for some students is that some building are old and every time you step on the floor students will hear a creaking sound. 


==Cost: 4 Star==
The cost is perfect for everyone its not that high and not too low. it will cause you around $1300 - $2000 per semester. They accept Financial Aid, scholarship and other grants.

==Instructor: 4 Star==
I encounter the best teacher in this campus. but some of my friends didn't. That is the reason why I scored this as 4 star. In my two years studying on this campus, all of the Instructor are very nice and approachable when a student need help.

-Tips:
I recommend Jim Price for being an awesome film art teacher, Dr. Gerald Mozur for logic reasoning, Jenny Margarida for English, Coral Kimble on Math, and Pat Rzewnick for speech class, If you're taking calculus. I recommend Fred Sexton, Open book exam. And he is very approachable and helpful.

Note: This is just my previous instructor that are very helpful and nice. It is your choice to pick this instructor or not. I am not responsible for anything.

name: Ja Bowl China Express
categories: Restaurants, Chinese
text: This was absolutely disgusting. The chicken had a gray tint to it and I could not do it. One star because crab Rangoon was good but the rest went in the garage

name: Fond
categories: American (New), Restaurants
text: I was very excited to visit this restaurant and  upon entering I was intrigued by the pleasant  atmosphere.  The wait staff was friendly and explained the menu.  An adorable bread basket arrived with 3 different samplings for us.  As we were enjoying our wine, the amuse bouche arrived and was a cod cake with remoulade.  It was so heavily salted that it was unenjoyable.  We split the Fall salad, which was a tiny mound of lettuces with vinegar and oil and a few crumbles of very salty bleu cheese. It was adequate, but nothing special or particularly delicious.  My entree was scallops with carrots and sun chokes.  The scallops were huge and the presentation was beautiful, but again the food was so overly salted that it was way less enjoyable than it could have been.  My companion enjoyed his pork loin with sqash puree and cabbage, which I tasted and was way more pleasing than my dish.  We were treated to a tiny dessert plate with baby muffins and itty bitty butter cookies.  The cookies were delicious!  I was happy to finally go to this restaurant, but also glad to have a discount certificate from Hot Sauce.  I would have been very disappointed to pay full price to eat at this establishment.

name: County Seat Cafe
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': True, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True'}
categories: Southern, Comfort Food, Restaurants, Breakfast & Brunch, American (Traditional), Sandwiches
text: Just was at County Seat for breakfast, but won't go again.  I ordered my eggs over medium and they were cooked hard and even had a crust around the edges.  The sausage patty was super dry and did not taste good at all. The toast came warm, but with no butter or jelly.  We finally flagged down a waitress who seemed surprised that we wanted those things.  She brought the jelly right away, but took a while bringing the butter.  By the time I got that, the toast was cold.  The potatoes were very dry, tasteless and over cooked.  About 2 bites of each was all I could muster and then only because I was hungry.  I don't like leaving negative messages, but this was that bad.  Another odd thing was that after pushing my almost untouched plate to the end of the table to be picked up, the waitress didn't even ask if everything was all right or anything like that.

name: Papa John's Pizza
categories: Restaurants, Pizza
text: I usually call in when I am driving home to order a pizza to go. Every time I call, they answer and then put me on hold immediately. Papa Johns really promotes the online ordering, it is all you hear when you are put on hold. Not sure if they are trying to brain wash me. Anyway, once I get a person back on the phone. They tell me the weekly specials, even though I just heard them while I was on hold. I am pretty boring and predictable when it comes to my pizza. I like the veggie pizza without green peppers. Last night I got the deal, where it was cheaper to order the large instead of the medium. The pizzas from here are amazing, I love the garlic butter container that comes in every box. This is my go to pizza.

name: Salon Ludic
categories: Beauty & Spas, Hair Salons
text:
I came to Illinois on business travel, had nothing to do so I got my hair done... I had Alyson she was super friendly, showed me around ect. I asked for more of a golden blonde, with a lot higher of a balayage, it was supposed to go about an inch from my roots.... which it doesn't... 

The first time I really wasn't happy, so she re did it, thankfully.  She also called to make sure I was happy which was nice... but she called the day that I was leaving, so what was I supposed to say, it doesn't look terrible, so I was happy enough.  

The cost is pretty good for this place, I paid about 150 for a hair coloring. Sadly in this case, you get what you pay for...  
in my pictures, the two in the tie dye shirt are from today!  The black shirt with the grey cardigan is from two days after coloring, and in the maroon shirt was me before I went into this salon...
Do you see a big difference ....

name: Steven Mueller Florist
categories: Wedding Planning, Florists, Shopping, Gift Shops, Floral Designers, Flowers & Gifts, Event Planning & Services
text:
I got a knock at the door this past Thursday. There was a man at the door with a beautiful floral arrangement. He handed them to me and wished me a happy birthday. 

When i looked at the card i saw that they were from Steven Mueller Florist. I've never received our bought anything from them. My daughter from Washington state ordered them from him. Probably the most beautiful and impressive arrangement I've seen. The lily's are so large,  just breathtaking.

name: St Louis - Granite City KOA
categories: RV Parks, Hotels & Travel, Campgrounds
text:
Nice folks and friendly showed us to our site
Liked that 
Sites old 
Tables and sites need some work
The train noise is something we like.
What we did not like was the WIFI my wife and I each had to call the WIFI service using our cell phone time just to get on line.
That's our $$$'s spent fixing your problem 
Then when you do get on line it's slow and drops out.
Please don't tell me you have WIFI when your server is close to the OLD deal up service.
For that reason I could not give more the two stars 
That and your sites do need an upgrade 
This could easy be a five star KOA with a little work and better WIFI service.

name: Hobby Lobby
categories: Home & Garden, Shopping, Home Decor, Hobby Shops, Fabric Stores, Arts & Crafts, Art Supplies
text: This place is awsome. I have used this place before, but now with planning a DIY wedding this place is even more amazing. The staff is vry helpful and everytime I need something I try this place first. If they don't have it, they will order it for you or give you a rain check. Just about everyhting we have used for our wedding has been bought here and I have had them order me multiple things that they did not have or didn't have enough of. They are extrememly helpful and will use this place even after our wedding is over.

name: TGI Fridays
attributes: {'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'full_bar'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForDancing': 'False', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'HappyHour': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'CoatCheck': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Music': "{'dj': False, 'background_music': False, 'jukebox': False, 'live': False, 'video': False, 'karaoke': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': True, 'latenight': None, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': None}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'very_loud'", 'BestNights': "{'monday': False, 'tuesday': False, 'friday': False, 'wednesday': False, 'thursday': False, 'sunday': False, 'saturday': True}", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': None, 'hipster': None, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': True, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True'}
categories: American (Traditional), Bars, Nightlife, Sports Bars, Burgers, Restaurants
text:
My husband and daughter and I went here and I wish we had not.  The place is clean and staff are friendly but the food is horrible and the tv's played womens golf.  Seriously?

My husband and I were starving and not picky eaters.  The menu pictures looked awesome.  We ordered the Ahi Tuna Crisps appetizer for about $9 but they were dried out fish with toppings on a few tortilla chips (4 to be exact).  There was so little food there.  They lacked any taste.  How they accomplished that I have no idea.

We both ordered the All-American Stacked Burger and the burger was absolutely soaked and dripping in grease (our plates had pools of grease when we picked them up --- about 1/2 cup worth at least on each).  The meat (which we asked for med-rare and pink inside) was well done & then some.  The meat was so dried out from over cooking it was chewy.  I struggled to chew it.  The tomato and lettuce was wilted and so thin you could see thru them both.  They looked nothing like the photos in the menu.  The burger in the menu looks like you get 2 juicy thick (3/4-1") patties, and what we got looked like a flat pancake (maybe 1/4" each).

My husband had mango pineapple lemonade and it was so sweet it was hard to drink.

My daughter ordered the children's meal slider cheeseburgers.  There were 2 with french fries, but only one came with cheese (the only barely had a tsp which was melted burnt).  The little slider cheeseburgers were so overly cooked they were as hard as hockey pucks and she could not eat them (even the buns).  I even tried cutting one up, then tried it myself when she could not eat it that way too.  It was awful.  She had not eaten all day and she usually will eat any & everything.  The chocolate milk it came with looked ok but was without chocolate flavor.

Out of the whole set of 3 meals ordered, the only thing we could eat was the french fries & the only drink was my water.

We looked at each other like the whole meal was a bad joke played on us.

It was so bad and off the mark, we are not going back.  For burgers, got to Red Robin.  They are so good and look just like the pictures.  For steaks, Long Horn or Smokey Bones.

I would give 0 stars if I could.  The food is seriously that bad.

name: Apple Cleaners
categories: Local Services, Laundry Services, Dry Cleaning & Laundry
text: I dropped off 1 suit and 3 shirts for my hubby.  The cleaning itself was good (removed a coffee stain), however their attention to detail on the pressing, etc was nothing to write home about and rather disappointing to say the least!  They put no less than 3 creases in the shirts where there should not have been any.  And of course hubby didn't notice them until he was already on his business trip because he has them cleaned and left in the bag to pack more easily for his trips.  They also replaced a button on one of his shirts (as a courtesy they said)...however this shirt had only been worn twice so it should not have needed to be replaced unless they did something to damage it or we're not careful when they pressed it.  For the same price, we received better service elsewhere so we will not be returning to Apple.

name: Alton Regional Multimodal Transportation Center
categories: Public Transportation, Transportation, Hotels & Travel
text:
My family and I were greeted early this morning by Amtrak Agent Rico, he was most helpful and a delight to speak with.  A clean restroom is a must and seat covers yay!!! Snack machines with some healthy choices too. Can't wait to take a ride myself!

Overall, great job on the "new" Alton, IL Amtrak Station! Modern, well lit, convenient parking lot right out front of the station.  Would've been 5 stars of they had heat lamps on the track side.

name: Sincerely the Craft
categories: Shopping, Arts & Crafts
text:
What a great addition to Downtown Belleville!! I just moved back to the area and was totally preparing myself for a 45 minute drive or more over the bridge to find a crystal shop, but this little lovely shop has alleviated that need. 
It's well organized and has a large range of choices. Stones, herbs, oils, handmade soup, candles and more. I was so happy to see that had herbs available to do Yoni steams and Yoni stones. What was even better is that they have very reasonable prices. 
Different classes are also available.

name: A & E Truck Center
categories: Oil Change Stations, Automotive, Auto Repair
text:
BBB gives this shop an "F" rating. I should have done my research. Let my situation be your warning. 

Worst experience with RV at the custom shop. RV was taken apart on day 2, 2 1/2 months later no work had been done. When we began questioning the work, Eric became rude and stopped responding. Removing the RV not an option as it was in pieces. RV was left on the road, unlocked, dead battery and we were told he was done. It was in pieces, torn apart, and ruined. It will take thousands of dollars to repair the damages and to replace the broken and missing pieces.  BBB will be contacted as well as legal action. Do not bring your vehicle to this shop and expect professional work to be done or professional communication with the owner.  I have posted the pictures of what my RV looked like in March when dropped off with Eric and the after pictures once his company destroyed it. 

Eric will have lie after lie after excuse and excuse. Will not answer the phone or use communication skills.

name: All About Eyes - Belleville
categories: Medical Supplies, Laser Eye Surgery/Lasik, Eyewear & Opticians, Shopping, Health & Medical, Optometrists
text: I'd like to thank all the staff at All About Eyes in Belleville for hanging in there with me during my recent experience with my new glasses. I've purchased several pairs over the years from this facility and have never had an issue. They've always been very helpful and courteous and my glasses have always been perfect right from the start. Recently, however, I went to All About Eyes with an eye prescription I received during an exam at my opthomologist's office. My new glasses were made according to that prescription and, unfortunately, that prescription did not coincide at all with my actual vision.  It took 4 tries and 2 appointments with Dr. Domeczek, a specialist at the Belleville location, to get my glasses perfect and all of this at no expense to me. Although repeated trips to the facility were needed I truly feel it could not have been avoided in this unusual case. All the staff, and especially the manager, Brooke, and Dr. Domeczek worked with me until I was completely happy and in love with my new glasses! I will definitely be back next time I need them! Thanks, All About Eyes !

name: Dunkin'
categories: Donuts, Food, Coffee & Tea
text: The staff at this Dunkin Donuts location are always polite, attentive, and work fast pace. It is the perfect stop for a quick bite to eat before work, or if your craving some breakfast foods later in the day. Their donuts are amazing, but personally I think the blueberry bagels are the best thing on the menu!

name: Jimmy John's
categories: Delis, Fast Food, Sandwiches, Food Delivery Services, Food, Restaurants
text: I work at nearby restaurant & I get tried of eating there. So when I need something light/fresh I order jimmy johns sometimes I have them deliver to my home. They have fast delivery hasn't disappointed me yet. My sandwich is always on point. & they cookies are so delish.

name: 4204 Main Street Brewery & Banquet Center
categories: Breweries, Food
text: Busy place this afternoon!  There was a bridal shower ongoing in the banquet facility and several beer flights being consumed at the bar.  My wife and I both had a Blonde Jeule to drink.  Very tasty brew.  I liked the fact that the beer menu told you how bitter was the brew.  The IPAs were listed as the most bitter.  My wife had the Pork Tacos and I had the Turkey Apple Wrap.  Both entrees came with a dill wedge and housemade potato chips.  Server was very helpful.  The only reason I gave them four stars instead of five is because they were out of chicken.  How could that be?  They also have a line of beer glasses and clothing items with the brewery's logo and the prices were not unreasonable.  I was attracted to the ceramic Red Solo Cup.  A sign on the door announced they are doing karaoke now on Friday night.  This was a good place to grab a beer.

name: Boston Market
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
categories: Restaurants, Comfort Food, American (Traditional), Sandwiches, Chicken Shop, Caterers, Event Planning & Services
text:
I stopped at Boston Market because I really did not want too much to eat.  I also wanted to try the new chicken masala they have been advertising.  I entered and waited longer than I should have to have my order taken, but I understood.

I got the chicken masala and it came with 2 sides. I got potatoes and mixed veggies.  I was told that they only sold one size drink. I really did not want a big cup due to not being able to drink out of a straw. I got my food. The potatoes were good. The mixed veggies were cold.  The chicken was good, but I ended up only eating the breast piece and that was it.  The sauce was ok but I expected more mushrooms. I maybe had 2 mushrooms on my plate.

I basically spent $12 on one chicken breast.  I really don't know if I would be back due to the prices.  Boston Market use to be somewhat cheap. I feel like $12 for chicken and a drink at a fast food place is a bit pricey.

name: Diamond Nails
categories: Beauty & Spas, Nail Salons
text:
I'm obsessed with my manicure. The attention to detail my tech made sure to take care of is amazing. Not a single flaw! Everyone was friendly and nice as well. I was going to drive to Nail Me Good in Hazelwood MO but since I live in Roxana I tried this place bc it's closer and i'm so glad i did.
Edit: the pedicure is really bad. I have a picture attached. I could have done a better job myself and my toenail smudged two whole hours after being painted because she put way too much polish on. Obsessed with my nails, mad I paid 20 dollars to have my toes painted when they ended up looking like this.

name: Old School Automotive
categories: Automotive, Auto Repair
text: Fair prices.  Oil change and tire rotation for $30.  Oil change for $20.  This is my place. They are knowledgeable and friendly.

name: Grimm and Gorly Too
categories: Shopping, Flowers & Gifts, Florists
text:
Support local businesses, especially when they're top notch.  They have the cutest shop setup with a lot of gifts to choose from in addition to beautiful flower arrangements at affordable prices. 
Nothing short of a wonderful experience with them!

text: I've been eating sushi for years and have experienced the majority of the most reputable sushi bars in the saint louis area and this is hands down the best I've ever had. I lived in Florida on the gulf coast for over a year and I was expecting to find a better sushi bar with all the fresh fish available but it turns out the best sushi is in granite city. Who would of guessed?

name: Bowl Haven
categories: Arts & Entertainment, Arcades, American (Traditional), Restaurants, Venues & Event Spaces, Event Planning & Services, Pizza, Bowling, Active Life
text: Had a birthday party there last year. We didn't get the pizza until it was time to leave. Signed up for kids bowl free, and they never had a lane open. Then last night I called to see if they had a lane and was told yes. I called the other foster parent and said meet there for our sibling visit and guess what. no lanes available. Never going there again even though they are 5 minutes down the road.

categories: Food, American (New), Restaurants
text: Let me say that for a place in the mall in a food court this place rocks! I eat here a couple times a month and it is really great food. The chicken always has great flavor and the veggies are always fresh and you get a ton of food and can't spend $10 bucks if you tried. This place could charge double and it would still get my business its that good. I have always gotten this as a take out because eating in the mall just isn't my thing and normally that would be something that would take a star away for sure but the food is just that good that it still gets a 5 star from me.

name: Taco Bell
categories: Restaurants, Tacos, Mexican, Breakfast & Brunch, Tex-Mex, Fast Food
text:
Thinking back, I was being pretty entitled about everything. Considering how complex my orders usually are, it wasn't fair for me to be going through the drive thru with more food than will fit on the screen.

I've since started waiting inside for my food, and every order has been correct. I shouldn't have blamed the personnel for rushing to get my food out to me, when I was clogging up the line.

name: Dentistry With TLC
categories: Orthodontists, Cosmetic Dentists, Periodontists, Pediatric Dentists, Endodontists, Oral Surgeons, General Dentistry, Dentists, Health & Medical
text: Reggie and Dr Smith were wonderful!! Thank you for your compassion to my sensitivity issues. It was a good experience with a dentist even when I didn't really want to be there. Thank you for helping me with my broken tooth, too!

name: Serra Honda O'Fallon
categories: Car Dealers, Auto Detailing, Auto Parts & Supplies, Auto Repair, Automotive
text:
Yesterday I bought a Certified Pre-Owned Honda Civic at Meyer Honda and had a great experience. I did my research at various dealerships on Sunday so I could look at cars without being distracted by salespeople. On Monday morning, I went back by to look more closely at a few cars I'd selected. Salesman Greg approached me and asked if I had any questions or wanted to test drive anything. He was very friendly and helpful, and he didn't pressure me into doing anything or try to upsell me on features that I didn't need. His focus was on what I was looking for and what would fit my needs the best. Yesterday (Tuesday) I went back in to get my car's value assessed and to negotiate the price with Greg. As this was the first car I was purchasing entirely on my own, I felt a bit nervous, but Greg put me at ease. He never pressured me, and negotiating the price of the car was as simple as talking to him.

I feel great about my purchase and confident in both the car and in Greg. Working in sales myself, I think it's very important to build a relationship with the salesperson. I don't think I could have had a better experience, and I'm so glad not to feel any buyer's remorse -- especially with such an expensive purchase.

So why only four stars? If the service department is as good as Greg told me they are, then this place will be worth a solid five stars. But since I obviously haven't had the car serviced yet, I can't speak to that.

I definitely recommend that anyone looking into a car - new or used, Honda or otherwise - stop by Meyer Honda in O'Fallon and ask for Greg. It never hurts to talk to one more person, and hopefully you'll feel as satisfied and comfortable as I did.

name: Popeyes Louisiana Kitchen
attributes: {'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'HasTV': 'True'}
categories: Restaurants, Chicken Wings, Fast Food
text:
I have to agree with Jai M. It is a chain, so the food is well known and when you get it, I have gotten exactly what I expected, no issues there. It is deep fried sin to the waistline.  The service however is just plain bad.  

I was just in there last night (Friday). I had to get my man cooties out of the house for a Mary Kay party...so off I went to get some fast food fried chicken. I was in no hurry, but my gosh.  I easily waited 10 minutes for items that are already cooked and just waiting to be served. I'm staring at it and I swear I saw at least one wing make a come hither gesture at me.

The crazy thing Friday night is there were plenty of people "working".  There was plenty of flurry and movement but no motion.  I am not sure if the worker quality is just bad or their layout/processes are broken. I do not plan to go back anytime soon.  If I want to wait for ready to go food staring back at me and get marginally rude customer service I'll go into shaky part of Belleville and get Church's.

name: AMC Edwardsville 12
categories: Arts & Entertainment, Cinema
text:
My first trip to the Edwardsville IMAX was this past weekend. I met a relative there to see a certain new film. I'd not been to an IMAX before other than the Science Center's Omnimax. It made for a nice viewing. The seats could have been a little bigger. 

It's a pretty standard AMC theatre. I don't know if I can describe it any better than that. Oh, the restrooms were rather classy, with a green marbled look. 

I doubt I'll return soon, as it's kind of in the middle of nowhere, but if you live out that way, it seems like a good option.

name: Jimmy John's
categories: Fast Food, Sandwiches, Restaurants, Food Delivery Services, Delis, Food
text: Our office orders delivery from this location all the time. They are always sending the correct orders and is usually in a timely manner. I rarely done-in, but today I did. It was loud and the atmosphere felt very rushed. I was standing in line to order and before the person in front of me could even put her stuff away the staff member was requesting my order. I refused to make the person in front of me rush, so I waited until she left to order which seemed to annoy the employee. All the staff was speaking loudly and were in constant motion behind the counter, all 10 of them. If you've ever been to a JJ, you know that's a small area. It wasn't a pleasant dining experience. I will not likely dine-in again, but I will definitely order for delivery.

name: Associated Pediatric Dentistry
categories: Pediatric Dentists, Health & Medical, Dentists
text: Clean and perfect place to bring the kids to their check ups.  Dr. Mello is a great dentist, she talks to the kids and parents with patience and knowledge. I highly recommend this place.

name: Jade Garden

categories: Chinese, Restaurants
text: I love this place, mostly because it's so close to my house. The food isn't the greatest, but certainly better than a lot of take-out Chinese I've had. I agree with a previous reviewer that the wait is always long. I live maybe 5 minutes away and it still takes 45 for me to get the food. I assume it's because they're making all my food fresh because it often burns my mouth on the first bite.

name: Colton's Steak House & Grill
