categories: Steakhouses, Restaurants, American (Traditional), Salad
text: We had the onion tanglers, loaded fries, chicken fingers and salads. Food was absolutely great! The sauces were bomb. Very reasonable prices. Service was wonderful! Jasmine was our waitress. She was fabulous!! Literally no complaints

name: Inspector Plumber
categories: Home Services, Plumbing, Kitchen & Bath, Shopping, Home & Garden, Contractors, Water Heater Installation/Repair
text:
Not as promised. Shoddy work. Couldn't even put a faucet on at the correct angle. Actual bill twice the estimate price with no detailed explanation. Poor communication between plumbers and the owner, who never inspected the work site to see what was going on. 
Go elsewhere- certainly not recommended if you're looking for craftsmanship. 
Failed job.

name: Taqueria Z
attributes: {'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'DogsAllowed': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsBitcoin': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
categories: Food Stands, Food, Restaurants, Mexican, Tacos, Street Vendors
text: I had been to Taqueria Z once before and had a couple tacos that were fairly good so I decided to go back.  The restaurant is small and only seats ~30 people (there is also an outdoor patio).  From the very limited chalkboard menu I ordered a  pineapple margarita and choriqueso (a chorizo, cheese & chips appetizer).  The bill totaled $16.18 which I thought was somewhat expensive for what I ordered.  I sat at a small table in the corner.  The tables/chairs were close together which didn't allow for a lot of personal space.  There were also cases of restaurant supplies stacked in the dining area further encroaching on the limited seating.  After a brief wait I received my food.  Not much for presentation but the food itself was flavorful.  The chorizo was spicy and greasy (just like it's supposed to be) with melted cheese on top.  The chips came in a grease-stained paperbag (I guess they were homemade???  I didn't see that mentioned anywhere.).  All in all, the food tasted good.  Just  don't expect much aesthetically.

name: Woody'z Pub & Grill
categories: Bars, Sports Bars, Restaurants, American (Traditional), Nightlife, American (New)
text: There was 5 of us & we all had the cod plate. Everybody said it was good & all left food on the plate. Meaning we were full of food.

name: First Watch

categories: Restaurants, Cafes, American (Traditional), Breakfast & Brunch
text: Not the Egg and I. Not the same restaurant, and definitely not the same level of service and quality. Quite a shame. The Egg and I was my favorite place around. 100% of the time we got great service, great food, and a great experience. This new place just doesn't measure up. I've been twice during off hours and peak. I sat and sat and sat, and no one came to say hi or take my order. The last time I just left. I probably will not be back. I really miss the old place. Damn shame. Real damn shame.

name: Stubborn German Brewing Company
categories: Breweries, Bars, Nightlife, Food, Pubs
text:
Located in the charming town square. I really liked this place!!!  The moment you walk in you are welcomed with the delicious aroma of yeast.  The place was packed. Found a cozy little corner for my friends and i could sit. Really good beer. Good service. I like that they allow you to bring your own snacks. Can't say enough about this place. Just a really great vibe. We definitely will go back!

Warning! Make sure you have a DD (designated driver) I counted 4 cops tucked away on our way back to St. Louis.

name: HouseMaster Home Inspections
categories: Real Estate, Home Inspectors, Home Services
text: Andrey went above and beyond his home Inspector duties in my Commercial Property inspection in Feb 2014. He is meticulous about his inspections and I would highly recommend him! Also a plus to know that HouseMaster is a veteran owned business! Well worth the investment! Thanks Andrey!

name: Happy Up
categories: Toy Stores, Hobby Shops, Shopping
text: Store was closed but the store owner was nice enough to open up and help us to what we needed! 3 more people came and she went out of her way to help everyone! Great location that has all your toy needs!

name: Studio Eleven
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '4', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'True', 'HairSpecializesIn': "{'straightperms': True, 'coloring': True, 'extensions': True, 'africanamerican': False, 'curly': True, 'kids': True, 'perms': True, 'asian': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsBitcoin': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'False', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'"}
categories: Beauty & Spas, Skin Care, Nail Salons, Hair Salons
text: Upscale salon. Massaging shampoo chairs! Separate room for mani/pedis, color bar, high quality products. I went in for a wash and blowout and decided to get my hair trimmed. The stylist was very professional. The salon is very quiet, not your typical noise filled salon. It was very pricey so I am unable to go every 6 weeks for a hair cut but if you want to treat yourself, you should make an appointment and enjoy.

name: Quality Inn & Conference Center
categories: Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Hotels & Travel
text: I was in town for a wedding and stayed 2 nights. The staff was very nice and helped me check in and out with ease. The breakfast was great with a good selection. The hotel it's self if very run down. The carpets need to be cleaned, the rooms need to be refreshed and the general upkeep needs to be addressed. The sign by the road doesn't work. My room smelled of smoke even tho the room said no smoking. The mattresses had stains in them. The bathroom was missing a heal bulb by the vent so you could see all the dust built up in the vent. Housekeeping moved some of my items when they came to clean and they didn't take my overflowing trash. This isn't the worst place I've stay but not that great either.

name: 111 Salvage
categories: Auto Parts & Supplies, Automotive, Local Services, Used Car Dealers, Junkyards, Car Buyers, Tires
text: I was removing a windshield that was ALREADY broken to access a dashboard and a long haired girl-looking dude (who smelt like feces) accused me of purposely breaking it (it was already broken as previously mentioned) and the h*ck trump supporter at the front desk charged me $32. Sad! I felt threatened by the man-child's presence when he pointed at his no-no square and asked me to touch it. I will be pressing charges.

name: Unkle Munkey's

categories: American (Traditional), Sandwiches, Arcades, Restaurants, Arts & Entertainment, Nightlife, Bars
text:
I've been here several times with friends and once for a P4P animal shelter fundraiser.  I give Unkle Monkey's two thumbs up!

I'd much rather go here for games than Edison's, and I'd much rather go here for a drink than the Main St bar scene.  This venue has a laid back 80's vibe with all of the classic arcade games, complete with PacMan, SkiBall, and a plethora of pinball machines!  Games are a quarter or two, and tickets can be saved up to earn a free drink from the bar or a menu item.  I store mine in a box at home (I'm not an avid SkiBaller, but figure I'll hang onto the tickets in case I save up enough for a free vodka soda)!

The staff are quite nice.  Their uniform consists of wearing a superhero/comic book themed t-shirt.  The full, U-shaped bar and tables are in the back.  The food is pretty good, too.  Both the sandwich combo I ordered on one trip and the giant Chop salad I ordered on a different trip were delicious!  They also have fun novelty drinks with video game themed names that are worth a try.  Kiddos have to be out by 9 pm - that's when the 17 and older kicks in and it's more of an adult scene.

name: Enterprise Rent-A-Car
categories: Car Rental, Hotels & Travel
text: Terrible experience I was in a car accident my insurance can use them I had to have the car longer than the insurance paid but I was fine with a called me every other day asking for a payment like I wasn't going to pay I paid it all very rude

name: Blue Agave
categories: Bars, Nightlife
text: Although billed as a tequila bar (and they have some excellent tequila!), the Blue Agave is probably better known as a beer establishment with 30 beers on tap and at least 70 more by the bottle.  Housed in an historic building in downtown Belleville, the Agave often sports free music and drink specials-- including Wednesday's "$2 you call it" and Thursday's $2 rails.  Part of the growing Belleville "strip," it's a must-stop pub if you like beer.  Specializing in craft beers on tap (not your typical Bud Light or Miller), the selection rotates periodically so that there's always something new.

name: Northgate Small Animal Hospital
categories: Pets, Veterinarians, Pet Services, Emergency Pet Hospital, Pet Groomers, Pet Cremation Services
text: Love Dr. Edgar!  I trust her & the staff with my dog.  Also, I think their prices are reasonable compared to other offices.  Highly recommend!!!!

name: Pope Animal Hospital
categories: Pets, Veterinarians
text: Convenient hours and reasonable cost.  Dr. Jones will see exotic animals and small mammals. She did a great job with diagnosing the issues with our Dwarf Robo hamster. She also spent a lot of time explaining what we need to do for ongoing care since medication options are very limited.

text: I don't know if the chef was just having an off night or what, but they just could not get the steak temperatures right. I asked for my steak to be medium well and my guest asked for medium. When the steaks came out, my guest's steak was well done and my steak was medium rare. We told our server and she apologized and took the steaks back to the kitchen to be fixed. When they came out the second time, my guest finally got their medium steak but my steak was very well done (it was actually a little burnt on the bottom). The server apologized again and took it back. Third time was the charm and they finally got my steak right.

text: Very oily!  I've eaten there twice.   I got sick both times.  There are better buffets in the area.

name: North Avenue Collective
categories: Used, Vintage & Consignment, Shopping, Home Decor, Home & Garden, Fashion, Women's Clothing
text: This store is beautiful!  Not moldy or stuffy like some vintage stores.  Everything is in excellent condition and lovely.  My friend and I found great dresses.  The woman helping us was very nice and cute.  I recommend checking it out and supporting Humboldt Park businesses!

text: The food here is the same as every year other Subway, but this one has a little bit extra. Flies buzzing around the food, gross. Also, the interior of the restaurant is dirty and I will never eat in a dirty restaurant. This place needs a makeover desperately and a deep cleaning. Employees are decent but no one's attitude can make up for what my eyes witnessed the 2 times I walked in there to order

name: The Home Depot
categories: Building Supplies, Hardware Stores, Shopping, Home Services, Home & Garden, Appliances, Nurseries & Gardening
text: After reading the first few reviews after being here I am surprised it got 3 star reviews because of the company's in china that make the stuff u buy that are missing nuts or bolts. That has nothing to do with the people there I was greeted when I walked I had a employee there ask me  what I needed help with I told him what I was looking for and he found it efficiently now I wasn't sure if it was a 100% what I needed so instead of him saying this is what we have!!! NAY S checked it out and found a phone number on the item I wanted and he called the company first hand for me and found out that it wasn't and saved me a headache of finding out the hard way when I got home then having to go back and return the item so he found me one that was and they had it!!! All I can say is the effort that he put in and the service I received from him was beyond excellent surprised he wasn't a supervisor to be honest he was the best help I received from any store or place I have ever met that's why I spent time to post a long comment all because of the effort he put in for me I really thankfully that I got to me a great person thank you!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

name: Sunrise Family Restaraunt
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'GoodForKids': 'True'}
categories: Breakfast & Brunch, Restaurants
text: Wanted to try some place new for breakfast on the weekend that didn't have a long wait, and Sunrise did not disappoint.  The service was so friendly and attentive and the food was large portioned and really good.  My coffee never went cold, and it was good too.  As another reviewer mentioned, the inside of this place is similar to a Denny's.  Ample seating, and no wait on a Sunday which was a huge plus being that the other "big 3" hot spots for breakfast all had long waits in the lobby for seating.  We called ahead before deciding where to go, and that is how we discovered Sunrise.

name: Shop N Save
categories: Grocery, Food
text: We come here for groceries because it is close to our home. Today while in the meat department I grabbed a pork roast and the packaging wasn't done properly and pulled my hand back covered in blood. When I turned and tried to find chicken breasts instead I saw a mouse run through an aisle and up into the rack of boxes of foods. I'm so disgusted and we won't be returning.

name: Jimmy John's
categories: Fast Food, Delis, Restaurants, Sandwiches
text: Good sandwiches though nothing to write home about.  Top notch service, food was almost done before paying!

name: Custom Sounds & Tint
categories: Car Stereo Installation, Auto Customization, Automotive, Car Window Tinting, Auto Glass Services
text: Made an appointment to have an install of an amp and subwoofer...explained that son home on leave from the Army for just the holidays.  They did a great job...everything turned out great!

name: Lily's Nails
categories: Nail Salons, Beauty & Spas
text: Got a mani pedi with French tips and my nails were done with the gel polish that is suppose to last for like 2 weeks so we will see. Staff was nice. Did a decent job on my nails...... not the greatest not the worst.  Cost was 48 for it all which didn't seem unreasonable.

name: AB & C Moving & Delivery
categories: Packing Supplies, Movers, Home Services, Shopping
text: Hired A B and C Moving to move my elderly mother's beloved piano to a senior residence.  Her piano tuner recommended A B and C because of their excellent reputation of taking special care during moves.  I could not be more pleased with the entire experience from start to finish!  Special thanks to Shirley who was a delight to work with on the phone.

name: Anderson Hospital ExpressCare Bethalto
categories: Medical Centers, Hospitals, Urgent Care, Health & Medical
text: You might as well visit the ER for the service that you get from this urgent care. I visited for hives that were quickly spreading after an unexpected allergic reaction. The employee who took my information kept getting my information wrong and complained the entire time. When I finally got through with that, the nurses that took my vitals rushed me through as if they were taking inventory and not asking a person for information about their ailment. When I finally saw the doctor, she talked to me for 2 minutes and then wouldn't prescribe anything - just that I should keep doing what I had started to do. I could deal with that but then there's the billing. After my insurance, they billed me over $400. $125 of that is for the doctor's 2 minutes. You would be better off going to the ER, at least then it might be worth the charges. I will never go there again.

name: Nothing Bundt Cakes
categories: Cupcakes, Food, Desserts, Bakeries
text: I can't say enough about the customer service from Aaron and his team. I ordered cakes for my daughters birthday and they accidentally left out part of my order. The problem was this wasn't realized until after they closed so they drove the rest of our order and more to our house so we would be ready for the party. It was the nicest gesture I'd ever received from a company. They made me feel like we were the most important customers they have and it was our first time there. And to top it off the cakes were incredible! I'd recommend them to everyone I know!

text: Usually buy wings elsewhere  it was told this place was right around corner. I decided to go there. Only got 15 wings and three were burnt and others were cook so hard they taste burnt. Will never again order from this place.

text:
Tacos are good and cheap and paired with a reasonably priced Margarita with salt on the glass - it's a good time!

The place is an average size for a dive bar but their different daily specials are pretty good. 

Hurricane's has been around since before my time and now has outdoor seating since you cannot smoke in bars in Illinois anymore.

name: Effinger Garden Center
categories: Home & Garden, Nurseries & Gardening, Shopping
text: Helpful staff, always have what I need, plants/flowers are always in great shape, family owned, in and out quickly. What more can I ask for? Well I guess I do ask a lot, but these guys never disappoint.

text:
What a find, thanks Yelp. It's so close to Scott AFB, right next to a motel. The place is off the beaten path so use the Yelp address and keep your eyes peeled. Old school decor/ family friendly/ Sinatra, Davis Jr and Dean Martin piped in over the speakers-we loved it!
We ordered Eggplant and Chicken Parm, a kids spaghetti, mushroom ravioli, bottle of wine and a pizza. The bill was around $70- what a deal! Huge portions. Very friendly service. Great with very young children. Definitely give it a shot.

name: TC's Treats
categories: Caterers, Event Planning & Services, Desserts, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Food, Shaved Ice
text: Always has great service and a lot of flavors to choose from! I recommend pina colada

name: Fringe Salon Hair Salon
categories: Hair Salons, Beauty & Spas
text: The staff were very friendly.  The hairstylist i had was Vanessa.  She did a really great job. She asked me how I wanted my hair cut but also made a few suggestions.  I have thick hair with some wavyness to it and I always wear it up but now I might be able to wear it down more.

name: Kruta Collinsville Bakery
categories: Restaurants, Bakeries, Food
text: The best bakery around. It's a shame that there aren't more establishments like this, but I suppose that's part of Kruta's magic.

name: Royal Gate Chrysler Dodge Jeep RAM of Columbia
categories: Car Dealers, Automotive, Auto Repair, Auto Parts & Supplies, Used Car Dealers
text: If I could give a ZERO I would. I called on a Monday to schedule my vehicle for a recall. Teri said she would call me back around 5 with a date & time....no call. I called Tuesday asked for a supervisor, I got a voicemail with no name, I left a message. I called Wednesday spoke with supervisor Nikki, she scheduled the appointment for Thursday at 8 am AFTER VERIFYING THE PART WAS THERE. Get to the dealership at 7:45, they said it would take a hour or a little more. I sit until 8:45 when they come on & tell me they don't have the part & it won't be in until 1. WHAT A JOKE! They gave me a rental (which they were suppose to do anyway due to it being a recall) which wasn't even comparable to my vehicle. The manager acted as if he didn't care all this while a bunch of employees standing around chatting about nothing. Oh yeah, I looked in the glove box and there is paperwork for 3 previous renters showing ALL their personal info, 1 from December 2 from February. Watch out if you do business with these people.

name: Mike's Pool & Spa Service
categories: Home & Garden, Shopping, Home Services, Pool & Hot Tub Service, Hot Tub & Pool
text:
The woman answering the phone is possibly the rudest person I've ever dealt with. I dreaded calling her. We scheduled a routine opening and they came out, took off the cover, and then told me they couldn't complete the process without the help of Mike himself. They left me with a swamp for a week before coming out to finish the job. I had to call three times because of no-shows and radio silence. He checked for leaks (the reason they couldn't open the pool) and said there were none.

Mike himself is nice enough, and knowledgeable. Honestly I would've just chalked this one up to them being busy, (why I called back) but when I recently called back to close the pool - the woman on the phone was so rude within the first two minutes, I hung up. I can't imagine a more miserable person being your point of contact with customers.

name: Best Buy Edwardsville
categories: Electronics, Shopping
text: Potential to be a great electronics retailer, but employees usually have a way to ruin it.  Had a sales person recommend one product one month and the following month tell me the exact opposite.  Don't lie to the customers, be truthful and helpful.

name: AAFES Scott AFB
categories: Shopping, Fashion, Department Stores
text: Honestly, I don't feel as though I save that much money by shopping here. When I go for a larger ticket item, like my MacBook Pro or iPod, I save the tax, but that's about it. Any other item you're probably going to spend less or equal to at Walmart or Target. Sorry BX, but Target is across the street from my apartment. Better luck with people who live on base.

name: Gamestop
categories: Mobile Phones, Books, Mags, Music & Video, Videos & Video Game Rental, Toy Stores, Video Game Stores, Shopping
text:
Pros: 
1. Conveniently located
2. My face-to-face encounter proves that the people working there are friendly and knowledgeable.

Cons: 
1. Prices are a bit high (this problem is not specific to this store but to the entire company).  For instance, Fable III used is only about $5-10 cheaper at GS than a brand new one at Target.  
2. They don't answer the phone.  I'll call when they first open and even 15 minutes after and even an hour answer and the phone rings ad nauseum.  

All in all, I like the people who work there as they're friendly.  However, when making a purchase decision, I won't use GS unless they're the only one who had an item in the region and when other factors don't matter.   Also, if you want to check if they have something without driving there to find out, you may be disappointed to learn that they don't always answer the phone during business hours.

name: Weber Chevrolet Granite City
categories: Tires, Car Dealers, Auto Repair, Automotive, Used Car Dealers
text: Well first off this is Granite City so you know it's bad quality. Plus this is a Chevy place. So basically this is a junkyard from 1983. I heard once that the same thing that happened in Maximum Overdrive happened here, but even more so. The cars used their tires as hands and started smoking joints through their tail pipes and pouring oil on themselves. I guess it was the munchies. If you want a bad, stoner truck this is your place to go!

name: Shangri-La

text:
Easily the best Hot Braised Chicken I've had anywhere. Portions were large too. The regular order of Hot Braised Chicken (C8 on the menu) would have been enough to feed two.

We recently moved into the area and this has just become our go-to Chinese place. Looking forward to our leftovers, as well as our next visit, which is sure to be soon!

name: Club Fitness - Collinsville
categories: Trainers, Yoga, Active Life, Gyms, Cycling Classes, Fitness & Instruction
text: I have been going here awhile and there are pros and cons. The good- the front desk staff and most fitness instructors are awesome! They greet you by name and really care about you getting a great workout. The negatives are the general condition of the building, the filthy group workout floor(which even though we have been asking them to resolve this for almost a YEAR now no-one seems to care!) Floor is NEVER cleaned PROPERLY there is human hair, huge dust balls, 2 items(a band aid and a dirt spot we dated Jan 2013 and still there). The floor was warping so they just ripped off that row and left the debris and construction crap there and never replaced it. With the flu in high swing I do not attend any weight class where I would have to touch or be on the floor since it is gross. More then a filthy dry mop is needed with germs, salty footprints,coffee spilled, and the major sweat puddles. This should be done DAILY! Also they advertise TV's on the machines well they have been missing many again for OVER A YEAR! They get ya but do not maintain the gym.

text: I have been coming here for years. And I have never had a bad experience. The staff is very friendly and they remember your name after multiple visits. I always get the club grilled and it has been amazing every time. One of the best sub places in the area. Try it east coast style.

name: Centerfield Park, Inc
categories: Mini Golf, Active Life
text: I had a horrible experience here before I could even walk through the door. One of the workers accused me and my friends of "doing suspicious activities" in the car since we were parked. In all reality we were trying to find the website of the park to see what time they not only closed but what activities were available. She parked her car directly behind my friends to block us in and kept screaming "WHAT ARE YOU DOING"! I highly doubt I'll come back here because clearly we were NOT welcome. She had an attitue when I told her the reason behind us still being inside the car. Spend your money somewhere else if at all possible, the treatment is not worth it.

name: America's Best Contacts & Eyeglasses
categories: Health & Medical, Shopping, Optometrists, Ophthalmologists, Doctors, Eyewear & Opticians
text: I was in need of some contacts pronto. They do take walk ins, and I was very grateful since I did not make an appointment. The tech greeted me and started me on my paperwork. The doctor was very professional. I was able to get some new contacts and ordered a new pair of glasses. The have some great packages for contacts and eyeglasses.

name: Jimmy John's
categories: Food, Food Delivery Services, Fast Food, Delis, Restaurants, Sandwiches
text: Typically a great experience, but tonight was the exact opposite. I called to explain that I didn't get avocado on two sandwiches that came with it and the response was"sorry, I didn't even realize that...have a good night." I'm honestly pissed off now.

name: h h  gregg
categories: Home & Garden, Computers, Electronics, Shopping, Appliances
text: They have absolute no idea what they're doing. Two weekends in a row now, I've been waiting for a delivery only to be told an appliance was suddenly not available on the day of delivery. They didn't even call me the first time; the delivery man just showed up with half my order and no explanation.

name: Jimmy John's
categories: Sandwiches, Delis, Restaurants
text: Freaky fast, freaky good, or at least that is what the radio comercial leads you to believe.  I'm sold on the freaky fast part as before I could request no onions and hot peppers on my Vito, the lady who was constructing my sandwich was nearly done.  On the freaky good part, I'm not nearly as sold.  The Vito is an Italian sandwich and it just didn't really stand out among other sub sandwich shops versions.  It was totally Meh, but I had a free coupon for the sandwich so I can't knock free food.  All in all, Jimmy John's is ok, but I will likely visit a different sub sandwich joint if I'm looking for an Italian sub.

name: St Clair Square
categories: Fashion, Department Stores, Shopping, Shopping Centers
text: Huge mall, probably the biggest and best mall on the Illinois side from Decatur down to Metropolis. There are two levels with all the essential stores inside. There are cool things for the kids, a food court and specialty stores sure to cure every shopping itch. It's always busy, so parking can be fun. But if you want to avoid crossing into STL, this is the place to shop.

name: Edwardsville YMCA

They offer more programs than imaginable at both locations, but I really love the rollerskating rink and I want to try the rockclimbing wall and indoor tennis courts at the Goshen Road location.

name: Walgreens
categories: Convenience Stores, Beauty & Spas, Food, Cosmetics & Beauty Supply, Photography Stores & Services, Drugstores, Shopping
text: The drive up pharmacy is the SLOWEST ever.   Have waited in line for approximately 15 minutes every time we stop.  Seriously thinking about going to another pharmacy.  The convenience of the drive through is not very convenient.  Do not recommend.

name: Tres Caminos Pontoon Beach
categories: Mexican, Desserts, Steakhouses, Restaurants, Tacos, Food, Seafood
text: Went with my family for dinner and a celebration!  Service was very good, even with lots of people there. The food came out quick and the presentation was very nice, not scrambled at all. Saw lots of big colorful drinks being brought outside where we sat. Salsa was not flavored very hot nor was it bland. I would prefer thinner chips but at least they didn't break when getting the salsa. I will definitely go back.

name: El Macho Taco
categories: Mexican, Tacos, Salad, Restaurants
text: My first time eating here, we got carry out because of covid restrictions.  I've tried only one other mexican place that even comes close to this restaurant.  Top notch service, flavor, and portions.  I can't wait to come and dine in once were allowed.  I'm certainly ordering again!  HIGHLY recommend!

name: CrossFit Edwardsville
categories: Interval Training Gyms, Trainers, Active Life, Fitness & Instruction, Gyms
text:
I started working in the Metro East in April of this year. I wanted to really start working on getting myself fit again, physically and mentally. To be honest though I was scared, I had not been in a gym to workout for over 20 years. I was trying to workout at home but I would lose a few pounds and gain it right back, I wasn't getting any stronger either. So I started reading reviews about local gyms and CFE kept popping up as the best around. Still I kept procrastinating. Then I had a chance meeting with one of the owners. We talked about the gym and she told me how to sign up for a free class to try it out. I did my free class, then did some interviews with the owners. I shared my short and long term goals with them. Coach G encouraged me to join the 6 week challenge program they have. It was perfect for me. I had to put some skin in the game with this program. In 6 weeks I lost 18 lbs and 7.5" from around my waist. I've gained confidence, every day tasks have become easier, I'm more flexible, I'm stronger, and I'm just generally happier.  It's not easy but it is simple. Just follow the program and show up consistently.

The best thing about CFE though is the staff and the other athletes. It really is community, that isn't something they just say. I was so worried I would be in the way of the "in shape" people, no one has ever made me feel that way though. The coaches are always there to give you knowledge, or praise, or a push when you need it. Joining the community at CFE was a great decision!!!

name: Troy Family Dental
categories: Cosmetic Dentists, Dentists, Endodontists, Pediatric Dentists, Health & Medical, General Dentistry
text: Dr boatman and his staff are the best. I have found the best dentist for my family and I. We will never go anywhere else.  The staff at his office are always very kind, friendly, helpful, and all around good people.

name: Jacobsmeyer's Tavern
attributes: {'NoiseLevel': "u'loud'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True'}
categories: American (Traditional), Restaurants
text:
I went to Jacobsmeyer's Tavern tonight with some friends. Out in Granite City, IL. What was I doing all the way out here? The world may never know. 

Anyway, we walked in, and it was a pretty hopping place! Lots and lots of 20-somethings there getting their drink (and eat!) on. Many attractive guys. I was a happy girl. 

Anyway, I ordered a Blue Moon (on draft -- delicious!) and...a fried bologna sandwich. Oh yeah. Don't knock it till you've tried it -- I used to LOVE this when I was a kid, so when I saw it on the menu, I just KNEW I had to have it. Only in Granite City, baby...only in Granite City. 

It was served with a side of fries and came out pretty quickly. The bread was toasted, and the bologna -- all three THICK slices of it -- was piled on, along with a healthy slathering of pepperjack cheese sauce. Health food this was NOT, folks! 

The sandwich was rich. Delicious, but I could only down about a third of it before my tummy cried for mercy. I loved every greasy bite that I did consume. 

Best part of the whole thing? It was CHEAP! The sandwich, along with a healthy serving of fries, was less than 6 bucks. 

Only in Granite City, baby...only in Granite City.

name: Rothman Furniture & Mattress
categories: Furniture Stores, Home & Garden, Shopping, Mattresses
text:
Very pleased! Probably one of the best experiences from start to finish I have had with a furniture company. 

LOVED our salesperson Pamela - we started chatting about our kids and husband's as we were waiting for the manager to get me a better price on a dresser I wanted for my 3 year old son. She got the price lowered for me twice which was Greatly appreciated because I was very happy with the final price. Then she had the guys measure my car trunk to see if I could take away that day and avoid delivery and sure enough it fit! The guys wrapped the dresser and mirror and loaded it in my car with no issues. I did have to get two other things delivered a mirror for my daughter and a table and they had delivery setup within the week which I was very happy about!

The delivery guys were great! There were 4 of them to setup a table and mirror which made me very happy because the process was very quick! They told me I may want to consider buying felt pads for the bottom of the chairs and table legs because they noticed the table and chairs slid a little with the plastic ones on my wood floor. They showed me and explained the care for the furniture and the warranty. Took a picture of the finished table setup and had me sign and left. I honestly couldn't be happier! The guys were clean and friendly and I felt safe with them in my home. 

I do not write reviews often but after the horrible experience I had at Ashley furniture this was worth sharing a good experience.

name: Club Fitness - East Alton
categories: Active Life, Trainers, Fitness & Instruction, Cardio Classes, Gyms
text: Been coming to this location for nearly 10 years. The building is starting to get run down a bit and the TV's don't work so good. The staff is always helpful and super friendly. The one thing that has me thinking i need to go to another competitor is the bathroom layout. They don't have a changing room. They rely on three restrooms for changing,showering,and other bathroom needs. So, that being said you spend a lot of wasted time standing around the the lock doors with other members waiting for a restroom to free up. I would rather spend this time working out or home with family. Hope, they would try to fix this issue soon. I have gave this feed back in all of the surveys they send out by e-mail.

name: Shear Sherrie
categories: Beauty & Spas, Hair Salons
text: Sherrie is absolutely AMAZING!! I had the pleasure of her doing my makeup for a wedding and it was like having an actual Snapchat filter on IRL! She does such, such amazing work!!

name: Creekwood Animal Hospital
categories: Pet Services, Hospitals, Health & Medical, Pets, Veterinarians
text: Drs. Allen and Jeff are passionate about their work. The office is nothing fancy, but its clean and sufficient. They treat you and your pets like family.  We like that they explain options and whenever possible try to save you money by trying easy fixes before running all sorts of expensive tests.

name: Target
categories: Fashion, Furniture Stores, Shopping, Home & Garden, Department Stores, Food, Grocery, Electronics
text:
Target is probably one of my go to and favorite department stores although I was a bit disappointed walking into this location. Don't get me wrong the employees appear nice and helpful but it seemed a bit outdated and the layout was not my favorite. I think the part that bothered me the most was the $1-$3 section is normally where  I buy random goodies that I never intended to buy but they are always presented so nicely that I just gotta' have it but not at this location. It is small and normally cluttered that I tend to avoid it. 
Overall it is Target (and not Walmart), I like their products and will continue to shop here.

name: Auto Spa
categories: Car Wash, Oil Change Stations, Automotive
text:
First and foremost, I have been a loyal customer and spent thousands and thousands of dollars at both Auto Spa locations within the past 10+ years! I would always buy their gift cards because they always had a buy 4 get 1 wash free. Every time I go get a wash, if I didn't have one of my gift cards, I would purchase a new one because like I stated before, I've been getting my car washed here since forever!! They had renovated this location within the past few months. I decided to go get a wash on 7/6/18 and the kid that was at the machine said I was no longer able to use my gift card starting the beginning of July. Well it was 7/6/18 and it was still the beginning of July. I asked to speak to the manager and he told me that they weren't able to use the gift card anymore because they got rid of the machines. Well you're still able to look up online that there is still credit. He kept on telling me that there's no way they know there's money on it because they got rid of the machine and that they have told people they had 6 months to use it when they renovated. First off, it hasn't been 6 months since the completion of their renovation. Second of all, again I told him they are able to look it up. If I'm able to look it up online, he can too. Also, I get my car washed a few times a month and was never told this! By law, gift cards no longer have an expiration date That's the law!

This was my place to go for car washes. I've recommend so many people to this place and now I will tell them to go elsewhere. I've never had an issue with this place until 7/6/18. They pretty much scammed me and I'm sure they did this to many other people too that still have their gift cards!

name: Tinder Box
categories: Tobacco Shops, Shopping, Head Shops
text: I have no clue what I am doing when it comes to cigars, pipes, etc. I had three different gifts to buy though and the two gentlemen working tonight were very helpful. The prices seemed reasonable too. I will be back!

name: The Abbey Espresso Bar and Café
attributes: {'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': True, 'breakfast': True}", 'HasTV': 'True'}
categories: Restaurants, Cafes, Arts & Entertainment, Coffee & Tea, Food
text: This seem like a very nice place to get an Americano. It has a very roomy interior with lots of seating and what looks like to be a stage. I went there hoping to find bags of coffee after reading reviews of how good their coffee was. The only reason this is a four-star review is because they do not have coffee to buy in bags. There were however small tins of tea that you could purchase

name: Saigon
attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'quiet'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'beer_and_wine'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'Ambience': "{u'divey': None, u'hipster': False, u'casual': True, u'touristy': None, u'trendy': None, u'intimate': None, u'romantic': False, u'classy': None, u'upscale': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{u'breakfast': None, u'brunch': None, u'lunch': True, u'dinner': True, u'latenight': None, u'dessert': False}"}
categories: Specialty Food, Imported Food, Chinese, Restaurants, Vietnamese, Ethnic Food, Food
text: Tried this place for the first time.  The PHO was great.  Everyone loved the food.  Will definitely return!

name: Sheridan's Frozen Custard
categories: Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Food
text: So I'm not a fan of custard, never even heard of it until I moved here. I much prefer the creamy ice cream, but if you must custard I like this the best. It is pretty good. They have generous portions and they go all out with the toppings, you get some in each bite which is great. Plus they're Super friendly.

name: Rally's
attributes: {'WiFi': "u'no'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': True, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True'}
categories: Burgers, Restaurants, Fast Food
text:
Don't do it.  I was just here, and I was not greeted by cashier, then she asked me to move to the front of the building since the order was taking a bit to be done.  Ok, no big deal.  I pulled around the front, only to have another employee point me to the other window.  I realize this is a Rally's, and the window to which he directed me was the other drive-thru window.  I followed his awkward pointing to pull forward to this window, knowing this was not the correct direction.  I was at the window for approximately two minutes, when another employee, whom I had not interacted, so she had nothing to do with the order, yelled and said, "I am right here!"  I thought maybe she had the food for me to pick up, but no, she yelled at me. She said I was parked in the wrong direction, which I knew.  I told her that another employee had directed me to park this way.  She then said something to the effect of, 'That's why they ain't paying you no attention!!'  
     Thirty seconds later, the employee who had directed me to the window handed me the food.  He was the only employee who that smiled, said hello, thank you, and even told me to have a blessed day.  I could've done with the smile only at that point.  Avoid this Rally's.

name: Luna Cafe
categories: Restaurants, Cafes
text:
This is listed as being in Granite City, but I think it's actually in Mitchell, but whatever.

This place opened in 1924 & has a rather colorful history.  Al Capone has been here.  You can still gamble a bit, as there are a few electronic-style slots.  Don't know about the ladies of the evening though, as this place was mostly filled with dudes who appear to be repeat customers.  In the "olden days" the cherry on the top of the neon sign would be lit to indicate that the gals were there.  

4 beers set us back less than $10, chatting with the attorney/insurance salesman/part bar owner was priceless.

We were highly encouraged to return for 9pm-2am (Fridays) Karaoke but we opted for a drive-in movie instead.  It was a tough choice.

Highly recommended but be prepared for stares.  They all know if you're new.

name: Primo's Italian Garage & Catering
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'None', 'HasTV': 'True'}
categories: Italian, Restaurants
text: We've eaten here twice.  The first time was ok but didn't love the pasta con broccoli.  Today's experience was terrible.  Admittedly, we didn't know they had some $1 pasta deal going on that people were losing their minds about BUT when you offer a deal like that you increase staffing.  We had an order for delivery and got confirmation that it would arrive around 6:49.  At 7:10 it still hadn't arrived.  When I called in they clearly were clueless.  It turns out that they never even made my order.   So the kid offered to personally deliver my order.  As nice as that was given they were short staffed I didn't think that was necessary and instead said I'd come in for pick up.  I had to insist that they make my order urgent and he said he'd try to have it ready in 20 minutes.  I receive a call from my friend while I was on the road to pick up my order that they were calling my name for my order was ready.  When I got there they didn't have it all ready.  My apology was two pieces of chocolate cake.  That was yummy the rest of the food was ok.  Ironically, I am typing this at 8:47 I just got a text saying my order is ready.  Insert eye roll.  Maybe they'll deliver it in an hour.

name: Rock Springs Park
categories: Parks, Active Life, Kids Activities, Community Centers, Public Services & Government
text: Excellent park!  Nice playground, large dog play area and extensive (paved) walking trails that are immaculately maintained.

name: Hendrickson Hair salon
categories: Massage, Nail Salons, Beauty & Spas, Hair Salons
text: Melodie did a really great job with my curly hair. The girl is awesome. She's funny and cool, got me in and out quickly (because I wanted her to, not because she was rushing) and I'm literally thrilled that I stumbled across some reviews that led me to her. Whew.

name: Denny's
attributes: {'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Caters': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': None, 'street': None, 'validated': None, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{u'breakfast': True, u'brunch': True, u'lunch': True, u'dinner': None, u'latenight': True, u'dessert': None}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'Ambience': "{u'divey': False, u'hipster': False, u'casual': True, u'touristy': False, u'trendy': None, u'intimate': False, u'romantic': False, u'classy': False, u'upscale': False}"}
categories: Breakfast & Brunch, Diners, American (Traditional), Restaurants
text: As far as Denny's go, this one is the best it gets. Chefs and staff are always quick and it's always been clean when we're there, including in the bathrooms. Recently what I had wanted was sold out, so I ordered something similar but did not like it. The manager let us order something else instead, which I thought was so nice.

name: Batteries Plus Bulbs
categories: Electronics, Electronics Repair, Mobile Phone Repair, Home Services, Shopping, IT Services & Computer Repair, Battery Stores, Local Services, Lighting Fixtures & Equipment
text: Came in without my receipt and they replaced my failing car battery, no questions asked, after about 18 months. I was ready to throw down and argue with the guy and he said, "Ok just sign here and we'll install your battery for you, for free" WTF??? It's crappy that I'm so used to being screwed over by other places that I'm surprised by good service.

name: Bollmeier Dental
categories: General Dentistry, Health & Medical, Dentists, Prosthodontists
text: Best dentists ever!  Such a clean building, great waiting room even though I didn't have to wait for my appointment.  Very quick.  Very friendly.  I would never go to any other dentist!

name: Nanny Lou's Kitchen
attributes: {'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'DogsAllowed': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Caters': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsBitcoin': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True'}
categories: Coffee & Tea, Restaurants, Soup, Salad, Delis, Sandwiches, Food, Breakfast & Brunch
text: Very good food.  This is a good place to go for breakfast or lunch.  They have biscuit sandwiches in the morning and cinnamon rolls and good coffee.  They also have a selection of sandwiches and salads for lunch.  Good selection of fountain beverages and they also sell dessert items (one feature today was Watermelon Cake).  Once upon a time this was the location of The Pour Haus, a local bar.  Nanny Lou's has been completely renovated inside and out with plenty of parking in front or in the lot in back (there's a rear entrance) -- so don't think of this as a hole in the wall.   I had the Cobb Salad and a large fountain soft drink and watched the cars drive by on West Main.  My wife had the Pecan Chicken Salad on Croissant.  We finished off with an ice cream sandwich and a Drumstick.  They also had large cinnamon rolls available, but my conscience dictated my capacity today.  I added the rolls to my "must try" list.  These local restaurants deserve your support.

name: Dollar Tree
categories: Discount Store, Shopping
text:
This place is usually pretty messy and i wouldn't recommend even considering that they will have helium, 9 out of 10 times they will be out of it.  So all those cute balloons you see, unless you plan to blow them up yourself i would check first.  They do have a great selection of ziploc and alluminum foil type stuff.  They have a great assortment of gift bags, wrapping paper and cards.  I mean if your looking to save a crap ton of money i would def come here all the time.

I prefer the dollar tree in belleville next to target, it has better stuff and is much cleaner with more isle room.

name: Dillard's
categories: Children's Clothing, Shopping, Women's Clothing, Men's Clothing, Department Stores, Fashion
text:
Return policy is lousy.  These guys are competing against Target, Wal mart, and especially Amazon. 

They are still operating on the old business plan. They beat me out of $40. I hope they get good use out of it because it's the last money they will get out of me.

name: Faller Photography Group
categories: Event Planning & Services, Photographers
text: Heartbreaking. This man has the only professional pictures of our sons first year. We purchased a package deal at Anderson hospital in early 2013. The package includes sittings for 3, 6,9, & 12 mo and a collage including a portrait from each sitting. Once a little longer than a few weeks past, after sitting down with the owner himself and deciding on what we were ordering,  we tried contacting them. Their voicemail box is full. No replies to the numerous emails I've sent. Last but not least, the for sale sign. No pictures. Just heartbreak.

name: Banfield Pet Hospital
categories: Pets, Veterinarians
text: Genuinely, the nicest and caring staff we've ever met. The took care of our first puppy Ronin as if he was their own. Unfortunately his ailments caused us to be quite frequent customers, each time they would greet him and make sure he was taken cared of, all the way to his untimely passing, which they made it easy for us to deal with.  Now that we have our new puppy Odin, he is given the same love and care from the staff. I cannot thank them enough for there service to our little ones.

name: Bark Avenue
categories: Pet Sitting, Pet Services, Pets
text: This place is terrible. Took my mom's standard poodle and Shitzu here. First of all, we were quoted one thing over the phone, and then charged much more than that upon picking up the dogs. I wouldn't have minded being charged more, had the service warranted it, but it most certainly did not. The owner was rude, unprofessional, and poor at grooming. Dogs were dropped off before 9am, and we had to call several times asking if they were done. She told me around 2pm that she had not even started yet, then finally called after 4pm and simply said "the dogs are done". Upon picking them up, the poodle appeared as though she had not even been bathed, she had a shaved the front part of the top knot on her head, the tail pom was almost completely shaved off, and she left all kinds of fur between the toes of the paw that should have been clipped. It looked absurd. Any experienced groomer should know that's not what a groomed poodle looks like. I could have done a better job myself, plus my dog would have at least been clean. Very disappointed with this place and I've been telling everyone I know not to patronize this "groomer".

name: Country Pride Truckstop Restaurant

text: When your more worried about chatting up with employees the TWO times we been here instead of checking up on customers your not very good at customer service!!! The coffee is WAY over priced and thus morning the biscuits were old... yuck!!! Breakfast bar is over priced for the sub par food your getting. Will not eat at this one again. Horrible customer service is what I hate most. Oh and I hate getting the check before I've even got my food!!!

name: Shop N Save
categories: Food, Grocery
text: Drew and Nathan are awesome! I've been coming here for years because it's convenient! ( However I do wish they had dairy-free ranch and sour cream) anyway always love stopping in.

name: China Star
categories: Restaurants, Chinese
text: I got the Hunan Pork w/chix fried rice and eggroll. Fried rice was very good which is a surprise from most Chinese restaurants like this. Hunan pork was good too. Ordered late, about 8:45 pm and was hot and fresh. Eggroll was mediocre.

text: Went there for lunch for a first time.  Ordered the Chicken Nachos appetizer.   Wow the amount you get could feed 4 people generously.  They could use more staff but the food was amazing.

name: Alex's Pizza

text: Some of the best pizza I've had in the area.  Ordered the Veggie Pizza and it was fabulous, everything was fresh and crisp, great sauce! Also had a pepperoni and Italian sausage and it rocked.  Alex's puts the other pizza joints to shame! Support a small business--go local. This is a pizza you won't regret!

name: Asia Garden

categories: Chinese, Japanese, Asian Fusion, Restaurants
text: Brought my family of six here on a Saturday evening.  The atmosphere is nice enough for date night but not too stuffy for the kids.  The staff was friendly and efficient.  We ordered Chinese, sushi, and sashimi.  Everything was very good.  Not too salty, which can be a problem with Chinese food.  My only complaint is that our food was lukewarm.  Definitely could have been hotter.  The sushi and sashimi were wonderful....fresh and tasty.  We will definitely be back.

name: Castelli's Restaurant at 255

text: Loved it and I'm coming back soon , our table ordered fried shrimp  chicken  salads and of course hot fresh bread. The house salad is delicious

name: International Oriental Food Market
categories: International Grocery, Grocery, Food
text: Excellent selection and very friendly owner.  She gave my daughters free oriental candies and was very helpful.  Pleasure to do business with.

name: Natur-al-Nail
categories: Local Services, Beauty & Spas, Education, Community Service/Non-Profit, Tutoring Centers, Specialty Schools, Hair Salons, Nail Technicians, Nail Salons
text: Best manicure I've received! The owner was able to set an appointment for same day that I called. Being an American salon that's not always able to happen. The owner did both my sister and my nails. She was super knowledgable and taught us how to probably form our nails, strengthen them, grow them out, maintain, and how to make our gel last longer. We were told if our nails chipped they would fix them for free. She even offered to paint my 3 year olds nails (she had been whining to get hers done), although another customer was waiting. If you want a proper place to get your nails done, make it here.  Just call ahead a couple days to make an appointment so you aren't disappointed when you can't get in that day. She's been in business around 25 years!

name: Decaro's
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'Ambience': "{u'divey': None, u'hipster': None, u'casual': None, u'touristy': False, u'trendy': False, u'intimate': False, u'romantic': None, u'classy': None, u'upscale': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True'}
categories: Restaurants, Pizza, Italian
text: The restaurant was fairly new, having just open this past January. The restaurant was clean and was recently remodeled. The service was quick and friendly. We ordered the cheesy garlic bread as an appetizer which came with marinara sauce. It was okay but not anything exceptional. The Shining Star was the pasta. I had the bacon mushroom alfredo while my boyfriend had the pesto penne. We both loved our meals. The waitress recommend we tried the pizza on our next visit as this was a popular dish. If you are in the area I would definitely try this restaurant. Plus the prices were very reasonable.

name: Ark Animal Hospital
categories: Pets, Veterinarians
text: Dr. Smith, Dr. Stahlheber, and their entire staff are so amazing! There is no one more I would trust with my pup! The staff makes scheduling a piece of cake, the techs are incredibly loving, thoughtful, and helpful, and the vets are top notch. I trusted Yelp recommendations when choosing a vet for Hank, and I couldn't be happier with the result. I seriously love Ark Animal Hospital and how they take care of my baby, and I will gladly recommend their services to anyone who will listen! Top notch!

name: Ross Dress For Less
categories: Fashion, Men's Clothing, Shopping, Home Decor, Department Stores, Discount Store, Women's Clothing, Home & Garden
text: I love Ross for all of the items they have at a lower price than its competitors. But the past two times I've been to this location, there has only been one cashier and the line goes all the way back to the aisles. It has taken about 10-15 mintues to get through the line before. I've also noticed multiple employees standing or walking around that could be called up to the front as back up cashieers. I wouldn't reccomend going here if you're in a hurry or on a schedule.

name: Seafood By Crushed Velvet
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'HasTV': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': True, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'WiFi': "u'no'"}
categories: Restaurants, Seafood, Food, Specialty Food, Caterers, Event Planning & Services
text: This place is yum! all food seems to be delish! i had the Under The Sea platter which consists of a lobster tail, shrimp, crab legs, corn, egg, potatoes, and some sausage. i also had some slightly spicy gumbo and a taste of my friends crab cakes. There were unlimited refills on soda. The staff was superb and very friendly. wish they had their liquor license but dont worry its coming!!! Definitely will go again!

name: Kellerman Dental
categories: General Dentistry, Sleep Specialists, Health & Medical, Cosmetic Dentists, Dentists
text:
The service I received  at Kellerman dental clinic was the best I've ever been treated at a medical or dental appointment in my entire life!  They go out of their way to be friendly and make you feel welcome and special!  

Not that it's second fiddle, but the dental care itself was outstanding!  Dr. Kellerman is thorough and adept at his craft.  Their facility is state of the art. It's hard to explain, but due to Dr. Kellerman's  personable way and the entire atmosphere, It was the best dental experience I've ever had, and I've lived in over 15 different cities. So I've seen all kinds of clinics as I have moved frequently.  

If you are looking for a new dentist, I couldn't recommend this place enough!!

name: Neal's Plumbing
categories: Home Services, Plumbing, Water Heater Installation/Repair
text: Neal's is great!  They came out on a Saturday and fixed a bent gasket that was causing a leak. He was very professional and explained everything thoroughly. Would definitely hire them again!

name: Grimm & Gorly Flowers & Gifts
categories: Food, Shopping, Cupcakes, Florists, Flowers & Gifts, Coffee & Tea
text: This place is wonderful! They now have a coffee/cupcake shop it is great. The floral arrangements are amazing and for what you get, I'd say quite cost effective. The service was very accommodating and I have nothing but great things to say about this business.

name: Hardee's
attributes: {'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
categories: Restaurants, Burgers, Fast Food
text:
2/3's of the way to work from my house sits a Hardees & Red Burrito restaurant. It is located on Route 3, close to the 270 interchange. 
It's a weird little area of Granite City, but I over look that and just get my morning needs filled. 

Since working in IL, I have only stopped here three times for a morning coffee and some type of breakfast biscuit. This morning when I checked in I was named Duke, with no fanfare. The workers went about with their morning duties as if I didn't exist. Finally someone spoke up and said, "we'll be with you soon, Sir". At least I got the respect of being called, Sir. I admit I arrived right as the doors were being opened, (5AM) but stop the morning busy work and give me my coffee. That sounded a little bitchy, sorry about that. 

All I've ever gotten here is coffee, a sausage or steak biscuit and today I went totally crazy and had a small order of hash browns. It's typical fast food breakfast and beats stopping at the QT closer to work. It fills the morning void in my stomach and makes me whole again. 

The staff is pleasant, considering it is not even dawn when I visit.  Kinda weird being Duke of a place your not totally excited about, but I'm glad it fills my morning needs when it's required.

text: Station is out of gas but they can't bother to put up signs or tell people trying to gas up. Waste of my time!!

name: St. Elizabeth's Hospital
categories: Orthopedists, Doctors, Health & Medical, Hospitals, Medical Centers, Home Health Care
text: On Dec. 23rd my dad Martin Loftus passed away after a long bout with lung cancer. He was in the hospital less than 4 days on the 4th floor. I have never experienced such wonderful care!! He was able to leave this world in peace and in comfort. A very special thank you to Kelly his breathing specialist and to Corey his nurse. These two care givers went above and beyond in making my dad comfortable and be there for us, his family through this difficult time. Much appreciation and admiration to the entire staff on the 4th floor , to dietary and nurses in the ER!!!!

name: Oz Night Club
attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'NoiseLevel': "u'very_loud'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': True, 'casual': False}", 'Music': "{u'dj': True, u'live': False, u'jukebox': False, u'video': False, u'background_music': False, u'karaoke': None, u'no_music': False}"}
categories: Dance Clubs, Nightlife
text:
The Oz accomplishes what it sets out to be: a decent fun time when the bars on the west side of the river close. The crowd is mixed, the music is a blend, and it's just generally somewhere fun to go. They have adequete security and do not put up with "East Boogie" foolishness; I've never felt unsafe there. 

The Emerald Room (their VIP area) is (usually) worth the extra $. They have top-notch DJs and are open later. The Emerald crowd is a bit older as well. The room has a more upscale feel and if I as taking a date to Oz, I'd go here rather than the general club area.

I've been to the Oz many times and while not always a "great" time, it's at least interesting people-watching.

name: Way of Lights
categories: Festivals, Religious Organizations, Arts & Entertainment
text:
I've heard about this Christmas light show for years and we finally drove over to check it out this weekend.  Took about 45 minutes to get into from the road, which we expected.  Once inside, it was disappointing to say the least.  Aside from the light tunnel at the beginning, it is a relatively sparse set up compared to places like Tilles Park off McKnight (the best I have been to in St. Louis for Christmas light shows).  

The other disappointing thing was that it took forever to drive through.  Probably 45 minutes to an hour.  Way too long, especially considering the show was so average.  

A bonus was that it was donation only, which we were happy to support.  Would not go back, however.  If you live on the Missouri side, save your gas and go to Tilles Park.

name: McDonald's
categories: Coffee & Tea, Food, Fast Food, Restaurants, Burgers
text: This place has a messed up parking lot but inside is cool, very trendy actually. It was all McDonald's but they have Fox news on the tv. Not good, I'll drive to the next one.

name: Running Start
categories: Shopping, Sports Wear, Fashion, Sporting Goods, Shoe Stores
text: Not overly impressive compared to some of the running specialty stores you see in New York City, but better than Dick's, or any other mainstream sporting good stores. Cute little store but not for the experienced runner. The prices were so-so on some items and expensive on others.  Listening to the heavyset employee offer analyzed recommendations to a younger female runner, I didn't really feel she knew what he was talking about.  Not once did he use the word pronation, and was putting the wrong shoes on her based upon what she said she was looking for.

name: T-K-Nails
categories: Nail Salons, Beauty & Spas
text: needed to relax so getting my nails done sounded like a good start.  spent extra to have gel done so they would last longer, but I felt like the girl rushed.  after only 6 days they started to lift and are very uneven. I wouldn't suggest this place to anyone.

name: JFires' Market Bistro

name: Quest Diagnostics
categories: Health & Medical, Laboratory Testing, Diagnostic Services
text: I recently needed blood testing and the doctors office sent me to quest n ginger creek so i called up there to see what all. This entailed.... I was sent on a wild computer maze of h ow to avoid talking to your customers.....I talked w at least 3 different phone answering computers of which no option was ever given to me to talk w a human being.....the last system actually said I know u want to talk w someone but that is not an option...I'm not making that up....my comment is..... If u r not. Smart enough to hire someone to answer your phones and talk to your customers as human beings then y should I give u my business....I work hard for my money and if this branch or co. Is that cheap or stupid not to realize that customers want to talk w humans than we should all send them a message and put them out of business by sending our business somewhere else....I'd rather drive an hour to talk w a human and be treated like one than deal w the shear incompetance of a place like this..... Just my opinion....

name: Rural King
categories: Home & Garden, Shopping, Hardware Stores, Pets, Home Services, Pet Stores, Farming Equipment, Building Supplies
text: The store it's self is fine besides the aisles always being blocked the gun department is my problem way to small and the staff that is usually there drive me nuts one is ALWAYS on the phone and doesn't know jack shit about guns which is whatever get in where you can fit but get off the damn phone, the other is older man who has either no sense of time or just plain doest give a shit carries on way to long of conversations about nothing while left your standing there, if there's a crowd you might as well just grab a chair and clear your schedule, Ive had to walk out on more than occasion I was really thrilled when they got the gun department but they've really let me down

name: Stars and Strikes Bowling Center
categories: Active Life, Bowling
text:
This is for their bowling alley snack bar.
Menu very simple. 
Burger, chicken sandwich and I think a turkey sandwich.
Fries, Tater tots, or side salad.
That it.
I suppose this is what the younger folks want.
I find. A chicken and fry and coke along with a burger, tots and coke is almost$20 dollars. It all just frozen store bought food.
Perhaps if they lowered the price I would not be so hard on them.
Anyways I think the Air Force could do better for the base people. Visited on a Saturday. Food place only I customer. 
Bowling alley was pretty crowded. I wonder why the bowlers were not eating. Now I know.

name: Auto Spa
categories: Automotive, Car Wash
text: My favorite car wash place to say the least. I've been getting my car washed here for years, and even after moving I continue to to do so. For what you pay at a gas station car wash, you can get here for the same price. But they hand dry your car. Customer service is pretty good, and I've only left is happy on a couple of occasions. They are open pratically all year round, even with super high/low temperatures. Make sure you bring cash because they do take tips.

This will give you the stomach ache of a lifetime and probably clog all your arteries... STAY AWAY!!!!!  smells unsanitary and the floors are slimy... Clean it up...

name: Enterprise Rent-A-Car
categories: Car Rental, Hotels & Travel
text: I have accessed Enterprise Rental many times in Alton, Illinois as well as twice now in Charles Town, West Virginia. I've never been anything less than completely satisfied--with the vehicle and with the service. They have never left me disappointed.

name: Papa Mendi's Grill and Bar
categories: Restaurants, Greek
text: Stopped for breakfast on the way by.  Staff was very friendly, helpful and attentive.  The food is standard diner food - nothing to rave about.  If you want "clean" food this is not the place.  Non-dairy creamer and non-dairy whipped stuff for condiments.  Over easy egg was hard cooked and grits were dry.  No fruit or veggies to substitute for bread or potatoes.  I guess it's all a matter of whether you care about food quality.  We probably won't be back.

name: Cost Plus World Market
categories: Grocery, Furniture Stores, Food, Shopping, Beer, Wine & Spirits, Home & Garden, Home Decor
text: They're pricey, but they are a specialty store. I usually only go there for ethnic groceries. They have a much larger selection than the grocery stores, and you'd need to go to an actual ethnic grocery store to find anything better. Browsing around, you'll always find something unique that you'll want on impulse.

name: 1 Nails
categories: Beauty & Spas, Nail Salons
text: Went in for a full Set. The nail technician dug her finger nail into the side of my finger so hard that it drew blood. She never said a word, yet there was blood running down my finger. She then got the drill and ripped skin off another finger and drew blood again without even saying sorry. My nails look absolutely awful. DO NOT go here!!!!

name: Lowe's Home Improvement
categories: Appliances, Nurseries & Gardening, Lighting Stores, Building Supplies, Home & Garden, Home Services, Shopping, Furniture Stores, Hardware Stores
text: I am finished with buying small appliances from Lowe's. No store guarantee. You must return the product to the distributor or manufacturer if there is a problem, and I can guarantee you there probably will be with the low quality merchandise they are selling. We bought a power washer Greenworks 1600 PSI, cleaned three quarters of the siding on our house, and it broke. Totally will not work. This is not the first time I have had problems with merchandise purchased from box stores.

name: St Clair Country Club
categories: Golf, Arts & Entertainment, Event Planning & Services, Country Clubs, Active Life, Venues & Event Spaces
text:
The new 2013 remodel has really brought new life to SCCC.  

 The new bar, lounge, dining room etc. look and feel great.   The bar area has been made much larger with plenty of High Def flat screens to enjoy your favorite sporting event.  The grounds have always been beautiful so no real room for improvement in that department.  All around this place has been brought up to modern standards and gone is the old stuffiness.  In addition, there are many new menu items and the preparation has been an improvement from the old menu.  I particularly like to new flat breads and other appetizer selections (fried calamari, shrimp martini).  They also serve the best burgers in Belleville.  They normally have a good selection of entrees featuring Steaks, Seafood. Poultry and Pastas.  There is something for every taste except perhaps vegetarians. They need some work in that area along with the entire St. Louis metro area for that matter. 

The service has also gone through a big improvement in 2013 although the evening black bow-ties and vest are too old school formal for my taste.
   
BTW- SSCC Management -wakeup and look at your web-site for crying out loud!  Your web-page still show the old finishing's before the remodel. Get with it . That was over 6 months ago it's time to update and show off the new digs.

name: Metro East Home Inspection
categories: Environmental Testing, Local Services, Home Inspectors, Home Services
text: Since the inspection by Metro East, our home has had a major basement leak, a roof leak, a chimney fire and a failed septic system. I would have been out less money with no inspection at all.
