text:
Used to be my favorite.  Ate there one hot summer day last year. Not the coolest temp in the dinning area and staff looked a bit over warm too. Got my favorite beef and broccoli which tasted good I thought.  Couple hours later at home got sicker than a dog. ER staff said "tainted food or lack of sanitation" caused my vomiting and pain.  They took the name of where I ate but I did not file a report.  I Don't Advise eating there. I will never go there again!    It was not worth a trip to the ER and my stomach 
Being pumped out.     BEWARE.

name: Midwest Carpet and Duct Cleaning
categories: Refinishing Services, Carpet Cleaning, Home Services, Air Duct Cleaning, Carpeting, Local Services
text: My husband found this company at the Saint Louis Home and Garden show and I am so glad he did.  We hired this company to clean our air ducts.  The two men who arrived were friendly and hardworking.  They worked quickly and efficiently, leaving our air ducts sparkling and sanitized.  We will definitely be using this company again!

name: Willow Park Apartments
categories: Home Services, Apartments, Real Estate
text: Management is horrible. Had mold growing for three years and never fixed. Had two leaks coming through light fixtures and was told its not an electrical issue just maintenance related. Reported drug activity as well and that was never looked into.

Had I known about such a ridiculous turn of events beforehand, I would have gladly gone to iHop instead.  Never again, Denny's.

name: Columbia Bridges Golf Course
categories: Golf, Active Life
text: Good course for the money. Greens are well maintained. Never had any issues just a bit out of the way.

name: Global Brew Tap House
attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'beer_and_wine'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'Smoking': "u'outdoor'", 'GoodForDancing': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'HappyHour': 'True', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'Music': "{'dj': False, 'background_music': False, 'no_music': False, 'jukebox': False, 'live': False, 'video': False, 'karaoke': False}", 'DogsAllowed': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': True, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}", 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
categories: Pubs, Restaurants, Bars, Brewpubs, Nightlife, Breweries, Food
text: By far the best beer selection in the area! Next time you're there ask for Brittany. She's extremely knowledgeable about every beer they have. It's a great place to go often as the draft list is always changing.  For the avid beer drinkers they even have a beer club to join!

name: Hi Tokyo
attributes: {'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'Ambience': "{u'divey': False, u'hipster': None, u'casual': None, u'touristy': False, u'trendy': None, u'intimate': False, u'romantic': False, u'classy': None, u'upscale': False}"}
categories: Japanese, Restaurants, Sushi Bars
text: I really wanted to like this place. Unfortunately, it was an utter disappointment. The spring roll was a joke. They were 2 bites each and super greasy. The shrimp tempura was marginally better but had absolutely no flavor, nor came with the standard dipping sauce or any sauce at all. The beef fried rice was probably the "best" item but even that was super greasy yet had zero flavor on the rough, overcooked beef. The rice and veggies in it were at least somewhat edible. The worst part was not only wasting my money on everything, but I had horrible cramps and multiple bathroom trips the rest of the night :( Instead of Hi Tokyo, this will be Bye Tokyo for me.

name: Shiny Nails
categories: Nail Salons, Beauty & Spas
text: I walked in without an appointment, and was seated for a gel manicure within a few minutes. The nail technician was friendly and efficient. My manicure is fairly average, nothing special, but still looks good. Overall, my experience was nothing out of the ordinary, and I will probably be back.

name: Mungo's Italian Eatery
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'DogsAllowed': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'BusinessAcceptsBitcoin': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': None, 'divey': False, 'intimate': None, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': None, 'classy': None, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': None, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'HappyHour': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'False', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False'}
categories: Seafood, Steakhouses, Italian, Salad, Restaurants
text:
My wife suggested we eat here on a whim. They were closed. Then we came back just as they opened. Most people dining at least had a jacket or sport coat, but they do not have a dress code. 

We had a great meal. Everything came out perfect and tasted great. Our trip was during Lent so seafood was on special. I had the fried lobster. This is out of character for me as I usually prefer turf over surf however I'm glad I took the chance here. 

The atmosphere is upscale for southern Illinois without being pretentious. Mostly younger people as staff that we saw but competent at their positions. 

On a whim I ordered an old fashioned. The drink was like water - in a great way. Nothing was wrong with it and I long for another shot at one. Normally I drink zero alcohol so if you're a professional you may have another opinion. 

Stop in for a great dining experience and be sure to try a cocktail.

name: Ooh La La Spa, Anti-Aging & Wellness
categories: Chiropractors, Health & Medical, Beauty & Spas, Weight Loss Centers, Skin Care, Medical Spas
text: As soon as you make your first phone call and talk to the staff, you will feel welcomed! Then, you walk through the door and you are overwhelmed with kindness and wonderful treatment! Ooh La La's entire staff and Dr. Jacobs helps everyone feel as beautiful on the outside as they are on the inside!

name: Macy's
categories: Women's Clothing, Fashion, Shoe Stores, Shopping, Department Stores, Men's Clothing
text: I like this Macy's. They have everything I need. My only complaint is they don't carry some of the higher end stuff!

name: Mr Twist Ice Cream
categories: Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Food
text: Great place. It's basically a family tradition to make several trips here each summer. It's located just around the corner from Wilson park so you can grab your ice cream and take a walk over to the sunken gardens. That's a nice day out in this city!

name: Castletown Geoghegan
categories: Pubs, Irish, Bars, Nightlife, Restaurants
text: Went here for lunch today and I will never go back. Super duper slow service. Only one waitress who was too worried about being cute.

name: Auffenberg Ford O'Fallon
categories: Car Dealers, Auto Repair, Automotive, Auto Parts & Supplies
text:
Terrible experience today. Went in at 9:30, due to tire pressure light being on. They check pressure, and one is down to 18 pounds (from 35 pounds). I inform the service manager that the light wasn't on last night. He walks up to my car and looks at the tire. Then they fill the tire he tells me to "keep an eye on it" and sends me away.

I then spend the next 3 hrs trying to get someone to properly inspect my tire. Meineke saw me, found the hole in the sidewall right away. But didn't have a tire my size in stock.

I go back to Auffenberg, but now it's 2:30 and their service dept is closed.

This could have been taken care of this morning at Auffenberg (where I bought the car 6 months ago), had they checked out my tire like I asked. I told them a tire doesn't lose 17 pounds of air overnight for no reason.

Finally ended up at Dobb's and got a new tire at 3:30.

Yeah, thanks for nothing Auffenberg North.

name: D & S Heating and Cooling
categories: Home Services, Heating & Air Conditioning/HVAC
text: This company was sent to my home by my home warranty company for an emergency issue. We had no heat when we woke up last Sunday. He came out pretty promptly, diagnosed the problem. I paid him the $100 deductible, he was to call in to get authorized to buy the replacement part. 2 days go by, nothing. We call the HW company they get him to come out and replace a part. He tells my wife it may take all day to warm your home. I call later from work to check and she tells me it's still cold. This guy was requested by the company to come back out yesterday and was a no call no show. Please don't waste your time or money with this company. Unprofessional and not reliable!!!!!

name: Elite Detail
categories: Gas Stations, Automotive, Auto Detailing
text:
Here is another great local business!  I took my wife's SUV in to get detailed before our baby comes.  I figured it is the last time her car will be clean so why not.  

I called Russ's on a Tuesday to see if they had any openings later in the week.  They got me in on that Friday.  I dropped the car off the night before and, received a call around 1 pm on Friday indicating the car was complete.  I could not have been happier when I picked up the car.  My wife's car is black with black carpet and black leather seats.  We have two dogs that ride in the car quite often.  Lets just say there was a lot of dog hair.  Russ's was able to get every bit of the hair out!  The car looked like it did the day we bought it.  They even detailed the engine!  My wife was very happy which makes me a happy.  All of this for $155 plus tip.  They even called a few days later to see if we were happy with their service.  You can't beat that deal!  

I highly recommend Russ's for all of your detailing needs.

name: Alton Tattoo Company
categories: Piercing, Beauty & Spas, Tattoo
text: Wooooow I am so happy with my results and will be posting pictures once it's shaded and healed. I worked with Kyle and he was quick, professional and listened to exactly what I wanted. He is a super nice guy with lots of knowledge and definitely knows what he's doing. The other employees at this place are extremely friendly and super talented as well. I highly recommend gettin any work here! They have great deals and also accept walk in appointments too. They're very versatile in style and create any looks you'd like!

name: Fairfield by Marriott
categories: Hotels, Hotels & Travel, Event Planning & Services
text: They canceled my confirmed reservation less than 48 hours before I was supposed to arrive for eclipse weekend and of course there is nothing else available now. I suspect they sold my room to somebody paying a higher rate who booked last minute rather than planning well in advance like I did!! They offered to transfer me to a holiday inn two hours north. There were other Marriotts in town selling for 500 a night or more and they refused to transfer me to one of those properties because they said it cost too much. Shady business practices. Manager couldn't give me answers that made sense to what happened. I have lost respect for the Marriott brand.

name: Hofbräuhaus St Louis Belleville
attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'Alcohol': "'full_bar'", 'Caters': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'HappyHour': 'True', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'GoodForDancing': 'True', 'BestNights': "{'monday': False, 'tuesday': False, 'friday': False, 'wednesday': False, 'thursday': True, 'sunday': False, 'saturday': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'False', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'Smoking': "u'outdoor'", 'Music': "{'dj': False, 'background_music': False, 'no_music': False, 'jukebox': False, 'live': True, 'video': False, 'karaoke': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': True, 'latenight': None, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': None, 'breakfast': None}", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': True, 'hipster': None, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': None, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}", 'CoatCheck': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False'}
categories: Sandwiches, Beer Gardens, Restaurants, German, Beer Bar, American (Traditional), Salad, Venues & Event Spaces, Seafood, Beer, Wine & Spirits, Bars, Nightlife, Food, Event Planning & Services, Breweries
text: This was our first time trying it. The food was really good. We had roasted and fried chicken, a giant pretzel, potato salad, and kids' meals. The stars come from the food and the atmosphere. The music was great! Although the food is good, it's super overpriced ($14 for a pretzel). My husband got cheese for his fries, and it was $3 for a side. The kid's burger doesn't come with cheese, and it was $1.50 to add it. The service was terribly slow. Our appetizer came before our drinks after waiting a good 10 minutes for someone to even come to the table. At the end, the server said I needed to check a 15%, 18% or 20% tip before she even ran my card. She didn't deserve 15%, but I felt forced to give it to her. And, if she would've been amazing, there was no option to tip more than 20%.

name: Fantasy Books & Games
categories: Shopping, Hobby Shops, Books, Mags, Music & Video, Comic Books
text: Awesome collection of toys, books, collectibles, etc... Just way too pricey for my taste. Some of the same items can be found elsewhere at noticeably lower $.

name: Judy’s Hands for Helping
categories: Pet Services, Pets, Dog Walkers, Pet Sitting
text: Unfortunately the stay from Judys helping hands was very poor. It was understood that Judy herself would stay at my home to watch my furbabies while I leave on a family trip. Judy assured me that her entire time will be at my home, and even  introduced me to her grand daughter who would stay with her through half of her stay due to her foot surgery. Needless to say no foot surgery and no Judy . I could not get a hold of her... and finally when I did it was through text, assuring me she would send daily photos . One photo in two weeks ! My pets require special meals due to allergies . All food was still frozen in freezer! When I arrived home , my home had been rumbled through and dogs dishes were empty in middle of lawn , including water dishes empty! I had a chewed up remote , chewed up mini blinds and my laundry basket chewed up as well. It was obvious my dogs were bored and unattended. When I asked about missing items she responded that she has no clue and maybe my dogs hid them! I would never ever recommend Judy or her employees.

name: Le Nails
categories: Nail Salons, Beauty & Spas
text: This use to be the best nail salon in the area and I was a loyal customer for over two years. Lily was always polite and professional and did the best job of all the employees. Due to employee gossip, I overheard that she was fired because of a family dispute. I still kept coming to give the other technicians a chance, but the new employees do not cut it. They do half the job and the polish does not stay on as long as it should. It is also worth mentioning that they have completely changed their nail polish center and stopped supplying matching gel colors and regular polish for your toes. They are pushing a DND brand which only lasted a week and a half! I would no longer recommend this salon. Time so search for a new one!!

name: Star Nails
categories: Waxing, Beauty & Spas, Hair Removal, Nail Salons
text: Came in at 10:30 on a Thursday for a pedicure and they sat me right down. They were kind and gentle with me ( I told them I'm extremely ticklish and my feet are sensitive) and worked well with me. I don't go get pedicures often because of that! But I'm glad I know I can come here and tell them that and they can still make my experience enjoyable . I went with the hot stone pedicure, which is recommended if you ever go there. It's $30 and So relaxing!!! I play volleyball a lot so my feet and my legs get abused often, so this was a very needed service

name: Los Alamos Mexican Restaurant
attributes: {'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '3', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False'}

text: We love this place and try to make it there at least once a week. The margarita specials on the weekends make it well worth the trip. Definitely splurge for the guac and cheese dip! Alamos dip is cheap and delicious. We love the staff, too! :) They make regulars and newbies alike always feel welcome. $2 margaritas on Monday and Tuesday too.

name: Walgreens
categories: Cosmetics & Beauty Supply, Shopping, Food, Drugstores, Photography Stores & Services, Convenience Stores, Beauty & Spas
text: It's a wags. It does have Lexmark 100xl print cartridges.

name: Zapp Thai

categories: Thai, Restaurants
text: We stopped in for dinner and had a pleasant experience. Our spring roll appetizer came out fast and was great. Our entrees were beef drunken noodles and beef pad ginger. Both were really good and there was enough food that we both needed to go boxes. The woman serving us was very sweet and we didn't have to ask for anything. Atmosphere was clean.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'HasTV': 'True'}
categories: Restaurants, Sandwiches, Delis, Fast Food
text: let me start by saying I love Quiznos! now that I have that out of the way I was pretty disappointed today.  I was pumped to have an awesome traditional, because they rock,  but was super disappointed instead. The service was fine my sandwich was hardly toasted at all and had a total of 4 olives and three onions on it.  smh for $6 it just want a good sandwich.

name: Peking Garden
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'WiFi': 'None', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'Alcohol': 'None', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': None, 'street': None, 'validated': None, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': None, 'romantic': None, 'divey': False, 'intimate': None, 'trendy': None, 'upscale': None, 'classy': None, 'casual': True}"}
categories: Restaurants, Chinese
text: Peking Garden is the best Chinese around. My wife and I live in Edwardsville which has some 6 or so Chinese restaurants and we drive to Collinsville. She always gets the Hunan chicken and I get General Tso's. The soups are good, I like egg drop and hot and sour. Egg rolls and crab rangoon also good. Great fried rice and we love the hot tea. The atmosphere is nice, servers are wonderful, and we always enjoy our time there.

name: Rogers & Hollands® Jewelers
categories: Watches, Gemstones & Minerals, Shopping, Jewelry Repair, Bridal, Jewelry, Local Services
text: My grandma bought her ring here, which was not cheap. For her 1-year anniversary they sent her a coupon for "$50 off a $100 purchase" , she thought it was just a $50 gift certificate, since they put "off a $100 purchase only" in fine print. We went in to get her ring cleaned, and looked at the bracelets since she thought what they had sent her was $50 to spend in the store. When we picked one I liked (which was $32) and she pulled out the certificate, and the man just looked at us like we were so stupid. Keep in mind the only reason I was going to get this bracelet was because she had, what she thought to be a "gift card" , so he told us that it was only good toward a $100 dollar purchase and we looked at other things that would add up to $100 dollars, we found NOTHING that I liked. The man was VERY rude to us, and we were actually giving them business at the time, because she took her ring to them so they could clean it. Overall, the two men that worked there were very very rude, and will not be going back to them.

name: Lowe's Home Improvement
categories: Shopping, Hardware Stores, Paint Stores, Home & Garden, Building Supplies, Home Services, Nurseries & Gardening, Appliances
text: Lowe's is a great home improvement store. I agree with John that it is a good idea to compare prices with the neighboring Home Depot.  The staff has always been helpful and willing to help me find what I need.

name: Kohl's
categories: Toy Stores, Men's Clothing, Shopping, Shoe Stores, Department Stores, Sporting Goods, Sports Wear, Fashion, Women's Clothing
text:
I bought some shoes for my mom at the Edwardsville
Kohl's but their rewards was down and I could use any of my coupons. I was frustrated so I drove a little down the ways to Kohl's in Collinsville to see if I could be reimbursed for the coupon I had before. After reading I decided it was best if I return them and use another 30% coupon elsewhere. So as I walk into return my shoes at the Collinsville Kohl's, I walk to customer service and this lady already didn't seem like she wanted to help me. I explained to her the problem and she just said "well where's the kohl's cash they gave you?" and I said "oh it's in the car. I can go get it!" she told me to forget about it and handed me my return money and didn't say bye or have a good day. I guess i'll be sticking to the Edwardsville Kohl's for now on!

name: Panda Express
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Caters': 'True'}
categories: Chinese, Fast Food, Restaurants
text: Went here for lunch, and the service was fast in spite of a long line. Got the Beijing beef on chow mein, and was pleased. The food was hot and fresh, and the beef specifically was appropriately crispy and spicy. On a whim, I added an egg roll to my order, and that's where I went wrong. It had obviously been sitting a long time, and tasted strongly of ginger. I couldn't even eat half of it. What a waste of money. I'll go back to Panda Express for the main dishes, but I'll never buy another egg roll here again.

name: Casey's
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}"}
categories: Food, Convenience Stores, Automotive, Pizza, Restaurants, Gas Stations
text: Their regular pizzas are awesome and they always have it ready when I get there. Little pricy compared to other chain pizzas though.  I have also picked up their breakfast pizzas for work and everyone loved them!

name: Allsup
categories: Health Insurance Offices, Health & Medical
text: Allsup helped me deal through the Social Security process in order to receive SSDI.  It took almost three years, because of Social Security's backlog, but I did receive a fully favorable decision/  My Allsup Rep at my hearing was professional and very knowledgeable.  I would like to thank him and Allsup for getting me my benefits.

name: Foreign Academic Credentials Service Inc
categories: Educational Services, Education
text: Great choice for credentialing services. They were super helpful at every step and went out of their way to make sure my needs were met.

name: Pure111
categories: Health & Medical, Skin Care, Medical Spas, Beauty & Spas, Eyelash Service
text: The service here is amazing, everyone is super sweet and very attentive to clients needs! The prices are also reasonable. I highly recommend micro-needling here my face glows everytime I've had that treatment done.

name: Holiday Inn Express & Suites Edwardsville
categories: Hotels, Event Planning & Services, Hotels & Travel, Venues & Event Spaces
text: The place is very attractive. Beds are comfortable.  However, no hot water this morning.  When we spoke to the desk, they asked "3rd or 4th floor?"  And then responded, "yeah we are looking into it."  No doubt this will be fixed but the lack of understanding that I paid money for a pleasant experience and didn't seem to be concerned that I was walking out disappointed means we won't be back.

name: Little Italy
categories: Italian, Restaurants
text: we went for mothers day. it was $60 bucks for 3 of us. the food was passable. My mom, who is a slow eater, had her salad ate before my dad or I got our soup. I got the chicken florintine. It was ok. My dad go spaghetti and meatballs. He had 2 meatballs. not like previous reviewer. My mom got the tuscan chicken. it was basically spaghetti w/asparagus and chicken. the portions were large. we all took half our dinners home. we filled up on the bread w/oil and cheese. i would go again, but not special enough to make a special trip. i did love the spumoni cheesecake. but menu price was $4.99. we got charged $6.99. i just did not feel like fighting the price since they gave free cheesecake to my mom.

name: EL Nino ​Mexican Buffet

text: EXCELLENT FOOD AND COOL VIBE! We came here when it was a Peruvian restaurant, loved it then and love it now! It's an old gas station but the owner has plans to remove the pumps to make the parking bigger. The food is great and El Niño himself is the cook! Inside they have more beer, liquor, and mix drinks than you could ever imagine! Plenty of daily specials, daily lunch buffet, and Karaoke on the weekends!

name: The Pasta House Co.
categories: Restaurants, Italian
text:
This review is in regards to Gus's Place. 
The delicious Pasta House menu has been gutted and only a few of the items remain. The rest of the menu consists of bar food. Judging from the items I've had it is BAD bar food. 
Just what the area needs,another place selling burgers and fries. YAWN. I don't know what made them think that slapping a few TV's on the wall and selling overpriced burgers and a few items from the Pasta House menu would drum up business but if this works I will be shocked. The service is so-so. Just like its always been. 
This place would be better if it made up its mind. Are you a run of the mill burger joint or are you an Italian restaurant. Either way I don't think I'll be back.

name: Crystal & Spice Shoppe
categories: Coffee & Tea, Herbs & Spices, Specialty Food, Food
text: This is the coolest little shop, and it's a hidden gem. You can completely skip Soulard and come here. They also have about 6 million coffee flavors that you can buy in bulk or in smaller sample packages. They also carry all natural remedies. I specifically love the foot spray for my gym shoes. It's non scented and it removes the scent completely. You can actually use it ON your feet, if need be. They also have tons of dip and appetizer mixes. Go check them out!

name: Dierbergs Markets
categories: Flowers & Gifts, Food, Grocery, Beer, Wine & Spirits, Shopping
text: I agree with the previous reviews. Nice selection, very nice ambiance, great deli section (possibly the best in town). Their bulk frozen shrimp is a pretty good deal. Not as good as fresh, but darn close. If you are into vegetarian, organic, gluten free, or organic foods - this place has the best selection. I come here every now and then because if you can't find something anywhere else - chances are, Dierberg's has it. I'd give them 5 stars except they are pricy. I envy the shoppers who can buy all their groceries here.

attributes: {'BikeParking': 'False', 'Caters': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True'}
categories: Mexican, Restaurants
text:
El Torero opened its doors a few years back in Granite City - where lunch options were once limited to either fast food or the same old restaurants time and time again.  It was such a relief to get a new lunch option.  It's conveniently located a few minutes from my job, which makes for a nice change from the ol' sack lunch.

EVERYONE is extremely cordial and helpful....the manager usually steps out to chat as long as they are not inundated with orders/customers.  They recently remodeled as well, which makes the establishment look bigger and more spacious although they have the same amount of sq. footage.  Their prices are incredibly affordable - esp. the various lunch specials.  The service is extremely efficient and fast as well, which works out well for the lunch crowd.

Food quality - I would lean more towards a 3.5 star rating.  It's tasty and hits the spot, but I cannot say it's my all-time favorite Mexican eating destination.  However, they do have great food.  I am partial to the nachos, quesadillas, and burrito/taco/enchilada combos.  You really can't go wrong with any of the delicious lunch combos.   I definitely recommend giving El Torero a shot if you are in the Granite City area.

name: Russell Stover Chocolates
categories: Candy Stores, Specialty Food, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Chocolatiers & Shops, Food
text:
This place is every fat kids dream or anyone who has a fat kid inside screaming to get out. I've really only been there for their blue bell ice cream but they have a huge selection of candy and chocolates. They have a huge jelly bean flavor selection that you can build your own bag from. They have some chocolates that you can buy that aren't pre-wrapped in a box and you can always find a free sample or two of something they are trying to promote. 

On to the ice cream, good selection of flavors and if you catch it right they have some very good unique flavors. The Krazy Kookie was very good with chucks of sugar cookie in it and they had a banana pudding ice cream that was every banana lovers dream. These flavors aren't always around but when you catch them they are a definite try for ice cream lovers. The service is always friendly, polite and helpful.

name: Erato Wine Bar & Restaurant
categories: Bars, Food, American (Traditional), Wine Bars, Nightlife, Restaurants, Beer, Wine & Spirits
text:
Recently went to Erato for dinner with a large group to celebrate a friend's birthday. Unfortunately, we did not have a great experience there service-wise. I don't think they are used to big groups, because we must have thrown the kitchen in for a loop with our 20 orders coming in at the same time (even though we called ahead to let them know we had a large group.) We waited over an hour for the food to start coming out for some of the people in our party, which came out sporadically in no certain order. I finally received my food after waiting for an hour and a half. The waitress seemed frazzled with the large number of orders and ended up forgetting a few of them. The most frustrating part was that neither the waitress nor the manager came to at least acknowledge/apologize how long we were waiting for the food. I think that could have gone a long way for our frustrated group. 

All of that aside, I had their croquettes which I thought were pretty good. Some people in our party had the fried chicken but didn't like it and thought the portion was too small. Another friend also tried the duck tacos, which he said was good but too small of a portion. 

In summary: I would consider going with a small group or a date. Service is slow... The portions are small and a bit pricey, but much of the food is pretty good. As well, Erato changes their menu frequently, so there might be something different to try each time. There is also a very extensive wine/drinks list.

categories: Beer, Wine & Spirits, Nightlife, American (Traditional), Food, Party & Event Planning, Bars, Restaurants, Event Planning & Services, Chicken Wings, Sports Bars
text:
Me and a couple friends of mine grabbed lunch here last Friday and I have to say nothing has changed since my last trip in which is a good thing in my opinion.  I ordered one of their 9" one topping pizzas and an order of their boneless wings.  

I've had the pizza many times so I knew exactly what I was getting.  It's a very thin crust so a 9" pizza is not exactly hearty.  I have enjoyed their wings on many occasions, but had ever tried their boneless wings.  Theoretically they should be the same, but how often does that argument fail.  While I liked the boneless wings as it let me not make a mess since I had to go back to work, I don't think they had as much wing sauce and flavor was their traditional wing counterparts.  

Hot Shots does not try to be something it is not.  It's a sports bar that serves up some pretty tasty food and offers a bunch of TVs to watch a variety of sports programming on.  I know I'll be back, question is just when...

name: Ace Hardware
categories: Hardware Stores, Home & Garden, Shopping
text: I like to shop local when ever I have the chance and this Ace is my go to place. Like Joe W. Sometimes items cost more than the big box home improvement stores but I don't mind because I don't have to drive far to get what I need and I know I will just what I need and expert advice from Mark or one of the other associate's. I also love their tool rental that they have on-site. I have rented their core airator for my lawn and had no experience with the airator and they walked me through how to use it and even loaned me loading ramps at no charge. If you want quality products and expert service try this Ace first. You will not be disappointed.

name: Brickstreet Brew

text: I thoroughly enjoy having a coffee shop on the brick street in Lebanon! The butterbeer latte is very tasty! The baristas are all very likable and easy to converse with. Super cute shop with a great atmosphere. Visit Brickstreet Brew - you won't be disappointed!

Luckily, Cooper was around to at least show that not all the dancers should be avoided.  It would have been 5 stars but Brandon screwed that up for me.

text:
Always great food and service. The gringo dip is the best cheese dip I've had in a while. The chicken Madeira is fabulous and always done just right. So yummy!! Grilled chicken salad is huge and always very tasty. Be prepared to wait if you come on a weekend night or after church.

Decorated very cute with lots of "stuff" on the walls like so many places to these days. Can get very loud in here, not a really good place for a date.

name: Goshen Coffee
categories: Food, Restaurants, Cafes, Coffee & Tea
text: This place is AH-mazing! The overnight oats are a personal fave - sweet & filling with fresh fruit and yummy granola. My kid loves the sticky toast. Coffee is some of the best you will find anywhere. I took off a star for a couple of reasons - first, pricing of some of the items is high (is the sticky toast is basically honey/butter on a small piece of toast and it is $4. Second, the drive-thru process is terrible - there is no preorder so there is always a long line at the window. Which brings me to my last complaint - the online ordering platform is less than ideal. You can only order a short list of items, customization is limited, you have to add items to cart multiple times for it to take.

name: Amira's Bakery
categories: Bakeries, Food
text:
This place is in a strip mall right down the street from my office.  I usually crave all kinds of middle eastern food, which I have easy access to in St. Louis, but it's hard to find good lunch options on this side of the bridge.  When I noticed this nondescript place on Highway 50 in a strip mall I made a note to try it.  I'm glad I did.

It's a great place for the value of the food and they sell many items like hummus, pita bread, some of their sauces, and various Mediterranean grocery items for you to take home.  It's clean inside and there is seating, but it's just basic cafeteria style  so if you're looking for posh surroundings this is not your place.  

If you want some quick, cheap, good food though, it's absolutely worth a stop.  They make their own Falafel, bread, hummus, and baklava  in house and it is delish!

The menu is rather eclectic  - it includes fried fish plates and sandwiches (tilapia, catfish and perch) and different kinds of chicken wings, but it all looks good.  

I had the falafel sandwich - spicy - and a piece of baklava for under 5 bucks.  The falafel was moist and flavorful.  I'll definitely be back!  

Also of note is that the person who helped me (who I assumed was the owner) was super nice and friendly.

name: Float Center Shiloh
categories: Local Services, Meditation Centers, Float Spa, Fitness & Instruction, Day Spas, Skin Care, Medical Spas, Active Life, Massage, Beauty & Spas, Professional Services, Massage Therapy, Health & Medical, Business Consulting
text:
UPDATE
Sherry sent me a text message on Friday, June 29, 2018 stating a refund had been sent to me. Today is Monday, July 9, 2018 -- 10 days after her text. I have not received the refund, and there has been no response to the email I sent yesterday. 


WRITTEN ON JUNE 27, 2018
I have come here several times over the past year and have always had wonderful experiences! Loek and Danielle are so delightful to work with - very low-key and really know how to help a person have a pleasant experience. In June, they offered BOGO (buy one, get one free) sessions, so I purchased one. When I went in for one of my sessions, Loek told me more than one could be purchased, so I purchased two more. I had used three of the six sessions and went in last night (June 26, 2018) for my fourth. What a nightmare!

Since Danielle & Loek both know me from having been there before, they usually just tell me which float I'm in, and I go back and settle in. Last night, I was greeted by a woman I had never met. She started telling me I had a birthday "gift" since yesterday was my birthday. I said "no, my birthday was last Thursday". She informed me it had to be either yesterday or today since there was a cupcake next to my name. OK. Fine. I decided not to argue with her. She didn't seem to know what the 'gift' was, so I asked her if I could just call in the morning to discuss it. No, that wasn't alright with her, and she kept right on rambling -- thinking out loud. I asked her two more times, if I could call in the morning since the clock was ticking. (By this time, it was 6:07, since she had stopped to answer the phone at one point.) She accused me of being late. (I walked in at 5:58. If anyone else had been working, I would have been done with my shower and in the float.) I attempted to explain to her that I would have been there sooner, except I had stopped to talk to and then text a person who was letting go of a loved one on life support. She stopped to answer the phone again. (They have voicemail which I usually get when I call them. Why she couldn't take care of the customer in front of her is beyond me.) Finally, by 6:14 pm, she had grabbed a remote and was storming back to the float, shouting that I needed to get in the float and talk to my spirit guides and angels. She's in the float room flicking the lights off and on, still yelling at me about talking to spirit guides. I'm trying to tell her I don't use the lights or music and trying to get her out of there, but she just kept on with her rant. I finally had to yell at her that she's "preaching to the choir". By the time she left me alone, I was so stressed out, I couldn't stand it. I went back out and said I wanted to cancel and reschedule. There wasn't anything available at any of the times that would have worked for me, so I ended up doing the float last night. By this time, it was well into the hour for the float. There was music blaring the first five minutes. I was so stressed out, I never could relax and enjoy it and didn't even get the full hour, more like 40 minutes. I took my shower, got dressed and got out of there. 

I had another appointment tonight and two more later in the week. This morning, there was a message on my voicemail from her (turns out, she's one of the owners and is named Sherry) stating that if I was going to be yelling at people tonight, then I'd better not come, and they would refund my money. I only yelled once because she would not listen to me, was argumentative and would not LEAVE ME ALONE! (all caps for emphasis, not yelling. LOL). I emailed her the following: "I'm choosing to write you instead of calling. I think it would be more productive. I have had no problems with anyone at The Float Center until last night.  Obviously, we have very different personalities that don't mesh well.
I would like to continue coming to your center but would like to do so when other people are working. From what you said on this morning's voice mail, it sounds like you will be working this evening. Please let me know if that's the case so I can make a decision about my appointment."

After a couple hours and not hearing from anyone, I called. Danielle answered. I asked if she would be working this evening. She said no, that Loek would be there, but Sherry might drop in. My appointment was still on the calendar, so I said I would keep it. After I got off the phone, I got to thinking about it and decided I didn't want to take the risk of running into Sherry. I immediately called, left a voicemail and sent an email. In the reply to my email, they stated they are refunding the $50 for the remaining BOGO but not refunding the $25 for last night's float as that was "free". Whatever....

I was planning to do weekly floats, but after this,...no way. They also have lost two new clients I was going to bring in next week. Oh, well!

name: Hardee's
categories: Fast Food, Restaurants, Burgers
text: Do I have an experience to write about!  This place tops all the fast food places I have had ever!  Let me begin by saying that I love fast food restaurants and Hardees rate high among many.  However, this one incident gave has given me second thoughts of ever going back, at least to this location on east end.  So we go in and ordered the favorite and so delicious bourbon burger combo.  We are handed the number and proceed to have a seat.  Waiting for a few minutes, the food is delivered to our table pleasantly.  Wow!  Does my burger look flat but not to waste time on taking a bite, I dove right in.  My friend is still playing around with the fries and had not noticed the burger just yet.  I, on the other hand, stopped and developed that look on the face of disgust.  You know the face when a baby is given a sour taste!  To my surprise as I look to investigate, there was no meat.  NO MEAT People!!!!!!!!!!  Now to other fast food, like White Castle or McD's, this would not be a big surprise since their meat are small enough to not notice.  But, to Hardees where they advertise 1 pound burger meat.  Come on!!!!  Skip the lettuce or tomato or even sauce, but the meat!  It was laughable if not upsetting.  I go to the counter and present the undesirable.  She was just as shocked as we were.  Come to find out!  They  had a new person in training making the food.  The trainer made this clear by pointing the finger and not blaming himself.  LOL!  So typical!  The lady at the counter gets them to make new ones and even said, "How do you forget the meat?"  They brought out the new meal.  It was as good as we have had in the past.  I just had to laugh at the experience.  All the workers were young people and, yes, we are all human.  But, in a work environment that aims for satisfied customers, one must put on the thinking cap and attention to details.

text:
I visited this restaurant during its first few weeks of opening.  Yes, the menus were printed on paper, but this was just fine since 1) It's know for its wings, not its filet mignon; and 2) It is in the opening stages.  My first observation was that the walls were a bit bare, but the dozen or so flat screens made up for that.

My wife and I were greeted and seated almost immediately.  There was a couple ahead of us.  Our server was polite as she made a few recommendations and notified us of the specials for the night.

The wings were great!  We thought it was awesome that we did not have to order a set amount of wings per flavor (we were able to mix and match).  Between the both of us, we tried 4 different flavors (lemon pepper was our favorite).  The fries were different, but tasty, nonetheless.  For desert, we had the funnel cake fries.  Yes, the portion size was small, but they tasted amazing with the ice cream.  I don't recall the price, but I'm sure I did not pay $5 for them.

Overall, this is a really good place for food and watching sports.  I think it may have the potential to eventually be great, especially being so close to SIUE and open late night.

Rated it 4/5 stars, because there's so much potential for this place to succeed.

Will be returning soon!  Maybe I will try a burger next time..

Once we were seated we were a little bummed they ran out of fish and chips. We ordered a steak sandwich instead which was good.

text: This is probably one of the best steak houses in the St. Louis St. Louis area (and hey...if you live in Edwardsville you only have to drive a few miles). Most places close early on Saturdays and closed on Sundays and we needed to head back to Chicago Sunday afternoon. After frantically calling 5 separate companies these guys were the only ones willing to get us in last minute. 
They were so kind and honest. These gentlemen got us fixed and on our way in less than an hour. 
Thank you!


$44.99 evaluation fee (which is credited towards any repairs)

categories: Heating & Air Conditioning/HVAC, Water Heater Installation/Repair, Home Services
text: Our AC went out days before the start of a predicted heat wave. Heritage was out the same day to evaluate our AC. They had to order parts, but came out on a Saturday to install them. Turns out that part wasn't the problem, so they gave us a few options including the price and warrenty length to help us make the best decision. We decided to replace the AC unit and coils instead of putting a band-aid on it. They gave us a very reasonable quote and time frame, especially considering it was Saturday. They came out Monday when they said they would be there and got the entire install done in less than 2 hours. They charged us the amount quoted. The owner, Jim, even called us Monday night to make sure everything was working and the house was cooling down. I would highly recommend them and will not hesitate to do business with them in the future.

name: Party City
categories: Event Planning & Services, Shopping Centers, Party Supplies, Shopping

I'm not sure why I even bothered coming here bc I don't like Italian food. I'm giving it one star because my husband and mom didn't like their food either and they do like Italian food. Mostly though I was annoyed with our waitress who was giving us an attitude from the moment our butts hit the seats. She seemed to have a problem with my kids. I'm sure waitressing a table with kids is typically a pain but my kids (ages 3 and 8) know how to behave in restaurants. I felt like she was either annoyed to wait on a table with kids or was having some other personal issue. Regardless, rude service.

Oh also, I was checking this place out for a possible location for my daughters private birthday party. I contacted the restaurant before my visit to inquire but no one returned my call. Glad I visited and was able to check it off my list of possibilities.

categories: American (New), Restaurants, Bars, Nightlife, Breakfast & Brunch
text:
Must try the 612 Burger on Tuesdays! I always enjoy visiting my local Houlihans in Fairview Heights. I was running errands and realized it was Tuesday and I wanted to try their new 612 stuffed burger that is only available on Tuesday. Well today was the day and it didn't disappoint!

My server Tony was fantastic and pointed out the burger as a special today and I told him that was exactly what brought me in for my visit. ( and my 20% off email coupon!)

To wet my palette, I started off with a strawberry guava iced tea (Tony was nice enough to accommodate me asking him to mix 2 syrup flavors) and I highly recommend doing that! It was delish!

My burger came out and it looked great. Fries were hot and perfectly cooked, burger looked picture perfect. 

The burger is stuffed with white cheddar, worcheshire sauce and a "secret ingredient" and the promo photos show this oozing center of this well cooked burger that makes you want to dance! 

Well it was a bit of a let down when I slice open my burger with the big reveal looking for the ooze and no oozey cheese. But it was cool, it was still good. I love that dijonnaise sauce on the bun- that was so flavorful and delicious! I also love the way the lettuce was shredded...I don't think they do that for all their burgers but they should. It wasn't shredded like cheap Taco Bell shredded lettuce but it just was very complementary to the burger.

Once again my experience at Houlihans was outstanding! The environment was clean neat and fresh smelling, Tony as a server was fantabulous, and my food was deliciously prepared perfectly. 

I love how Houlihans corporate really takes the time to shake up their menu seasonally so you can still enjoy your favorites on the menu, but if you want to try something new, you can. They do a great job of having something on their seasonal menu that appeals to everybody. You may not want to try everything, but there is at least one thing that makes you say, "Hey! I want to try that!" 

I will be back to try the creme brûlée flight- the chocolate rhubarb and the butterscotch sounded phenomenal! But I indulged enough today with the burger. Until next time Houlihans in Fairview Heights, keep up the good work!

name: Smallcakes Cupcakery of Fairview Heights
categories: Cupcakes, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Food, Desserts
text:
Cupcakes! Who doesn't enjoy beautifully decorated, fresh baked, moist cupcakes? Well Smallcakes in Fairview Heights is open and I am excited Fairview has a sweet shop of its own on the main I-159 corridor. It's a little further down past Krispy Kreme if you are traveling south, but it is GREAT I can stop there for a sugar fix when I am doing shopping in the area. The place is beautiful and new, clean and pristine and you are greeted with a smile and cheerful hello upon entering! The staff is friendly and informative and I love patronizing places where people seem to love where they work and have a passion for talking about their products. 

I always have to get the basics- a yellow cupcake with buttercream. I find chocolate has a tendency to mask "eh" products, and people who love chocolate tend to focus on their love of chocolate over the actually taste of the product the chocolate is in. Also chocolate cake tends to be a more moist cake just because of the combo of ingredients and how they bake together. White or yellow cake can't be masked. If it is dry, flavorless and nasty you will know. That is NOT the case with Smallcakes! Now remember it is a franchise concept, and although each one is locally owned and operated, there is still a standard across all locations and this doesn't disappoint. 

Please patronize this place! I love Woods bakery in O'Fallon and I love The Cup in Edwardsville, but as much traffic that passes through Fairview Heights, let's keep this place going! Check this place out and support them! 

Please keep up the standards, Smallcakes Fairview Heights team! Don't make me regret my glowing review in 6 months!

text: My food was good, but my margarita was great! Very prompt and friendly service. I would definitely recommend them.

name: O'Fallon Illinois YMCA
categories: Active Life, Child Care & Day Care, Community Service/Non-Profit, Summer Camps, Gyms, Local Services, Fitness & Instruction
text: Probably the best YMCA I have been to yet. I attended this for a local 5k and really enjoyed it there. Great staff, good location for running and it is pretty big.

name: Memorial Hospital - Shiloh
categories: Health & Medical, Hospitals, Emergency Rooms, Urgent Care
text: Took my 95 y/o Mom to have lab blood work-up. Very little wait time. Personnel very professional. Spoke with chaplain. Lab personnel gave us coupon for coffee and donut for Mom was fasting. Nice touch.

name: Trusty Chords Record Shop
categories: Books, Mags, Music & Video, Shopping, Vinyl Records
text: I have been to quite a few record stores in the metro east and I have to say, this is one of the best! The customer service was amazing. The selection was amazing. The organization was amazing. I will be going back!!

name: McDonald's
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Ambience': 'None', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': None, u'validated': None}"}
categories: Restaurants, Burgers, Food, Coffee & Tea, Fast Food
text: I went into McDonald's tonight to have dinner. This is my local McDonald's and I go there quite often. Tonight  I couldn't get over how dirty the place was. I was able to look around the dining area and see that most of the tables needed wiping down. The trash cans were full. There was debris's on the floor. The soda machines look to be in disrepair they were missing faceplates and generally  looked like crap. The catchup dispensers both of them were in operable. As we walked through the doors we could look down behind the counter and see a pile of trash right around the drive-through window that the crew apparently was cleaning up but you could still see trash on the floor there. I was with the group and every person I was with stated the same things how dirty the place was tonight. I noticed that the Redbox machine was gone. In the small alcove where it once stood there was a ladder and various other things that probably should've been put away in the back. It was very disappointing their regional or local managers need to look at this and correct it. This is how people get fired.

name: Vintage Tea Room
categories: Tea Rooms, Food
text: We went for an early Mother's Day Lunch here and had a lovely time. The owner is very friendly and seems to be a bit of a character. Our waitress, Amanda, was very friendly, attentive and nothing was a problem.  I had the roast beef sandwich with pasta side salad and it was delicious. We enjoyed trying the different teas. You get to try 2.  You can try more if you want to pay extra.  The scones are lovely and moist. I had white chocolate and apricot. Yum. The inside of the tea room is decorated really nicely. We enjoyed ourselves and I think it deserves 5 stars.

name: McDonald's
attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'Caters': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'"}
categories: Food, Restaurants, Coffee & Tea, Fast Food, Burgers
text:
Both times I've been to this location I've had a terrible experience. It is slow and disorganized. Today was even worse than last time. In the drive thru i asked for hot fries- they came cold. I asked for new fries. Somehow they were colder: seemed like they had been microwaved unsuccessfully. The person in front of me had to yell at the speaker several times to get their attention. My turn was no different: no greeting. I asked if anyone was there and they came back with "you can order when you're ready." The previous customer's order was still on screen. When they started adding my order i alerted her that there was extra food. She apologized and deleted each item...it sounded like there was then confusion ahead of me in line...

After trouble in the line and getting cold fries: I pulled out of the drive opened my chicken sandwich and it was cold, rubbery, and all in disarray with mayonnaise everywhere inside the box. I finally gave up and went elsewhere Without eating anything.

It was chaotic and frustrating. I encourage people to drive on past to another mcdonalds location or hit one of the more responsive fast food chains nearby!

name: Bike Surgeon
categories: Shopping, Bike Repair/Maintenance, Sporting Goods, Outdoor Gear, Bikes, Local Services
text: Yea! These wonderful people fixed my very dopey Huffy bike and started me on a wonderful journey. I appreciated them not laughing at my bike or me for wanting to ride it. They were extremely encouraging and invited me to upcoming events. I felt like they were as jazzed as I was to get started biking. The repairs and adjustments done ony bike were not cheap, but, I didn't know how to do them...I was more than happy to pay them for their expertise. I love their dog, too.

name: Super 8 by Wyndham Fairview Heights-St. Louis
address: 45 Ludwig Dr., I-64 Ex 12 St 159 N to Ludwig
categories: Hotels & Travel, Hotels, Event Planning & Services
text: This hotel provides enough of the basics and was a good deal at about $20 cheaper than all of the other nearby hotels. You'll get a clean room, shampoo, conditioner, cups, towels, toilet paper, microwave, refrigerator, breakfast, and wi-fi. The hallways felt stuffy and smelled musty, but neither of these things were a problem inside the room. The water pressure in the shower was low, but I pretty much expect that of every hotel.

name: Clean Machine
categories: Automotive, Car Wash
text: I've moved across the river and I miss Clean Machine so much! Clean Machine offers a quick, affordable, full-service car wash along with an interior vacuum, dashboard wipedown, quick window cleaning, and even a trunk vac for a reasonable price. There's nothing like it in the city - you either spend $6 or more to wash your car yourself or you pay through the teeth for detailing. Sometimes you don't know how good you have it until you move away.

name: Pita Pit
attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'HasTV': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False'}
categories: Greek, Food, Restaurants, American (New)
text:
I've been to Pita Pit before in CA so glad to see one here. Went there twice with store opening promo coupons and had the Chicken Souvlaki and Teriyaki Maki (local) pitas and both were fantastic. My wife had Buffalo Chicken. Teriyaki Maki (with philly steak) was awesome with most ingredients grilled. Buffalo Chicken was not very hot, would have liked it a little hotter. The guys working were very friendly and helpful and it definitely seems like the place is trying to make a good early impression to establish itself. The eating area outside is quite pleasant actually!

Compared to something like a Subway, I'd say it's a bit better and that goes along with the little higher cost. I could definitely eat there a lot if I wasn't limiting my eating out.

text: Awesome saloon. Can't beat the atmosphere. Perfect baseball bar. Lots to keep you busy. Check out the Pink Panther neon they stole from Mulligan's in Peoria.

name: Slackers CDs & Games
categories: Books, Mags, Music & Video, Music & DVDs, Shopping, Videos & Video Game Rental
text: Some decent prices but the staff is mediocre; not unfriendly but not very competent, either.

name: Target
categories: Department Stores, Shopping, Fashion, Furniture Stores, Food, Grocery, Home & Garden, Electronics
text: Always check your receipt when buying something on sale. Can't count the times I have bought something on sale and they have charged me full price.

name: Champagne & Lace Bridal
categories: Fashion, Bridal, Shopping, Plus Size Fashion
text: I will start by saying I did not end up buying my dress here, but I had an extremely positive experience. This was the first place I went and I had absolutely no idea what I was looking for. Kayla was super helpful and was able to help steer me toward a style of dress that looked really great on me, but that I wouldn't have necessarily been able to find on my own. Everyone who worked there was very friendly and helpful. Super recommended.

name: All About Pets Veterinary Hospital
categories: Pets, Veterinarians
text: Been going here for 5 years now. The staff is great, they are helpful in working with my schedule if I just need to run in for something and they're really great with our poodle Mr. Horatio!

name: White Castle
attributes: {'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'Caters': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': None, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}

text: We came here after at night in St. Louis!! Was expecting fast service like other white castles... nope!!!! We sat for over 40 minutes in a 5 car line. Then was asked to pull forward once we got to the window. No. No. No. This is my first ever review, and I will never be back. No thank you.

name: Rib City
attributes: {'WiFi': "'no'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'Alcohol': "'full_bar'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True'}
categories: Restaurants, Barbeque
text: This was my first visit to Rib City. It is restaurant week in Alton, so they had an amazing offer for lunch. Half side of ribs, two sides, toast and dessert for $10. Heck yes!!! The ribs arrived without sauce and you had three options on the table or they could bring their secret hot sauce out from the kitchen. The sides were your standard sides, sweet potato fries were extra. It was a very short waiting time for our food. The ribs fell off the bone. My baked beans arrived in their own dish with a spoon.(Even better) the French fries were good but too much to eat. I ordered the sweet potato pie. It was a little slice of heaven. We ate in the bar which was very nice, but the service was alittle slow. I will be back, hopefully with a server that is a little faster.

name: Steve's Auto Body
categories: Body Shops, Automotive
text: Steves Auto Body did an amazing job on my car after I was hit.  They made the process so stress free and easy for me.  Handled everything including getting me a rental car.  I can't say enough good things about them.

name: Grand Rental Station
categories: Party Equipment Rentals, Machine & Tool Rental, Event Planning & Services, Local Services
text: Do not go. It was my sisters wedding, we were trying to get errands done for her and they were the worst vendor out of all of the wedding vendors we dealt with. This lady was extremely unpleasant and did not help accommodate at all. Pay x2 to go anywhere else.

text: Wife and I went after a HS sporting event. Nice atmosphere with a large bar and plenty of TVs with  great selection of draft beers. Tuesday special is steak kabobs. Plenty of food and very good. We will definitely be back out next time in town.

name: The Home Depot
categories: Shopping, Home & Garden, Nurseries & Gardening, Appliances, Hardware Stores
text: Had the best service today! I went in not sure if I'd be able to get what I needed for a project for my classroom but thought I would try. I had been to one other store and was told it was impossible to do and they couldn't cut wood to my needed dimensions. I walked in and waited a few minutes but the employees knew I was there and made sure to ask if I needed anything while I waited. It was my turn and I explained my project (I'm trying to turn milk crates in to seats for my classroom) and was immediately taken back to the lumbar section and was told they could cut me the amount and size I needed on the spot!! It gets better though. Since I am a teacher one of the employees made small talk and asked about the project really making me feel better about the whole experience and seemed to know I was going to be purchasing this with my own money. We found the wood but then I notice the guy looking around a pile of scraps and I'm a bit confused but hey he knows more than I do so I just wait. He pulls out this piece of wood that looks almost the exact size I need but just in small squares. He cuts it and gives it to me no charge since it was scraps, making this project so much more affordable and honestly turning my day around completely! Thank you so much!!

name: The Coffee Box
categories: Coffee & Tea, Food
text: Excellent coffee place in Maryville, it is worth the drive.  Cold Brew is amazing as was the bakery items.   They also sell speciality coffee whole beans and the flavors are like none I have ever had!   Highly recommended if you are a coffee person, way better than Starbucks!

name: Schiappa's
