categories: Chicken Wings, Restaurants, Pizza
text: The food was really great, some of the best wings I've had! Their pasta sauces were pretty amazing too. Great staff! Definitely recommend.

name: Carpet Care Plus
categories: Office Cleaning, Home & Garden, Home Services, Contractors, Furniture Stores, Carpet Cleaning, Home Cleaning, Shopping, Local Services, Professional Services
text: Excellent service and customer care! Highly recommend them to anyone needing carpet cleaning. Used the company for several years and they're great!!!

name: Domino's Pizza
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': False, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}"}
categories: Restaurants, Salad, Pizza, Sandwiches, Chicken Wings
text: This is my boyfriend and I's second or third time coming back to this dominos and previous times have been fine. We ordered our usual hand made pan pizza with extra cheese and extra sauce. You have to be careful because they don't always put in the extra sauce that you specifically ask for. My boyfriend checked the pizza immediately at the window once we received the pizza by messing with the cheese (to assure we don't receive the same pizza back) and checking for extra sauce. There was barely any sauce on it and the employee took it back for "disposal" and "recooked" a new pizza for us. We get the so called new one 15 minutes later and don't check it, trusting the establishment to have made us a new pizza with the right specifications we put online. We get home and other people try the pizza and comment on how there's a hole in the pizza with burnt cheese, the same exact spot where my boyfriend messed with the cheese. They just reheated the pizza so it seemed hot and fresh when we got it. We're sure no consequences to the people who did this to our order will be made so that's disappointing, but the new pizza they made for us was fine.

name: Cold Stone Creamery
categories: Cupcakes, Food, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Custom Cakes, Event Planning & Services, Caterers
text: Customer service was horrible. I was one of two customers in the store, the other one was checking out. Two girls stood around while I waited for 5+ minutes without any acknowledgment. When I was helped I ordered one dish and the girl just walked away and I had to wait yet again for my second dish to be ordered. And to top it off my toppings an ice cream were hardly mixed. Next time I'm grabbing Orange Leaf instead!

name: IHOP
attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'WiFi': "'free'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': None, 'latenight': None, 'lunch': None, 'dinner': None, 'brunch': None, 'breakfast': True}", 'Caters': 'False', 'CoatCheck': 'False', 'HappyHour': 'False', 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': False, u'lot': None, u'validated': None}", 'Ambience': "{u'divey': False, u'hipster': False, u'casual': True, u'touristy': None, u'trendy': None, u'intimate': False, u'romantic': None, u'classy': None, u'upscale': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
categories: Restaurants, Fast Food, Breakfast & Brunch, American (Traditional), Diners, American (New), Burgers
text: I reluctantly stopped in this morning at my son's request, because he loves the food.  I say reluctantly because I've eaten at many IHOPs across the US and almost always have a lackluster experience, usually because of bad service.  We walked in and were seated right away.  The only negative thing I will note is that the greeter was a ridiculous mumbler.  "Howmanyyougot?" I'm sorry??  "Youwannakidsmenu?"  Huh?  Once we were seated, our waitress was quick with our drinks, and made sure we were not ever in need of anything.  She was outstanding, and it kills me that I lost the receipt with her name on it.  We were seated near the entrance on the 4th of July if that helps management :-) The pancakes, eggs, hash-browns and bacon were delicious, and met every expectation I had, but the wait staff were what made our meal outstanding.

name: Popeyes
categories: Fast Food, Chicken Wings, Restaurants
text:
I just left after a 30 minute wait in the drive thru. For the first time I didn't check my order thinking surely it's correct after waiting so long. I was wrong. I ordered a large fries ($4.09) and received a very small fries...after waiting 30 minutes while, others drove off. 

I'm extremely disappointed! Always check your food before pulling off.

name: Starbucks
categories: Food, Coffee & Tea
text: This is a great little Starbucks that I enjoy coming to before or after work. It can get very very busy though, especially on a Saturday.

name: Caulk's Xtreme Collision Center
categories: Auto Detailing, Towing, Automotive, Body Shops
text: I took my Toyota Tacoma there after a minor wreck.  All that was required was body work.  They went the extra step to make sure I was taken care of with the insurance and the rental car set up.  Everyone there that I dealt with was extremely friendly and very knowledgeable of insurance and body work.  My truck looks great.  I am EXTREMELY satisfied with the work and the service of the staff.  Lonnie went above and beyond to make sure I was kept up to date with what was going on.  If I ever need ANY body work done again I will go to Caulk's Autobody without hesitation.

name: Woody's Drive-In
attributes: {'Alcohol': "'none'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Caters': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True'}
categories: Burgers, Restaurants, American (Traditional), Food, Juice Bars & Smoothies
text: As a small child growing up in Jerseyville when we made trips to the Alton area during the summer we frequently stopped at Woody's and I became a life long fan. Flash forward to the early 2000s when I was a student at LCCC I rediscovered this as a great place to eat on a budget. And again years later as a commuting professional, I would meet my dad here regularly to catch up. Just recently I took my wife who isn't a fan of fried chicken in general here and she is readily looking forward to her next visit. They aren't aiming to win any beauty contests but the fried chicken is undeniably tasty.

name: Club Fitness - Granite City
categories: Gyms, Fitness & Instruction, Trainers, Active Life, Cardio Classes
text: Not as big as the other gyms, but clean, plenty of machines with little to no wait (except for extremely busy times). It can take awhile to fix broken machines, but it's never kept me from my workout. Friendly staff.

name: Caliber Collision
categories: Windshield Installation & Repair, Auto Repair, Auto Glass Services, Automotive, Body Shops
text: Expert and friendly care! I was greeted with a warm welcome by the front office team, Shelley and Karen, who walked me through each step in the process making my drop off short and simple. Bill, my estimator, equipped me with periodic updates via text message-which were outstanding and informative. He provided information I could act on without overwhelming me. My car was complete on time. At pick up, Bill and team walked me through the repairs and the work done on my car using plain language that I could understand. Bill provided explanations for each item on my maintenance report and answered each of my questions. I had the full attention of the entire team- pick up was painless and quick!

name: Piasa Armory
categories: Education, Gun/Rifle Ranges, Firearm Training, Guns & Ammo, Active Life, Shopping, Specialty Schools
text: Very knowledgeable and friendly. They help me pick out the perfect gun for my husband. The conceal carry course was very informative.

name: Tire Choice Auto Service Centers
categories: Tires, Automotive, Auto Repair, Oil Change Stations
text: Wow! I've come here too many times where it's now my fault if I keep coming. They seem only half focused on the job at hand and silly embarrassing mistakes happen it seems on a daily basis. Good luck with all that.

name: Gateway Classic Cars
categories: Automotive, Used Car Dealers, Car Dealers, Car Buyers
text: With over 3.000 cars for sale, everyday, it is the largest in the country. With 18-showrooms in markets like St. Louis, Louisville, Chicago, Detroit, Indianapolis, Tampa, Orlando, Ft. Lauderdale, Houston, Dallas, Nashville, Atlanta, Milwaukee, Philadelphia, Denver, Scottsdale, Las Vegas and Kansas City, and more coming, it is now the largest in the nation. If you are looking to sell or buy a classic, collector, exotic, sports, European, luxury car, truck or motorcycle, look them up. They have exported vehicles world wide in the 20-years of their business. An excellent company that has 37,000+ global clients.

name: Sizzor Shak
categories: Beauty & Spas, Hair Salons, Makeup Artists, Skin Care
text: Let me just say that I found it sooo worth driving the 45 minutes from my residence in south st. Louis county to Collinsville for my appointment. I'd do it again in a heartbeat. It was clean, inviting and the staff was great. I didn't really have a set plan on what I wanted done, and my stylist, Amber, did an excellent job of helping me narrow down a color and knew exactly the cut I was looking for. I was also pleasantly surprised, as I was prepared to pay over 100 dollars for a cut and color and I had not reached that threshold. if I had any complaint at all, it would be that parking is very limited and I parked a couple blocks away. Everything else was very pleasant.

I walked out with what I needed for now, and I will be back. Exceptional service!

name: A Storage Inn
categories: Home & Garden, Hotels, Local Services, Event Planning & Services, Hotels & Travel, Self Storage, Shopping
text: I contacted A Storage several weeks ahead of my cross country trip for storage space. They immediately responded to my request. They assisted me with local information regarding the area. After my arrival the process was super fast and I  unloaded all my personal belongings into the storage. Several weeks has passed and I located an apartment. It took me several days to pack all my belongings. Thanks again for all the support! Would definitely recommend this place!

name: KFC
categories: Fast Food, Chicken Wings, American (New), Restaurants, Chicken Shop
text: They demolished their old building and built it brand new and for weeks cars were lined up in their drivethru, but not anymore. The three times I've been there since they reopened were all horrible. The chicken was terribly greasy, (to the point I just didn't want to consume it) which is unusual because the KFC in Granite City always tastes fine to me. Friends have had bad experiences as well with them getting orders wrong. I'd knock it down to poor management.

name: Holiday Inn Express & Suites Pontoon Beach
categories: Venues & Event Spaces, Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Hotels & Travel
text:
The good: the understanding manager who helped us get out of this creepy room. 

The bad: the dirty room that we were offered as accommodation. At first glance it seems as if the place is ok. At a second glance you start realizing that you are either standing in a stranger's hotel room or standing in your unclean room with trash in the cabinet, fridge, and bathroom. 

The bottom line: this was the only time I have experienced this level of product and service with this hotel family. Hoping for a better experience in the future.

name: Cambridge Dental Care
categories: Dentists, General Dentistry, Health & Medical
text: The staff are always friendly and very helpful! My daughter and myself love going here! Dr. Brubaker is very knowledgeable and up on the latest technology and trends in dental care. He recommended Orthotain for my daughter when she was in first grade. Now when all her friends have braces, she has straight teeth! And it was WAY less than paying for braces!

name: Secretary of State
categories: Public Services & Government
text: Quick and painless, This place was amazing. I was needing to renew my sticker for my license plate. Some local banks sell them, but you need cash if you don't bank with them, since I was at work I knew this would not work. I know that most people do not have pleasant experiences at with the Sec of State offices. The lines are always crazy long. It was raining and maybe that help with the lack of people in the office. To my delight, they had a line that was just for people that only needed a sticker. One person was in line in front of me. An attendant stated that someone would be with her shortly. Sure enough, someone was at the line in less than 5 minutes. I stepped up, the lady was friendly. It took less than 3 minutes to get my sticker. I was expressing my delight to the attendant at the process being quick and painless, her comment... "Tell your friends..." Better yet I will share it on Yelp

name: Car-Tech Automotive
categories: Automotive, Oil Change Stations, Auto Repair, Tires
text:
If I weren't disabled, I'd have done all this work myself. Instead I made the mistake of trusting someone that took advantage of me.

First of all he had my car for over 3 weeks. It took me doing research online to track down the problem for him that he couldn't figure out. That should've been my first warning. Not very knowledgeable.

I asked him to do a complete tune-up, flush and fill, and an oil change on the vehicle. As cruddy as the anti-freeze looked just a few months later, I have my doubts that part was done. The oil change was written nowhere on the receipt, so that never got done. But it's the spark plugs I have a real issue with.

For 6 spark plugs I was charged $271.88 for parts and labor. As with any transverse engine, the back 3 plugs are extremely difficult to get to. That explains the high labor cost. However, because it's so difficult to check that they were actually changed, some, less than honest mechanics, will simply skip all the work but charge for it anyway. That's what happened in my case. 

I was cheated and robbed, and would NEVER trust this guy around one of my cars EVER again. I caution anyone that goes here to make sure the work he charges for was actually done. ALWAYS ask for your used parts back, and when you can, actually watch them do the work.

name: WIT Cafe
categories: Food, Cafes, Sandwiches, Restaurants, Bubble Tea, Bakeries, Coffee & Tea
text:
Product: boba is super fresh. the drink taste heavenly. Thai tea was on point! (Ive been on that Thai tea binge lately.)
Customer service: smile all around and got some tips around the St Louis area.
Price: a little bit pricey but for the quality of the drink, I'm okay with it. :)

The vibe of the store is super relaxing, super clean. 5/5 and def will be back for more boba in the future.

name: Bel-O Cooling & Heating
categories: Heating & Air Conditioning/HVAC, Air Duct Cleaning, Home Cleaning, Local Services, Contractors, Home Services, Plumbing, Appliances & Repair
text: Hottest day of the year and had a power bump and my AC stopped working. Called my regular guy and he was busy so went to a big company. It was of course 3:45 so I got charged for an after hours call. Ok come out please. The guy was here for 10 minutes and told me my ac fan motor was out. Would be at least 700 -800 to fix. This is a old AC unit and he suggested it was better to go with new. 6400 for a whole new unit to include blower and furnace but can't install till Tuesday. Ok so until then?? Be  hot. Great ok. Pay him 130.00 for nothing.  So my regular guy calls me back and comes to check it out. It's a capacitor, he charged me 85.00 and I have AC. I will NEVER buy anything from Belo or call them again. Nor will they ever be recommended by me. Quite the opposite. Scammy!!!

name: Edible Arrangements
categories: Food, Florists, Flowers & Gifts, Chocolatiers & Shops, Gift Shops, Shopping, Specialty Food
text: I must start off by saying that I have had previous positive experiences with this location, BUT for Valentine's Day-don't do it!!!! I placed an online order on February 1 to be delivered on February 13(intentionally done NOT on Valentine's Day as to get the order properly). I called about 4pm on Feb 13 to make sure that my order was still coming. I was told yes it was on the truck & out for delivery. I was at work but my daughter was at home waiting for a surprise. At 7:30pm, she still hadn't received her surprise & I tried to call back but they were closed. I called the next morning to inquire as to what happened after I had been told my order was out for delivery the night before. A manager got on the phone & said that she wasn't sure what happened but that they could re-deliver it but obviously not on that day as it was Valentine's Day and they had too many other deliveries(WHAT???!!!! my order was already late) Anyway, after agreeing to give me 50% refund & delivering the package on Thursday(3 days later than was originally scheduled), my daughter finally got her Valentine's surprise. Guess what? The order was NOT refunded by 50% as promised AND the arrangement was not fresh(not sure if it was the original order that was supposed to be delivered on Monday or not). The strawberries, the most important item in the order, were bad & my daughter didn't enjoy them. I am VERY disappointed in this location. I know that Valentine's Day is a big day for many businesses but I thought ordering in plenty of time ahead would be sufficient to get around this issue. I would recommend only ordering from this location when it is not a major holiday.

text:
Excellent atmosphere here, real family run feeling.  It's more apparent with the micro store attached to it which sells foreign food supplies.  
I had the catfish nuggets and jalapeño poppers.  
The catfish nuggets were out of this world, perfectly seasoned and fried.  They were still succulent which is not the easiest thing to do on this thick catfish.  The platter came with a generous amount of fries to compensate the overwhelming amount of nuggets. 
The poppers were fully stuffed large peppers that oozed cheddar cheese and left me wanting more......guess you could say once you pop(pers) you just won't stop(pets).
Their pizza also comes highly recommended from my coworkers.

name: I Scream U Scream
categories: Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Food
text: Great ice cream, but make sure you have cash as for some crazy reason she still doesn't  take any credit cards.

name: Platinum Tanning
categories: Spray Tanning, Tanning, Beauty & Spas
text:
BIggest rip-off of a place ever. Stay far away. I had to hire an attorney to get me out of all the legal problems this place caused me. After looking through the contract, my lawyer specifically said the owner has loopholes for everything to ensure that you can't get out of the contract without paying ridiculous fee's.

The worst part of my experience was that I was told by the owner himself that as long as I cancelled before the next billing cycle on the 15th, I wouldn't be charged again. I went into cancel on the 1st of the month, the associate told me that she did so, and I didn't go back again. Four months later I was served with an outrageous bill stating that I failed to make payments. Funny because in all that time I wasn't notified once that I had missed a payment, and I had been told that my account was cancelled.

When I went in to speak with the owner, he wouldn't say two words to me and told me to "speak with his attorney."

When I first signed up I was fed lies about how great of a deal I was getting and he even threw in discounts because I attend SIUE. This man parades around acting like he is so nice and helpful to college students, when in reality he makes his money by ripping us off. He may have satisfied customers but that is ONLY because they haven't tried to leave yet and I feel sorry for when they do because they are in for a nasty shock,

AVOID AT ALL COSTS.

name: Bank of America
categories: Banks & Credit Unions, Financial Services
text:
Megan's frustration is certainly understandable and in retrospect, they probably should've explained what was involved, including cost, to cash a check  as a "non-account holder"
My experiences, as an account holder, have been superb. The staff, especially Dawn (one of the managers) are wonderful. They call me by name, explain things to me, help me out with special requests, etc. Always a warm greeting when I arrive and depart. They are true professionals.

name: EXO Nail Bar
categories: Cocktail Bars, Bars, Nightlife, Beauty & Spas, Nail Salons
text: Really enjoyed my time here. Beautiful location and friendly and helpful staff. Had a lovely pedicure with a sweet and friendly tech. Manager was always checking on everyone which was nice. My only complaint is my manicure. The tech was also very nice and helpful I asked for a French tip powder manicure. He took his time to make sure it was perfect. Upon leaving my nails looked pretty good. A few filed unevenly. Nothing big. Now my nails are usually sore after getting them done but the next day they were extremely sore and my nail and cuticle are cut all over the place. There's weird like in the manicure as well. I paid about 70 for the nail job and manicure which is fine but I wouldn't get the same French tip again.  Beautiful place and lovely staff. Just unfortunately didn't receive the best results on my first visit. I hope to come back however.

name: Lady Nails
categories: Beauty & Spas, Nail Salons
text: I was early for a dinner date with a friend so I stopped in for a pedi. Steven was my technician and he did a fabulous job. I am very sensitive and he was gentle and took the time to do a great job! I don't live in the area but will make the trip in the future to have a pedi from him again!

Frank's is not closed. He moved up the road to Cottage Hills, the old Red Apple, Round Table, or which ever place you know it as. He told me he took out a long lease so he could stay open for years. 

I love the food. Go for the breaded pork chops. The breakfast  options are perfect diner fare. The service is always friendly, and the owner is a particularly nice guy. Go there.

name: Eric Booth - Ellerbrake Group Keller Williams Pinnacle
categories: Real Estate Agents, Home Services, Real Estate, Real Estate Services
text: Eric Booth helped us relocate from Alaska and purchase our first home. He could not have been a better fit for us, as he came from a military background and knew how to work within our timeframe moving to a new base. Eric's knowledge and dedication to getting us the perfect home made the process a breeze. He was always available to talk day and night and seemed to always respond to any questions or concerns immediately. He was quick to iron out any wrinkles throughout the process and communicated very clearly what was happening every step of the way. Eric really does work for you and fights to get what you want. We learned so much from him as he helped us make our first venture into the real estate market. We could not have made a better choice for our first home purchase and would highly recommend him to anyone buying a home.

name: Recess Brewing
categories: Food, Breweries
text: The best part about this place was the large open window to mainstreet.  The IPA (22 11)  we tried was horrible, this is saying a lot the company I had a almost exclusivity drinks IPAs and decided two drinks was all she could muster.  the flavor was similar to bile really disappointing.  I'm hoping we just tried fluke beer because it would be nice for a place like this to make it in edwardsville.

name: S & L Concessions - Mission Essential Barber Shop
categories: Barbers, Hair Salons, Beauty & Spas
text: Hands down, this place is a great pace to get a haircut. The only thing I wish they would improve is the ability to add a tip when using your debit card. They have an ATM which charges you $3, but i would rather them add $2 to the price of a haircut than use the ATM just so I can give the stylist a tip.

name: Kritter Kare's Howliday Inn
categories: Pet Training, Dog Walkers, Pet Groomers, Pets, Pet Sitting, Pet Services
text: You guys are the best! We had a death in the family and had to leave town unexpectedly.  We called and got Rocko in right away with no problems.  Throughout Rocko's stay we got pictures and updates, which we absolutely love!  Our ride home took much longer than expected and we didn't make it in time to pick Rocko up before closing.  We called and staff was extremely accommodating and said it'd be no problem to pick him up the next morning.  When I picked him up he smelt amazing and his coat was shiny!  We love the "one stop shop" grooming and boarding!  It is so nice having your facility in our town.  THANK YOU!

text: I'd be really sad if I had to go anywhere else for my eye care. Dr. Helfrich has a beautiful new office that you must see. But beyond the ambience, you'll find a very caring optometrist and a competent staff.

name: Clarkson Eyecare
categories: Optometrists, Eyewear & Opticians, Shopping, Health & Medical
text: Saw the past reviews on yelp & still returned for a 2nd visit (1st was in '11). The staff was very helpful and informative. They answered all my questions. The doctor was retired Air Force and was very complimentary about wanting to stay in the area after his service. Susie was wonderful and very patient when it came to helping select the frames I wanted. I had a very good experience!

name: Happy Days
categories: Food, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt
text:
It's tough to screw up ice cream and I'm happy to report that Happy Days chose their name well. The ice cream is great, the choices are many and the price will make you happy too. 

Eat inside or take it on the road. Just go treat yourself soon!

text: First place I came to do a root beer run while in town on a business trip.  The root beer here was very sweet and creamy, with hints of vanilla.  I paid $1.30+tax for 16 oz cup.

name: Midas Tire & Auto
categories: Oil Change Stations, Auto Repair, Automotive, Tires
text:
I went to Midas for the first time to get an oil change and tire rotation since I got a coupon for $20.  They immediately pushed for the $40 synthetic oil change with tire rotation.  I agreed.  I started talking to the women in the (unpleasant) waiting area.  They'd all come in for oil changes and had been there for hours because the mechanics had "found serious problems" with their cars.  One woman had been there for 6 hours for a 3 year old car (finishing with a $1400 bill).  It became apparent that Midas lures you in and then pushes for tons of other repairs.  

The mechanic had me follow him into the garage area (1 hour after I arrived) and showed me all of the "serious problems" my vehicle supposedly has.  He said I must be leaking oil (which I've never seen on my driveway), my tires were "shot", etc.  I said no thanks, just do my oil change and rotation.  They gave me an estimate anyway for $1300 which didn't even include new tires.  When I went to pay, there was confusion about whether they used the synthetic oil or not.  I honestly never saw them CHANGE my oil or filters.  Plus I said I didn't see them rotate my tires.  The cashier said they couldn't rotate them because I hadn't followed their advice about needing new tires and it was dangerous.  So I didn't even get half of the work I wanted done after being there for 2 hours.

To sum up, don't go to Midas and throw away the coupons you get in the mail.

name: Alvers Auto Repair
categories: Auto Repair, Oil Change Stations, Automotive
text:
A++ service.   Active duty military shipping my vehicle overseas ... ran into parking brake problem during inspection.  Alvers paused working on another vehicle to help me (they understood the urgency and time crunch I was in).  It was fixed/adjusted in 40 mins!  Best $45.00 I ever spent.  He also drains fuel for inspection purposes, however don't know cost.   

I would highly recommended him for short notice vehicle inspection problems. 

Definitely not the same service the other reviewer had that I read from 2016!   Very professional, friendly, accommodating and honest work.

name: Locks A 2 Z
categories: Home Services, Keys & Locksmiths
text: Very timely. Great service and very knowledgeable. I will use them again and I would highly recommend them.

name: Gold's Gym
categories: Fitness & Instruction, Yoga, Gyms, Active Life, Trainers
text:
I absolutly love the theater room, they have never played a re-run in over a year that i have been a member, for those of you that like to run but get bored easily this room rocks!! the pool is never too crowded and open all the time which is nice too! Also, they just got all new dumbbell weights and the machines are still practically brand new, they have a sauna in the locker rooms, and to top it off if you have kids, and heres the kicker for you, they have daycare included in your membership for 2hrs a day...so its pretty much like the gym is free!  

i know they have a lot of classes to offer and if you need anything they are pretty good with getting it if its reasonable

name: Kumars Restaurant
categories: Restaurants, American (New)
text:
Great prices, tasty eats, very friendly and prompt service, and watching the old folk gab can be interesting. 

I think Anthony and his guest did themselves a disservice by ordering meatloaf and tuna salad. I would not call ordering those dishes "playing it safe" in any diner. When I go to Kumar's, I order an omelet or biscuits and gravy, and I've never been disappointed with the quality. 

Another plus. Serious coffee drinkers out there know how important it is that the waitress keep coming with refills, and they do that at Kumar's without you having to remind them.

name: Magic Nails
categories: Beauty & Spas, Nail Salons
text:
Asked for a pedicure and a shellac manicure. Got a (rushed) shellac polish change (didn't even offer me a manicure) and then moved hastily into a pedicure. The pedicure was decent. At least that technician recognized that I wasn't happy with the poor polish job on my nails and talked with the owner to have it corrected. But my nails were polished so poorly, streaky and edges poorly done or not covered in polish at all. I have more gel polish glued to my skin that actually on my nails. To "make it right" the owner out another coat of polish on my nails. If you know how gel polish works, I have a mound of nail polish. It looks terrible. I paid my $35 fee to get out of there, and I promise I will never return. Hopefully I don't pick up a fungus, it wasn't very clean either. I should have known
 better.

Their food is always cold there needs to be some better management and some major changes this used to be our go-to McDonald's from  now I will drive 15-20 minutes just to avoid going to this location! awful customer service the owner should be ashamed of their self for allowing this.

name: Great Clips
categories: Hair Salons, Beauty & Spas
text: This place is awful. Went there with hair almost to my hips and asked for a lob, got told that  um that's not a bob(which I never said!) showed the stylist a pic that she half- assed looked at,then the girl (Sharon?) sprayed SOME of my hair down and used clippers to cut around the ends of my hair & then was just walked up to the register and waited for me to come up and pay. No making sure it was even, no asking of how do you like it? NOTHING..  The stylist was RUDE and disrespectful. I am so sad I let her cut my hair off. i will never go here again- even for a boys cut- as unprofessional as she was she may grab a bowl and use clippers around it!! Avoid this place...unless you are in the mood for disappointment- then by all means..

name: Michaels
categories: Hobby Shops, Arts & Crafts, Shopping, Knitting Supplies
text: I wouldn't necessarily call myself crafty, but I do find myself here every now and again. They boast a little bit of everything for nearly every craft I can think of. Candle wicks were the reason for my most recent visit. I guess they're not as commonly found as I previously thought (can't find them at Walmart). They had several varieties at a reasonable price. The employee that helped me was quite friendly and knowledgeable. They had a very efficient check out line as well.

name: The Cyclery & Fitness Center
categories: Shopping, Fitness/Exercise Equipment, Sporting Goods, Bikes
text: Showed up here at the Shiloh location to purchase a new cyclocross bike. After briefly talking to a salesman and explaining that I had a month ago just purchased a road bike from the edwardsville location I was left to go talk to other customers. So after a few minutes another sales man came up and asked if I needed help I explained my whole situation again. After I test rode two bikes i was left to my own devices, granted there were only two sales people there on a Saturday that was concerning. At the end I had the bike I wanted all piked out which was about a $2k bicycle no one re approached me to sell it. So I left after 20 minutes of being left so I went to bike surgeon in o Fallon and spent my two grand there and traded in the road bike I purchased from the cyclery. I will not be back and I wouldn't recommend them.

name: Time Out Sports Bar & Grill
categories: Restaurants, American (Traditional), Nightlife, Sports Bars, Bars
text: Was in town and stopped for a beer. Very friendly bartender and nice atmosphere. Will definitely be back!

name: Lone Star Steakhouse & Saloon
categories: American (Traditional), Restaurants, Steakhouses
text:
Only have been once, and won't go back.

Wait for the table was long, and the wait for the food was even longer.  They were out of a few of the things that we asked for, and the steaks were not good at all (overcooked, bad cuts of meat, etc).

name: Smokey Joe's
categories: Pubs, Bars, Nightlife, Sports Bars, Restaurants, Local Flavor, Pizza, Barbeque
text: Great bar, great people, and real cold beer! They have 13 different beers on draft! Fun bartenders, very friendly people! They serve pizza, chips and they have 5 big screen tvs or you can listen to any music on touchtunes. Also they have a nice covered patio to enjoy on a hot summer night.

name: Lowe's Home Improvement
categories: Hardware Stores, Shopping, Home & Garden, Local Services, Appliances & Repair, Home Services, Appliances, Nurseries & Gardening, Building Supplies
text: I would deem this your typical neighborhood Lowe's. Their selection doesn't really differ from other locations that I've been to. I will say they didn't seem to have quite enough people working during my last visit. I was looking for the right sized hooks to display my extensive Starbucks city mug collection and there was no one to be flagged down. I ended up buying hooks that were too big and had to return them. They did offer many difference sizes, so finding perfect size won't be an issue. Their prices are average, but they do have a military discount.

name: Chic N Pig
categories: Poke, Food, Sandwiches, Barbeque, Southern, Restaurants
text: Good pulled pork and mac and cheese. They do have an unadvertised 2% service fee when paying with credit. Seems kind of cheap but not a dealbreaker.

categories: Fast Food, Tacos, Breakfast & Brunch, Mexican, Burgers, Restaurants
text:
Jack in the Box on Homer Adams is a late night experience. JB offers an eclectic menu with everything from egg rolls to greasy tacos. I suggest ordering a large quantity of tacos and supplementing the order with random sides from different ethnic food sources. Waiting in the drive-thru after midnight is a time investment, but it will pay off.

Also - rival fast food joint McDonald's is known for shutting down the milk shake machine when the late night staff is working, but as the man working the night shift Jack in the Box window told me - the milk shake machine at JB is always on, and "it brings all the boys to the yard."

5. The number of employees behind the counter.

name: Millpond Brewing & Incubator
categories: Pubs, Bars, Nightlife, Beer Bar, Breweries, Food, Brewpubs
text:
You want a place with creative, delicious beer? 

You want those beers served to you by genuinely nice and extraordinarily fun people?  

You want those nice and fun people serving you delicious beers in an awesomely restored vintage space?

Go here.

Other notes:

+ You can bring food in. They also have food trucks on specific dates (check social media). 

+ Lots of great outdoor space, but even inside the big garage doors can let lots of fresh air (and light) inside. 

+ They have growlers for sale if you want to take any beer you try & like home.

+ There is additional parking in a lot on S. Kossuth St. about 1.5 blocks up from the brewery.

+ They have TVs (in case you wanted to watch a game) and board games (in case you get tired of talking to the people you came with).

name: Student Union Cafe

text:
This is my favorite taco stand in the St Louis area! The food is authentic and they serve a good variety of meats. The prices are lower then the other taco shops in Fairmont City, and my favorite is the barbacoa and my wife's is the carne asada, but they are all great. Your meal includes free chips, salsa and guacamole. Yes that's right, FREE! If you have never had AUTHENTIC Mexican tacos, then give them. Try a jarritos Mexican soda or the Agua de Melon drink and you'll thank me later.

This is really a store with a taco stand, and they have a good variety of products. I love when the guava and prickly pear are in season because they make great smoothies. We also get other specialty items there.

name: Papa John's Pizza
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}"}
categories: Pizza, Restaurants
text:
It's difficult to love a pizza place where your first and last word must be "No." 
Papa John's Customer Service Rep: "Thank you for calling Papa John's ... would you like to try ....?  
Me: "No. Instead, I'd like to order ..."  
PJCSR: "Would you like to upgrade to .... for just $x more?" Me: "No, thank you."
PJCSR: "Would you like to add breadsticks or ...?" Me: "No."
My daughter liked the pizza, but I disliked the phone call.  
PJ advertising focuses attention on quality ingredients, and the pizza tastes okay. The ordering experience seemed topped with excessively aggressive promotion and perfunctory politeness, and the combination left a bad taste in my mouth.

name: Schnucks - Fairview Heights
categories: Bakeries, Florists, Restaurants, Flowers & Gifts, Drugstores, Shopping, Food, Delis, Grocery
text:
I don't know what it is about this store, the "ghetto Schnucks," as it seems to be known, but whenever I walk in this store, I feel the life being sucked out of me. 

The vibe in this store is depressing and the crime rate must have gone up dramatically in this store, as there are cameras everywhere and you can't even buy $4 worth of stuff with a credit card without getting asked for your ID.

The service is okay in this store, and has actually improved.  A year or two ago I got so frustrated waiting in line with a full cart that I simply left the cart and the store and went to Dierbergs.  There were about ten people in line with one checkout counter open.

This store is okay if you need a couple items, but if you have serious shopping to do, I'd go to Dierbergs.

Also, to top off the experience, a friend of mine saw a janitor steal a huge bottle of liquor at this store.  He grabbed it off the shelf and stuffed it in his shirt.

name: Candlewood Suites Ofallon, Il - St. Louis Area
categories: Hotels & Travel, Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Venues & Event Spaces
text:
You know that feeling you get when you expect something to be mediocre, but come to find out, it's not bad at all? That's the feeling I got when I stayed here for 2 weeks. I love the amenities and coziness of this hotel! Nice gym with new machines, free washer and dryer, a mini-market for your convenience, and a DVD library in the lobby. I'd be sold already just by hearing that their laundry facility is free! I especially liked how there are a lot of choices of restaurants to try out near by. 

First off, my colleague and I were fortunate that they had rooms available for us at last minute due to a bad incident at another hotel close by. I was placed in a handicap room because it was the only one available at the time. So the bathroom shower stall was wheelchair accessible. The room was great for being an extended stay hotel. Complete with a 2-range stove-top, microwave, dishwasher, a regular size fridge, and all the necessities you need in a kitchen (such as pots, pans, wine bottle opener, etc.) you almost feel like you're in a mini-apartment. 

Some other things I liked was their updated warm and modern furniture. They give you plenty of hangers, and their iron was clean (no crusty water residue left from previous use). The placement of the desk/dining table made it a perfect spot to get work done or eat dinner. The room comes with a DVD player. The mattress was firm yet comfy. And the bathroom was huge in terms of floorspace. 

My only gripes were that the vanity in the bathroom was small (see picture attached) - I didn't have a whole lot of room for all of my most important beauty products. And if you don't turn off the shower head while you're soaping yourself or washing your hair, the floor will get wet all the way to the toilet. Luckily there's a big drain in the middle of the floor, but the water won't drain unless you swept it in with your extra towels. I had to waste a few just to use them as floor mats. Also the bathroom sink faucet was the kind of faucet you see in a public restroom - you have to keep pressing it to turn it on, and it won't stay on unless you keep pressing it. Imagine how long it took to finish up in the bathroom without the luxury of constant running water. On the other hand, it's a good way for the hotel to conserve water, so it didn't totally suck when you think of being "green". Also, my room was right behind the elevator. So the whole time I was thinking my neighbor's heater was loud every time it came on. Turns out, there's no room on the other side if the wall - it's the elevator being used each time! I had to get used to waking up to the sound of the elevator going up and down. 

The front desk people are helpful. The gentleman was nice enough to help me lug all of my suitcases out to my car. I really appreciated that. I would definitely look into staying at other Candlewood Suites in the future.

name: David's Bridal
categories: Accessories, Shoe Stores, Fashion, Bridal, Shopping, Flowers & Gifts
text:
I would not have used David's Bridal if all my bridesmaids lived all in one place.  Unfortunately they were all over the country and David's bridal was the only store in all states.
First, they forgot to add my shoes to the order.  Even though I specifically remember giving them the shoes I wanted to purchase. Second, once I realized this mistake and ordered a pair of shoes, we picked out the color i wanted but I had to come back later to have them dyed.  I come back and they have no idea what I'm talking about and I had to choose a color again (There are 6 different shades of ivory) 
Third, one of my bridesmaid dresses came in with an oil stain so it had to be returned.
Fourth, one of the flower girl dresses was defected and tried telling my mother in law it was okay and refused to fix it. When she took it to another seamstress she agreed that it was defective.
5th two of my bridesmaids shoes were dyed incorrectly. Fortunately my NY bridesmaid sent her shoes to us (they were correctly dyed) and the maids who got theirs dyed in Fairview could tell theirs were wrong and get it fixed days before the wedding. 

All over bad service and quality! I would never used if I had to do it all over again.

And after all my trouble and telling them everything. All they gave me was a free dye (5$) on my shoes.

Not a fan.  The atmosphere is all wrong for a bbq place.  Bible quotes on the wall and elevator music in the bar, doesn't scream BBQ to me.  

I find the smoked turkey to be okay.  The ribs are also okay.  But, the sides are absolutely horrible.  Everything is either fried or smothered in butter.  The hush puppies were not great and the kids menu is basic and pathetic.  

I also wish Bullys would attempt to make a homemade BBQ freshly so they wouldn't have to use HFCS as the top ingredient, but, not here - three different sauces table-side all with HFCS as top ingredient.  

The wine list is absolutely shameful.  

Its the only BBQ in the area so it is often packed - I don't see the attraction.

categories: Nightlife, Bars, Caribbean, Restaurants
text:
Summary:
Good place, different for this area. Inexpensive. Healthy food choices, regular choices. Friendly staff. Will come back.

Review:
This is a nice little place over by Wang Gang, Joe's Pizza, and Subway and a couple other places.  It used to be a Japanese place, but it's been re-done with pictures of the islands, beaches, toucans, and Jimmy Buffet music.  Some of the decorations are a little cheesy and only a few look professionally done, but it's really part of the whole theme, so I didn't mind it too much. The waitress we had was super nice.  We were also the ONLY ones in there, which was weird.

I went here for lunch last week with some work mates and we all got different plates, but I think everyone was happy.  

For appetizers, we ordered empanadas and two orders of chips/salsa. With the chips, we got two kinds of salsa, the mango kind and the "Smoke Damage" kind.  My co-worker who likes spicy stuff said it was a little too hot for her, so we switched to the Pico de Gallo salsa. The mango one was really good, but needed something extra.  The empanadas were about 5-inches long and filled with your choice of chicken or shrimp AND some kind of cheesy sauce. I was not expecting the cheese or for them to be deep fried. (hello, read the menu!) But, they were still good. I wouldn't order them again because I'm a freak and don't like cheese or deep fried stuff, but I'm guessing a lot of people will like them. My workmates liked 'em!

For lunch, we had a few different things. The most expensive thing on the menu is a steak at $14.95. No one got that.  Two gals ordered the Caribbean K-bobs ($9.95) - one with chicken and one with shrimp, both with lots of veggies. Both looked and smelled fantastic and got great reviews, I think this is what I'll get the next time I come back.  One gal ordered a jerk burger ($7.95) (which was good, but I think she was shocked at the bun. It's not a regular hamburger bun.) and two gals got B.A.L.T.'s ($6.95 each), which also got good reviews and looked really good. One of them got fries, which looked sorta like Wendy's fries. (which, if you like Wendy's, isn't a bad thing at all!)  I got the Veggie Overload salad ($7.50) (which lasted for four days - they have HUGE portions.) It was fantastic because there are so few places where you can get a spinach salad! (I'm not from the Midwest, so adjusting to the food here has been a challenge.)

We were having a bit of a work meeting and asked them to turn down the music (which was blaring out of a speaker directly over our heads), and they happily did so.  Our waitress brought extra napkins and refilled the glasses without having to be asked. (again, the place was empty, but I think she was pretty good nonetheless.)

I will definitely go here again as it seems to be one of a few places that have different and healthy stuff, but also serves burgers and fries. They have a good kids menu, too. I think this would be a great place to bring kids because of the bright colors, easy to eat foods, happy staff, and since it's not too quiet, you don't have to worry about someone getting fussy and turning heads. :o)

And I must say that as a former Hawaii resident, I'm happy to have anything tropical around.  I'm a little worried about it being so empty at noon, though.  I hope it sticks around.

name: The Edge
categories: Active Life, Shopping, Restaurants, Cinema, Arcades, Mini Golf, Arts & Entertainment, Laser Tag, Hobby Shops
text: Fantastic time at the Edge!  The edge offers fun and games for people of all ages.  We had a boys birthday party there and it was a blast.  The staff are well trained in dealing with screaming children who are loosing their minds with excitement and clearly have come to terms with it and yet somehow seem to enjoy it day in and day out. The edge offers plenty of party space for small or large groups and the prices were reasonable for what you get.  The kids and adults had a blast (pun intended) playing laser tag and staff here were also exceptional in dealing with slightly organized chaos.  There is plenty to do to keep everyone engaged and on schedule.  Highly recommend for parties of all ages.  A good time for all!

name: AutoCenters Nissan
categories: Car Dealers, Used Car Dealers, Auto Repair, Oil Change Stations, Automotive, Auto Parts & Supplies
text: Best Car Dealership EVER!  Just leased a new Nissan Murano.  They were everything you would want in a dealership. non-pressure, courteous, upfront and honest.  Definitely worth the short drive from STL.

text: I'm from out of town and was looking for some Chinese take out. Called in an order of combo fried rice and wontons. Food was ready when I arrived. Order was right.  Staff was friendly. I got back to the hotel and it was very good for the price, $11. Going back later this week to try it again.

name: Auffenberg Hyundai
categories: Automotive, Auto Parts & Supplies, Car Dealers, Used Car Dealers, Auto Repair
text: I have never felt compelled to write a good review about a car dealership or car salesman but our experience at Auffenberg Hyundai in O'Fallon, IL  was such a great experience that I just had to do it.  The whole sale took only about 35 mins because we had our price set and they already had a vehicle on the lot that met all our criteria and was actually already way less then we had researched as a good price. Our salesman, Scott, was not pushy or your typical sleazy car guy.  He was great. Can't recommend,  Scott, highly enough. I would definitely go back to these guys again for our next purchase.

name: Jack's Premium Car Wash & Quick Lube
categories: Automotive, Car Wash
text: Repeat customers here! 2 visits and both with friendly staff and at great price for the clean car. The young staffers do a great job on the interior and they work fast. I am not a car person, just want to get in and out, and with my money's worth. I am glad I tried this place; I wouldn't go anywhere else.

name: Afterwords Books
categories: Used Bookstore, Bookstores, Shopping, Books, Mags, Music & Video
text: Great book store, friendly staff and they always have great deals. Plus you can almost always get store credit for your old books as well.

name: ChillOut Frozen Creations
categories: Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Food
text: Chill Out is the most entertaining stop for ice cream in Alton. They have about 10-15 different flavors of frozen yogurt, which they rotate out often. It leaves something to look forward to trying with each visit. The service is nice and I've been asked if I've had the tour of the flavors both times I've visited. My favorite part is the toppings; there is an entire buffet table full of toppings from all kinds of cereal, to sugar cookie dough bites, to fresh fruit.  I recommend giving it a shot because it's unlike anything else in the area.

name: Hipskind & McAninch
categories: DUI Law, Professional Services, Lawyers, Personal Injury Law, Divorce & Family Law, Criminal Defense Law
text: I had a great experience working with Brady to come to a favorable resolution to a recent traffic violation. He was attentive, courteous, and very quick to respond to any questions or concerns I had. I highly recommend Hipskind and McAninch. I couldn't have asked for a more positive experience or results. Thank you Brady!

text: They open at 8am. I came in at 930. The toaster oven wasn't turn on i had to wait 15 min for that to get heated up. I wanted ranch in my sandwich didn't have any full. Just didn't seem like who opened or closed the store did a,good job at all. Not prepared at all.

name: Savvi Formalwear
categories: Formal Wear, Fashion, Shopping
text:
AVOID AT ALL COSTS

Absolutely horrid experience. Before I explain what happened, I want to make it known that I attempted to dispute this with Savvi through their website roughly one month ago and have not received a response. 

I was a groomsman at my good friend's wedding and rented a tux from Savvi for the event. I was extremely disappointed with my entire experience, as the suit did not fit correctly from top to bottom. The jacket was too small in the shoulders and too wide in the lower torso. I couldn't even cross my arms. I actually told this to the gentlemen who had me try it on and all he could offer was giving me a larger size jacket, which would not solve this proportionality issue. I obviously said no. In addition, the pants were too baggy, too long, and hardly fit around my waist. I noticed this when I tried it on as well but figured I could wear a belt, only to discover these pants were not designed with belt loops. No matter what I did, my pants became looser and looser throughout the evening. It was extremely embarrassing to have to HOLD MY PANTS UP AT THE ALTER. I walked awkwardly down the aisle, stood uncomfortably, and nearly dropped my pants walking back. It was one of the most embarrassing experiences of my life. I was stuck sitting in a chair for the remainder of the night because I was terrified of my pants falling off on the dance floor. 

I'm not sure why they even bothered to measure me. Nothing fit. I could have used the money I spent to BUY a brand-new suit of decent quality that would have fit better. 

Don't go here.

name: Terry's Appliance Center
categories: Home & Garden, Appliances, Electronics, Appliances & Repair, Local Services, Shopping
text:
Just bought an A/C unit here - had some serious problems - they took care of it right away.
No problem.  I've never had a better experience.  
Seems like they will do anything to fix things,
& with appliances something always needs fixing.  
Don't go anywhere else!

name: Petco
categories: Pets, Pet Services, Pet Training, Pet Groomers, Pet Stores
text: I took my dog here yesterday to be groomed. The groomer and I talked about everything I wanted to have done; the specific length, face shape, and nails. Upon picking up my dog 4 hours later she looks nothing like we talked about! She is almost completely shaved!! And her nails are horrible! She is a malti-poo so she has longer hair on her tail and the groomer said she would trim it instead SHE SHAVED IT! I will never be taking my dog back here.

text:
The beer was uninspired, even on tap, and the food was blanned. 

I ordered a double cheeseburger, which came out with a single patty. After pointing this out to our server, I then had to wait several minutes for the second patty, which they brought out on a separate plate, so I had to add it to the burger that had been sitting in front of me for several minutes by hand, as the server did not deem it appropriate to take the burger back and have it assembled properly. I'd hoped the burger would be amazing after such a ridiculous experience, but it was absolutely boring.

I've yet to be back, though I did make the poor decision to buy one of their canned beers outside of the brewery, a "double" IPA. It was the definition of "meh".

name: Little Caesars Pizza
categories: Restaurants, Pizza
text:
Alright so the kids wanted pizza.  We decided on Little Caesar's.  They have an ultimate supreme that is pretty good. 

Here is a great tip.  At a lot of these chain pizza places they do not put a lot of sauce on it.;  Order it with extra sauce.  Especially here!  They fresh make the pizza and it is awesome.  We can have it home while it is still scalding .  

Hot and with extra sauce their pies are pretty good.

text: The entire crew at Bernhard Automotive is top notch. Dave Bernhard, the owner, is extremely honest and will never try to overcharge you or convince you to have work done on your car that you don't need. The staff is friendly, fast and on time with their appointments. Our family takes all three of our cars there and have only had excellent experiences. The food is very good and includes most of the standard dishes you will find at other Indian buffets.  Reasonably priced and a great option for lunch.  I have been to many lunch buffets in the St. Louis area and this is as good as any.

name: Apple Cleaners
categories: Laundry Services, Sewing & Alterations, Local Services, Dry Cleaning & Laundry
text: Very disappointed with service. When I picked up my clothing, there were stains and the employees were very rude about it.

name: Budget
categories: Hotels & Travel, Car Rental
text: Love love love my experience I had with the staff and  owner. He  was nothing but friendly, patient and helpful. I would recommend this FAIRVIEW Heights location to you all. I was visiting out of town and he asked how my trip was. I forgot to fill the gas tank up all the way and he even gave me the opportunity to go fill it up and explained I would have to pay $10 a gallon if I didn't. He was awesome!!!! Thanks for the great guest service you offered me! And the patience you granted me every time I called with numerous questions. Thanks again

categories: Music Venues, Food, Arts & Entertainment, Desserts, Bars, Nightlife, Restaurants, American (Traditional)
text:
This place is amazing. They have indoor and outdoor seating, high tops, booths, and regular bars. There are dozens of t.v.s & big screens and you can watch pretty much any sporting event you can think of!  There are also bars inside and outside and there are so many drink options; draft beer, craft beer, every kind of liquor and signature cocktails.  

The food is also great!  So much variety.  On our recent dinner visit; I had the all you can eat crab legs and they were delicious. The house-made "chips" were a perfect accompaniment as was the biscuit. My wife had one of their wraps and it was stuffed full and really tasty. She was satisfied as well and our service was super fast!  This is a great place to have some fun....there's plenty of room, plenty of food, and plenty of alcohol! 

Oh, and while they didn't have live music while we were there because the Blues game was on they do have a great lineup of bands to check out. We will absolutely be back!

name: New Frontiers Home Furnishings
categories: Furniture Stores, Shopping, Home & Garden
text:
When it comes to furniture, I am very picky and New Frontiers Home Furnishings meets and exceeds my expectations. Being constructed of solid hardwood is a must and 8-way hand-tied springs are at the top my demands. For me, buying furniture is an investment. When I buy, I buy quality so it last forever, or until my taste take a drastic change. 

My taste in home furnishings are fairly traditional, with a slight lean towards country and NFHF fulfills them with a large selection. In addition to styles on display in the store, you can order from manufactures catalogs. 

Keep in mind, many of the items and brands at NFHF are made to order and are not sitting in a warehouse waiting to be delivered. If you want quality, you need to be patient. Good things comes to those who wait. 

The Sales Professionals here are down-home friendly, no high pressure selling like you get at most furniture stores where the sales people work on straight commission. They listen to your likes, request, price range and guide you to the best selections available in house or via special order. 

Delivery is not free, there is a minor fee, but it is worth the price.  The men who have done all my deliveries have been courteous and respectful of my home.
This last time when my McKenzie Queen Size Storage Bed needed assembly, they took extreme care with my new investment and its surroundings. 

If you are looking for quality furniture, make the drive across the river to Alton and shop New Frontiers Home Furnishings. When you're done, stop by Fast Eddies for a good cold beer.

I love the concept of this store- independent grocery store where I can buy organic. I know small stores have to charge more to make it than big big stores. I do t mind paying a little more to shop local but you have to be rich to shop here.

Edit: the one thing that is affordable here is the produce.

name: Chuck Baer Realty
categories: Real Estate, Home Services, Real Estate Services, Real Estate Agents, Property Management
text: They are a complete joke and totally inept.  STAY AWAY.  They are supposed to be managing my property and they don't respond to emails or phone calls.  I've had to call them multiple times over the last few months to set up my account and it still isn't done.  They are a complete mess.  Totally unprofessional.

name: Captain D's
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'DogsAllowed': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'False', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}"}
categories: American (Traditional), Fish & Chips, Seafood, Restaurants, Fast Food
text: I love fish.  I could live the rest of my life without meat as long as I have fish.  My husband doesn't like fish, so we have never dined-in at Captain D's.  Because my husband is wonderful and knows how much I love fish, he brings home a carry-out meal for me at least once per week.  I think each fish they serve varies from OK to absolutely delicious.  The portions tend to be large (except for some of the sides) and I can usually eat half of the meal the first day and finish the meal as my dinner the next day.  The staff has been kind and courteous each and every time my husband and I have gone through the drive-thru together, and according to my husband, they are just as kind each time he goes alone.  My personal favorite on the menu is the grilled tilapia meal, but so far I haven't tried anything I didn't like.  We don't usually buy appetizers when we eat out, but we do at D's.  I usually get the clam strips every time, and when they have the fried pickles, which sound gross but are heavenly for all of the salt lovers out there - like me. I usually get an order of the pickles every day - even when I'm not having D's for dinner.  Overall, Captain D's does a good job serving seafood in the middle of the country, at the same time as providing good service.  I know I will continue dining here all my days.  Cheers!

name: Willies Tire Shop
categories: Automotive, Tires
text: Unbelievably fast, professional, and affordable! Went in thinking I would need a new tire but my mechanic just patched me up and sent me on my way. Will be coming back any time I need work done on my car.

name: Villa Marie Winery & Banquet Center
categories: Food, Wedding Planning, Wineries, Restaurants, American (Traditional), Event Planning & Services, Arts & Entertainment, Nightlife, Bars, Wine Bars
text:
Arrived at 7:00 p.m.  last  Friday night  for a birthday party. 

First the pros: lovely setting by the lake very enjoyable.  

The cons: place is very poorly managed,  terrible service, bartender was alone with dozens of people waiting for drinks, waited 13 minutes to order a drink, no prices shown on the wine menu (?). I asked where the extra help was and he said another bartender was coming later. She did, however, then he left so the problem continued. 

Since the place is huge I asked where the birthday party was but the bartender did not know so we just had to walk around to find someone in the party we knew.  Our party planner had met with a VM rep and had a designated area for us. 

It was very telling that the parking spot right at the entrance was marked: MANAGER PARKING.  Another reviewer said the review from SP is actually the owner giving the winery 5 stars.  I get the picture.

categories: Bars, Nightlife, Restaurants, Dive Bars, American (Traditional)
text:
I don't know about the food since we arrived later in the evening - around 9:30. The place was packed with a variety of people. Mostly loud ones. Standing next to my friend I nearly had to shout at him. And that was just the crowd. It was hard to hear the music over the crowd. A true first for me. Everyone seemed to be having a great time, just couldn't get over the noise. 

The bartenders enjoyed taking the opportunity to ensure that the guys knew who they were and that they were working for tips, specifically their tips. The waitresses tended to ignore the tables that were not full of guys. I couldn't get her to stop to take our order. We had to rely on trips to the bar. Had about three drinks. Don't think I'll get the opportunity to have a fourth.

name: Cahokia RV Parque
categories: Hotels & Travel, RV Rental, Campgrounds
text:
So first time here. I chose it because I needed affordable tent site on my way up north. 
First off Apple direction were spot on. The site, a patch of grass, fire ring and picnic table. (Perfect)So no unusual wear and tear on my kit. You do not have some glorious view but I am not here for that besides this place is really about proximity so keep reading about the shuttle.
Pool looked fun but I was beat. 
Laundry was reasonable but make sure you bring liquid soap. No powder or crystals ( not sure on Pods.) 2.50w/2.00d
The whole place was clean and seemed well run. Showers are combination not coin driven, I have been burned by this so I asked. Believe me a plus. 
I missed the restaurant, looked great but closed at 8.
Met a sweet family traveling who shared some grilled chicken, touched my heart.  Local noises did drop off a lot after 10pm.
They offer a very reasonable round trip shuttle to St Louis. Looked like 10/20 depending on locations and a small up-charge depending on number of party. Not a big deal as it is round trip. 
All in All clean, looked well managed and located close to some great sites. Lots of happy campers were in my view.
WiFi worked but it is for all, so slow service makes sense but really get your faces out of the screens and live like we did in the 1990!
Anyways I am heading to the rack. All quite is at 10 and so far lots of respectful campers. 
That is what really make anyplace worth a stay so stay classy Yelpers!
Quick update: super clear showers and bathrooms
I was leaving and I believe I met the owner and without sounding too sappy, super nice and helpful with an unexpected need. A++ service I bumped it all the way to five!

name: LA Nails Studio
categories: Nail Salons, Beauty & Spas
text:
I went for a relaxing manicure and felt more stressed being there. The lady that did my nails was not friendly; she kept speaking in her native tongue to other employees, rushed through the massage part (which I was really looking forward to) and then left me to dry my nails for over 25minutes...she never checked on me...I couldn't even see if she was still in the building. I would've left earlier but I hadn't paid yet...I thought she'd at least want that. 

Even though the price was fine and the work was okay the service was horrible and I won't be going back.

name: Hampton Inn St. Louis-Columbia
categories: Event Planning & Services, Hotels & Travel, Hotels, Venues & Event Spaces
text: This is the second time we have stayed here. The facility is just as nice this time as it was a couple of years ago. We like staying here as it is a little off the main and seems to be quieter. The rooms are very nice, adequate space, clean and a clean duvet cover which is very important to us. The staff is very nice and helpful and I was greeted very warmly and recognized as an Honors member when I checked in. The breakfast staff did an amazing job on the second day we were there as a whole bus load of kids descended at the same time for breakfast. They cleaned out everything in sight and the staff had to really struggle to keep things full. Somehow they managed and the next day you could not tell that any of them we ever there. My only complaint was that they allowed someone with a puppy dog to walk around in the food area. I do not think hotels should allow dogs or any animal for that mater inside and certainly not in the food area.

attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'WiFi': "'free'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'False', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'CoatCheck': 'False', 'BusinessParking': 'None', 'HappyHour': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'HasTV': 'True'}
categories: Restaurants, Salad, Sandwiches, Delis
text: In my efforts to find food that is both delicious AND healthy (recently put on doctors  mandatory orders to eat a healthy diet) I've FINALLY made it to Mcalister's. A pleasant surprise! I expected decent healthy food. what I got was good food and service uncommon these days. You are greeted immediately when you enter and your order is taken and promptly delivered to your table. I dont think Ive ever waited more than 4 mins. I have actually gone back 3 days in a row.. and I dont generally like to eat the same stuff back to back. The Tables are always clean and They come out and refill my drink without my asking them to. They are attentive but not overly bothersome. I will definitely be returning.. often. If you are nearby and looking for a good option for lunch or dinner mcalisters is the place. Tell Em Joe Sent ya! (This will not mean ANYTHING or do ANYTHING for you and they will not know who the hell Joe is) but eventually if I go in and introduce myself they might say "OH YOUR Joe! You send EVERYBODY here! and maybe I will get a FREE sandwich!

name: Our Health Club and Spa
categories: Fitness & Instruction, Pilates, Massage, Day Spas, Beauty & Spas, Active Life, Yoga, Tanning, Gyms
text:
I have lived near this gym for quite some time and never stopped in. I finally decided to and I was pleasantly surprised. The facility was very clean and well laid out. They have a swimming pool and saunas in the locker rooms, which I absolutely love!

Their cardio selection is quite large. As for weights, it's got a good variety but it's not going to blow your mind or anything. That being said, if you can't do all the work you need to do in this place, that says more about you than the gym!

They also have a juice bar that is very reasonably priced and they will make you essentially whatever you want and it tastes great.

Finally, the manager, who I believe is Logan, was incredibly friendly. I talked to him on the way in and out and he made me feel welcome even though it was my first time. He was even kind enough to let me scan the ingredients he put into my smoothie so I could track calories.

Great experience and I will absolutely be back when I'm traveling!

name: Fantastic Sams
categories: Beauty & Spas, Barbers, Hair Salons
text: Let me go ahead and leave an updated review for anyone who may not have been here recently and the lack of talent they currently seem to have.  My poor mom went here yesterday to get a hair cut.  Jewels was the individual who cut her hair.  She dry cut (didn't shampoo or bother even dampening it). She turned my moms chair away so she couldn't see, my mom expressed concern in her lack of technique and the fact you CANNOT get hair even by dry cutting coarse, wavy hair, let me say it again, wavy hair????  How are waves going to lay even dry?  Anyhow, the girl ignored my poor moms pleas and continued to weed wack her hair.  She is now going to Aveda in Fairview to have it fixed by a professional.  While I will say, the manager offered for my mom to come in and they "could look at it", clearly she doesn't want to risk being butchered ANY farther.  So if you want a cheap trim and a ridiculous hair cut, this is your place.  If you want a great cut and style, I'd run so fast until your legs gave out to get away from this place!

name: Krupp Florist
categories: Florists, Shopping, Flowers & Gifts
text: Great designs! Very honest people! Great delivery guys & gals. Thanks for being our hometown Florist.

name: Country Estate Kennel
categories: Pets, Pet Sitting, Pet Groomers, Pet Training, Pet Services, Pet Boarding
text:
Good communication and compassion to all.
My dog was very clean and his hair was very nice and fluffy. The owner is very nice. The two men, Josh and Eric were very attentive to animals. my dog had a cleaner allergy reaction and the owner disclosed and has good follow up.

Make sure you check for allergies.
