name: Sammy Nail
categories: Beauty & Spas, Nail Salons
text: First time coming here and I wasn't really impressed. I did a manicure with gel nail polish. She soaked my nails in acetone, then scrapped the polish off with her nails vs a tool. Once she was done, she just got up and walked away. Then a man came over and just stuck his hand out to look at my nails. I guess they were switching people.. but of course they didn't inform me. I don't believe the equipment was sterlized either. My nails look great but the customer service was very medicore. I'd only come back if I was desperate to get my nails done. (Don't mind my uneven nails, I broke them before coming in)

name: Granite City Driver Services DMV
categories: Public Services & Government, Departments of Motor Vehicles, Restaurants
text: We went to the granite dmv rather than the edwardsville one as the people were somewhat snappy last time we were there. They were so nice at Granite and just super chill and friendly. We really appreciated it too! Thanks.

name: Jerry's Tire Sales
categories: Automotive, Tires
text: I have been going here for over 4 years now after living in other places and using other shops for my car needs. This place is by far the best.  They always seem to have the customer's needs as their primary concern.  They will not recommend that you pay for unnecessary parts or services. They also seem to sell quality components. If anything goes wrong they go out of there way to make it right. They are always very friendly and reasonable. It has been a great find for me.

name: Motel 6
categories: Hotels & Travel, Bed & Breakfast, Hotels, Event Planning & Services
text: The bed was mostly comfortable, the staff was friendly. One of our beds had a cigarette burn in it, the towels were dirty and we were in a smoking room but it really smell a lot like smoke like they never clean it out at all. Would not stay here again, felt like I could have caught something there. But it was cheap and you get what you pay for.

name: Klein's Brand Source
categories: Mattresses, Local Services, Shopping, Home & Garden, Appliances, Appliances & Repair
text: if you need a washer or dryer REPAIR count on it being out for a month!

name: Belleville Area Humane Society
categories: Animal Shelters, Pet Stores, Pets
text:
i gave them 3 stars because they do a good thing. now why i did not give them 2 extra stars. i decided i want a puppy. i wanted to go through a humane society. i found a dog a really wanted.keep in mind i already have a 18 year old cat and a 16 year old dog. 

1st-day--they said no, stating that we do not take care of the animals we got. hogwash. my dog is 16 how could she live that long if we don't take care of her. she did not get an optional shot. that at her age was not a big deal. so i asked if i got her the shot could i still get the dog. the girl said yes. so, i took the proof up there for them to see. 

2nd-day--they said that i had to take the older dog up there for a meet and greet with the new dog.when we walked in they had the dog i wanted in with another couple. being 16 she did not want anything to do with the younger dog. so the guy was a little rude about saying no. just rude enough to make me cry from disappointment.

i realize that they want the best for the animals.but  the application was like filling out a loan application. and it is almost easier to get a credit card than a dog from here. i would not discourage anyone from getting a dog from a shelter, even from this one. I think i will stick with going to st. Louis humane society, if you want a dog from here make sure you are married and have no other animals. 

BTW ......i did get a puppy off of craigslist. yes i did pay too much for a mutt(shepard mix). ($50) but he has been the best dog. i love him so much i had my fave tattoo artist tattoo a pic of him on my back. and somewhat gets along with all members of the family. human canine and feline.

name: Burger King
categories: Fast Food, Restaurants, Burgers
text: The chicken is so different from any burger king  that you would expect it does not taste the same it is gross to me.

name: Sweet Bakery Creations
categories: Bakeries, Food
text:
I came in on a Tuesday morning to get donuts for work. It was 730am and they didn't have any ready yet. Their excuse was they are closed Mondays. I've never heard of a bakery that doesn't start making donuts at 3am to have them ready for opening. I was already there so I decided to get a variety of cupcakes. They didn't have enough of any single flavor to get a dozen of the same kind. They were terrible! No one in my office liked them. Dry cake, browned crust from over baking, and poor flavor for icing. I tried two different kinds and it was the same for both. I was trying to be nice to coworkers but that was a big fail and they teased me telling me not to bring in anything from their again. 
This bakery had a second chance with a three layer, three flavor birthday cake a family member bought from them. Same review from several family members...dry, over baked, weird tasting icing... No one liked it. I was really hoping this place would be good since it so close to my house. Unfortunate.

name: MidAmerica St Louis Airport
categories: Transportation, Limos, Airports, Public Transportation, Airlines, Hotels & Travel
text: Better experience than last time.  Last time i flew out of here TSA was on a power trip but so far no problems

text:
At first glance I thought there would be a long wait to be seated since it seemed busy. I was surprised to be seated almost immediately. The food was delicious and authentic. I think the servings were decently sized. I was able to eat half and save the rest for a different time. I think from the time my family and I arrived and left about 30 minutes had passed. La Fonda will continue to receive our service in the future.

Changed rating to 4 stars. The service is still quick but I was quick to judge on how "authentic" the food is by one plate. I would say it is more Tex-mex.

name: Jack Schmitt Chevrolet of O'Fallon
categories: Auto Parts & Supplies, Auto Repair, Automotive, Tires, Car Dealers
text:
I drove away an hour ago with my newly detailed new-to-me Chevy Volt, and I could not be happier. Jack Schmitt is the second dealer we went to, but it should have been the first. We knew we wanted a Volt, and the first dealer we went to used a bait-and-switch internet ad to lure us in. We decided to keep looking and came across the perfect option at Jack Schmitt. Not only was the price similar to what we wanted at the other dealer, but we got leather, navigation, a back-up camera, and more for the price of a base model at the other place, and they did everything they could from a financing standpoint to get us the best interest rate and loan terms. 

We were already thrilled, but the awesomeness didn't end there. It had been raining when we test drove the car, so we hadn't noticed that one of the Volt decals was cracked (totally weird). Tim, who was not our sales person, but who helped us out as we were leaving, reminded us to come back to have the car detailed (it had been raining, so it hadn't been done). I pointed out the cracked decal and mentioned that it was going to bother me. Tim took note, and before I had a chance to come back in for detailing, he called to tell me a new decal had arrived. Today I brought the car back, and now it's completely perfect, new decal and all!

Everyone we worked with at Jack Schmitt Chevrolet was fantastic, from the non-pushy sales people to finance to the service department. They treated us right, gave us a great deal, and put us in a car we will love for many years to come. Two thumbs up from me!

name: Town Hall Archery

text: Really like this bow shop. I have purchased my latest bow there and they seemed like they really knew what they were talking about and was able to show me the best choice for what I was going to use my bow for. The prices are about in line with about everyone else and the indoor range is pretty nice. I have shot the range there several times which was great but I think that if you spend $1500 bucks for your entire set up you should be able to shoot in either range for free. There are lots of places that you can purchase your bows and accessories and I think you would like that customer that buys from you to keep coming back. All and all its a good place to go and the staff is knowledgeable and its close to where I live.

name: Catch 22
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'GoodForKids': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'Caters': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'"}
categories: Restaurants, Seafood
text:
Oh boy. Where do I start??

This is why people sneer and say, "Midwest? Oh, you can't get good seafood there." And as having lived my entire life in the Midwest, I always say, "Yes you can. You just have to know where to look." But not at Catch 22.

Catch 22 bills itself as an upscale restaurant. It certainly is with the price range, with the lowest entree on the menu being $11 and most of the entrees being in the high teens to $35. It definitely is not pretentious either in decor or manner. But I don't know if I would call it upscale. The decor is very minimalist, but doesn't do anything to the restaurant. It's as if someone painted, but forgot the decorating. It's also very dark. Not ambient or cozy, but dark. I actually give props to the serving staff for not bumping into things. It's very roomy in front, but the eating area is super crowded. I guess, part of it is how the building is, but it's just a weird setup. 

The serving staff is very nice, but they are very easily overwhelmed. I had hoped with them being in business for awhile, that this would work itself out, but not really. The more people, the more confused they become, especially if those people are in groups. I think part of it is also the kitchen staff because they are always behind. I've been there when people have left because the wait was too long. 

The menu now notes that sandwiches are not available after 4 pm. That's good. On one occasion, I tried to order a shrimp po'boy and was told smartly that they don't serve it at dinner. Well, it wasn't marked; I don't have ESP. On another occasion, a friend tried to order it and was told that they were out of it. Really? At lunch? Sigh. Now they're only open for lunch on Fridays and Sundays, and there's brunch offerings somewhere. Those po'boys are harder to find than a HP touchpad. 

All the dishes I've tried tend to be on the fishy side. I feel that most of the seafood has been previously frozen. The scampi is definitely generous on the butter. Oh yes, and I remember the first time I was there, they ran out of choices on the sides. 

I like the fact that it is not a chain, but I really wish the owner(s) would focus on a niche. Choose a couple of things, and make it stand out. Is it a bar? Is it a upscale restaurant? They're doing a chocolate lounge thing nowadays too, and honestly, there is no sense of identity anywhere.

name: Creekside Gardens
categories: Shopping, Nurseries & Gardening, Home & Garden
text:
This place is huge! Fair prices, excellent staff, amazing, unique selection and very well organized. 

 Most of the nursery is covered so you could even shop in the rain! The friendly laid-back women working here really know what they're talking about. 

 I found a huge selection of geraniums, impatiens, petunias and calibrachoa in more colors than I've seen anywhere else. Really unique coleus varieties, pink alyssum, pink leaf shamrock, and the list goes on. It's mostly about the flowers but no shortage of trees, shrubs, and anything else!

Annual 2 packs were $.84, 4-inch pots mostly $3.29, and prices went up from there. Slightly more expensive than large chains like Walmart, but well worth it for the selection and service! 

Creekside's greatest feature is their hanging baskets! Overflowing, they are hanging from every possible place. They also have pre-arranged pots which would make a great gift or give you ideas on how to arrange new plants in a pot or window box!

Bonus, the bathroom was super clean and decorated!

name: Valvoline Instant Oil Change
categories: Auto Repair, Oil Change Stations, Automotive
text: I was looking for a quick oil change as my past visits to Firestone and Walmart have taken well over 2 hours. If you're looking for fast and friendly service, this is the place. Many mechanics have tried to scam me in the past, thinking I'm a clueless woman who will pay for whatever they recommend, sometimes even doing repairs without asking my consent. This is not one of those places. I remained in my car the entire time and could observe what the mechanics were doing. Everything was thoroughly explained to me, including oil options and the benefits of each, as well as recommendations directly from my car's maker (Jeep). The entire process took 15 minutes. My husband thought the price might have been a little more than other places, but the 15% military discount, extremely quick service, and friendly, non-pushy, informative salesmanship made this a 5-star experience for me. This is my new go-to for car maintenance!

text: We recently hosted a 50th Anniversary Party at the Crystal Garden and I could not be happier with the venue.  They handled set up and clean up and the meal was AMAZING.  This is not your typical "banquet food."  The chicken piccata was fork tender, deliciously sauced & seasoned, and obviously cooked & served fresh.  The roasted veggies were firm and full of flavor, and the wild rice pilaf was perfect (not dry!).  Fresh bread rolls & salad to boot!  We brought in our own cake and paid the extra plate fee (which was discussed ahead of time). Honestly, they did such a nice job slicing & serving the cake, it was well worth the plating fee.  We also discussed centerpieces and room arrangement ahead of time & both were handled to my satisfaction.  My advice would be to simply make sure you discuss everything ahead of time.  Karol & Bill are lovely & very accommodating, but they are not mind-readers.  Make sure you cover the details & I'm sure your event will be a success!

text:

name: Tire Choice Auto Service Centers
categories: Tires, Automotive, Oil Change Stations, Auto Repair
text: I've been using this tire store for close to ten years now.  Their customer service and "expertise" has steadily gone downhill over the past year or so.  Today was the last straw.  For the THIRD time in a row, I have made and appointment for either oil change, tire rotation or whatever, only to show up on time and have them tell me, "Nope, we don't have you scheduled for anything today."  Each time I called and talked to them directly on the phone, confirming my appointment.  Their time is valuable.  So is mine! I can't afford to take time off work, just to have them tell me that I don't have an appointment.  Patronize them if you like.  I'm done.

attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': None}", 'Ambience': "{u'divey': None, u'hipster': None, u'casual': True, u'touristy': False, u'trendy': None, u'intimate': None, u'romantic': None, u'classy': None, u'upscale': None}"}
categories: Italian, Steakhouses, Restaurants
text:
The food was fine but the staff needs to familiarize themselves with the differences between the lunch and dinner menu. Both kitchen and waitstaff. Not a huge problem. For the price, I can deal with a little inconvenience. However, what I do NOT like having to deal with is watching the owner(? Manager? Not sure who he was) chastise the waitress publicly (who did great, she just seemed new to the job). This happened twice, in earshot of most of the customers, and is really unprofessional. Not for her, but for him. Take this kind of crap behind closed doors. I felt awful for her and embarrassed to have overheard their conversation, especially with the untone he took. Word of advice, if you want people to come back, treat your staff with kindness. Most people don't care if a waitress makes a small mistake. A good attitude can make you forget a lot of things. One thing that's hard to forget is bad management. If you want good people to work for you, you will need to treat your people with respect. Otherwise you will fail like so many other restaurants.

Round two: I don't know why we went back. Our waitress was not around because she admitted that she forgot all about us. We kept having to ask the bus boy for refills or whatever else we needed. He was awesome. The waitress was not. And, yet again, the manager was yelling at his employee as we left. The food was fine, and if they could get their act together they might have a chance but it is not looking promising.

name: Super 8 by Wyndham Waterloo
categories: Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Hotels & Travel
text: We stayed at this Super 8 last night. It was quiet and clean. They had the correct reservation. The lady who checked us in was efficient and personable. We had to leave about 5:30 this morning for business, so didn't try the breakfast. A lady was setting it up when I checked out and it looked like standard motel free breakfast offerings. My only complaint was people who had to leave earlier than us walking down the hallway talking. Folks, you aren't in your own home! Be quiet when you are in the public areas so early! Not the fault of this motel, though; just rude people who don't think.

categories: Tex-Mex, Restaurants, Mexican, Tacos, Fast Food, Breakfast & Brunch
text: I was in a hurry and I needed to grab some dinner. The girl at the counter was extremely friendly and quick to take my order. The food was quick to be delivered. That is where the goodness stopped. The tacos were so greasy, my stomach hurt for the rest of the evening. .... Taco Bell please take the time to drain the grease.....

The place is a hopping place, but perhaps a bit too much, as it took forever to get a beer from the bar. And even though the music was great, the place is really loud. You can't really talk to someone without yelling at least on the night we were there. 

The best thing was the pizza which I would definitely recommend. Still, I'd be hard pressed to go back when you have to wait (for an eternity or so it seems) to get a beer at a brewery. That's just crazy.

categories: Restaurants, Italian
text:
This was a rough dinner. We arrived and the front door was locked, even though they were open and we could see people inside.  Maybe that should've been our sign to go, but we walked in through Shenanigans, which is attached.  

We ordered, and my wife's Caesar salad came out first, but it was so smothered in dressing, you literally had to scrape some off e lettuce and spinach to taste it.  Then as she was near finished with her salad, my spinach calzone came out, but it had to go back because the cheese inside was still uncooked.  So it came out again. And was cooked, but my wife was already done eating, and when I bit into the calzone, it had almost NO sauce, only cheese and the vegetables.  The only thing in there less than the sauce was the spinach...wait, wasn't this supposed to be a spinach calzone?  

So long story short, the wait staff was somewhat apologetic, but nothing was done to try to make it up.  All in all, I was unimpressed.  It wasn't awful, it just wasn't good.

categories: American (New), Restaurants, Burgers, Breakfast & Brunch
text: We went here for lunch today..if you like HORRIBLE FOOD and SERVICE this is the place to go..the server that seated us took us to our booth and plopped the menus down on the table and walked away without saying a word to us..I ordered Rib Eye Steak and it was so bland and full of fat..it said your choice of potato came with it but when I said I wanted a baked potato the server said only after 4pm..do ovens not work before 4pm???..so I ordered the American Fries which some of them were so hard I couldn't eat them and some were not cooked all the way and were raw..the salad was so so..huge chuck of cucumber and tomato which I am guessing the kitchen did not want to cut up..the husband ordered the BBQ Ribs..he said they tasted like they were reheated from the day before..the bbq sauce was not cooked on the ribs but just poured on as an after thought..the roll was in a sealed package which I have never seen at any other restaurant before..the service was just as horrible as the food..our server spilled tea on my husband's napkin and silverware when pouring it into his glass..she gave no apology or cleaned up the spilled mess..she just walked away..when she brought out the food she spilled some of his mixed vegetables on the table and again no apology..the customers at the booth behind us sent their food back..they said the potatoes were raw and the bacon on the BLT was so hard they couldn't eat it..we had eaten at this place about a year ago and it was a decent place to eat..not now..we both brought home way over half of the horrible meal to give to our dogs but decided we did not want to subject them to this horrible food as it upset both of our stomachs after we ate what little of it we did eat..so it was thrown in the trash..a hard lesson learned today..we will not be going back to this place.

attributes: {'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Caters': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
categories: Pizza, Restaurants
text:
First, let's talk about the food. The pizzas we got were piping hot but really, they smell better than they taste. They weren't bad; they just had virtually no flavor. Nothing special, and frankly, a tad pricey for being so bland.

My other problem was with the means of payment. I ordered online and submitted, but somewhere in submission, the order software erased all of my delivery information and defaulted to a carry out order. I'm tech savvy, and this app took me nearly 30 minutes to order between hopping between options and different menu items. Regardless, I noticed and called them immediately. The kid on the phone changed this to delivery but then called me back saying he needed my credit card to add the delivery fee. Now, I'm in a business that does delivery. Had we already had a customer with some hassle, who had to call in, hung up and then you have to call him/her back for credit card info for a delivery fee...yeah, I probably would've said forget the delivery fee this time. Didn't happen, and that's okay. I have no issue paying for what I get. However, the kid, apparently, charged the whole thing to my credit card, and without realizing this had happened, I gave the driver cash to pay for it. Now, through all this, we got this situation settled, and my boyfriend went to pick up my cash the following week. However, my money sat there for two-to-three days. I had to call them when I contacted my credit card company about the TWO charges on my credit card---once a partial payment of $10---which is what I had intended all along--through the app and once for the WHOLE amount...AND they had my cash. When I called Sunday to talk to someone, I was told no manager would be in until Monday at 11 but he would leave a message to call me. Well, my lunch hour rolled around---well after 1:30 PM, and the charges were still there, they still had my money, and I'd still not heard from a manager. So...I called my credit card company. They 3-way'd in the manager, and we talked about it. He said he was confused why I'd sent cash, but instead of calling me, they just stuck it in the safe....for three days. They had my number on my order, in the computer, and to call me back to charge me for delivery, but no one thought to call when the driver returned with cash, and they were confused? Regardless, we picked up the cash, and the partial payment wasn't charged to my card after all was worked out. 

Being in business, myself, I can absolutely appreciate them handling a sticky situation professionally. That is what got the extra two stars. The lack of action regarding that issue and the not-so-hot pizza only garnered the one.

text: Where kid can be a kid! This place is old. It smells old but they manage to keep the games/machines up to date. They even took out the playground area and put in bumper cars. Downfall is if you're there during off peak times where there's only a few kids there others cannot use because there's not enough kids to fill the cars. Every time I've been in here, there have been many tables that are dirt and left alone without anyone cleaning it up for a good hour. That's disgusting. When the people leave or they're done eating, the staff should clean it up immediately. Tokens here cost 33 cents but if you spend 30$ it cost 25 cents. Each machine requires only one token but games last for less than 30 seconds. The characters on stage need to be replaced and cleaned up. They look so scary up close lol

name: Barnes & Noble
categories: Toy Stores, Bookstores, Books, Mags, Music & Video, Shopping, Video Game Stores
text: I guess I'm the exception but when I go TO a bookstore, I expect to find books. Upon searching the kiosk for several new releases by authors they carry in-store, nothing was available. It was the most useless trip to a bookstore, period. I didn't check the minor racks at Walmart or Target. I decided to go to a BOOKstore. Yet, these items were nowhere to be found. I understand if they were older titles or rare, but that wasn't the case. I give the 2 stars because the cashier was very friendly, and I was able to buy two random gifts there. No, they weren't books or book related. Sad, huh?

name: Ross Dress for Less
categories: Women's Clothing, Fashion, Home Decor, Home & Garden, Department Stores, Shopping, Discount Store, Men's Clothing
text: I wasn't terribly thrilled with Ross. I plan I giving them another shot, but upon our first visit, we were shopping for Special Needs ladies for a chaperoned summer trip. Their plus size availability was dismal. It was mainly work out pants. We had to have those two ladies wait until we went to a different store, like Cato, so we could find them appropriate outfits. My biggest complaint was trying on clothing. As staff, each of us was assigned to two ladies. Because two were plus sized and had nothing to try on, we had three staff members to help four ladies. However, we were absolutely smothered by the staff and security at the dressing rooms. I understand controlling loss. However, because we needed to but three full outfits for each lady and had multiple options for both tops and bottoms, the incredibly strict number of items made this a very difficult trip. We didn't want to steal anything! We just wanted to compare the blue and black tops!  You also couldn't be IN the dressing room without a number on a card saying how many items you have. We were assisting ladies with special needs that needed help putting certain things on or whatnot. Because they were changing it was difficult to switch pieces in and out to keep our number of items IN the dressing room to six or less, and by insisting we have the "number of items" card while in the dressing room, we finally had to have all three staff with one lady at a time. We couldn't take the "0" "number of items" card outside of the dressing room with us, so when I ventured out into the store for a replacement top and came back to a totally different attendant, I got to explain myself and the situation all over again. The folks at Burlington also preferred six items or less but understood what we were doing AND the situation and worked with us. They were present but not hovering, overbearing, and difficult to work with. Stopping at Ross added an extra hour and a half to our trip merely because of the hoop jumping in the dressing room.

text: If I could give 20 stars, I would. I had another seamstress basically destroy my wedding dress and Carol at Alexandra's fixed everything. She spent her time really looking at how the dress should fit my body and made sure I was on board with her suggestions and made sure it was how I wanted it to look. My dress was absolutely perfect when I picked it up. People raaaaved about my dress and it's all thanks to Carol! Not to mention she had sooo much work to do and was a fraction of the price. I'll be a customer for life!

name: Queen's Cuisine
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': True, 'casual': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForMeal': 'None', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True'}
categories: British, Tea Rooms, Event Planning & Services, Coffee & Tea, Venues & Event Spaces, Food, Cafes, Restaurants, Bakeries
text:
We recently tried Queen's Cuisine for the first time, based upon a newspaper article I had read, supplemented by online reviews.  It is in a small building in downtown Edwardsville; they have a very small parking lot, but allow a few extra minutes to find parking if that is full.

There were several interesting choices on the menu, with food items not commonly seen elsewhere.  I had the Cornish pasty, which was very good: a tasty filling with a mild but distinct flavor, surrounded by a crispy crust.  The House Side Salad was also good, with a mild balsamic vinegar dressing.  I had English Breakfast tea, which was steeped in a nice large-one-serving tea pot. 

My wife had the "Bit of Everything" (the contents of which can be found in the Queen's website's online menu), and found it to be quite good.  She had a seasonal tea, which she also liked.

We shared two desserts: a Victorian layer cake, and a lemon-blueberry scone; both were quite tasty, and unusual.  We also tried the "clotted-cream", and a lemon garnish; both added to the dessert experience, at least with our particular two items.

Service was quite good on this not-too-busy day; we arrived for our 12:30 reservations, with few other diners present.  A few other groups came in by 1 PM.  An oddity, is ordering up at the counter, but having the food brought to the table when ready.  I would have preferred full table service, but perhaps this setup is common in England.

The decor was simple but tasteful, with British photos and items on display.

Prices were moderate, in line with other "nice" lunch places.

There is also an afternoon tea offered on certain days; we plan to try that at some time.

Overall, we enjoyed Queen's Cuisine, and plan to return when we want a rather unique food experience.

text: Who Runs out of Hamburger Buns at 6pm on a Friday night?  Needless to say, my husband and I arrived on 4/22/2016.  The specialty burger with sauerkraut caught my husband's eye.  First words out the waiter's mouth, we are out of buns and do not have sauerkraut.  But someone has just left to get buns..okay.. He then went on to explain many of the menu items may not be available because he menu is incorrect or something of the sort.  He was super nice and really tried to make up for the fact that management and the kitchen were lacking to say the least.  When my side order of waffle fries did not arrive, the waiter blamed it on the kitchen.  He said she said I believe is the excuse.  They were rushed out however before I was able to finish my wrap.  The food was okay, Bacon cheeseburger for my husband and I go the fiery chicken wrap, 1 hour later. Yep it really took that long. Guess it was the errand of getting more buns.  The homemade ranch dressing is very good.  On a side note, a friend of mine with a party of 12 were seated near us on the patio.  When we left they still had not had their salads.  Apparently they were seated and forgotten about.  OUCH!

name: Best Western Plus Pontoon Beach
categories: Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Hotels & Travel
text: We were in the area for a invitational race. Didn't want to stay in St. Luis so we decided to drive the approximately 10 miles from the race park to Poontoon Beach. Our Room was clean, but a little dated. The Shower did not have much water pressure, but was useable. I do wish they had left more towels in the room. Beds were a little hard in my opinion and I am used to a firm mattress. Breakfast was always clean, and hot. The lady who keeps everything prepared was super friendly and remembered we were there for the races. Check in was a breeze, parking could be a bit of a challenge with a pick-up and trailer IF they are booked up. We were here for 3 nights on a weekend. (TFS) and the rooms have been quiet, with little to no noise. Considering there is a Police Department in front of the hotel, and there are several other hotels in the area there was not little to no traffic in the area.

name: Mueller Veterinary Services
categories: Veterinarians, Pets
text: I had Mueller Veterinarian Services out for the second time in the last 3 years today and once again I was extremely impressed! Dr. Mueller has a great team with his assistant Audrey (and today there was a gentleman named Kevin who is completing an externship). I like that Dr. Mueller takes the time to explain what he's doing to my animals and he's always very helpful and nice about answering my many questions. He castrated two of my pet Scottish Highlander bulls and floated the teeth of one of my mares etc.... he's very knowledgeable and professional and friendly I will always use him! I like that he informed us of our options but let's us make the decision & doesn't put pressure on you and respects your choices (we are very careful w vaccinations). The first time he was out he castrated my gelding and My Pet Goat :-) both of which are doing great we have never had any issues!

name: McKendree Metro Rec Plex
categories: Fitness & Instruction, Swimming Pools, Skating Rinks, Active Life
text:
This place is brand new but the layout is very strange. There is only one row of cardio equipment on the top level, many of them have a great view of the drywall. The functional fitness area is small and lacks a lot of the basic equipment one might find (like jump ropes!) 

What's with the tiny locker rooms? No sauna? Not to mention the locker rooms are adjacent to the pool so it's always hot and humid in there, even with the fan they stuck in there. 

I do like the weight room, and unfortunately that's about it. I come here because it's close by.

categories: Pet Services, Pet Sitting, Pets, Pet Groomers, Animal Shelters, Pet Boarding, Pet Adoption
text:
I love Spencer Pet Rescue for the great work they do taking in homeless dogs and cats and finding them homes.

I adopted my two dogs from Spencer.  Spencer is very easy to work with, and adoption was a breeze.  Of course, you need to submit an application and be chosen as a match to get your new pet. 

They post their available pets on PetFinder so you can look over the animals available for adoption before coming for a visit.

I haven't used Spencer Kennel's boarding services yet, but I'll update if I do.

categories: Golf, Active Life, Restaurants
text:
I went golfing at the course today for the second time, and I had a BLAST!
Knowing last night that today would be a gorgeous day, my friends and I decided on going golfing somewhere near St. Louis. Our criteria for the ideal location was somewhere inexpensive (including golfing with a cart--as we're immatures/amateurs), somewhat close, not too crowded, and somewhere where we could enjoy the sunshine. This Far Oaks Golf Club fit the perfect bill for all of these.
We were able to book a tee time without any difficult for mid-afternoon. We each paid only $22 for 18 holes, and this price included the cart fee! 
In terms of golfing, we had an challenging though incredible amount of fun. We got better as the day went along, and I think part of why we could get better was because the course is difficult but not outlandish. There are red, white, blue, and black tees; we chose the white which offered a very fair challenge for our skillset (well...lack thereof). The course weaves in and out of neighborhoods with beautiful houses, and there are several dog-legs both left and right. The par 3s were my favorite because birdies are doable on all of them--and I even got one! 
The course was not crowded on this day, and I doubt it is crowded most days as it is somewhat out in the middle of nowhere. Our group of 4 allowed a few groups to play through us, and we still finished in about 4.5 hours. Like the previous reviews stated, there are no/few marshalls, but that didn't affect us negatively at all.
The club inside has a large food and drink selection, and the golf shop is everything you'd expect it to be. One thing I didn't see out on the course was a water stand, which would have been nice. Other than that though, no real complaints from this guy.
Great job, Far Oaks! I'll be back shortly!

name: The Cup
categories: Desserts, Bakeries, Food, Cupcakes
text: I've never had a bad experience with the Cup. I frequently buy cupcakes there for special occasions, and they are consistently delicious. My favorite flavors: Confetti, Salted Caramel Crunch, Touchdown, Smores, Ruby, Rally Cup, Mummy, Hope, and the Grasshopper. Don't be afraid to try new flavors, as I've never been disappointed by one, except for perhaps the red velvet cake, which wasn't bad, just not as rich and overwhelmingly delicious as some of their other options.

But, I will continue to shop here because I love it so much and the owner seems super nice. They are opening up a kids store soon and I have a feeling that I will fall in love with that store too.

categories: Italian, Chicken Wings, Restaurants, Pizza
text:
I have been to a handful of Pizza Hut buffets and this one the worst. No one was present to seat me when I walked in, so I just took a seat and waited. I eventually had to go up to the counter when I saw someone there to order a drink. The woman working was nice enough - it's not her fault that there only appeared to be 2 people working. It was a pretty rough go though. 

The tables were dirty but had place settings on them. I chose one that looked clean but had a general stickiness that made me uneasy. 

The pizza was as good as any other Pizza Hut so give it a shot if you like their food. Maybe I just caught them on a bad day.

name: DIRECTV
categories: Television Service Providers, Home Services, Shopping, Electronics, Professional Services, Internet Service Providers
text: This is what you get to watch each time it rains with direct tv.  Horrible reliability.

It's got old school "cheers-like" bar decor, lots of regulars of all ages and decent food.  I have not tried the pizza, but the customers rave about it.  Like all Illinois bars, it is nonsmoking.

categories: American (Traditional), Seafood, Restaurants, Steakhouses
text:
The location is nice. The service was OK, but not really considering the bill we got at the end (more on that later). Long story short, we ordered two specials without knowing the price, but expecting to pay around $30, considering what was on the menu. We got our meals after about 45 minutes. Mine (Beef Wellington) was just OK, but was too salty, and the mushroom sauce tasted like it was from a packet, from the crusty mushroom bits to the msg aftertaste. My wife's (Lobster Ravioli) was inedibly salty, which is a shame because it was edible otherwise. 

The real surprise came when we got the bill - my dish was $55, my wife's was $35, for a total bill with tip of $120. I take responsibility for not asking the price of the dish, but the fact that a $120 dinner for two was inedible left a really bad taste in my mouth.

name: Shiloh Chiropractic
categories: Health & Medical, Chiropractors, Physical Therapy
text: 5 stars...because 6 is not an option.  Outstanding service supported by phenomenal staff!  Professional, courteous, and efficient best describes this business.

name: 1st Street Lounge
categories: Bars, Nightlife, Lounges, American (Traditional), Pubs, Restaurants, American (New)
text: Tried their chicken adobo tacos tonight. Food looked and tasted fresh. Chicken seasoning was very good. The chips tasted like they were freshly made. Overall it was a wonderful experience. The staff was also super friendly. I'll definitely be back!

name: Five Guys
categories: American (Traditional), Restaurants, Burgers, Fast Food
text:
I'm rating them so low for the absurd value disparity. Was the food good? Yes. Worth the money? No.
I got the small burger ($7+) a drink and some peanuts (no charge on them). Burger reminded me of a larger Steak N Shake sandwich. Interior of this restaurant is similar to Freddy's. Everything is self serve. Rock music is way too loud. But the prices: $10+ for the regular sized cheeseburger, $4 for small fries, $3 for soda, add tax and modest tip and you're over $20! I'll spend half that somewhere else and be just fine.

name: Dobbs Tire And Auto Center
categories: Auto Repair, Automotive, Oil Change Stations, Tires
text: I had a belt break and took it to Dobbs where they changed the belt, thermostat, and water pump in August. On my way home in December I had car issues and took it to a mechanic back home. Dobbs had used a cheap thermostat that had busted and was not regulating my engines temperature. They also after raking up a large bill tried to sell me more than I needed. Never going back again.

name: US Nail Salon
categories: Nail Salons, Beauty & Spas
text: Love this place!  Friendly staff, good prices, got me in quick! I will come back here again and again!  My experience was so great that I got my mom, dad, and sister to come too.  Now we all choose US Nails as the place for our manis and pedis!

It appears that it is under a new manager and the server, Madison was outstanding. It was very busy and almost every table was full, that being said, she provided a great customer service and our food came out quickly and hot.  The server Madison was so good, that I actually ask to speak with the manager to let him know how great her service was. 

I had the double steak burger and a cup of chili. Both were very good.

text:

I believe she was the same person who performed the preliminary test before we actually saw Dr Ernst, who (whom?) was great with my very nervous 5 yr old. He was patient, kind, and put her at ease. 

Overall the facility was nice, the personnel were phenomenal and I'm looking forward to taking the rest of the family.

name: Lux Nail Spa
categories: Nail Salons, Beauty & Spas
text:
My mom and I decided to go here on a Sunday to get pedicures. She had heard a few good things about the place so we decided to venture over and I am so glad we did! On first glance, the shop is not the most aesthetically pleasing--posters of hands and feet with glammed out nails were covering every wall and there was an odd fountain in the corner. However, the looks shouldn't deter you from the great service! There were around 8 people working at the time and we were quickly seated and drawn hot water. I asked for hot water, but when it was too hot to put my feet in, the woman who was doing my moms pedi (later I found her to be the owner) quickly rushed over and put in some cold water to even the temperature. There was a decent selection of polish, however I've seen better options. Mostly OPI though so definitely quality colors. 

Down to the quality--the young girl who did my nails was super talkative and friendly and my mom and I absolutely loved getting to know her! The pedi itself was spectacular as well. For $20 we got a basic pedi which included nail trim, cuticle care, skin care, massage, hot towel, and polish. Not to mention the time that was spent--each of our sessions lasted about 30 min and great care was taken to be sure we knew what would be going on each step of the way. We definitely will be coming back in the future to Lux!!

name: LaDrew Automotive
categories: Auto Repair, Transmission Repair, Automotive, Wheel & Rim Repair, Auto Customization
text:
This is the best service shop in the Metro East.  Chris is one of the top mechanics around.  He used to be the manager of the Valvoline around the corner for years.  He is an honest man in a dishonest industry.  Finally, he is a "car guy".  Go in and ask him about his chevelles, you'll make a friend.

He maintains both my cars.  He also keeps my oldest sons car running in top condition.  He maintains my fiancées van as well.  I would not trust so many family members lives with Chris if he were not top notch.

Finally, he is never over estimate and times he can the best fix or the cheaper alternative depending on your budget.

name: Eagle Coin Stamp & Jewelry
categories: Local Services, Watch Repair, Jewelry, Jewelry Repair, Shopping, Gold Buyers
text:

name: Sears Outlet
categories: Appliances & Repair, Local Services, Shopping, Appliances, Home & Garden, Outlet Stores, Mattresses, Furniture Stores
text: A very well-organized outlet store.  We were very surprised by the wide variety of washers and dryers they had available.  We were very grateful that the sales staff didn't try to rush us as we made our decision on new appliances.  Prices were very favorable.  We were able to find close-out items that were not returned or scuffed.  Check-out was efficient and the salesman answered all the questions that we had.  I prefer to shop here away from the local mall.  Much more parking and it's a lot closer to the front door.

name: Buffet City
categories: Restaurants, Chinese
text:
I'm sorry, but I've been here twice at different times and found the food to be disgusting. I will definitely not be going back.  All of the food had a general sogginess to it.  One dish was simply some kind of cubed meat that you would ordinarily find inside a low quality Mexican dish. 


I'm by no means a food snob, so don't think I'm writing this off simply because it's a Chinese buffet.

categories: American (Traditional), Restaurants
text: Solidly good fried chicken. I wish I could give it 5 stars but occasionally it is dry and not very fresh in spite of the place being busy. The chicken would benefit from a brine. Still the chicken is good, the coating crunchy and you receive a good value for the cost. The white box is an excellent value. The simple stand and the low prices make it a solid choice. There is enough chicken to share, and if you order an additional side it is easily a meal for 2 people. The mushrooms are delicious. Bring cash, like most of the good local places in Alton, they annoyingly only accept cash payment.

name: Wendy's
categories: Restaurants, Fast Food, Burgers
text: Food is ok, but the service is the slowest I have seen. If you see more than three cars in the drive-thru, go inside.

name: Sip & Chew Express
categories: Sandwiches, Breakfast & Brunch, Restaurants, Coffee & Tea, Soup, Comfort Food, Desserts, Food
text: This place just opened... It is wonderful! I had some business at the courthouse and stopped in afterwards... Walked out with a Chai latte that could probably use another shot of espresso which I will ask for next time I'm in there... It's a cute little place... They serve breakfast and lunch along with coffee. At the time I was in there, they were having a special Caribbean lunch deal... I did not have time for lunch, but I sure do like my latte! I definitely plan to return.

attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'Caters': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'"}
categories: Restaurants, Italian, Specialty Food, Hot Dogs, Food
text: Tried Tasty's today because I read about it in the newspaper.  Ordered the Italian sausage with fries and drink.  About $8.??  Lady at the counter was nice but I had to wait longer than usual and the apparent owner had to tell her I had been standing there a while.  The food came out fast, which is about the only thing I can say good about the place.  The sausage was luke warm.  Did not appear to have been grilled.  Probably boiled earlier, then microwaved before they gave it to me.   Didn't see that but no grill marks.  The sausage was only fair.  The french bread it was on was the best part of the meal.  The french fries were disgustingly limp and soggy with little flavor.  I am not sure how they accomplished that.  T Had a Sprite soda with the meal.  For a brand new soda dispenser the drink was very flat and I threw it away.  The place did appear to be clean, but I doubt I'll be back.

text: I have been to The Boarding House multiple times and I have loved every experience. It is a great place for a girls' night or a date night. categories: Steakhouses, American (Traditional), Buffets, Restaurants
text:
Mid day lunch!!! I know some people are not fans of buffets for various reasons. Me on the other hand.... if the place is clean and the food is fresh and plentiful, I'm in! My family and I have patronized this location for some time now so the idea to have lunch here was a no brainer. I'm sure everyone is familiar with the set up of a buffet style restaurant. You seat yourself, choose whatever food you wish to have while a server refills your drinks. Nothing fancy. The restaurant was clean as it always is. Our server, Tiff was quick to stop by and introduce herself. Now it's time to chow down and this is where the disappointment begins.....
Fried Chicken = Dry
Roast Beef = Dry
Bourbon Chicken = Burnt
Corn = Bland
Fish = Bland
I did enjoy the banana pudding and the Rice Krispie treats! Again, this is a place that I go to often and I'm sure I will go again. For some reason the food today was simply not up to par.

text:
This is a typical high end club.What I mean is the decor and environment is what you would expect. Food prices are high,  and quality could be better. My salad could have been fresher, baked potato not so over cooked, meat without so much fat, etc...

Don't bother going early as most of the dancers do not show up until after 9:30 to 10 pm. They will quickly try to get you to agree to a lapdance at the $40 a song price. Some of the girls are very good looking,  most are average.

In my opinion don't go to the St. Louis area for adult entertainment. Spend your money elsewhere. Maybe an escort from backpage would be a better alternative if you dare.

attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'DogsAllowed': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Caters': 'False', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True'}
categories: American (Traditional), Fast Food, Fish & Chips, Seafood, Restaurants
text:
I can't say too much about a place that serves seafood at a fast food restaurant because the two should not be in the same sentence.  Good seafood is not fast food.  Just saying!!!  
Well, anyway, this place is not that bad for a drive thru.  We considered this place for late Sunday evening (8/12) meal.  It was a toss up between this or Popeyes.   Fairview Heights cop that pulled over a motorist and, of all places, motorist pulled in Popeyes parking lot.   So, off to D's since it was across the street.  Guy at the ordering speaker was pleasant in taking our order even though we took our time deciding.  At the window, the same gentleman, greeted us nicely and asked what sauce we wanted.  I had said reds sauce, ketchup and was not sure what else so the gentleman offered tartar to go with the fish and malt vinegar, (never heard of such a thing), and honey mustard.  The amount of food we ordered, all his suggestion complimented the meal.  It was kind of him to help us out.  Food came out hot and smelling awesome.  The fries just came out of the fryer.  Service was great but food was not so great.  Thin portion of fish-almost like long fish sticks.  The stuff crab was decent but the skewered grilled shrimp was so so.  Without the good window customer service, it would have been a 2 star.  As such, I would say the place is ok!

text: Best coffee ever. Crystal is the sweetest server and always remembers my order. I stop by there every chance I get.

name: Best Buy Fairview Heights
categories: Electronics, Shopping, Department Stores, Fashion, Computers, Home & Garden, Appliances
text:
My AT&T DSL router died and rather than spending an ungodly amount to have them ship me one overnight, I discovered that this Best Buy had one in stock (the other Best Buys did not).  I ordered online and did the in-store pickup option.

Ordering was a breeze and when the beautiful wife and I arrived at the store, we were quickly helped and on our way.

The staff that we interacted with were both super nice and friendly.

From Downtown St. Louis, it was a pretty straight shot on I-64 to get here.  Not any worse than going to Brentwood.

name: Pine Tree Laundromat
categories: Laundromat, Laundry Services, Local Services, Dry Cleaning & Laundry
text:
First, and foremost, there are plenty of functioning washers and dryers which are clean. I don't expect anything more, or less, from a coin-op laundry; but, you do get more here: friendly staff, a clean environment, plenty of seating (and even a table to eat at), a VERY clean restroom, a children's play area, and lots of oscillating fans to keep you cool.

I read a review that complained of being asked if she'd been here before, which I find odd since, generally, a courteous employee will want to make sure you know where to find things and are all set to wash. Second, a reviewer complained about being told, "no loads after 8:30" - but, that's posted, clearly, on each entry door.

Overall, I'd go out of my way to come back here if in town again and needed to do laundry.

name: Lou Fusz Preowned Center Metro East
categories: Car Dealers, Automotive, Auto Repair, Auto Parts & Supplies
text: I came in looking to test drive a KIA Optima. After Learning that it had just been sold Tim took me to his desk and showed me other availability for the same vehicle at other locations and told me he could order it in. I then asked about another vehicle that was on the lot. I test drove it and after a few hours I ended up taking it home. Tim made the process easy and fast! I didn't expect to go home with a new vehicle at all that day. He got me the best offer possible and made sure I was well taken care of. I highly recommend this place. Ask for Tim Heatherly. Tell him Excel sent ya.

text: I took a 16 year old family member here on 1/13/18. The counselor was great and very sensitive to the child's age and mental state. The male Indian M.D. who saw her was rough, insensitive, and disrespectful. He treated her like trash and was completely unapologetic about it. He yelled and screamed out in the hallway! I felt this man had no respect for women at all. I would not recommend this clinic to any woman it's a nightmare!

name: Troy Veterinary Clinic
categories: Pets, Veterinarians
text: I am a client of Hawthorne Troy, but Troy Veterinary Clinic opened up and they seemed pretty good about not charging an office visit, or a tiny office visit fee, for little things like heartworm tests and vaccinations. I took my dog there to do a heartworm test once. However, when our sweet boy Zeke was at the end of his time we called both vets to see who would be more reasonably priced for the 'procedure'. Hawthorne was a little pricier, but Troy Vet Clinic wanted us to pay an office visit fee for them to see him before they would agree to the 'procedure'. We opted for Hawthorne, and we were glad. They were so kind and respectful during that very difficult time. Now, we're watching my sister's dog for an extended time and we want to get his shots and heartworm test. So, Troy Clinic was going to be more reasonable than Hawthorne (minimal office visit fee when doing vaccinations). So, even though we had been put off by their attitude with our Zeke situation, off we went to Troy Vet Clinic. They had never seen this dog. They have only seen my other dog for a heartworm test, so we don't really have a feel for the staff there, and I've never even met the vet. Although, when I stopped in a while back to get some heartworm medicine, I spoke with the girl at the front desk and was told that my brand of choice had been discontinued but that they had Heartgard. I asked her if the active ingredients in the Heartgard are the same as the ones in my old brand, as I knew my dog's system did well on the old brand. I could see by the flash of inner confusion on the girl's face that she had no idea what the active ingredients were. However, she must have decided that it was easier to come up with an answer than to try to figure it out, so she piped up "Yes!". When I asked her what that active ingredient was, she got that confused look again. So, I gave her my best "You just LIED and we both know it" look. I checked, no they aren't the same. I guess it's a good thing that I was asking because I'm overprotective and not because my dog is freakishly allergic, because that invented answer could have been a big problem. So, needless to say, the staff at Troy Vet Clinic haven't earned our trust yet. The vet tech who saw us for our vaccinations was extremely young and unsure. She announced that she would take my dog to the back to do all the vaccinations and the heartworm test, and I very politely stated that I wished to remain with him while they did what they needed to do. That startled her. She said all her equipment was in the back room, so I offered to follow her to the back room, or suggested that she could bring her 'equipment' to the exam room. She went mildly fluttery and stuttery and had to go out and check with someone else. She returned to tell me that I could not remain with my pet because it was against policy. She cited insurance issues as the reason. I was adamant about not turning my pet over to people who were increasingly causing me alarm, and my husband was very upset. He explained to her that the dog is part of our family and that the staff had done nothing to earn our trust yet. Some discussion later, we ended up leaving vowing never to return. The staff just doesn't exhibit the regard for our family members that we feel they should. So, skip forward a few days. I receive a certified letter from the vet at Troy vet clinic saying that yada yada obviously we are unhappy with their service and don't trust them yada yada yada and we should find a new vet. No kidding? That's just what I was thinking. I absolutely DON'T trust them with my beloved animals, and I absolutely WILL find a different vet. There was absolutely no chance that I was ever going back there, but they felt it necessary to spend $6.11 to send a certified letter divorcing themselves from a potential client, essentially trying to punish me for being a voice and advocate for the members of my family who have no voice. I find their behavior extremely disturbing, very arrogant, and not at all in the best interest of pets and the people who love them. I will heartily recommend AGAINST Troy Veterinary Clinic and Dr. Julie Mears to anyone who asks. I miss my old vet who didn't charge outrageous office visit fees when they weren't needed, who greeted my dog with a big smile and open arms, and who I trusted to treat her with love and respect at all times, whether I was there watching over his shoulder or not. I miss my old vet whose goal was healthy happy animals not paying off his student loans or shuffling as many dogs as possible through his office every day. I miss my old vet who spoke to me about my dog's care, not in little placating words, but about research and biology and physiology. If anyone knows a vet like that in the area, please let me know. In the meantime, if you're in Troy, I recommend you visit Hawthorne Animal Hospital (and I recommend them over Troy Vet Clinic without ever having met the new vet at Troy Hawthorne!).

text:
We've eaten at other Joe's pizza restaurants and this one is similar. Not the largest dining room and tables fairly close but adequate. Place seemed clean and cheery.
We ordered the Chicago Style pizza and a Caesar salad. The salad was a cross between a Caesar and a garden so I'm not sure what they were thinking (onions, tomatoes, cucumbers.) but it was fresh.
The Chicago pizza arrived incredibly gooey - they didn't skimp on the cheese! But I wanted it a little more firm so I asked if it could be put back in the oven. A cook (manager?) came out and politely explained that he couldn't bake it any longer or it would burn. So I asked for a regular style pizza and that one arrived cooked to our liking. 
All in all, they seemed to be trying very hard to please.

text:
Excellent brick oven pizza in small-town southern Illinois. I got the Buffalo chicken ranch pizza. It was pretty tasty, with loads of bacon, and blue cheese. Honestly, the ranch was the downfall. Blue cheese, bacon, chicken, cheese, and Franks would have been perfect. My wife got a reuben, and enjoyed it; the fries served along side of it were outstanding. We started with an order of bacon-wrapped stuffed jalepenos. Super delicious. They were so damn good!

The service was excellent. Friendly, attentive, and interactive.

name: Joe Boccardi's Ristorante
attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
categories: Italian, Restaurants
text:
I went here twice just to make sure the 1st time wasn't a fluke. We went on a Wednesday and believe it or not they have a guy going table to table making things out of balloons (?!?). I checked the sign out front to make sure I didn't mistakenly drive to Chuck E. Cheese. Nope. I politely tell the gentleman I'm having a private conversation and would he mind skipping our table. He looked at me like I just shot his dog. Anyhoo. 
The food. Meh. The prices suggest you will be eating higher end Italian food. Wrong. Mediocre at best. Small portions. Little to no seasoning/flavor. 
Living in the Belleville area you need to just look at a restaurants parking lot to gauge the quality/value. The lot here is almost always empty. 
The people have spoken.

name: Sonnenberg Landscaping Material and Supply
categories: Building Supplies, Home Services, Landscaping
text: Very professional and competitive prices. I got my big green egg from them and they delivered and assembled for free so I could surprise my significant other. I have been in there several times since then and they have great service!

name: Dairy Queen Grill & Chill
categories: American (New), Restaurants, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Food, Burgers, Fast Food, American (Traditional)
text:
Confetti cake blizzard What!

This is a newly built Dairy Queen. Who doesn't like a little ice cream on a hot day. I noticed the Confetti cake blizzard on the menu. I asked the guy behind the menu board. He highly recommended it and added that I should add a chocolate dip to the waffle cone. The sad part was their debit machine was broken and you could only use cash. This does happen often at this place.

name: Dollar General Store
categories: Department Stores, Shopping, Fashion
text: I came into the store  to buy some medicine for my son. I waited in line for over 20 minutes because the ladies computer  froze. Which I understand is not the ladies fault, but they didn't even open the other register until 20ish minutes later, the line had atleast 9 people in it. I watched 3 people including myself leave without purchasing anything. The store always seems dirty and the floors are so uneven you can barely push your cart. One of my least favorite  dollar general store.

name: Excel Transportation Services
categories: Limos, Transportation, Airport Shuttles, Hotels & Travel
text: Excel was supposed to pick up my wife and I at 4am for flight to Mexico.  Called the driver 3 times with no answer.  On our way to airport he sent us a text and said he set his alarm wrong.  Having called them we were told that it was our fault as we did not call our driver 30 min in advance to remind their driver to show up.  This is despite the fact when we called the driver the call went straight to voice mail.  This cost me $296 with no reimbursement and no apology.

name: Cutter's Bar and Grill
attributes: {'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'very_loud'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'BestNights': "{'monday': False, 'tuesday': False, 'friday': False, 'wednesday': False, 'thursday': False, 'sunday': False, 'saturday': False}", 'HappyHour': 'True', 'Music': "{'dj': False, 'background_music': False, 'no_music': False, 'jukebox': False, 'live': True, 'video': False, 'karaoke': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False'}
categories: Bars, Sports Bars, Nightlife, Pubs
text:
Good lunch spot!  Daily specials and decent thin crust pizza.

Food is 4-stars, but service is a bit quirky and tough to figure out for rookies.   Sit in the bar area, you go get your drinks separately at the (not at the grill).  Sit in the dining area, waitress will get your drinks.

Cheap wings for happy hour one day a week....pizza is pretty legit!

They don't maintain a solid website or FB page, so don't bother looking for one...rely on Yelp!

Unfortunately, I MUST take away some stars because you will walk out smelling like the grill your food was cooked.  Why?  Good question.  The ventalation above the grill could use some attention.  It's not dirty like nasty, but dirty like it doesn't do it's job and it's easy to see.  

Don't let that keep you from going, I'll be back...it's a risk I'm willing to accept for great 4-star food.

Oh and PS...don't ask for them to make changes to what they offer.  Just deal with it! :)

Get that grill vent working properly and y'all will get my (coveted) 4th star!

text:
I think I made my last visit to St. Louis Bread Co/Panera. Taking the family to a deli/bakery should NOT cost $40 for two adults and two kids. Way too pricey for my blood. The drinks are $2.49 for a small fountain drink . Ridiculous!

Don't get me wrong, the food is great! The sandwiches and pastries are delicious. It's just too expensive! We are talking about a deli chain here!

name: Orange Leaf Frozen Yogurt
categories: Food, Desserts, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Do-It-Yourself Food
text:
Just a great place to grab some frozen yogurt! 
Contemporary atmosphere and very clean! They have so many selections and topping! The staff is always friendly! It is a great family spot or date night!

name: Schnucks Alton
categories: Florists, Food, Grocery, Flowers & Gifts, Shopping, Bakeries, Drugstores
text:
This is the best Schnuck's I've ever been to. The liquor selection is very comprehensive and the beer selection is right sized to find what you want without lacking for something local and special. 

The meat selection is the best I've seen and the counter people are super friendly and helpful to make sure you get the cut you want. 

There are discounted items all over the store and I haven't found any store in the STL with better pricing other than Aldi which isn't quite the same thing as a general grocery store like this.

The staff is helpful and will help you find anything you are looking for. I'd highly recommend the Schnuck's in Alton.

categories: Nightlife, Dive Bars, Bars
text: This bar sucks..my wife and I had lunch there during July around 12:30 . When we came out 45 minutes later several items were stolen off our lawncare trailer..we had parked outside in clear plain view of their video cameras. Went back inside and talked to manager. He said no one was there who knew how to review video and took our number down and said someone would call us..waited several days and heard nothing so we started to call daily and always got some stupid excuse. Then they said the guys who could watch video was on vacation. We went up there a couple days later and after waiting at the bar for 45 minutes the bar tender says well we don't know how to review previous days on our system. Bunch of liars and thieves at this bar and must be real idiots not to know how to use their own video system.

name: La Quinta by Wyndham O'Fallon, IL - St. Louis
categories: Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Hotels & Travel
text: This hotel is consistent with other similar newer La Quinta Inns & Suites. Modern, convenient, clean, welcoming staff, great prices.

text: Sooooo... I put a pretty honest and really tough review on here a while ago.  They read it.  And they made a ton of changes.  Not because of me, but because they really care.  We eat here three or four times a week and absolutely love this place.  The food is always great - try the pizza - and the staff is just wonderful.  The owner and manager and about half their team always say hello and make sure we are happy.  Macs is our go to place.  Try it and it will become yours too.

text: I originally went with this place for my parents because some of the prices were lower but man you get what you pay for. I won't ever go here again.

name: Source Juicery
categories: Food, Restaurants, Juice Bars & Smoothies, Gluten-Free

All the  employees are very knowledgeable and they also have expanded summer hours.

attributes: {'Smoking': "u'no'", 'WiFi': "'free'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForDancing': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': True, 'casual': True}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': True, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'Music': "{'dj': False, 'background_music': False, 'no_music': False, 'jukebox': False, 'live': True, 'video': False, 'karaoke': False}", 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'HappyHour': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'BestNights': "{'monday': False, 'tuesday': False, 'friday': False, 'wednesday': False, 'thursday': False, 'sunday': False, 'saturday': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': True, u'lot': False, u'validated': False}"}
categories: Restaurants, Bars, Nightlife, Pubs, American (Traditional)
text:
This is a place to come for the atmosphere and a maybe a beer, but not for the food. The place had a pretty cool vibe and was set up nicely. I visited during a non-peak time, on a weekday and sat in the bar booths. 

I had the beer cheese dip as an appetizer and it was the highlight of the meal for sure. Very tasty. I ordered the Foundry burger with fries as a main course. Call me cheap, but if I'm paying $13 for a burger, it better knock my socks off. This one fell short. It wasn't bad, but it wasn't memorable and it certainly wasn't $13 good. The seasoned fries I got with the burger were pretty good, but still not good enough to warrant the price. 

Also, I realize there may not be high demand for non-alcoholic beer, but for such a "beer-y" place, you'd think they'd stock at least one brand in bottles. I don't drink alcohol but enjoy sipping on a N/A beer occasionally, especially with a burger, and was disappointed to find they didn't have any. 

My official advice, it would be a good place to meet someone for a first date, or grab a beer after work in a much classier setting than some of the other bars on Main St. But if it's a burger you crave, head a little further north, save yourself $10, and get a charco cheeseburger from Northside Dairy Haven.

text: I have never had a bad experience at this place! Fast service, great margaritas, excellent food, and did i say specials!! Beans and rice come with most dishes, not as an extra like most restaurants. Food is consistently good

name: Chesley Fence & Deck
categories: Fences & Gates, Decks & Railing, Home Services, Contractors
text: Don't do business here. Will not come to your house for estimate. You have to do your own measurements for a repair and send pictures also. After sending the information they never call. Then they claim I never sent an email. I resend the information no call back. They tell me they are very busy but want my business. Never any apologies.  I would go somewhere else.  Aggravating and waist of time

name: Marcus O'Fallon Cinema
categories: Cinema, Arts & Entertainment
text:
I went to see the new Harry Potter movie here and had a horrible experience. The theater was ridiculously hot, it smelled like a locker room that hadn't been cleaned for a month, and the projector was set so that you lost the top part of the picture!

While I used to like this theater, it's gone down hill over the last year or two and still charges outrageous rates. If I'm going to pay that much to watch a movie, I'd rather go to the St. Louis theaters & enjoy myself.

name: Pizza Hut
categories: Pizza, Chicken Wings, Restaurants, Fast Food, Italian
text: The Pizza Hut buffet is just what you would expect if you like pizza and are not a health Nazi. They have a good variety of all-you-can-eat pizza and they will make a type you request if you ask nicely. There is also a simple salad bar: mixed greens, broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, green pepper, mushrooms, etc. They also have one of the pasta dishes out as well as two type of bread sticks, both savory and sweet. During mealtimes they tend to be crowded but the waits aren't long. Service is good, fast, and friendly. On Tuesday evenings I some times take my grandchildren as they have the buffet on Tuesday evenings and it is free for children under ten.

name: The Egg & I
