categories: Cafes, American (Traditional), American (New), Restaurants, Breakfast & Brunch
text:
On my recent day off I stopped into The Egg & I for breakfast around 8 am.  I was promptly greeted and seated upon arrival.  The menu has a tremendous selection of dishes made with eggs and a few that don't like pancakes and waffles.  

First of all the service was excellent. My waitress was very friendly and helpful.  

I chose the bacon and cheese omelet.  The omelet was HUGE!  It was very fluffy and covered in cheese.  It was served with ranch potatoes and 4 large pieces of wheat toast. The ranch potatoes were awesome!  I was also excited to see that they offered a bold coffee option.  The coffee was delicious.

This has to be the best breakfast I've had in a long time.  I will definitely be back.

name: US Post Office
categories: Public Services & Government, Post Offices
text: It is a great very quick full service post office much better than our old one in downtown Collinsville

name: Sonic Drive-In
categories: Event Planning & Services, American (New), Burgers, Hotels & Travel, Restaurants, Hotels, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Food, Fast Food
text: I typically am a very easy going customer. I understand mistakes happen & orders get mixed up. That being said every single time I come here nothing goes right. It takes at least three times of me telling the person taking the order for them to get it right. That's when the fun begins. You pull around and wait in line while the poor kids on skates struggle to stay vertical taking each order car to car until finding the correct one. There seems to be no organization to the place & these servers look like complete idiots. More than once I've witnessed skaters ramming into the side of cars, it's happened to me. If you order a large here be prepared to get a small. If you don't want any toppings on your ice cream, expect double. I think the basic problem is lack of training. The staff is always friendly. The food (when correct) is tasty & I think these two things are what keeps me coming back and giving them another shot. Basically, if you're in a hurry or are a high-strung customer don't come here. If you're up for a laugh and about a 10 minute wait, drive on in.

name: Dex's Tree Service
categories: Tree Services, Snow Removal, Home Services, Firewood, Local Services
text: Have had them out on several occasions for trimming and tree/stump removal.  Always great service and reasonable prices.  Very professional and true to their word.  Great to work with.

text: Stopped in this morning (Saturday) to grab a quick breakfast. Much to my dismay, it took over 30 minutes to get two biscuit & gravy meals. No biscuits ready, very slow service, and what seemed to be workers in a trance. This will be our last trip to this location.

name: Rose Endodontics
categories: General Dentistry, Endodontists, Health & Medical, Dentists
text: I cant say enough nice things about Dr. Rose and his staff. He is very knowledgeable, caring, up to date, pain free, and compassionate. When I called his office they said they didnt have an opening for a week.  I explained the pain I was in and the staff said they would talk to Dr Rose and call me back.  Shortly there after she called back to say come on in.  Dr. Rose said he didnt want me to wait any longer in pain.  What a compassionate caring man.  I had a root canal that evening. After the procedure he gave me his cell phone number and said if I had any problems not to hesitate to call. How many doctors or dentist do that?  He is one in a million.

text: Good food but I have never experienced worse service on delivery! What a joke, prepare for at least an hour and a half...Get it together IMO'S you have 1 job.

name: Chef's Shoppe
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '3', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': False, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}"}
categories: Shopping, Home & Garden, Kitchen & Bath
text:
This is a lovely little store, really. Pricing varies. Kitchen textiles, I find them to be a bit high. Some of those oven mitts and aprons you can find cheaper elsewhere. Overall, you're looking at Williams-Sonoma prices, but without the drive to Plaza Frontenac. 

A little cramped in the store, wish there was a bit more space. Staff is a bit young, so know what you're looking for, since they're unknowledgeable when it comes to the products. Although, there are a couple of older ladies during the day that do know their cookware. 

If you sign up for their email alerts, you know when they're going to have a 10% off everything in the store on Saturdays. Which helps if you're eyeballing a new Lecreuset dutch oven. 

Overall, I recommend this store to any closet gadget collecting women and cooks in general.

categories: Shopping, Home Services, Hardware Stores, Nurseries & Gardening, Appliances, Home & Garden, Building Supplies
text: The store is scattered.  No one around to help.  Not alot in stock. The cashiers were nice though.  Only reason I gave it 2 stars

text: I was delighted to find good Indian food in the St Louis suburbs for a reasonable price. You can order food mild to spicy, and everything is authentic and delicious. The portions are generous as well, and the staff is courteous and helpful. A great restaurant.

text:
I've always been a fan of Pizza Man...however...tonight the experience negated the good food.  My main issue this evening was the fact that it took them 45 minutes to bring out a 14" thin crust pepperoni pizza. They were not very busy, but were obviously understaffed and overwhelmed.

The pizza was as good as ever, but they need to remember that they are not the only privately owned pizza joint in the area anymore -- their service needs to be excellent if they want to keep their customers from going to the competitors.

name: Walgreens
categories: Beauty & Spas, Convenience Stores, Shopping, Food, Drugstores, Cosmetics & Beauty Supply
text: Just had to leave due to employee rudeness.  We came in to print out a picture here. The two kiosks were being used, one of them by an employee.  As the line started to build, another employee came over to hint that the other employee should free up the kiosk, but no luck.  The employee at the kiosk, then asked each of it's in line if they needed help, and each said they were waiting to print pictures.  Instead of actually helping by getting up, she kept at whatever she was working on.  The other employee then came over and offered to finish up what she was working on later if she would free up the kiosk.  The employee at the kiosk, then loudly said she'd be there a while and kept doing what she was doing.  The line then shrank as we all left.

name: Sips N Splatters
categories: Nightlife, Arts & Entertainment
text: We were at the Maryville, IL location and had a wonderful time. The staff is amazing and encouraging. Don't worry if you don't have a big group, it doesn't matter.  Bring your snacks, some wine and a friend and you will have a great evening.

name: Tropical Sno
categories: Food, Desserts
text: Hot weather got you down? Need to get in touch with your inner Hawaiian? Time for a trip to T-Snow, located at the entrance to Water Works Swim Club, east "behind" the business strip near Montclaire. Four sizes and prices $1.75 - $3.50, and more flavor combinations than days in the summer. Don't leave home without your dollars and cents, 'cause they don't take plastic here.

categories: Restaurants, American (New)
text:
I took my wife here for her birthday. We just moved to the area from Los Angeles, and everyone told us we had to try this place. We could definitely see why. It has a great atmosphere, and good food.

On "Tenderloin Tuesdays" you can pick any steak on the menu plus two sides for $15. Seemed like a good deal, so I ordered a New York strip steak with salad and green beans and my wife ordered the tenderloin with a salad and baked potato.

The service was good, but our food took for-ev-er to come. Like, pushing an hour and a half.

However, once it did come out, it was delicious. The cuts were great and mine was huge. The sides were tasty. (One of my pet peeves is when I go to a nice restaurant and the salad is obviously straight from a bag. This salad wasn't.) My steak was cooked a bit less than the medium I had ordered, but it was close enough for my taste.

Over-all our experience was very nice, and we'll definitely be back. (I have  a feeling I'll want to bump my rating up a star after another try.) We especially want to try their famous fried chicken!

EDIT: Second experience was similar, minus the long wait. Love this place!

name: Lucy n' Ricardo's

text:
We have been here twice now and the first time the place was only open a month so the service issue we had (party of 12) I figured was just a new thing and they would figure it out. 

Well same service issues 3 months later. The food is ok at best. If your looking for exciting food with new flavor keep going. If you are in a hurry keep going. If you was an ok meal and are not in a hurry, stop by and you will find something that works. 

The bar needs some more training. When I ask for a drink on the rocks and it comes back frozed and the wrong drink, thats bad.  

The reason for 3 out of 5 stars if the sheer size of the margarita. Its huge!!!

name: Top Nails
categories: Nail Salons, Beauty & Spas
text:
I'm going to be generous and give this place 3 stars because they were so friendly and their dog snowball is so cute  I don't think this area will ever compare to the places I use to go to in San Diego. I miss home so much especially miss the best nailshops. The lady didn't really clean my toes nails, I know good pedicures where they cut the cuticles and all but she just moved the tools around my cuticle nail bed

Update: its only been 2 days and my nails already look like they are a week and a half old. I'm so dissappointed thinking that saving a couple of bucks going here was a great idea... NOT!! Ladies spend that extra $ cause its worth it in the long run.

name: Underground Artworks Tattoo And Piercing
categories: Piercing, Tattoo, Beauty & Spas
text:
This place is great. I went in for my very first tattoo a week ago, and I've been raving about them to anyone who'll listen ever since! First off, the shop is INCREDIBLY clean, not a wisp of dust to be found, from what I could see. It was nicely decorated, as well. I wanted to bring the couch home with me, it was so comfy! 
One thing to help y'all out, they don't do over the phone appointments. You need to have your deposit ready in order to schedule one, and they don't do plastic. They DO do walk ins as well,  I just hate waiting, and I knew I'd be nervous, so I HAD to schedule an appointment. While Greg was making up my drawing (stencil?), he asked several times if he had the spelling of my kids names correct. I remember him asking at least one other time while he was tattooing me. Before we sat down, he reminded me that I didn't have to get it all finished in one session, just in case I wussed out. We got me situated in the chair, and he got to work. I kid you not, I barely felt it! I was terrified that it was going to be excruciating pain, and it felt like someone was running their fingernail over my skin. during the whole session, we chatted back and forth, Greg kept making sure I was alright, and before I knew it, 2 hours had passed, and I was done! When I looked at mt new artwork in the mirror (it's on my shoulder), I almost cried. It was exactly what I had envisioned. The colors, placement, everything. I couldn't have hoped for a better first experience in body art! I'm already planning my next one, and it's only been a week, haha.  I would definitely recommend Underground to anyone. I'll definitely be back!

name: JJ Spa & Nail
categories: Nail Salons, Beauty & Spas
text: First visit was awesome, great service and price. Then the second visit for a fill-in with color and design, it was all great up until it was time to pay- it cost more than the first visit, and he said because I got eyebrows done, um? No I didn't, only a fill-in on my acrylic nails with polish and design. The owner, Tony seemed so indifferent about it then proceeded to tell me that the next time I come in that he'd give me a good deal, whatever, why not do it right that day!?! I'm never coming back. I need consistency with prices. So unfortunate.

name: Fire-N-Smoke Wood Fired Kitchen
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'beer_and_wine'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': None, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'DogsAllowed': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': None, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2'}
categories: Barbeque, Fast Food, Restaurants, Burgers, American (New)
text:
I echo everyone else's negative critique on service and the ordering process!  Very poor!

We visited the O'Fallon joint.  It used to be a Ravanelli's.  We picked a booth next to a row of stacked firewood.  The wood was wet. It stank! We really didn't key on the order until we got our food. I suppose we could have moved since there are NO table servers, but we struggled through it.  Take home box....where are they? I walked around for 5 minutes looking like a lost sole until I finally found them.  Another do it yourself task. Let's review; we seat ourselves, we get our own drinks and condiments, we get our own take home boxes, I have had better service from McDonalds! Oh, and no deserts!

We wish they had kept it Ravanelli's.  We always had good food, good service, and the deserts were excellent!

name: Wingstop
categories: Restaurants, Chicken Wings
text: I placed an online order it said 16-21 minutes to be ready. I went after half an hour. Then waited an additional 25 minutes  inside. Ridiculous. My order says complete but they tell me it isn't ready. I'm beyond annoyed at waiting an hour for a 16-21 minutes order.

name: Inman Heating & Cooling
categories: Home Services, Heating & Air Conditioning/HVAC, Plumbing, Home Cleaning, Water Heater Installation/Repair
text: We called them as our a/c unit had gone out. The lady who answered the phone mumbled so much that I didn't understand much of what she said, but I was pretty sure they were coming to help us. Two hours later my husband called to clarify and the lady told him they would be here sometime and if he wanted faster service he could call someone else, so thats exactly what we did. Sigman Heating and Air Conditioning was here in 30 minutes and they were kind and concise on the phone. Unfortunately because of Inman we had to pay an after-hours fee! So even though they didn't do anything they still cost us money. A million thumbs down to them!!

name: Tropical Nails Spa
categories: Beauty & Spas, Nail Salons
text: I have been a few times since they have opened and have had a different technician each time.  The service has always been great and my nails have always looked good regardless of the technician.  The facility is clean, spacious, and the prices are excellent.

name: Jacob's Herb Shop
categories: Specialty Food, Food, Health Markets
text: I've alway thought this store to be over priced.  However they carried a few hard to find items so my girl would make an occasional purchase from this establishment.  The owner will tell you anything to get you to believe that you need an item in her store.  This the worse place to go for honest health advise. A few weeks ago my girlfriend made a purchase that rang up as $64.00. However a few days later when she decided to use the product she discover the price tag on the bottom of the bottle was $42. Dollars $22.00 difference.  With recipe in hand we went back to Jacobs Herbal shop so they could fix this and refund us the difference.  The owner via telephone told us that because customers will change the price tags she could not refund us... WHAT.... ARE YOU SEROUS? and she wouldn't refund us our $22.oo. don't shop there you can get the same items off the Internet at half the prices. We discovered this a day later. This store us a ripe off.

name: The Goddard School
categories: Summer Camps, Education, Specialty Schools, Active Life, Local Services, Preschools, Elementary Schools, Child Care & Day Care
text: We love The Goddard School in Shiloh IL, everyone is so friendly & caring. It feel great to know my child is in a place where she is well cared for & cared about. She has grown so much since she started & I could not be happier.

name: Portrait Innovations
address: 6540 N. Illinois, Ste 102, The Shoppes at St. Clair Square
categories: Session Photography, Photographers, Shopping, Event Planning & Services, Photography Stores & Services
text: I have to give these gals a great review! We were on time for our session and we knew we had a few minutes to wait as I couldn't think of a more chaotic occupation trying to deal with so many different dynamics other than daycare, but I digress. Angie was polite and kept in contact with us to let us know how much longer we had to wait, after about 15 minutes we were taken back and we began our session with our one month old. She had so much patience with her and truly knew what she was doing and made our session perfect, all the while juggling other clients coming in with/without appointments and phone calls. We never felt neglected. Our photo packages were clearly explained and outlined for us, she even let us customize absolutely everything we purchased. While juggling everyone we needed to meet with Jessica and fine tune our selections, she was simply fantastic! Her and Angie make a great team! These ladies went the extra mile and stayed about an hour after closing to make sure we were happy. 12 hour days for both these ladies and if they didn't get a thank you all day here is one from us! Thank You. Please consider Portrait Innovations for you next family photos, you'll be glad you did!

name: Metro Eye Care
categories: Shopping, Eyewear & Opticians, Health & Medical, Optometrists, Medical Centers
text:
Exceptional service, friendly staff, great frame selection.  Dr. Janssen was very friendly as well as the staff.  Thank you for a great experience.  I will definitely recommend your office to friends and family.
Update 11/2015 - returned for my annual check up and still very pleased with my exam and the staff.  Friendly and extremely helpful.

name: The Ticket Guys
categories: Arts & Entertainment, Ticket Sales, Performing Arts
text: I have used The Ticket Guys on many occasions from theater tickets to sporting events. Any customer service representative I worked with has always been very professional and accommodating to my requests. My seats have always been exactly what i am after for whatever event I am attending. If you are thinking about using them, don't hesitate another second!

My wife ordered the Huevos Twisteros which was chorizo chili topped with 2 eggs, avocado, tomato and some other items. Both were good, I actually liked hers better. text: Worst Guitar Center I've ever visited.   I went there to purchase a guitar but couldn't get anyone to assist me.  I ended up driving to the Guitar Center in St Louis,  over 20 miles away to buy the guitar.   I decided to try them again because I need a guitar stand and picks.  I asked for assistance several times but the two salesmen I asked were too busy yucking it up.  No other customers were around so they weren't busy, just rude.

name: AXIS Edwardsville
categories: Home Services, Apartments, Real Estate
text:
THIS IS THE ABSOLUTE WORST PLACE TO LIVE!! Management has screwed me over so many times, without any explanation and no compensation. My car got towed even though I had my parking sticker on my vehicle; I got no explanation and no compensation for my troubles. I had to drive 30 minutes to pick up my car, and had terrible service at the tow company as well. 

Management also kicked me and my roommate out of our apartment for over a week to redo our floor. We received no compensation for our troubles and terrible service from the staff. After we finally got back into our apartment, the water was still turned off for another week. It took the maintenance staff 3 months to redo the wall that they tore into during the project. I have attached pictures of this mess.

They are constantly coming up with new fees to charge their residents, which they say is "service fees" on top of the $730 that it costs to live at this dump. Management and maintenance is extremely unprofessional and inconsiderate of the residents satisfaction. I DO NOT recommend living here; The Reserve and Greenhill apartments is 10x better and I've lived at Axis for 2 years.

name: La Quinta by Wyndham Collinsville - St. Louis
categories: Hotels, Event Planning & Services, Hotels & Travel
text: This place is brand new. Why stay anywhere else in the area? Also, their luggage carts are cool.

name: Keils Antiques & Collectables
categories: Shopping, Antiques
text: Cute store. Its in an old building and just has a nice feel to it. Lots of cases of jewelry and the whole upstairs is vintage clothing (mostly 60s/70s/80s with a couple older pieces mixes in). Prices varied from good deals to overpriced. I found a few treasures. They also have old-timey candies and some reproduction kitchen accessories. One thing I didn't like was that there were really great looking things hanging up and on shelves behind the counter that were for sale - but on ebay only. I saw a few I wanted to buy, but they wouldn't sell them in person. Worth a look if you are in the area.

name: Kennelwood Pet Resort
categories: Pet Sitting, Pet Services, Pet Training, Pet Boarding, Pets, Pet Groomers
text:
This place is really, really bad! The only thing they give much effort to is continuously abusing online review systems to remove their negative/true reviews. 

This place abused our animal, refused to provide the care we paid for, failed to meet even basic requirements for the packages we paid for for our animal, and sent our dog home limping and cowering from our hands for a month. I'm in some online animal groups in our community and many people agree that kennelwood is a nightmare and very abusive in many aspects. This is just my opinion and you can make yours, but I'd advise highly that you go elsewhere.

text: I've been here several times in the past few years and every time we visit... the waitstaff is sub par, not very friendly at all. The hamburgers are tasteless...the fries are always greasy and cold. I never suggest to go there... Its always some unsuspecting friend. You would think they would read the reviews and fix stuff, but it's always the same. Won't be back unless owner changes and or management.

name: Clarkson Eyecare
categories: Eyewear & Opticians, Optometrists, Health & Medical, Shopping
text: We had a bad time with Dr. Baker and Clarkson Eyecare.  My daughter got her eyes checked for contacts and glasses.  She had sunglasses made from the glasses prescription which were unwearable.  The ground rose into her eyes and they made her sick.  She lives out of town and was coming home for Thanksgiving break.  Sam's also offered to extend our warranty and to make new lenses if she could get her eyes rechecked that Thanksgiving weekend. Sam's said that in such situations the problem was usually that the astigmatism measurement was wrong.  My daughter called up Clarkson and they promised her the doctor would check her prescription on the Friday or Saturday of Thanksgiving weekend.  When my daughter went to Clarkson, they said the prescription matched the lenses in the sunglasses.  If my daughter was having problems with the prescription she had something seriously wrong with her eyes and needed a full examination.  Dr. Baker refused to see her and check the astigmatism.  We were forced to go and see the optometrist at Walmart and pay $58.  Sure enough, Mr. Todd said that the astigmatism measurement was off.  We took the corrected prescription to Sam's and they remade the glasses for free.  Problem solved thanks to Walmart Vision Center and Sam's.  I guess these fancy places sometimes aren't worth the money and certainly don't offer extra service.  Dr. Baker at Clarksons was totally unwilling to go the extra mile.  Nice Thanksgiving behavior!!!

name: Olsen Veterinary Clinic
categories: Pet Services, Veterinarians, Pets
text: Jenna Kueper, who works here, is also involved with Four Paws Sake rescue group in Maryville, IL.  These are not "rescuers", they are dog nappers.  Just know that she is watching to see where pure breds are having litters so they can come confiscate your puppies and call you a "backyard breeder" when you try to get them back.  Dr. Olsen might be great, but his staff is corrupt.

We certainly will return!

name: Supercuts
address: 1171 N Greenmount Rd, Green Mount Plaza O'Fallon
categories: Hair Salons, Beauty & Spas
text:
Supercuts facility looks nice, and it's easy to get in if your coming off the interstate.  Not so much if your coming from the McDonalds\Moto Mart side.  

There is a small "L" shaped waiting area, but they have wifi which is nice if there is a long wait.  You can request who cuts your hair on their online app, but I'd recommend you request a person 30 minutes before you intend to get there, and be aware of shift changes as that person might not be there if you take your time (it happens lol).  

Price is on par with other similar style chain haircut areas, so I was expecting the same quality and service.  As with any service industry job tipping is an integral part of the employee income (I make it a habit to tip well above and beyond if the service is truly deserving).  Sometimes they have coupons or sales on Facebook.  They have a military, firefighter, and police discount.    

But, this place has one of the best kept secret in the area, a quality hair cutter...er...stylist\barber, and I'm exposing it.  I've had my share of "jacked" up haircuts in various places and now that I've found someone to cut my hair the way I want it is a huge relief.  

I get my hair cut every other week by only one stylist, Mariana.  My family also gets their haircut with her.  She has the most outstanding customer service I've seen anywhere, managed my expectation and the haircut I want vs. what I can pull off lol, and a lot of life experience outside of the Midwest.  Makes for good topics of conversation.  Greeted with a smile and always an excellent haircut.  I would recommend you go there, but might want to reserve early as when I go, Mariana usually has a large wait from other people wanting to get their haircut from her.

name: Salon Whimz
categories: Hair Salons, Beauty & Spas, Wigs, Shopping, Waxing, Skin Care, Nail Salons, Cosmetics & Beauty Supply, Hair Removal
text: Love this place. My daughter had her haircut here and Lisa was amazing. She made sure any adjustment she needed to make she talked to me about it... I already have my appointment scheduled : )

name: Metro Glass Service
categories: Auto Glass Services, Home & Garden, Automotive, Hardware Stores, Glass & Mirrors, Home Services, Shopping, Home Decor, Kitchen & Bath
text:
We've used MetroGlass for decades for everything from car windows to window panes
blown out by a sleet storm to small antique picture frame glass replacements, with great results.  They are cheerful, helpful and efficient.  The woman in the office collects items to
support our military forces, an added attraction to do business there!

name: Bridal Manor
categories: Shopping, Formal Wear, Fashion, Bridal
text:
Just a note that this rating is based solely on the experience of shopping for bridesmaid dresses ONLY.   I'd really like to give them 5 stars just based on the fitting rooms and shop setup alone, but unfortunately have to lower the grade for two reasons.  The primary reason is that because of her experience at several other shops and the long drive from O'Fallon, IL to Waterloo, my Maid of Honor called ahead to ask if they had a good selection of bridesmaid dresses in plus sizes (24 & up) and with higher necklines & straps available in-stock for her to try on.  She was told that they did indeed have that kind of a  selection available for her to try on, so we made the trip out there.  Much to our chagrin, they did NOT have much a selection at all in larger sizes.  So, thanks for letting us waste a trip (& gas money) to head out there.  The second reason for the lower grade is because, like too many other shops, there's just not much of a selection in available larger sizes to actually try on in the store (for bridesmaid dresses, anyway).

That being said, the sales ladies were very nice and the selections they did have available on the rack were all very nice looking--- on the hangers.  Really wish they would've had more than the one for my friend to try on, because the material that a couple styles of dresses were made out of was absolutely gorgeous...   Even though they were a bit pricier than other shops.  I would still recommend them to others.

text: The food here is consistently outstanding. I have eaten here many times.  They allow you to customize the degree of spiciness of a dish, by giving a number from 1-10. So far I have only dared to go to level 7.  Most recently I tried the Murg Sharabi, an exotic blend of creamy spices, chicken and mushrooms that perfectly complemented their tea.  Service is sometimes a little lackadaisical, but food more than makes up for it.

name: U.S. Post Office
categories: Public Services & Government, Post Offices
text: My transaction was completed today at 10:35. I've had excellent service by postal workers at other locations, but I will gladly drive out of my way if it mean avoiding another experience like the one I had here. Clerk #05/Steven was unprofessional, rude, and reeked of cigarette smoke. Instead of going through all the required questions about the package I was shipping...no harmful/hazardous chemicals? Perishable items? Restricted items? Insurance? Nothing was asked. He printed out the labels and placed them on the box. When I mentioned that I wanted insurance, he said under his breath "I wish I would have known that before." I'm sorry sir, but you DID NOT ASK. He cancelled out the transaction and finished the transaction. No bye. No thank you. Nothing again. Any job where you provide a service to a customers should get that service along with great customer service. Again, I'll go out of my way if it means avoiding another Steven experience.

text: This clinic is amazing.  Every exotic vet I called for a quote ranged from $340-$600 to have my rabbit fixed. It's extremely importation that you get rabbits fixed since they have a high change of getting cancer if you don't.  It's also important that the vet know how to work with rabbits since there's so many small details that can kill them. Hertz second chance did a great job and I'm fortunate to have found them for my rabbit.

name: 3 Rivers Solid Surface & Remodeling
categories: Flooring, Cabinetry, Contractors, Home Services, Countertop Installation
text:
I can't believe the reviews I've just read.. Are we talking about the same company, because none of those poor reviews reflect the service that was provided to my wife and I. Let me start by saying that everyone that I've dealt with during this whole process,  was so very professional,  and pleasent, but a couple of them really shined bright. I called because the "Granite Daddy" commercials really grabbed my attention. But as a smart business man, I had to have as many estimates as possible. Money isn't  a factor in any of my decisions,  but like to know if anyone is to "cheap" or "expensive", because they are usually the ones to stay away from. Although RCG came in under everyone else,  it wasn't far from the average. I called the advertised number, and was greeted by the office girl Chandra, (sorry if that's wrong) and shortly after, " The Granite Daddy" himself called to set up our in home consultation. Now I can see why some may be rubbed wrong by Bob, but after talking with him a while, my gut, which is never wrong, pushed us forward, and we signed the contract. Bob's son Rob came out as scheduled for measure, spent a good hour or so double and triple checking his numbers, explained in detail the process to follow,  and left my wife and I feeling confident in our descision. The day of install was a bit different than explained, by the fact that Rob was to do the tearout, install, and reconnect of the plumbing, all in the same day. I wasn't quite sure that was possible, but again, felt comfortable after seeing how efficient the tearout went. So after carrying in the first couple pieces of granite, the other installer Joe (Bob's Grandson), pointed out a significant problem with the granite, and my heart sank in my chest, and I just knew this was going to be " the too good to be true" senario, and the job would not be completed in the time frame promised. A few minutes later, Rob came to me, explained where the problem occurred,  and offered a few solutions to fix it.. I told him I didn't care how he handled it, we were going out of town the following day, and we would really like it finished before we left. Rob told me not to worry, he would fix the problem on site, and have it finished regardless of how long it took. I swear it had to be the longest install ever, but in the end, it was 110% perfect. Rob and Joe spent hours installing, fixing, and reconnecting our plumbing, so when we left for vacation, we knew we'd be coming home to a beautiful kitchen. My hats off to everyone at River City Granite one of the best experiences we've ever had in home remodeling. . Thanks again
..

categories: Restaurants, Pizza, Italian
text:
3/3/2017

This little jewel of a place is less than a mile from my home,  yet I have never visited. I just got off work and was not in the mood to cook nor did I really want anything at home. I did a search on Yelp for nearby places and lo and behold this place popped up. I  looked at the pics and one caught my eye....I was instantly craving pizza when I saw it.  So I go in and was greeted right away. I showed the lady the pic and said I want this and only this...what is this!!! Lol She got a kick out of that. She told me it was their deluxe pizza on a hand-tossed crust. I ordered that with extra cheese. We chatted while I waited and I learned this was a local place that has three locations, customers are crazy about them, and the sauce on the pizza is a sweet sauce. 
I instantly panicked as I dont like sweet pizza sauce; however she put my mind at ease that it would be fine. 
I get home...I put this wonderful looking creation on my plate and as Im walking to sit down I impatiently took a bite........

This was everything to me! It was hot and the salty toppings balanced that sauce right on out. There was also a spiciness that most likelt came from the pepperoni.  

From here on out whenever I crave pizza I will be going here!!!!

name: 1 Nail Salon

name: Palm Beach Tan
categories: Beauty & Spas, Tanning, Skin Care, Spray Tanning, Tanning Beds

name: MedExpress Urgent Care
categories: Health & Medical, Urgent Care, Medical Centers, Walk-in Clinics, Doctors
text:
I have had mixed results with urgent cares so my expectations were not that high.  I am happy to say that my expectations were blown away.

First, I was immediately greeted by the front desk staff. It was painless as they were friendly and attentive to my needs.  I supplied my insurance info and they took it from there.

I was second in line to be seen but the wait time was nominal.  I was taken back where my vitals and medical history was take.  The nurse could not have been nicer, made me feel like I was important patient.

Once that was done, I had a short wait for the nurse-practitioner to come see me.  She was also courteous and professional.  She listen to my medical issue and was able to diagnose the issue.  The nurse came back with the shot and I had to wait around to make sure there wasn't an adverse reaction to the shot.

Once I was done, the staff offered to fill my prescription on the spot.  It was a little bit expensive but the convenience was well worth it, so I didn't mind.  Not that I'm looking for reasons to visit again, if an issue arises, I will be back.

name: Domino's Pizza
categories: Restaurants, Sandwiches, Chicken Wings, Pizza
text: I haven't even tasted the pizza yet. I came in to order a carryout. The woman who helped me clearly hates her job (and probably rightfully so) but it was very evident in her customer service. She was harsh and talked as if I was inconveniencing her. Another worker in the back looked at me and I smiled but he totally blew me off lol. The girl that just handled my credit card was making the pizzas bare handed sans gloves. I'm not sure if she used sanitizer or not. At the temperature the food is cooked I'm almost positive that any germs will be heated away, but it's the principle of the matter. Again this review is on service alone. I gave it two stars because the other girl working there was super nice. Don't know who the heck she is but she deserves employee of the month.

name: First Western Inn
categories: Hotels, Event Planning & Services, Hotels & Travel
text: DO NOT GO HERE UNDER ANY CIRCUMSTANCES!!  Room decor is extremely outdated and room is dirty. Can smell the dirt in the carpet. Bed is uncomfortable. Room has a fridge but it is not clean on outside or inside.  If you are looking for a place to stay the night, fork out the extra money and stay somewhere else. You have been warned.

name: EDGE 5 Theatres
categories: Cinema, Arts & Entertainment
text: Love the theater seating and the bar is nice. Food is nothing to write home about but quality of the entire venue overcomes that. Arcade & laser tag add an extra bonus feature.

name: Elite Retreat Day Spa and Salon
attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsBitcoin': 'False', 'HairSpecializesIn': "{'straightperms': True, 'coloring': True, 'extensions': True, 'africanamerican': False, 'curly': True, 'kids': True, 'perms': True, 'asian': True}", 'WiFi': "u'free'"}
categories: Hair Extensions, Day Spas, Hair Salons, Beauty & Spas, Massage, Massage Therapy, Health & Medical, Nail Technicians, Nail Salons, Tanning
text: Don't get me wrong the place was beautiful inside and everyone els seemed happy except me when I was charged $50 for a burnt bikini area that still hadn't fully been waxed. The woman that gave me a "Brazilian wax" told me she might not be able to get all the hair but I didn't know she meant she was going to rip 30% of my hairs out and leave the rest with my super burnt raw skin. As a professional she should have just flat out told me my hair was to short and I needed to come back later, but instead she asked ME if I wanted her to keep going (I've never done this before how was I supposed to know what I should've done) and being a head strong girl I assumed yeah why not let's just get it over with... Worst decision of my life. And worst of all it's just embarrassing I haven't cried over pain in a long time and the night of the day I got it done I was sobbing. So I guess this isn't the spa to get a Brazilian but that doesn't mean it's a bad place!!! I just had a bad experience and wanted to save anyone els from it.

name: Eclipse Car Wash
categories: Car Wash, Automotive
text:
The BEST car wash in the Midwest!  
Driving through the tunnel leaves my car streak free & shiny while getting every single bug off of my windshield.  The vacuum stations are FREE, powerful, easy to use, and conveniently placed on each side of the car.  The staff is professional, friendly, and helpful.  Even the landscaping looks gorgeous.  Finally, a car wash that I look forward to going to.  I won't go anywhere else.

name: KFC
categories: Restaurants, Chicken Wings, Food, Chicken Shop, Fast Food
text:
My mom was stuck at home in Cahokia without anyone around to go shopping.  I called KFC from California.  The manager helped me get an order ready for a taxi to pick up.

The staff went above and beyond the call of duty.  My mom is giggling, eating chicken, and thinks I am the best son, ever.  Thanks!!!!

name: USAVE Cleaners
categories: Laundry Services, Local Services, Dry Cleaning & Laundry
text:
I've been using these folks for a little over 2.5 years and can say I've never really had a bad experience. Well, except the one time the lady rung my total up wrong, had to run another transaction through but failed to include both receipts with my order for when I went to pick up my stuff. So when I went to pick up my order the lady basically called me a liar when I said I already paid in full, but gave me my stuff anyway. But that was a single incident out of at least 50 transactions I've had with them so I won't let that deter me from future business. 

The first time I had my slacks dry cleaned somewhere else I almost choked when I got the bill. $4 to dry clean a pair of slacks? Really? So imagine my surprise when I found these folks. If you are really in a hurry you can get same day service but you have to drop your stuff off by 9 am. Typically your order will be ready for pick up the next day after 5pm.  They are closed on Sunday, so don't try to pick up your dry cleaning when you are out on a Sunday afternoon. 

All in all, for the price they are hard to beat. I've never had a pair of slacks damaged in any way, the one time I had some funky creases in my slacks that should not have been there, they took them back and pressed them real quick while I waited. I'll continue to use these folks as long as they are convenient to get to and I have a need for that service.

name: Freer Auto Body & Accessories
categories: Body Shops, Automotive, Auto Repair
text: Just picked up my car ahead of schedule! Great friendly service, and great job. My car looks like new. Thanks much!

name: Motel 6
categories: Hotels, Event Planning & Services, Hotels & Travel
text:
Not the cleanest motel 6 but far from the worst I have stayed in.   

Bed was comfortable and clean.  

Bathroom needs some help.  Water coming through the floor tile.

WIFI needed password but management didn't provide upon check-in.

name: Sugarfire Smokehouse - Edwardsville

text: Best Smokehouse ever! Everything is amazing!  They have unique specials everyday, as well as standard Smokehouse fare, including a Carolina pulled pork sandwich and some fancy salads.

name: Calvert's Express Auto Service & Tire
categories: Auto Repair, Automotive, Tires
text:
We took my husband's car here because we had a coupon for a $14.99 oil change (the cheapest I've ever seen). After dropping his car off, we went off to do other errands and I told him every time I take my car to these "cheaper" places, what you save in money you spend in time. I've waited 4 hours before. We made it to a couple places by the time he got the call saying his car was ready. I was pleasantly surprised! 

They were very friendly and efficient. I know where I'm getting my next oil change! Keep your eyes peeled for those coupons in the mail -- they make a difference.

text: Ordered delivery (4 dollar delivery fee that does not go to the driver, really Imos?).  Toasted ravioli was cold and soggy, actually the entire order was cold when it arrived. Very low quality product.  Imo's is never my choice cause I hate provel cheese but I like the salad dressing so I will tolerate the pizza from time to time but this was definately sub-par.

name: Auffenberg Volkswagen - Service
categories: Automotive, Auto Repair
text: The folks in the service department are pleasant and helpful.  I trust them to take care of my VW.

name: China One Buffet
categories: Restaurants, Chinese
text: They recently revamped the buffet here and added sushi as well as frog legs and steak to dinner buffet. I went in for lunch and for about 7.50 what they had available didn't seem worth it. Add another 2 bucks for a soda and the over all price with the selection doesn't add up. Food was ok and sushi was what I would expect that didn't make it right in front of you like other places. I guess if you don't feel like driving to Belleville, Fairview or St Louis it may seem a better bargain to save gas but I rather go somewhere else for what I spent. Wait staff at least are nice and check on you for refills and plate removal.

name: Coffee Mill Diner
categories: Donuts, Cafes, Breakfast & Brunch, Food, Restaurants, Coffee & Tea
text: Great local coffee shop! Coffee was fantastic. The staff was super friendly and accommodating and the donuts and pastries looked phenomenal. Can't wait to go back again!!

name: Wisper Internet
categories: Professional Services, Home Services, IT Services & Computer Repair, Local Services, Internet Service Providers
text: We have had awesome service from Wisper ISP. We get fast speeds, awesome local service, rarely any down time and when there is they will readily credit your account upon calling and asking. They frequently have local thank you parties in all of the areas they serve and have annual parties at their office location thanking its customers. The price and unlimited service is tops and for a local company that still and will be local, is the one of the best things. Employees are very personable and easy to talk to.

attributes: {'Smoking': "u'outdoor'", 'GoodForDancing': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'full_bar'", 'Caters': 'True', 'BYOB': 'False', 'Corkage': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'DogsAllowed': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'CoatCheck': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Music': "{'dj': False, 'background_music': False, 'no_music': False, 'jukebox': False, 'live': True, 'video': False, 'karaoke': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Ambience': "{u'divey': False, u'hipster': None, u'casual': True, u'touristy': False, u'trendy': True, u'intimate': False, u'romantic': False, u'classy': None, u'upscale': None}", 'GoodForMeal': 'None', 'BusinessAcceptsBitcoin': 'False', 'HappyHour': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BestNights': "{'monday': False, 'tuesday': False, 'friday': True, 'wednesday': False, 'thursday': False, 'sunday': False, 'saturday': True}"}
categories: Cocktail Bars, Bars, Nightlife, Burgers, Restaurants, American (Traditional), Sandwiches, American (New)
text: My girlfriend and I have been anticipating the opening of Copperfire for some time now, as we drive by it while returning home from work on a daily basis. We finally went last night and have never been more disappointed in a restaurant. As we were walking up to the front door, we overheard one couple leaving while stating "literally the worst food ever". When we walked in, there was no hostess and we were greeted by several drunken restaurant patrons who stated "good luck getting service" then laughed. We stood at the hostess stand for over five minutes before one patron at the bar noticed us and told the bartender that people were waiting The "who appeared to be manager" who we could see the whole time, finally set his coffee or latte down and came to greet us. While smacking gum, he sat us down and took our drink order. When the server brought our drinks they were completely wrong. After bringing us the correct drinks, we proceeded to order appetizers (meatballs and wings), the server had to return back to the table twice after ordering to ask us what sauce we wanted with the appetizers. At this time we could see the manager two tables over talking to another couple and giving them a refund for their poor experience. After that, we saw a drunken lady fall out of her seat and knock over several chairs. Not one employee approached the lady to check and see if she was alright. A few minutes later the server returned to take our dinner order, in which she stated they were out of both items we were ordering (meatloaf and chicken). At this point we told her to cancel our appetizers and decided to leave. The entire time, we could not figure out this "identity crisis" of a restaurant. Was it as restaurant, a sports bar, a social house or a club? The walls were bare, a random barn door hanging above the entrance, a jukebox, the noise was overwhelming, the number of easily observable intoxicated patrons were stumbling everywhere, and there were sports playing on all TV. We dine out quite often and this was the worst restaurant experience we have ever had.

name: China Lin Restaurant
categories: Restaurants, Chinese
text: Very friendly place with dine in or carry out and delivery. Prices are very reasonable and there are specials. The food is always tasty but it is a loose interpretation of what these dishes are at most Chinese restaurant. With that said most food here tastes a lot alike. Again it is not bad, just kind of generic and different than what most other places taste like if you order the same dish.

text:
This place is really, really good.  I had the soup/sandwich combo with a dessert (from some pastry place in Waterloo).  The sandwich was delicious and the soup was homemade and out of this world.  I can't even begin to describe how much I loved that dessert.

Make the trip to Milstadt for lunch.  You won't be disappointed.

name: Valvoline Instant Oil Change
categories: Auto Repair, Automotive, Oil Change Stations
text:
Late hours is a plus.  

This is a fleet vehicle.  I would NEVER pay cash prices at this place.  It looks like 100 bucks for oil change and tire rotation.  Have these folks not heard about the bad economy?  Also many Jiffy Lubes vacuum the inside of the car as a courtesy.  

The waiting area is not much.  No tv, no radio, No reading materials.  The interior is not exactly clean, not exactly dirty.  It was hot in there as well.

The bathroom is clean, since there is no toilet paper!?!

They tried to talk me out of the tire rotation?  Supposedly due to the lateness of the hour.  

I wonder if they would still charge the fleet supplier?

Also, a small point, but no  manager came out to talk to me.

text: I have finally worked my way up to having dinner here, and I'm glad did. The dishes were creative and delicious. The wine suggestions are spot on, and the weekly wine tastings are fun.  I'm looking forward to see how this place continues to develop.

name: Evermore Gallery Tattoos
categories: Beauty & Spas, Tattoo, Piercing
text:
I brought my newly 18 year old cousin to Evermore this afternoon to make an appointment for his first tattoo. Immediately upon walking in we were greeted warmly by the receptionist and one of the artists who pointed us in the direction of another artist in shop that would work the best for the piece my cousin is wanting. He lost his dad last year and the tattoo is a memorial, so it is very important to him.

I have plenty of experience with tattoos and tattoo shops with over 14 tattoos of my own. I didn't want to take my never inked, naive cousin to the place that I frequent due to difference in art style and the edgier/harder atmosphere, so based on friends' experiences with Evermore and the clientele they usually receive (college town, locals, walk-ins) I thought this would be the perfect place for him. It totally is. 

Thank you so much for making his first tattoo experience pleasant, not intimidating and so far very smooth. He is due in next week and I am more than comfortable after meeting his artist Cole, who was very informative and kind. Two thumbs up from this overprotective family member!

categories: Bars, Nightlife, Restaurants, Mexican
text:
I placed an order for takeout today at 12:45 p.m., which included the following:

Cheese Nachos
Enchaladas Famosas
Burrito Jalisco

The lady on the phone was very nice, and said our food would be ready for pickup in 10 minutes (which was the first red flag).

I showed up 10 minutes later to pickup my food, and it was ready. The restaurant looked nice on the inside, but there were not many people there. I am not sure if that was because it was just past lunch time, or if people generally don't like the food (I am leaning toward the latter).

I drove right home to take the food to my family (I live extremely close to Zapata's).

The consensus was that everything was cold, soggy, and tasteless. It is hard to believe that something that was just made could be cold and soggy, but it was. It seemed like everything  was microwaved. The chicken and beef tasted like it was not seasoned at all. I had to add hot sauce to my food just to make it taste decent.

Good points:

Customer service
Speed
Price
Restaurant looks nice
Portions
Provided tortilla chips and salsa

Bad points:
Food was terrible on many levels

Obviously, for a restaurant to receive a good review, the food has to be quality, and Zapata's certainly failed to provide that. I will certainly not be coming back.

name: Mary Jane's Solid Oak Furniture
categories: Home & Garden, Shopping, Furniture Stores, Office Equipment, Outdoor Furniture Stores
text:
Stumbled onto this shop during a trip to St Louis.  
Totally overwhelmed by the vast assortment of high quality Amish furniture.  Met Mary Jane as well as Don her husband.  MJ runs the retail showroom and Don works in the shop making some of the furniture.
It is nice to see a shop that carry's such nice stuff.  In a day and age where furniture is cheap and imported from who knows where and of dubious quality, and thrown away 5 years later, its great to find stuff that you can enjoy, and pass on to your kids and grandchildren.  You pay more, but you get more..  Plus the styles are timeless classics.  
Went in to look... and bought three pieces.
We will make this a must do when in the St Louis area..

text:

Good service also. 

Hoping for more local craft beer choices next time. 

Awesome place.

categories: Comfort Food, Arts & Entertainment, Farms, Specialty Food, Shopping, Butcher, Food, Nurseries & Gardening, Restaurants, American (Traditional), Home & Garden, Pick Your Own Farms, Fruits & Veggies
text:
I have been meaning to write a review for Eckert's Pick Ur Own for awhile now. The hubby and I have gone numerous times, picking apples, strawberries and blackberries. The bounty we've picked has even been the topic of many of my blog posts and gluten-free food recipes I've made for the blog. We LOVE Eckert's. I was going to give it a beautiful 5-star. 

Then a few weeks ago I talked a group of my mom friends and their kids to come out and pick blackberries. We all had a blast and loved every second of it (and If at all interested in seeing the blog post on this picking adventure, here is the link... http://www.magpieatheart.com/back-to-the-blackberry-fields-we-go/). After rolling in and paying for our blackberries, we decided to give the restaurant a try. I am Celiac, and so is another Mom and her daughter. I had seen reviews and it mentioned on their online menu that they can accommodate gluten-free eating. Great! Perfect!! We all happily walked over to the restaurant at about 11:30am... and that's were the "happy" ended.

Perhaps we should have made a reservation? Perhaps it was six moms and six two year olds walking in to the restaurant that "spooked" the lady in charge of seating? But we were greeted by a grumpy and rather rude lady who said they really didn't have room at the moment and she'd have to "see what she could do" to seat a table of twelve. There were many empty tables at this point. But we all set our kids into their convenient kids play area and waited.

Ten minutes passed as we watched group after group that arrived after us be seated before us. Our very hungry kids were starting to get antsy so one of the group went up and told the seater that we were willing to break up into two or three table to be able to be seated sooner. I was not the one to go up so I'm unclear as to what exactly was said, but again, it wasn't friendly. 

Long story short, after standing there for twenty-five minutes without being seated we left. I would have loved to try the food here. All of us would have. But from the rudeness we were shown I don't think any one of us will be back. Poorly played, Eckert's Restaurant. Poorly played.

text: McAlister's has always been a favorite of mine since I went to my first one in Mississippi. First off if you live in the Edwardsville area come in and try this new location out! I ordered the choose 2 and had the Spud Max and the New Yorker sandwich.  The sandwich was served hot with melted cheese on rye bread. name: TJ Maxx
categories: Department Stores, Fashion, Shopping
text:
There are several TJMaxx and Marshall stores closer to where I live but this is the first TJM I have ever been to and it never disappoints. I can usually find some really great deals toward the end of a season or find some random things that are priced lower than other places.

First of all, don't expect to walk into a high-end store with all the frillies. You'll find bargains here if you have the patience, young padawan.

Now to serious shopping business! One of my regular purchases from here is a triple-milled French lavender bath/shower soap because they usually have them for a much better price than what I can find online or from Nordstrom Rack. This specific store carries a good variety compared to the others and I normally come out with a few soaps so I don't have to come back very often. They also have great deals on salon brand shampoo and conditioner although if you are looking for specific ones, it could be a hit and miss. They have some facial cleanser for cheaper than what you could get them for from Beauty Brands which is wonderful. If I can get something for less, I definitely will! 

I have made several purchases from here including shoes, accessories, home necessities, clothing and have never been disappointed. I have been buying some food containers here for my lunches and they have awesome deals on those. I might replace all my old storage containers in a few more visits!  Some of the things here might be last season's but those would mostly be the shoes and clothing. As far as the home essentials and hair care products, I don't think they really go out of style.

My only issue is that this place is not so organized. Like I said, patience.

text: I was drugged here, presumably by one of the bartenders. I went out with friends, whom very literally, saved my life. I have been a bartender for 5 years, so I know what my drinks were made with and how much I can consume. I was actually the designated driver and drank the absolute least out of us. I was completely fine until my last order, then I remember nothing. I have been drugged/sexually assaulted while unconcious several years ago. This felt the same. I couldn't even stand up, much less  walk or drive. At this point, I remember vomiting uncontrollably and being fearful for my life. It took me a long time to process if I would post this review, but after hearing many similar stories and that a recent bartender had been found drugging people for months, I decided that it was for the best interest of the community to share my experience somewhere. I have searched google for similar experiences, and they go back YEARS. I'm never going here again, and I will never recommend it to anyone. To all my girls (and boys) out there, I'd advise you to stay away for your own safety. I'd give zero stars if I could.

text: I went to this nail salon today. I got the deluxe pedicure for $27.00. After they painted my nails they put me in me front of a fan and left me there for over 30 minutes. I was supposed to get a paraffin wax included in the cost of the pedicure. I do not have time to wait that long for the paraffin wax. I walked out (of course after paying) and I'll never ever go back to that salon again. I felt ignored and I also felt that after the salon ran my get credit card they did not care anymore about me as a customer. I will definitely be looking for a new nail salon.

name: Penn Station
categories: Fast Food, Sandwiches, Restaurants
text:
The best sandwich they have is the Philly Steak, I eat here because of its location, for a chain restaurant they have that one good one and then the rest are o.k. in my opinion.

The building itself is nice and clean, plenty of spots to dine at.  The service is good, no complaints there at all.

My sandwich looks great always and is presented fairly well for me.  It has always looked delicious and the smell of the sandwich, you can tell they keep fresh ingredients for their sandwiches and tasty vegetables nice and plump full of flavor.  The meat seems well prepped.  Good clean tasting food, never greasy to me, the Philly has a little bit of oil on it making a savory sandwich, but nothing terrible overwhelming, only great flavor.

The fries are the best.  You will get plenty of the fries and they are really good, I think they cut those fresh daily.  No frozen old taste, just clean and delicious.  If you don't want anything else get the fries!

attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'False', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': True, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False'}
categories: American (Traditional), Buffets, Restaurants
text:
Heard of Golden Corral for many years and after dining with wonderful friends who love to "eat" - we decided to make it an afternoon delight!  We met at the Golden Corral located at 1079 Collinsville Crossing Boulevard in Collinsville, IL.

It is one price for all you can swallow.  I started out slow . . . inquired with our friend Michael is they offered an orientation before you dive right in - no orientation really needed.  You get a plate and start the hunt!  They have nachos, tacos, breakfast foods, main courses like sirloin steak (even had a gentlemen cooking your meat for you), salads - did not try this area - and then dessert zone. 

Meatloaf was delicious and fresh . . . as was the thin crust pizza.  Mashed potatoes were warm and tasty as was the chocolate covered marshmellows on a stick - had seven of those.  It was a buffet, right?  The yeast rolls were fresh from the oven and with honey butter . . . VERY VERY VERY tasty.  

Will definately go again . . . just take it slow - none of my plates were full at all - and the fried chicken drum sticks were over-the-top mouth watering.

So next time you are up for a place with everything - check out Golden Corral in Collinsville, IL - just off I-70 in front of Home Depot.

name: Farmer's Market
categories: Specialty Food, Fruits & Veggies, Food
text: Love this place...they always are friendly and treat you well.  They have wonderful plants and great fresh produce!

name: EXO Lounge
categories: Cocktail Bars, Dance Clubs, Wine Bars, Lounges, Bars, Nightlife
text: Stopped in here, not to get my nails done, but just to have a cocktail, and by GOLLY, it was reeeeally good!!!  I talked with the barmaid and ended up choosing the Sugar and Spice cocktail and it was unlike any other cocktail I've ever had.  She suggested that I lick some of the salt from the rim before taking a sip and she was SO right!  Can't say enough about this drink.  It wasn't cheap, but worth it as far as I am concerned.  The service was excellent and I'd definitely stop back in here.

text: Oh mister donuts you have not changed a bit since the last time I've had you...20 years ago. These are not the best donuts I've ever had but the taste of these donuts bring back childhood memories. I personally enjoyed their donut holes more than any of the other donuts. There was not much of a selection around noon. Most were sold out. These donut holes gave me some major indigestion that lasted until 6AM the next day. I guess I haven't had sweets/oily foods in awhile.

name: Hoof & Paw Animal Clinic
categories: Pets, Veterinarians, Pet Sitting, Pet Boarding, Pet Groomers, Pet Services
text: Horrible experience with the vet at Hoof & Paw.  He was mean to our Yorkie and rude and insensitive to my daughter whose pup he was seeing for a lump on his jawline. He grabbed our dog by the throat and basically assaulted him.  He kept telling my daughter that our dog had cancer and was going to die so we may as well just put him down.  He looked at her and kept asking how much money SHE had to spend on him to try to make him well.  He then said it would be really expensive and the cancer would come back and kill him anyway.  He never tested our dog for anything.  He literally grabbed him by the throat, palpated the area, then gave his grim diagnosis.  That was 2 years ago.  He is still alive and well...no cancer treatment required.  We've come to decide it must have been a tooth abscess or something.  Horrible, horrible experience for me, my daughter, and our Yorkie.  Needless to say, I will not go back.

name: St Louis Veterinary Center
categories: Pet Groomers, Pet Boarding, Veterinarians, Pet Services, Pets, Pet Sitting
text: The best! Absolutely great people and great care for your pets. My dogs have had everything from routine visits to complex surgery and I cannot say enough good things about Dr. Mattes and her team.

name: Family Physicians of O'fallon
categories: Health & Medical, Family Practice, Doctors, Internal Medicine
text: I'd previously written a bad review of this place then I had a change of heart and took it down. I should have left the original review up. Always go with your "first mind."  The administrative personnel at this "clinic" are thoroughly incompetent. Bottomline: They referred me to Belleville Memorial for a procedure that Memorial wouldn't do without seeing me first and cost me $54 unnecessarily. Save yourself headaches and find yourself another family physician. The doctors are capable but the admin personnel will routinely drop the ball and screw stuff up. They just don't seem to care.

name: Kaldi's Coffeehouse
categories: Coffee & Tea, Food
text: Kaldis is my lifeline. If not for the caffeine, then for the smiles and friendly chatter from their always personable staff, who I adore as friends. Thanks for always making my day a little brighter.

name: Market Basket
categories: Specialty Food, Meat Shops, Fruits & Veggies, Food
text: Ohhh.... My husband just bought meat. There.... The smell so bad....it permeates the food anything u buy there...ugggg... Could not eat it made me gag....walk in the place and u can not misss the smell... And its. Thru all the food.... Dann dudes.... Clean your meat department.... Or change your ventilation......something....fire your meat manager or store manager.....it could be a nice store other than the smell......

text: Very rude. Pulled up at the drive thru, I asked if she could hold on a minute so I could decide what to order for my girlfriend and myself. She then yelled "You know, you can order" I then ordered my food and pulled up to the next window to pay. She didn't say a word. When I got home I opened the bag to find my food in a paper tray with another paper tray on top.... I was expecting a box, the food was cold and it seemed like my food was just thrown into the bag.

categories: Mexican, Restaurants
text: I have never been a huge fan of this place but I thought we would give it another try. The mood/decor is about the same as any typical restaurant. Our waiter(s) was very nice and polite although he did put lemons in our water even though we asked for none. No big deal. The drink glasses are giant so they don't need to be refilled as often. That is a plus. Our food came out extremely fast. I got the enchiladas supremas (4 different enchiladas). The sauce/salsa on top was kind of meaty. It tasted like a cheap red sauce out of a frozen 'Italian' dinner. The beef didn't seem to be cooked as much as it should have but none of us got sick or anything. My meal had too much lettuce and my enchiladas were somewhat soggy because the plate was watery. Like I said, I have been here many times and thought I would give it 1 last chance. If you are in a pinch and this is the only Mexican you can get, I would give it a go, but I like El Mezcal in Bethalto better.

name: Pink Poodle Pet Salon
categories: Pets, Pet Services, Pet Groomers
text: This is a wonderful place to bring your pets for grooming.  We bring our two dogs here and they always do a great job.  The staff is really nice and the place is super cute!

name: Jiffy Lube
categories: Oil Change Stations, Auto Repair, Automotive
text: I visited this oil change place because it was the closest to me. I asked the manager to check if my coolant had been topped off because my temp gauge was going into the red. He asked the service tech did he do so. He replied, "If here gauge is going into the red, she might need a new sensor." Fine. I pay. I'm off. Not 60 seconds later, the gauge is rising. I go up a few blocks to Auto Zone to buy some coolant and I go straight home. The next morning when my car is cool, I pop the hood and check my coolant and NOTHING HAS BEEN ADDED. I called the manager and explain that nothing was added to my coolant reservoir and not even the dust that was on the cap and reservoir had been disturbed. No finger prints, nothing. The manager offers a 15 dollar off coupon, which I picked, but then I started thinking, next time it may be worse! I might not even get my oil changed out or worse, not getting what I paid for, not to mention that the same incompetent technician works there.  I will not be back. DO NOT GO HERE. A couple days later, after I ADDED some coolant, my car's temp gauge is operating just fine and I didn't need a new sensor, either.

name: Lonnie Nail Spa
categories: Beauty & Spas, Nail Salons
text: I went in for a pedicure, and I wanted extra service so I went ahead and got what they called a Nu-Pedicure.. For the price I paid, it was well worth it.. I had no problems during the duration of my visit, everything was fine. I go to the dryer to wait and have my Polish dry when she came over and asked if I could pay now.. I proceeded to give her my debit card. She came back with the receipt and a pen to fill it out. She then stood over me, watching me as I fill out how much I was going to tip her. I then calculated what a 15% tip would be.. I wrote everything down, and signed. She took the recipt and gave it to "Lonnie". Lonnie then interrupted my phone call I was on to ask if the amount I put on the tip portion of the receipt was correct. I then said, "Yes, that is 15%...." she replied back very rudely, " Yea.... Hmm, okay"... Very rude, and unappreciated I would say! Anyway, after that, I was still drying my toes. The woman came back over and put some type of oil on my toes, making my feet very greasy. I get pedicures almost every week when I can, and that is not what they do after you are completely done and drying your nails. I was confused and irritated. I asked her to get me something to wipe it off, she then try to grab my socks and wipe my feet off..WHAT!? I don't understand. Needless to say, that experience really made an impact and I will defintely not be going back to "Lonnies Nail Spa"!

name: Shenanigans Bar & Grill
categories: Restaurants, Pubs, Nightlife, Bars, American (Traditional)
text:
During the day, this is a normal chain family restaurant (with lots of crap on the walls). At night, they push all the tables to the side and it becomes the closest thing to a frat party that you'll find in Edwardsville. 

The last time I was there, someone was jumped in the parking lot and came inside bleeding from his scalp. Generally you can find a group of girls creating spectacle by grinding on each other towards the end of the evening. 

I can't understand why the police don't wait at the exit of the parking lot and arrest everyone who leaves there for driving under the influence. 

I've never had the food, but something tells me I don't have to...

name: Hideg Pharmacy
categories: Health & Medical, Drugstores, Medical Supplies, Shopping, Pharmacy
text: Great resource if you require some medical equipment; they have a full range in stock and reasonable prices for renting wheelchairs, etc.  The staff are very professional and they make everything easy.

name: Tienda El Maguey
categories: Food, Grocery
text: Sooooo disappointed! La Gardenia was my favorite Mexican place in the area. Waited for the remodel so we decided to try it out tonight. It had a new name El Maguey, so I asked the hostess,  is the menu still the same?" She said it was and that the name just changed. So we decided to stay. The menu was nothing like La Gardenias, and the food failed in comparison. It took forever, the service was awful, never checked on us after dropping off the food. Will not go back for sure, so bummed out!

name: Dobbs Auto Center
categories: Tires, Oil Change Stations, Automotive, Auto Repair
text: I cannot thank these guys enough for helping me every time my engine light pops on, my tires need to be rotated or I need to schedule a last minute oil change before I go out of town. There manager Doug is so friendly and patient with everyone who walks through his door, Steven has been great at getting my car in last minute, and Cory (the new service manager) does a great job explaining everything to me how I can understand it. Thanks!

text: I regularly make the drive from north St. Louis County to Columbia, IL because Val's treats are AMAZING! Everything is crafted by hand, from scratch, with love and artistry. Don't miss the peanut butter bars and sweet potato mini bundt cakes!

name: Mission Accomplished Tire & Auto
categories: Automotive, Oil Change Stations, Tires, Auto Repair
text: Mission Accomplished has taken care of our three family vehicles for several years now. They are available, they listen, they promptly update us on the status of diagnostics and repairs, and in our opinion, they charge reasonable fees for repairs. Everyone is always polite and prompt in service. It's great not to have to call around to many different mechanics for estimates since we know we'll always get a fair and honest deal. Thank you for always taking great care of us MA!

name: My Love Nails
categories: Beauty & Spas, Nail Salons, Hair Removal
text: I've been coming to this place for about a year because its close to my house. I have HORRIBLE calluses on my feet and can never remove them properly. This is one of the only places that actually use the little callus scraper thing. They are always nice and get me in right away, even when I walk in. I love them! I love the big TVs and they always have something good on, like a movie, or right now they have the ball game on. For the price, I think you get a lot. One of the cheapest pedis is $23 and they take the time to rub your feet down and it includes a paraffin wax dip. Love this place! Wish had the money to go back more often :)
