name: Mueth's Tavern
text:
We have been coming to Mueth's (locals say Meeth's BTW) since before the old place burned down and replaced by this modern and good looking up to date sports bar.  You can even charge your phone as outlets all have usb.

Menu has burgers , chicken wraps, pizza. etc. Never been seriously disappointed.The summer menu has fried chicken and fish Friday thru Sunday. Each day has a special. Staff is very friendly. $6 beer pitchers. Franzia wine $3.  Soda free refills. Separate room for parties. Lots of TV's.  Cardinal memorabilia on walls. 

Smithton is so fortunate to have a first class sports bar as the owner did an excellent job rebuilding after a terrible fire to the older place. All sorts of folks come here like golfers to celebration parties to just couples. 
Entertainment from bands at 9pm or so. 

On street parking only 
$1 charge for credit cards but modest menu prices make up for that. 
Street side patio seating.  

If you want to get away from big city hassles come to Mueth's for a nice country drive and small town hospitality without the pricey menus.

name: Circa Boutique
categories: Women's Clothing, Fashion, Shopping
text: Love to support local businesses.. this is one of my favorites! Walk in for 1 thing and walk out with 4 (at least!) Cute, fun clothing and gifts that are all reasonably priced!

name: Stonewolf Golf Club
categories: Active Life, Golf
text: Hands down one of my FAVORITE courses. I split my time between Dallas and Scott AFB and it was so great finding a Nicklaus design so close to home. Just about every hole is exciting and a few area thrill ride. The greens give you a taste of what's it's like for the guys in tour, and you need to place those approaches in the right spots to keep those strokes down. The club house is nice and the staff that I've encountered have all been very nice. I always look forward to a round here!

name: Alton's Best Cabs
categories: Hotels & Travel, Transportation, Taxis
text: i just called to be picked up and was told theyvwould be here in 15 min. so i waited right in front of the door for 30 min. so my wife called them back and was told thatvtheybhad already been here and waited 5 or 6 min. impossable #1 i was right in front of the door like i said 2. the dogs were never phased like they are anytime a car is here.tgey flat out lied.

name: DraftKings at Casino Queen
categories: Casinos, Arts & Entertainment
text: Upon checkin the computer kept freezing up but they kept me at the counter for almost an hour trying to get it resolved.  Than about 9pm one evening we discovered they had a laundromat, when we tried to use it we found out we needed a key!  Yikes, don't you think they would have told us about their amenities and given us a key to them?  Out of the two other people I spoke to at the RV Park one of them had also not been given a key.  Than when I tried to tell the onsite manager about it on checkout she went thru an elaborate explanation of how they always follow a script and that just couldn't have happened.  We were patient with all this but than when our travel plans changed and we checked out at 3:12pm instead of staying another night they charged us for a full night!  At least they could have prorated it or something.  Besides the customer service issues the RV park is merely a concrete pad.  The one nice thing was each space had a small tree and they had a nice park for kids but no pool.  Next time I come to St Louis I will definitely not be coming here.

name: Nirvana
categories: Beauty & Spas, Nail Salons, Hair Salons
text:
I m surprised that they don't have many reviews. But anyways it was my first visit in finding someone/some place better than franchised places. I really liked the service. Finally I found my place after trying out so many different places as I moved here last year.  

Def recommended place specially for guys.

name: Anytime Fitness
categories: Active Life, Trainers, Fitness & Instruction, Gyms
text: It's a pretty good gym. A little small for my liking so I'm branching out to new possibilities. It served its purpose though and the staff was always very nice.

text: Yummy pulled pork. Just enough smoke and spice. Who needs sauce?  The sauce is smoky sweet. Sauce on side. Wait staff attentive and food out quickly!!

name: Hair Saloon
categories: Beauty & Spas, Barbers
text:
Blades used to cut this Ninja's hair was proved worthy. After a long day this Ninja recommends you get a Signature Cut. 
It comes with a really beautiful stylist, hot face towel, neck and shoulder massage and complimentary drinks always. (non-alcoholic)
After a long day of doing Ninja stuff this is a great place to get a haircut. I asked if they did shave (non-pubic area) and because this is a state run by a bunch of sissy's it will require a special license to do so. 
Walk into this place and you can feel your testosterone levels rise. Do you have ED?This place will probably cure it. You have TV's in every corner, Sportcenter, News, Putting Green, Checkers, Shoe Shine Station and best of all Hot Women. Add more cleavage and *censored* and this place will earn the coveted 5 Ninja star. 
Hair Saloon I give you 4 Stars and "I'm not only a hair saloon member, I'm also a Ninja." ;)
That quote was all original BTW.

name: The Abbey
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}"}
categories: Cafes, Tobacco Shops, Restaurants, Shopping, Food, Coffee & Tea
text:
um. this is by far the cutest coffeehouse i've been to. 

i'm not going to lie, belleville, illinois is kind of a random place to be, so i wasn't expecting much from this cafe.... but it's SUPER CUTE. there is a ton of cute artwork on the walls, and it is connected to a little bookstore. they also have a handpainted linen thing hanging on the wall - the decor is just so cute (and wonderfully eclectic - seems like all of the pieces are made by local artists!). 

they also have a little bookshelf in the back that is called the abbey lending library - bring a book, borrow a book.... aw.

i ordered an italian soda ($2.35 including tax) and it's yummy. 

lunch is served from 11am-2pm

there is a LOT of seating inside, and there is also outdoor seating. also, the background music is pretty low, which makes for a peaceful time.

go here! you'll like it :)

categories: Wraps, Restaurants, Salad, Fast Food
text: This is one of E-Ville's newest chain restaurants located next to Dierberg's.  I've been here twice and both times I tried the buffalo chicken wrap with brown rice.  While the wrap was good, it wasn't very flavorful.  I expected more from something with "buffalo" in its name.  As a side item, I had the hummus and tortilla chips.  The hummus is awesome.  It is probably the best part of the meal.  The offerings seem to be a lot more healthier than other fast food restaurants.  I will probably be back to try other items on their menu.

name: Super 8 by Wyndham Belleville St. Louis Area
address: 600 East Main Street, Hwy 159 and E Main St.
categories: Event Planning & Services, Hotels & Travel, Hotels
text:
This place was fine-and-dandy August 20. We're not talking Ritz. But it was a clean room, the AC worked, and the bed was firm. Fridge and microwave, plenty of hangers. Bathroom was clean.

This was where we needed to be. Walking distance to dinner and HS reunion location. Pammy and I shared a room. It worked out fine. We both had a queen bed.

Check-in guy was so nice and told me about the breakfast buffet and where the ice machine was located. Very personable.

I would go again. Free WIFI.

name: Posh Nail Lounge
categories: Nail Salons, Beauty & Spas
text: Made an appointment and they were right on time. The wine was good and the service great. I love the pedicure I got and the wine was an added bonus. I would definitely recommend this place.

name: Yo Toppings
categories: Food, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Hot Dogs, Restaurants
text: Tonight was my first experience at Yo Toppings. We were greeted at the door , they explained the process and we started. This business has only been open for six weeks. Ten different yogurts to try , too many toppings and sprinkles to count.Plenty of inside and outside seating. Games and a small foosball table made this a true family place. Check it out.

text: First of all, if I have to wipe off my cup because there is more cherry syrup on the outside than on the inside, that is a problem.  Second of all, when I get home I find that my order is wrong, that is also a problem.  At this point I'm thinking three strikes and you're out.  But then I took a bite of the Royale burger.........Oh glorious joy!  That burger saved them from getting one star.  This Steak n' Shake needs some help in the customer service arena.  The food is good.  Well, the food that they get correct.

name: Sam's Club
categories: Shopping, Wholesale Stores, Food, Grocery, Drugstores, Fashion, Automotive, Department Stores, Tires
text:
Still have a temporary card because, twice now, I've been recommended by the greeter to get my permanent card, twice I've waited in line only to find out that their system was down. How come nobody tells the greeter these things? 
Then, as I was trying to check out, they tell me that my membership hasn't been paid! I've paid & used my temporary card there before. I didn't have the time nor the patience to go Back to member services AGAIN to figure out their problem. When I have the time & patience, I will return to see if they've finally gotten their act together.

categories: Tea Rooms, Restaurants, Coffee & Tea, Cafes, Bakeries, Food, American (Traditional)
text: One of my favorite easy laid back Sunday brunch go to places. I haven't had much of the coffee because I'm very picky about my coffee. I love the quesadilla and my son really enjoys the pancake with sausage and this kid is picker than I am!  The hubs enjoys the coffee and tells me I am really missing out. Maybe next time I'll give it a shot....until then, add this place to your "to eat list". Fair warning though, the window sitting area is great unless it is sunny because you will get blinded. PS, I LOVE flowers and they have the cutest little center pieces of fresh flowers.

name: Quality Inn O'Fallon I-64
categories: Hotels & Travel, Event Planning & Services, Hotels
text: Check in was easy. Room was marginal. A/C wasn't on and room was super muggy.  All in all room met cheap hotel expectations. Breakfast was all right. But 30 minutes into a slow morning trashcan shouldn't have been full.  Maybe the staff, whose uniform evidently included Victoria Secret sweat pants, could have emptied the trash instead of fixing herself breakfast.  Guess you get what you pay for?

name: Audio Tech
categories: Automotive, Auto Parts & Supplies, Car Stereo Installation
text:
Awesome! I just stopped by after reading another viewers comment and decided to ask  them to quote 4 (2 pairs) new speakers for my husbands suburban. The owner immediately confirmed we needed new speakers, quoted them ($150 less than another local company over the phone) and had them installed within an hour. He is a small shop, so if he is working on another vehicle, you may need to schedule an appointment, 
I will only come here in the future and highly recommend this shop! 
He doesn't take advantage of his customers and honestly recommends what you need.
He has won awards for best sound, so he obviously knows what he is doing. 
In the past, I have left places feeling taken advantage of and his experience was completely different. 
Highly recommend!

name: Duke Bakery
categories: Donuts, Bakeries, Restaurants, Food
text: We used Duke Bakery for our wedding, but we went with the brownies instead of cake. Brownies are hands down better than cake anyway, but Duke brownies are amazing. We ordered several varieties and cut them into fourths.

categories: Sandwiches, Restaurants
text: Updating my previous 5 star review. Before I posted my previous review I read a few comments of how customers were treated poorly. I now understand why. I am still a regular to eat here after a year and a half. I still eat here about once a week, sometimes more. Im at the point where I get one of two sandwiches and he could guess what I want when I walk through the door. This time the owner decides he cant make a "special sandwich" because he is too busy. I have noticed over the year this place is Almost always busy. If business is good why is this shop always understaffed? It is not my fault that you're  busy, it is your duty to please the customer. Now to my "special sandwich." I wasn't requesting additional toppings you need to cook or anything out of the ordinary. My alter was a different sauce and subtract an ingredient(bacon). If anything that is SAVING you time because you Don't have to cook the bacon. But no. The owner didnt have the time. So congratulations, you just lost a regular.

Cons: Need sound panels, the place is loud.  TV's are small.  Our large group all agreed that the tacos were terrible.  Other food at our table was good.  Need more draft beer selections.  When we go out, we don't want cans and bottles.

text: When I am in Millstadt, this is one of my favorite places to eat.  I get the egg drop soup and the special fried rice.  It is VERY good, and the prices are very reasonable.  I love that it is a family restaurant and I was waited on by the owners children.  They are cool kids.  It is nice to see kids willing and happy to help their parents.  It is right across the street from the school, so it is handy if I am there for a school function.

name: Laura Buick GMC
categories: Auto Repair, Automotive, Tires, Used Car Dealers, Car Dealers
text: Had a very pleasant experience with the folks at Laura GMC Buick. Discussed a vehicle over the phone, everything they told me was accurate, and a I got a great car at a good price. Took a longer than I'd like wrapping up paperwork but otherwise it would have been a 5 star experience.

text: The food at this location is absolutely delicious! I ate here a couple times while visiting family over the summer, and I had no complaints at all. All of the dishes were very clean, and I think it's nice that they bring your food to you, and bus the tables. It was just unbelievably cold in there. That's really the only thing I didn't like.

name: Meckfessel Tire & Auto
categories: Auto Repair, Automotive, Tires
text: Service was quick  and professional. I like to spend my money in the community where I live. Meckfessel's was the same price as the larger tire outlet with a more professional level of service. I am very pleased with my purchase.

name: Aquatic Treasures
categories: Pet Services, Pet Stores, Aquariums, Local Fish Stores, Aquarium Services, Pets, Active Life
text: We drove a while to get to this store and it was a disappointment. The store seemed empty from the front. There's a lot of tanks in the back which had a lot but seems a bit pricey. Overall it was a nice store. What made me give the low review was the staff. There were two people and neither even said hi to me until I said hi to them. They seems bothered we were there. I asked a question about a tank and the guy acted like I was dumb and didn't know what I was talking about. He looked it up only to be surprised when I was right. We left without buying anything and I won't be back. Probably worth a look if you're close but I wouldn't make he drive from STL.

name: PTs Brooklyn
categories: Nightlife, Adult Entertainment
text:
The quality of girls is low. Most were visibly pregnant when we were there.

The positives are that it is cheap. Don't let the girls con you. All can be had for very little.  The bouncers stay out of the way as long as you stay in line.

name: Green Mount Family Dentistry
categories: Health & Medical, General Dentistry, Orthodontists, Dentists, Endodontists
text:
I will be looking for a new dentist, not here. 
I moved here from out of state and opted to go here because, well, first impression seemed like they were clean & organized. And when I asked a coworker from the area about it, he didn't go there, but said the Littlefields were pretty well known in the area as a "dentist" family.  
I have been here 4 times. Twice for annuals & twice for fillings.  Coming from prior dentist (in another state) I had a few "watch" areas.  
On my first appointment they told me one of my watch areas would need to be filled. Dr. Niflin (my spelling of her name is probably wrong) did the filling, on the spot, as it was small & quick. She did an excellent job. I was impressed with the technology the place used & the doctor & hygienists were very friendly & attentive. 
On my second annual, all my "watch" areas now needed to be done, I was told. For multiple years at my old dentist, these were watch areas that they said weren't getting any bigger, but regardless, a watch area will eventually need to be filled anyway (in my opinion).  Because they were on different sides of my mouth, they instructed me to do 2 different appointments so my whole mouth wasn't numbed at once.
Now for my low rating: for the first side, I had Dr. Littlefield.  Very nice, but nothing seemed to go right. The dam kept slipping, the filling wasn't setting right, the filing to get the filling to match my bite after - nothing. She tried hard & everything finished & seemed well.  When I went to floss before bed that night I found extra sensitivity between the two different locations that had the new fillings and a spot where 2 of my teeth had been cemented together (that weren't part of the work site). I figured after the filling the sensitivity to the spots was normal so I ignored it. After 3 days of trying at least 3 times a day, I was finally able to break the cement & get the floss between the 2 teeth. Seems normal again. But the sensitivity by the filling sites remained & when flossing those spots, the teeth were not even remotely close together anymore. I couldn't chew on that side without LARGE pieces of food falling in & causing pain. 
When I went back in for the one on the other side, I had Dr Niflin. I asked her about the sensitivity/pain/large space between the teeth now.  She recognized the teeth were further apart now than they were/should be, but said unless it was making me uncomfortable, it wasn't going to cause more damage/be bad.  She did the one filling, once again basically perfectly.
Since it wasn't going to hurt anything having the gap in my teeth (it is 2 spots back in molars), I figured I'd see how it went.  Alittle over a month later now, my gums are inflamed in those spots, bleeding at times, my mouth hurts, and if it wasn't obvious I can't chew on that side without something stabbing my gums there. I think even some of my gums there has died & fallen off (or in dental terms recessed) making my molars feel slightly "loose". All this literally happened within like a day recently (the very bad gum stuff). I have been diligent in my dental care, so that is not the reason. In fact, the spacing is so far apart now, that before the work, I could barely get floss in, now the spacing is so far that the floss doesn't even work & I've had to use a finger to take the large pieces of food out that flossing, brushing, & mouthwash leave behind.
I was actually on here, yelp, to find a new dentist to fix me so my mouth isn't in pain. If it was just one thing, yes, we're human, we do make mistakes/not perfect. But this was both places she went in my mouth are now bad & even a place right next to it! (And there's filling crud stuck on my teeth yet so they're no longer smooth). That's all more than one little mistake, which I'd understand.  
If you do go here, just make sure you have Dr Niflin, she's good.  I'd avoid the other doctor. And the office in General is very clean & nice. I just worry about the competency based on my experience.... (I feel very bad writing this, but it is truly how I feel, and how annoying/bad my mouth feels.)

name: Meineke Car Care Center
categories: Automotive, Tires, Oil Change Stations, Auto Repair
text: I have been calling service centers to price brake pad / rotors. This was the only place that refused to give me a price on the phone. If I wanted a price I would have to go in so they can remove the tires before giving me a price!  Why would anyone fall for that,???

name: Four Points by Sheraton St. Louis - Fairview Heights
categories: Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Hotels & Travel, Venues & Event Spaces
text: It's an old hotel and it smells. There is some sort of carpet-mildew/mold problem (I saw it all over in the first floor hallway by the gym) and if you're lucky, your room won't stank and your carpet will be dry. Room was pretty dirty, and of course smelled like mildew infested butthole. The gym is a joke, one treadmill was broken of course and one was falling apart. This place is not cheap to stay at so either pitch a tent on the lawn to save cash or find somewhere else.

name: Familia Dental
categories: General Dentistry, Orthodontists, Health & Medical, Dentists
text: This is a very dirty place , in the exam room the floor is so  nasty looks as if this place hasn't seen a mop in years, appointment was at 2:00 - wasn't seen till 3:45 they make sure you pay first before you get to be seen . As everyone passes your room every one can see in , hear , no privacy at all . Came here as a last resort, im telling you very very dirty.

name: Artiste De Fleurs
categories: Shopping, Flowers & Gifts, Florists
text: I ordered flowers for Mother's Day about a week in advance to be delivered ON Mother's Day Sunday and they delivered them the day before without any notification whatsoever. They even sent me a confirmation email today saying the flowers were delivered on Sunday, even though my mother received them Saturday! You shouldn't provide options on a website that you don't actually offer. They also screwed up my boyfriend's order, wrote the wrong name on the card and sent an entirely different bouquet than what was ordered, and THEN rudely gave him a really hard time about getting a refund, saying she should, "Go get the flowers back since you want a refund." Ridiculously unprofessional. The only reason I'm leaving 2 stars is because the bouquet itself that I ordered was beautiful. Everything else was a complete mess.

name: Bodywork and Spa Professionals
categories: Beauty & Spas, Massage Therapy, Health & Medical, Reflexology, Medical Spas, Chiropractors, Skin Care, Massage, Day Spas
text: I was going to be in for the day and pampered myself with the 2.5 hour Royal Treatment. Rose was excellent and I will be rebooking if I'm in the area again.

name: Twisted Key Escape Rooms
categories: Active Life, Escape Games
text: I loved this place! My group unfortunately didn't win but it was so much fun! We were able to work together and to get in even without a reservation on a Saturday night. It was a good time and the staff was super nice and when we asked for clues our woman was amazing at helping us. I'll probably come back and take my parents here because this is exactly the type of thing they would love.

name: Maxwell's Restaurant
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True'}
categories: Italian, Restaurants
text: Maxwells DOES have a strange decor! I ordered a Greek salad and it was good. Nothing over the top just a simple salad. Ive had better but Ive had worse. overall not a bad experience but as I sat there I couldnt help but wonder what the place looked like in (I Imagine the 1940's) when It was a house.. I ASSUME it was a house at one point.. it has all the symptoms of a house turned business. All I wanted to do was rearrange the layout and build a couple of walls.. knock a couple down.. anyhow the food was decent and if we went back I would try something else.. but I AM on a quest for Healthy food and I dont believe italian is on that list..

name: Ron's Shell Service Cntr
categories: Automotive, Food, Gas Stations, Convenience Stores
text: Reliable service.  My family has been going here for car repair for years.  They will call with an estimate before starting on more expensive repairs.  They've always been professional and understanding.

name: Tiny's
categories: Pubs, Nightlife, Bars, Restaurants
text: Had cod fish on Friday and was it good!  Good taste and real cod pieces; not the square patties you get at some places. Nice size portion as well. Love their slaw and my son had the chicken wrap which to my surprise was excellent. Burgers were good too. Good job, cook. Service was well received too. My family had a fun evening with challenges at the foosball table.

name: Pizza Hut
attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'HasTV': 'True'}
categories: Chicken Wings, Italian, Restaurants, Pizza
text: I debated on 2 or 3 stars. How about 2.5? 3 stars on the $10 pizza specials - love to order the pepperoni lovers pizza. 2 stars on efficiency. The staff is usually friendly but I swear I've had more snafus with my orders here than any other pizza place I can think of. Lost pizzas, wrong pizzas, wrong prices, etc. Seems to be a revolving door of employees and that might be the reason for such inconsistancy.

name: Viviano Heating & AC
categories: Home & Garden, Appliances, Home Services, Dry Cleaning & Laundry, Local Services, Heating & Air Conditioning/HVAC, Shopping
text: I highly recommend Vivianos - we had a complete heating and cooling system installed and the crew was fantastic, thorough and the equipment superior. We had several estimates from different companies and not only did Vivianos beat the price but did so with better equipment and unbeatable service. I highly recommend Vivianos!!!

name: Bailey Cakes
categories: Food, Bakeries, Cupcakes, Custom Cakes
text: Very friendly and helpful at every step of the way, my cake pops turned out awesome! Would definitely order from them again

name: LookAfter Hair Company
categories: Beauty & Spas, Hair Salons
text: Considering the fact that I was beginning to look l like an extra from Game of Thrones, I decided to get a haircut. Googled local places when I was in O'Fallon and went based on the reviews. Walked in with no wait. Ian gave me possibly the best haircut I've ever had. It seems that every barber I went too wanted to discuss politics or fishing and I'd inevitably get a haircut that looked just like theirs. Not the case this time. My wife and I were both happy with the results (which rarely happens!) I'll be returning here when I'm passing through. I almost considered knocking it down to 4 stars because of something most chains seem to do. Throwing a myriad of offers at you (such as "Fart the national anthem of Paraguay on Tuesdays and receive 5% off!") and it has always annoyed me. But in the grand scheme of things, it's really no big deal since I look suave as hell now.

name: Two Fat Guys
categories: Restaurants, Delis
text: Interesting set up. Previous reviewers aren't kidding about the aesthetics of the location. You walk in and it's completely carpeted, there's a dirty looking fridge and a long counter. The food is cooked on a forman type table top griddle. Unfortunately, it didn't taste any better than what we make at home, it wasn't the best quality of meats. The desk in the back with the bottle of Crown Royal and a pile of rotten looking crocs sandles really was the cherry on top.

name: Domino's Pizza
categories: Restaurants, Pizza, Sandwiches, Chicken Wings
text: I would give it 5 stars but sometimes my pizza delivery is a little late arriving to me. But other than that I really enjoy the food when I don't feel like cooking, especially the oven baked sandwiches

name: Shake Rattle & Roll Drive In
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': False, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True'}
categories: Sandwiches, Restaurants, Burgers
text: Great little drive in that's not exactly a "drive in." You do drive into the parking lot and they do come to you, so it's similar. Anyways, it was a surprise to find this place because we had been in the area so many times and wondered why we haven't seen it before. But we're glad we found it and the food was delicious. The family had burgers and they were pretty good and juicy. I had a catfish sandwich that was so good I took my time eating. We also had their fries which were very good with the variety of sauces they had. I really like the garlic aioli sauce. Such a unique twist on a drive, but enjoyable sitting and listening to all the Oldie Goldie tunes. To say the least, I definitely recommend this place and will be back.

categories: Bars, Venues & Event Spaces, Event Planning & Services, Wineries, Nightlife, Wine Bars, Restaurants, Arts & Entertainment, Food, American (Traditional)
text:
How cute is this place? My husband's work had a function here and I'll be honest that I had fairly low expectations. Their wine selection was decent and pours were on the generous side. The $2 wine glass deposit is a bit silly, as I consider stemware to be part of the cost of doing business. The function room was large with a beautiful view of the grounds. 

The wine list accommodates a variety of wine and beer drinkers from the sweet side (oh that sangria was almost kool-aid like) to the Sonoma/Napa varietals.

name: Helitech Waterproofing & Foundation Repair
categories: Damage Restoration, Foundation Repair, Home Services, Structural Engineers, Waterproofing, Contractors
text:
I have not had issues with this company... Yet, but now I am nervous.  We trusted them w a lot of money.  I hope we do not have a harrowing experience that you all have had.  Today I will give them a 4 due to some ideas I had and they were wrong.  After the job started I noticed screws were not aligned and there were places I could slide my hand down.  The second crew that came in did add more screws and that helped.  When asked why the screws weren't aligned I was told we worry about getting your basement dry and not how it looks.  So far that is the only complaint I have.
Those laborers stood out in the rain all day long and carried concrete back into my basement in five gallon buckets.  The teams was respectful.  The came in and did what I was told they would do. So far a dry basement.  
I have not contacted Helitech about the un aligned screws because it sounds petty.  They suggested I put walls up over the hydra 300.  I am not at that point right now.
To say the least I am pleased.

name: CBD Kratom
categories: Tobacco Shops, Vitamins & Supplements, Shopping, Herbal Shops, Bars, Nightlife, Health & Medical, Vape Shops, Hookah Bars, Head Shops
text:
Most overpriced kratom I've ever purchased- average quality. Will not return.
49.99 for 90 capsules.
Order online or purchase from any other vendor anywhere and it will cost you less.

name: Federico Chrysler Dodge Jeep Ram
categories: Auto Repair, Automotive, Used Car Dealers, Car Dealers, Auto Loan Providers, Auto Parts & Supplies
text: WOW! Federico Dealership is the epitome of excellent customer service! I was greeted immediately with friendly, warm smiles and they made me feel like I was the guest of honor. From the moment I walked through the door, until the time I left, they made sure that I was taken care of and executed nothing short of superior service. They were also extremely accommodating and exceeded my expectations on my trade-in, as well as gave me a great deal on my new Jeep Renegade! I have bought other cars in the past from other places but I've never walked away feeling like I did here! They will forever have my business!!!

name: Eclipse Tan
categories: Beauty & Spas, Tanning Beds, Tanning, Spray Tanning
text: Love tanning here and Elise is awesome! Elise has been in the business forever and her spray tans are amazing! If you're spraying in a booth you are missing out.

name: Charter Communications
categories: Professional Services, Home Services, Internet Service Providers, Television Service Providers
text: I wish I could rate the service provided by Charter Spectrum and not their employees. The service is a 1 or less in my book. I've had them for 17 years and the last 2 years of service has been terrible to include the loss of over 14 years of emails without any resolution.  If there was another provider, I'd recommend them over Charter Spectrum.

name: Sacred Grounds

categories: Breakfast & Brunch, Food, Coffee & Tea, Restaurants
text:
Been twice -- great latte, especially the large triple shot. Use Mississippi Mud beans, and that is truly as good a coffee as you can get -- it rivals or beats any bean I've had in Seattle or Portland!

The wraps and paninis are good, but not perfect -- although the cucumber sauce on the falafel wrap is homemade and amazing. The eggplant panini was good, but the grated cheese hadn't melted.

The baked goods are surprisingly good. A lemon-coconut bundt cake yesterday looked so plain, but tasted amazing. The chocolate biscotti are great, but the other biscotti were ok (but not great).

Some good art on the wall in rotating exhibit. Otherwise the decor is sparse/spartan. 

I like it.

name: Columbia Dental Center
categories: Cosmetic Dentists, Health & Medical, Pediatric Dentists, Dentists, General Dentistry
text: Fantastic dental office! The dentist and staff are all extremely kind, caring and incredibly helpful and supportive. My husband is normally very nervous and anxious at the dentist but they all went above and beyond to put him at ease. He actually enjoyed his visit and is looking forward to going back to see them all again. Can't recommend them enough!!

Great place for couples!! Drinks are decently priced, staff is super friendly and from what I've heard from staff and the girls themselves is that they all look out for one another and thats important in this kind of Industry because you never know what kind of weird creepy men will walk in and are capable of!

name: Krispy Kreme
categories: Food, Donuts, Coffee & Tea, Bagels
text: What can I say about the awesomeness that is Krispy Kream? I've visited many through the years and this one held up to the standards that I'm used to.  Drive through, hot doughnuts... happiness!

name: Olde World Jewelers
categories: Jewelry, Shopping
text: George, owner of Olde World Jewelers, is a true artisan! My wife & I were recommended to them by a mutual friend & honestly, we couldn't have been happier! My wife wanted to have her wedding band made from some of her deceased mother's jewelry & some of her diamonds used as well. George was very accommodating & was able to create a band that my wife was thrilled with!

name: Auffenberg Chrysler Dodge Jeep Ram
categories: Car Dealers, Auto Repair, Automotive
text: Might be better to make the the drive distance than to go to this dealer for service.  Called twice to schedule service on a recall part they ordered. First call the individual could even figure out how to see my account and I had to call back to get some one different. Second call was met by a VERY Rude individual that could find my account but not the recall and then went in to tell me I should know it. When I explained what was on the dealers service paperwork she stated that wasn't accurate enough and what does my recall letter state. I then got frustrated as I gave it to the service department for them to order it so she should be able to see it in my account! Then when I asked to speak to her manager was hung up on! Go somewhere else!

name: Solve Your System
categories: IT Services & Computer Repair, Local Services
text:
I have been building computers for nearly 20 years and have been published more than a dozen times in three different countries, but even I need help sometimes. That's where these guys come in. This is where you'll find a level of professionalism that you may not be used to. This is not like going to your local Best Buy where the kid you're talking to really only knows what he was taught on his monthly computer training. They also have normal pricing and not some jacked up pricing standard.
.
Recently, I went there to buy a video card for my daughter's computer and was happy to see it was a normal price even when all of this crypto currency mining is going on. Online retailers are selling this exact card for 50% more just because they know they'll get it. You'll never find me in a Micro Center or another big box store looking for computer parts. Solve your system will always have my business and my respect

name: Hardee's
categories: Fast Food, Restaurants, Burgers
text:
Just had an extremely disappointing experience with the Hardee's in Godfrey/ Alton.  We ordered 2 Big Roast Beef sandwiches to bring home but first we had to go back through the drive through because they failed to include any sauces.  The sandwiches were cold and very dry plus there was a paltry amount of meat on the them.  Also quality control was very much lacking.  So much so that I grabbed my kitchen scale only to find that one sandwich had 2.3 Oz of meat and the other had 1.9 ounces of meat.  That made me wonder just how much beef there is supposed to be.  Now, the Hardee's site has no information on the amount of beef, just a total calorie count and nutritional breakdown of the total sandwich.  But I did find a couple calorie counter sites that did give the info with a breakdown.
According to those reports the Big Roast Beef has 85 grams of beef, but upon doing the math 85 grams comes to roughly 2.99 ounces!  So, get with it Hardee's and ensure better quality...oh yeah, that au jus that's advertised was completely missing!  Dry as a bone paltry sandwich!

name: Downtown Belleville YMCA - Kern Center
categories: Child Care & Day Care, Summer Camps, Fitness & Instruction, Local Services, Gyms, Active Life, Community Service/Non-Profit
text: I enjoy the downtime Belleville YMCA because of the staff they have, they have the Sauna you could use after a good workout, & it's an all around good place for he Family.

text: This is a neat little Italian place that isn't too upscale, but is also small and quaint enough for a quick work lunch.  They have great toppings and definitely have their own recipe.  It is a little pricey for what you get.

name: West Belleville Nail Spa
categories: Beauty & Spas, Nail Salons
text: Best nail service I've ever had. Truly the most friendly people I've ever encountered. I came with my mom and my two boys ( ages 10 & 6) and we all got pedicures! Very attentive and kind. Will only come here! Love that they are sweet with kids!

name: Chipotle Mexican Grill
categories: Fast Food, Restaurants, Mexican
text: Won't go back for some time.  Quality is 50% decent and 50% bad.  Today was last visit in some time.  Brisket was burnt and over seasoned, couldn't eat it, and quality of staff is poor.  Teenagers with bad attitude, and get sauce and cream all over covers of food, when asked if they are going to wipe it up was told to get napkins over on side.

name: Kettle River Furniture & Bedding
categories: Kitchen & Bath, Furniture Reupholstery, Mattresses, Home Decor, Furniture Stores, Local Services, Office Equipment, Shopping, Home & Garden
text: We bought a dining room table, chairs and buffet from them, along with the table pad. everything arrived quickly and looks like new even though it is now two years old. We had an awesome experience. I saw the negative reviews, but glad we went there. Took about a week to receive our furniture -where when we bought from Ashley we were told 4 and it took 9!

text: My husband and I love traveling around finding local cafes that source local and CLEAN food. And major bonus if it includes delicious coffee. Proving Grounds did not disappoint!!! Wonderful place & wonderful employees! We drove 40 minutes & will be back!

name: ZaZa Nails & Spa
categories: Beauty & Spas, Day Spas, Nail Salons, Nail Technicians
text:
I absolutely LOVE this place! The prices are great, the service is great, and the job that they do on my nails is amazing!
I love that when I walk in the door, I get greeted with a smile. I'm usually asked what I want, before I even sign in and even when I don't have an appointment, they still manage to get me taken care of. 
I've been here three times, so far, and have loved each manicure! 
Sometimes, there can be a language barrier at some places, but not here. I love that I can sit and chat and joke like we're old friends. I can't express enough how great this place is; I tell everyone, who will listen, where I get my nails done!!

categories: Chinese, Restaurants
text: We've lived in the Godfrey/Alton area for 2 years now and finally found good asian food.  We didn't expect to find authentic food at a place with such a generic name.  I ordered the pho and it was delicious and in a huge bowl.  The owner said her pho broth is simmered for a full 24 hours, and I can tell the difference.  My wife ordered beef and broccoli which was also good.  They have a full menu of normal Chinese food, plus three Vietnamese dishes.  I recommend trying this place out.  It doesn't look like it, but it's a real find.  We will be coming back soon!

text: All the staff are overly friendly which isn't a bad thing but I understand it probably means they are begging for as much business as possible.  Nothing really stands out about the casino, it's riverboat gambling while docked and the furnishings seem dated.  Just a relatively small gambling place clinging on to the older clientele, I was the youngest there by far.  God bless them for trying but this isn't my cup of tea!  Everything just felt *sad* in there, no vibrancy, no life, just another business struggling to make ends meet or so it seems.

name: Verizon

text: Scott did a fantastic job helping us return and exchange our phone.  On our second trip we had virtually no wait.  Scott was well informed of the programs and options.  He explained everything in terms we could easily understand.  I was simply impressed with the level of service.

name: Hawthorne Animal Hospital
categories: Pet Boarding, Pets, Pet Groomers, Pet Services, Veterinarians, Pet Sitting
text: Took my dog to Hawthorne animal hospital today.  The staff is very nice and professional . Diesel wants to thank you. He's feeling much better. Thank you, I highly recommend this place for your pet's needs.

name: Reconditioned Appliances
categories: Shopping, Appliances, Local Services, Home & Garden, Mattresses, Appliances & Repair
text:
Only 1 star.  A minus 5 stars would be more appropriate. My daughter was ripped off by them and also a friend. The latest a dryer that made squeal sounds. The tech found bad bearings. Solution? Not replacing the motor, spray grease into it. Oh good the bearings just have a quiet growl to them. Could maybe get another 6 months out of it. 
I traded the washer/dryer set back to them for freezer. Of course it sells for less money. But did it work?  You bet it didn't, 3 degrees above zero does not make it a good freezer. After returning it and leaving it for a week it's still not right. I was lied to about it. I won't try to get into the conversations. I know about Refrigeration and I will do the repairs. Liars and cheaters is what you get at this place.  They get the appliances from anywhere it's free. Even from the road side. Please tell everyone you know.

name: ALDI
categories: Beer, Wine & Spirits, Organic Stores, Grocery, Food, Specialty Food, Fruits & Veggies, Discount Store, Meat Shops, Shopping
text: I went here for the first time in a long time today and the renovations look great.  All of isles seem bigger.  Everything feels less crowded than before.  The food quality is good, and the prices are even better.  Wonderful location.

name: All About Eyes - O' Fallon
categories: Eyewear & Opticians, Health & Medical, Shopping, Laser Eye Surgery/Lasik, Optometrists
text: Had my initial eye exam done at another optometrist office. Came in to get a couple pairs of glasses, was able to get two adorable pairs, for about 150 less than  what ONE pair was to cost on a special at another eye dr. When I got my first pair in, the script seemed off, so the manager there was extremely nice and helped verify forst the measurements and that the lenses had the exact lense script, which lead to having a re- test of the script -which was done in office and sure enough it was my script. The ladies in the office were great, helpful and informative, as well as very personable. The optometrist there was wonderful.He was patient during the exam, didn't rush and made sure to give my eyes small breaks in between to keep my eyes from overstraining while figiring out the correct eye script. Felt very calm, not rushed to choose between "1 or 2 " in the slides and he was very knowledgeable in questions I had pertaining to eye health. Will definitely reccomend this office to everyone and will be coming back myself for sure. Thanks All about eyes!!!

attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': True, 'casual': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'False', 'CoatCheck': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'Smoking': "u'yes'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HappyHour': 'True', 'DogsAllowed': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsBitcoin': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'False', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
categories: Shopping, Nightlife, Tobacco Shops, Jazz & Blues, Arts & Entertainment, Performing Arts
text: I'm not a cigar smoker, but we went to the Cigar INN for the first time on my birthday. Even though all of us have lived in the area our entire lives, we'd never ventured in. I have to say this place is incredibly cool! This night, in particular, a friend of mine was hosting karaoke, and the crowd was a pleasant mix of people. Drinks were reasonable and well-mixed. The idea of the stairs is neat, but for girls in heels, it's not so awesome. Not a deal breaker--we will just choose different shoes next time. The ambiance is unique--especially to Belleville. You feel as though you're in an exclusive jazz club. It isn't that it's insanely swanky or too high end---it's very comfortable, but also has that vibe of a "secret club." Okay, so that's a cheesy way of putting it. It's a cool place. That's all. It's definitely a hidden gem!

name: Nautilus Fitness Center
categories: Fitness & Instruction, Gyms, Active Life, Trainers
text:
My son brought this flyer home from school, so I called them to see if I had to be a member or could I just pay for the boys to play in the Playland. The guy on the phone told me non members have to pay $3, and members pay $9 a month......which my sister in law, who's a member there said that for members it's free. Okay....we go there, and I told the man behind the counter, we want to go to the Playland.....and he acted like I was speaking Russian or something. 
He asked me.....
Are you a member? 
No. I just called here and I was told I didn't have to be a member. 
Well you can't just leave your kids here, we're not a daycare.
Why would I leave them here? 
So then he ask this other dude. 
What do you say? How do you want to handle this?
And he's like.....
Well kids are $3 and everyone has to pay.
So its $3 each?
Oh no no.....you guys need a 7 day pass, which is $15 each.

Why is it, that when I called there I was told one story. Now that I'm in front of you, it's something else. They were making up stuff as they went along. What is you policy. Why doesn't it say membership required for children to play in the Playland area on the flyer? What pissed me off even more was how hurt my son was because he didn't understand why we were leaving. The two men were extreme rude and snobby. And I hate to bring race into it, but that's what it felt like. Why would I think a gym is a daycare? Why would I leave my 3 year old and 1 year old with strangers? For him to even say something like that, made me mad. Terrible customer service. One of them main reason I brought my kids there or even considered going there was because I'm tired of taking my kids to the mall to play in the little area there. And it's not like it was a great play area....it was the same play equipment that they have at Chick -fil-a, and McDonald's. I'm trying to keep my kids from eating fast food. So if I can get the same experience from a place like a gym, and promote healthy, fun activities for my kids, I'll gladly pay for that.
Thank you Nautilus for upsetting my son, and losing future member.

text:
We have taken dogs for grooming, boarding , and training at Cindy's Critter Camp for over 10 years.  They're super nice and accommodating.  I have trained 2 of my dogs through their class and it was a very good experience, they learned how to heel so well! 
  One of my dogs does not like strangers and Cindy's is the only place in the Edwardsville area that can handle him for grooming.  So they are a godsend for that spunky little mutt!

name: The Mission Thrift Store
categories: Shopping, Thrift Stores, Discount Store
text: This is probably my favorite thrift store in Belleville. The staff is so friendly and engaging, and to be honest, I spend hours here every time I go. The items flow in and change quickly, and while I love SalvArmy, too, unlike them, if something isn't priced, at Mission, they can give you a price and still sell it to you. This fall I found tons of brand new black basic leggings. They had almost a whole rack of them. Don't know where they came from, but I was sure excited! I also love the organization. Other stores are organized, but I feel as though Mission has a better handle on it and keeps a clean, fairly uncluttered space.

name: Quality Inn & Suites Caseyville - St. Louis
categories: Hotels & Travel, Event Planning & Services, Hotels
text: With many other choices in the area I'd go somewhere else.  The bad smell of the room was the first thing I noticed upon arrival.  First thing I checked was the window in the room, and it was unlocked...leaving your room unsecured isn't the best practice.  I was leaving the room and noticed (luckily the first time) that the door sounds like it closes all the way, but you can push the door open, so unless you pull the door closed, anyone can walk right in.  I caught the unsecured room issue right off the bat and I'll deal with the smell for a night, however the front desk gives a courtesy call at 1030 to notify you that check out time is 11.....That's good!  Then at 1045 I'm waiting on the other people I came with to get ready to leave and some guy from the hotel staff walks right into my room without knocking or anything.  I look at him and asked if I could help him with anything and he turns around and walks out then turns back and asks if I'm checking out today, I tell him that I am and suggest to him that it's probably not a good idea to just walk into somebody's room, I also suggest that he knocks on the door before walking in.  Something like that is completely unacceptable, and I won't be back.

name: Sam's Club
categories: Discount Store, Tires, Electronics, Shopping, Food, Drugstores, Grocery, Wholesale Stores, Fashion, Department Stores, Automotive
text: Sam's Club is a glorified Wal-Mart.  You really have to watch the prices as often times Sam's is not cheaper than Target.  I have a few complaints about Sam's. 1. They do not accept coupons.  I like to use coupons to save money.  I shop at Sam's to save money.  Why can't I do both? 2. They stop carrying products I like.  If I'm buying it, why don't you keep stocking it?  3. They don't accept Visa Credit cards.  What??? Who the hell accepts credit cards but not Visa?

name: ReloPro
categories: Landscaping, Movers, Home Services, Handyman, Couriers & Delivery Services, Home Cleaning, Local Services, Shopping, Packing Supplies, Packing Services, Junk Removal & Hauling
text: I could not be more please with the experience I received from ReloPro. With a medical emergency the previous evening, I called in the morning desperately in need of a couple people to assist me in completion of a move. I was elated that there was a crew that could assist on such short notice. Thankfully all the big items (couch, bed, dressers, etc.) had been previously moved but the movers showed up with a truck and we knocked it out from first box to delivery in two hours. It was a fantastic job, with extra care given where I needed it (boxes with breakable items, i.e.: glass, light bulbs, etc.). Both gentleman were friendly, fantastic movers, and very no-nonsense/get the job done right in the way they assisted me. I would absolutely recommend them to anyone looking for a move in the Belleville/Swansea/Fairview Heights/O'fallon/Scott area. I will be utilizing them again if/when I move. Thank you both very much for your assistance and professionalism."

name: Sonic Drive-In
categories: Food, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Fast Food, Burgers, Restaurants
text: I live close to here and often go here. The service is sometimes slow, but the food and drinks are always really well made. My favorite is the grape or peach cream slush. Some other locations make it a bit weaker, but here it's always perfect. I had to come on here and write this because all the negative reviews. Don't know what that is all about. I've never had a bad experience, but I go knowing I might have to wait a bit. I've seen at least one person get mad and drive off because they were mad about having to wait.

name: Grooming by Pam
categories: Pet Sitting, Pet Stores, Pet Services, Pet Groomers, Pets
text: They were so unbelievably nice.  My poor little dog has the hardest time getting her nails trimmed, and she kind of sounds like someone is trying to hurt her.  They were so gentle and sweet with her.  My other dog just got trimmed down for the summer, and he looks so handsome.  I will definitely be taking my dogs back to this place!

categories: Food, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Fast Food, Restaurants, Burgers
text:
Let the record show, I love the Culver's chain.  But this trip was simply "meh". 

We stopped here on the way to St. Louis, because it's not something we have in Southern Illinois, but is something we all love. 

This place was absolutely slammed. The drive thru was loaded, so we went inside and were met with a line that wandered back into the dining area. The line moved pretty fast, which was unexpected. But once we got our numbers, the wait was suuuuper long. The girl with the biggest order in our group of four's came out immediately, and the one who just ordered a shake came out like 20 minutes later. It just seemed to be a hot mess all around.

The cheese curds were delicious, but the concrete mixer wasn't right. It was supposed to be turtle cheesecake. I didn't get one cheesecake piece, and there was so much caramel in it I couldn't even taste the custard. 

It's better than no Culver's, but it's definitely not the best location.

name: Sweet Katie Bee's Organic Bakery Café
categories: Coffee & Tea, Bakeries, Food, Juice Bars & Smoothies
text: Went on Saturday morning for a smoothie.  It was delicious!  Husband had a cupcake and a cup of coffee.  The service was great and we had the place to ourselves.  Will definitely return.

name: Anderson Hospital ExpressCare Glen Carbon
categories: Medical Centers, Urgent Care, Doctors, Health & Medical, Hospitals
text: I injured my foot/ankle so badly, the pain was excruciating, and my foot/ankle was turned totally sideways. It swelled up A LOT. My husband carried me in there and the dr looked at it quickly and X-rayed it, then sent me home with crutches and with strong pain meds. No instructions. I had to ask him. Later found out from my primary dr, that the dr from Anderson Express Care told them my ankle was not broken. So my primary dr had me go to physical therapy! When I told the Physical therapist what happened, he said only a very few are that bad. Then he looked at mine. He was shocked how disfigured and still heavily swollen it was and deeply bruised all over. They did minimal work on me since it was still so injured. After a couple of months I went back to my primary dr saying it is not getting better. She just said pretty much that we don't need to x-ray it again because Anderson Express Care dr already said it wasn't broken. Back to more physical therapy. A few months later of no improvement I went back and pretty much demanded to be seen by a specialist.  Got an appointment with a foot/ankle specialist. He took one look at it and sent me for x-rays. He came back and said, "Your ankle is broken! Why in the world have you been going to physical therapy and trying to walk on it!! And you tore all the ligaments and tendons at the same time. He put me in a boot and I was not allowed to walk on it at all except to the bathroom and back to the chair for months and months. Thanks for the misdiagnosis Anderson Hospital Express Care that cost me almost a year of not getting the healing I needed. 0 stars if I could!

name: Meineke Car Care Center
categories: Auto Repair, Automotive, Tires, Oil Change Stations
text:
On 7/6/2019, I take my car into a Meineke because it's making this weird, metallic rattling/scratching sound from the rear right of my car. They diagnose the issue as a bad wheel bearing and make the replacement. I sign the paperwork, make the payment and leave. On the way home, the sound returns. I bring it back and they claim they fixed it by trying some other things such as re-torquing the parts and/or filling the differential fluid. This process of me leaving and returning goes on for about 3 or 4 more times that day until they eventually claim the new bearing they installed is "bad" as they've had similar issues with other Ford (I have a Lincoln, which is made by Ford) customers, so they need to order a new bearing to install which will be available Monday. Before I leave, I ask what happens if this doesn't fix it to which the advisor, Joe, tells me he will partner with his GM to issue a refund.

I work about 40 miles from my home, so I take Monday off to deal with this based on how much of my Saturday I spent there. I go there and they do the install of the second new wheel bearing. The sound stops... until Tuesday morning.

On Tuesday morning, the sound comes back on the way to work as loud as it was normally. Once I get to work, I call up Joe at the Meineke and tell him it's back. He tells me to come back in. My boss lets me off a little early so I can get there since they close at 6 PM. So I get there around 3:45 PM or so. They test drive it and then have me drive it around with one of their technicians in the back seat. It took a little for the sound to come back but the technician told me he could hear it and we could go back to the shop to take a look. After awhile, Joe and another gentleman come in (I think his name was Adam), and tell me they can't find anything mechanically wrong with the car and that they're not hearing the sound. He also then proceeds to, conflictingly, tell me the the guy who rode with me thinks the sound might be coming from the speaker? The sound system wasn't even on. The sound does not sound like an electrical short or something. Joe then tells me they can't provide me a refund and that they also changed out the brake pads and rotor (which is indicative that they even stopped believing it was the wheel bearing that they charged me for) and to sign some new paperwork agreeing to this. I signed nothing and told them I want my money back, and they don't budge but suggest I get a "second opinion".

The next morning, I recorded a video of myself going to the gas station before work with the sound coming back as proof it exists of which I still have the video.

I took it to the Ford dealership near my work and they heard the sound. They claimed it was being caused by the heat shield rubbing against my rear driveshaft and re-tightened it. I contact the shop and speak to Adam (the guy from before) as Joe was not in and tell them of the dealership's findings and to start my refund. He said he would talk to Joe and they would contact me tomorrow. Well, it's now 5:04 PM on "tomorrow" and they closed at 4 PM. Radio silence.

I want my money back.

name: Casa Maria Express
categories: Restaurants, Mexican, Caterers, Event Planning & Services
text: Called in an order for lunch takeout and the food was fantastic!  Have eaten at the Belleville location 3 or 4 times and we love the food and service. Very consistent.  I ordered  a few favorites Aroy con Pollo and Maria's Enchiladas.  Order took 15 minutes and when I arrived the small location near SAFB had all of their approximately 6 tables full with Military having lunch.  Very courteous professional service. My favorite Mexican restaurant.

name: Banfield Pet Hospital
categories: Veterinarians, Pets, Pet Services
text: I wish I could give this place negative stars. If you care about your pet, DO NOT BRING THEM HERE. The staff are unknowledgeable and unfriendly. I brought my dog in for a heart worm test and heart worm medicine. They insisted that I had to get an exam in addition to the heart worm test and that no vets in the area would give a heart worm test without a regular exam. The fees would have been $100. Fine, no biggie. Then they told me they wouldn't be able to schedule her in for 2 more days because they were booked. I thought walk-ins were welcome? Apparently not! I went ahead and scheduled an appointment, but as we were leaving I decided to call Hawthorne vet up the road just in case because the gals at Banfield just didn't seem that smart. Really. Not only were we able to walk right into Hawthorne and get help, but they didn't require a full exam and the heart worm test plus medicine was only $40. I think I found our new vet! So please, I cannot stress enough that you should NOT bring your pets here. I also agree with the other reviewers that they try to rip you off. For shame, Bandfield. For shame...

name: US Post Office
categories: Public Services & Government, Post Offices
text: This place is always packed! Granted, I don't frequent post offices, but when I do...I wait. For quite awhile. It's not their fault, people just have a lot of crap to mail! This most recent visit, I was very happy to hear they offered the commemorative Civil War stamps! I had been looking for these all over. The man that assisted me was incredibly polite and attentive. It would be kind of silly to say "I'll definitely be back." Of course I will -- I live in O'Fallon.

name: The UPS Store
categories: Local Services, Shipping Centers, Printing Services, Notaries, Mailbox Centers
text:
Nick and Sam give new meaning to the words customer service. They both go above and beyond to help customers with their shipping issues.  I'm an older person who needed help with an Amazon return. Not only did Nick help me with the transaction, but he was professional, knowledgeable, courteous, and kind. He and Sam both went above and behind to assist me. 
Nick and Sam make the Shiloh UPS store a friendly atmosphere with their efficiency and willingness to provide customers with assistance. I highly recommend this UPS center!!!!

name: KFC
categories: Chicken Shop, Fast Food, Chicken Wings, Restaurants
text:
Our order wasn't large. I understand if you didn't have our items ready, but waiting 16 minutes without an explaination is just poor training & service. We weren't the only people who waited, either. I can only assume that the others feel as we did & wont come back.
It would also have been great if, after waiting so long, they could have offered a small side item or an," I'm sorry you had to wait so long," would have gone a long way.
It was rainy. The inside of the restaurant has no door rugs & between the water from the rain & the oil in the air, the stone floor is quite slick. So please be mindful of that, especially if you're bringing children or any elderly.
The restaurant is, to be fair, a bit messy but overall it is clean.

name: Steven J Hyten, DMD
categories: Dentists, General Dentistry, Health & Medical, Oral Surgeons
text: First, please know that I am in no way related to Dr. Steven Hyten nor am I related to anyone in his office.  Dr. Hyten removed two of my teeth yesterday afternoon.  He was EXCELLENT.  I had opted NOT to receive any kind of sedation and, therefore, I was grateful and calmed by his thorough and on-going explanation of everything that he was doing: "Now....this may be rather noisy" or "I am going to be exerting a bit of pressure" or "Just let us know if something is uncomfortable." The members of Dr. Hyten's staff are unusually kind and supportive and knowledgeable---and extremely articulate in explaining everything PRIOR to the procedure and in giving specific instructions for steps I needed to take FOLLOWING the procedure.  It's no fun getting teeth pulled....but I absolutely could not have HOPED for a BETTER experience than I had yesterday at Dr. Hyten's office.

name: Oliver C Joseph
categories: Auto Repair, Car Dealers, Hotels & Travel, Automotive, Auto Parts & Supplies, Car Rental
text:
We brought our jeep here before the warranty expired to fix what they determined to be a broken water pump and a steering wheel that always looks like it's pointed left even when you're driving straight (it basically looks as though you're making left turn even though you're not) When we picked it up to drive it home, not only was the steering wheel still crooked, (They said it's not creating any problems so they didn't see a need to fix it) but now we also had a FLAT TIRE! Who sends someone home with a flat tire!?! We turned around and said "our car has a flat tire!" 
Then, I brought our car back one last time because suddenly our spare key (which we have been using for 2 years) was causing our anti theft feature to kick in and the key was useless. It would turn the car on but not allow you to drive, and the remote lock/unlock feature stopped working with that key too. I made an appointment for the next day and when I showed up for it they said they didn't have any appointment for us. He looked at me like I was the one who screwed up the date, but then told me later that there system has been "losing appointments here and there sometimes"... What the heck!?! Then get a new system and don't make me feel like I'm inconveniencing you. 
Then he told me "I can try to reprogram it for $55 but if that might not work and you may need a new key which will cost an ADDITIONAL $200, that's in ADDITION to the $55 attempt ton reprogram. I told him that was too much and if the reprogram doesn't work I will just have to live with one key, and then he tried to sell me a service package to make sure everything else was running smoothly with our car that would cost $715! What!!!?!!! Never again will I come here. I didn't want to come here after our last experience, but my husband said this was the only place this side of the river that had a service department. Looks like we'll be crossing the river for our future needs.

name: Altitude Trampoline Park - Glen Carbon
categories: Active Life, Trampoline Parks, Parks
text: My kids had a blast here and they can't wait to come back. The only thing that I didnt like: the workers here dont make the children follow the rules. The rule states no cellphones but yet half of the kids here were jumping with phones. Now please keep in mind that you have to sign a safety waiver before your child jumps. But why? Why even sign a waiver when no one follows the rules and that is ok.

attributes: {'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'HasTV': 'True'}

text: If you want IMO's, order from any other location. My favorite thing to order is the breadsticks with provel cheese and meat sauce. I ordered these breadsticks, a pizza, and an order of hot wings from this location. The breadsticks were absolutely horrible (no flavor, tasted old), and they forgot the meat sauce for dipping. name: Helitech Waterproofing & Foundation Repair
categories: Contractors, Home Services, Masonry/Concrete, Foundation Repair, Waterproofing, Structural Engineers
text: Called and set up an appointment for 1pm to look at a crack in my basement. They called me at 12:59 to let me know they were going to be late. 3pm rolled around and they were 2 hours late, so I called the office to ask if they were still coming. They said they were not able to get in touch with the person coming out, but they would either have him call me, or the secretary would call me in 15 minutes if they still couldn't reach him. Another hour goes by, no call, so I call again, they say that they spoke with him and he is 10 minutes out, another hour goes by. I call to cancel the appointment and they say he is pulling into my driveway. So they finally show up 4 hours late for the appointment, and then give me a quote to repair a crack thats $150 higher than the 3 other quotes I received. Not a great experience. I can understand that appointments sometimes change at the last minute, but terrible customer service, follow through, and communication of what was going on, especially since I took off work to meet with them at 1pm, and they showed up at 5pm, when I would have already been home from work.

name: Hampton Inn O'Fallon
categories: Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Hotels & Travel
text: Our son is a college freshman near this town and I did a lot of  research on the hotels in the area before choosing this one. From the pictures and few reviews, it seemed modern and really clean. We were not disappointed. The place was roomy, brand new, clean, with comfy beds, and the desk attendants were very friendly and helpful. It is also near a really nice steak restaurant where we had dinner. We were here in August during Covid, so didn't expect a hot breakfast, which was fine because we ate with our son anyway.  There was a nice coffee station available throughout the day in the lobby. We would definitely stay here again as school is still in session and I miss my kid!

name: St. Louis Paranormal Research Society
categories: Historical Tours, Professional Services, Tours, Hotels & Travel, Restaurants
text:
Mark was our tour guide and he was low-key hysterical. My boyfriend and I did two tours back-to-back and during our second one, it was just my boyfriend, Mark, and I. After the tour ended, us three sat and talked for about thirty minutes, which was great. 

The tour itself was pretty cool--although there's walking, it's not strenuous by any means. The only thing I was disappointed in was that we didn't get to go inside any buildings and a lot of it seemed like speculation. I think it would be more convincing had I been able to go inside some of the homes, buildings, etc. 

Overall, my boyfriend and I had a blast.

name: Dreamland Palace German Restaurant
attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': None, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': None, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'HasTV': 'False', 'Caters': 'True'}
categories: German, Restaurants
text:
I guess a couple of things might run through your mind when you see a German restaurant in a rural town.  The glass-half-full crowd would think it's quaint; they're proud of their heritage and the history of their town, etc.  For us cynics, it's hard not to wonder if a bunch of nazi war criminals found a refuge right here in Illinois farm country.  I saw a collection of old Mercedes by the garage.

Such is life in post-911 America, I guess.  Any chance to be suspicious, I jump on it.    

The people at Dreamland Palace were very nice, and this place definitely reminded me of some of the restaurants I visited in Germany.  The soundtrack was probably "Live From the Hofbrau Haus" and really made the scene complete.  The other thing we loved here was the beer - huge glasses of hefeweisen on draft and a nice selection of bottle beer, too.  Our favorite was the Paulaner Dubbel Bock. 

For an appetizer, we had something called brat bites, or something like that.  They were deep fried pieces of bratwurst and came with some brown mustard.  They were good, but please don't tell my doctor I had them.   For entrees we ordered Jaegerschnitzel, breaded veal with a mushroom gravy and something called Black Forest Schnitzel, which I don't recall seeing in Germany; chicken with ham and swiss on top.  For sides, we had potato pancakes, German potato salad, green beans and red cabbage.  You got to go through the salad bar before your meal, which reminded me very much of dishes you might find at the Hometown Buffet.  Definitely no seconds.  Probably the best things were the chicken and potato pancakes.  The rest was just okay.  The aren't a lot of German restaurants in the St. Louis area, but I don't think there's really a need to drive way out here for a fix.  

To summarize:  Great beer, okay food, very authentic German atmosphere and friendly service.

name: Fantastic Sams
categories: Barbers, Hair Salons, Beauty & Spas
text:
The Collinsville Fantastic Sams is located in an older strip mall behind several other businesses. In addition the storefront is small so it's not the easiest place to find.  However, once you do the stylists here are always friendly and willing to engage in good conversation while you get your hair cut. They always ask if I want the wash and never act like it's too much trouble. 

Because of the positive experiences I've had, I drive out of my way to get my hair cut here. And even though I'm driving further, the $11 price for a cut more than makes up for a the extra money I would spend at places closer to home.

P.S. They have a rewards program too!!

name: Eddies Travel Center
categories: Grocery, Hotels & Travel, Food, Travel Services
text:
Restrooms clean. New fangled sinks. They do not use he soap dispenser function though. Only cold water. 
Store fully stocked. Not too many deals. They do have hot breakfast items. 
Cashiers seem totally distracted. Mind not on their job. No bag or receiver offered. You must ask & sometimes twice. 
Parking lot & fuel islands clean & attendant keeping trash empty.

name: Kohl's
categories: Sports Wear, Toy Stores, Shoe Stores, Sporting Goods, Fashion, Shopping, Women's Clothing, Department Stores, Men's Clothing
text:
Great place to shop for almost anything - especially clothes. Love the discounts. Also, best service department - hands down. No fuss - give you either cash or store credit. Bought something 3 years ago - never opened it. Took it back and they said "We don't carry it anymore but we'll give you store credit." That is service!
Now - if they would just QUIT asking me at checkout "Will this be on your Kohl's charge card?"

name: All About Eyes - Collinsville
categories: Medical Supplies, Eyewear & Opticians, Laser Eye Surgery/Lasik, Shopping, Optometrists, Health & Medical
text:
Been here twice. Doc had to pull metal shrapnel from drilling out of my eyes. Quick, painless, and turned out to be a pleasurable experience. The eye doc really makes you feel comfortable, even with metal stuck in the eyeball. 

The second time I needed proof of my color deficiency and from phone call to out of the office was 30 minutes. Quick. Professional. Affordable. And accurate. Great place great service. The kind of place where you'd want to be friends with the Doc and employees.

name: East Gate Grocery
categories: Ethnic Food, International Grocery, Restaurants, Food, Specialty Food, Grocery, Korean
text:
It's a tiny grocery store \ "restaurant."  Not really a sit down place unless you can speak Korean, and I use the word restaurant very loosely here.  I just order over the phone what I want and pick it up, its always good.

CASH ONLY!!!CASH ONLY!!!CASH ONLY!!!CASH ONLY!!!CASH ONLY!!!CASH ONLY!!!CASH ONLY!!!CASH ONLY!!!CASH ONLY!!!CASH ONLY!!!CASH ONLY!!!

Food is nice considering there aren't many places around the O'fallon IL area that serves Korean food.

name: Cherry Berry - Self Serve Yogurt Bar
categories: Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Food, Desserts
text: I love this yogurt bar ! My favorite so far in this area. So many flavors & toppings to choose from. Such a great atmosphere. And the employees are always so friendly.

name: Chef Gutzler's Butterfly Patio
