text: My girlfriends and I came here after a workout class for breakfast and mimosas.  The omelet and croissant sandwich were delicious.  The mimosas were tasty too.  We will be back!

name: Mertz Ford
categories: Car Dealers, Automotive, Shopping, Auto Parts & Supplies, Auto Repair, Tires
text: Had a wonderful car buying experience here. Would definitely work with these guys in the future. I had my 2001 Honda Civic for almost 11 years, and they helped me trade it in for a spectacular 2011 Ford Fusion Sport. They helped me get the best deal possible, and I couldn't have asked for a better outcome.

name: Schubert's Smokehouse & Meat-Packing Company
categories: Smokehouse, Meat Shops, Specialty Food, Food
text: This place has the best beef smokies around, PERIOD!  Many flavors to choose from too.  I go here just for smokies and usually not much else.  I used to live quite close and would stop in frequently.  The beef summer sausage is just average at best, but not bad.  I took some deer meat to have smokies made at Schuberts, and they were not as good as their on-hand beef smokies.  I have had their steaks and brats and they are really good.  This place is quite expensive, but they do have quality products.  5 stars would have been granted if prices were a little more friendly.  Lehr's Market in New Athen's, IL is the only place you should go to for deer processing.  Best brats would be Schneider's in Waterloo, IL.  Schubert's is a quality meat market with very good products.

name: Ted's Motorcycle World
categories: Motorcycle Repair, Motorcycle Gear, Shopping, Automotive, Motorcycle Dealers
text: While I did not buy a bike here today, I left happy, without the usual stress of having to deal with high pressure sales tactics.  Our sales person,Dave, encouraged me to test ride several different bikes, to  give me a better idea of what I would want to buy when the time comes.  He took extra time to educate me on the different types of bikes and advantages of each.  I will definately return to purchase a bike soon!

name: Red Top Barbeque & Chili

text: I ordered the half chicken and it was dry and not even hot. The green beans and Mac n cheese were bland and the ribs weren't anything special. All the food wasn't worth eating and went to my trash cans mouth rather than mine. #Disappointed.

name: DoubleTree by Hilton Hotel Collinsville - St. Louis
categories: Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Venues & Event Spaces, Hotels & Travel
text:
I could really use a half star right now because this place lacked the attention to detail that is befitting a 4 star review, yet it surpassed mere A-OK.
It's a nice property, well suited for business travel or an overnight stay with the family.  The lobby and other communal areas are modern, clean, and stylish.  The staff is friendly and efficient.  The rooms are well appointed and comfortable.  The bar is welcoming and well provisioned.  But I had two problems that obviate a 4 or 5 star review:

1) There was, what appeared to be, a fresh stain on the fitted bed sheet, and the sheets were very wrinkled, as if they hadn't been changed after the last guest. I slept in the other, non-stained bed. Major problems with that.

2) 2 of the 4 treadmills were not functional.  Why have them if they are going to collect dust?

All in all, a nice place.  And if you don't want to dine captively, there are plenty of restaurants in the immediate vicinity.

name: Ann's Bra Shop
categories: Lingerie, Swimwear, Fashion, Plus Size Fashion, Shopping
text: If I could give this place a 0 star I would. FIrst off I'm a 34H so finding a bra in that size is hard and thought this place would be perfect. I was in fitting room with a new fitter and she was trying me on in all the wrong sizes finally almost in tears said I'm done I just want out of this fitting room. Leaving I saw rack of clearance swimsuits and found one I liked. I took up to counter to pay and she said wasn't on clearance even though was on that rack and was very rude. I was so upset about all afternoon I decided to call the store manager to tell her about which I never do and she was even ruder. She said she didn't believe a word I said and her sales lady was nicest person in world and goes to church every sunday. So needless to say I will not be back and be telling everyone I know to avoid as well.

name: Pro Automotive Services
categories: Auto Repair, Automotive, Oil Change Stations, Tires
text: Pro Automotive is AMAZING.  They do great work at reasonable prices.  I've been taking my cars to them for years for just about anything that makes a funny sound or anything that makes the check engine light come on.  They always come back with the honest answer.  Here's an example.  I bought a used car and the A/C made a funny sound.  I took it back to the dealer and they said it was the blower.  They wouldn't cover it under warranty, but offered to fix it for me and gave me an estimate.  I took it to Pro Automotive for a second opinion, and their price to replace the blower was much better.  Turns out the blower was fine, just filled with acorns.  (Acorns!?!?)  They fixed it for a small fraction of the original estimate.  They could have just replaced the blower and I'd never have known, but they were honest.  Even though it cost them some money.  This is the kind of place I'd feel comfortable sending my kids, my wife, or my parents.  Taking your car to the shop can be scary.  It's hard to find a mechanic that you can completely trust and feel confident they they're always going to do right by you.  This is that mechanic.

name: Smokey Bones Bar & Fire Grill
attributes: {'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'WiFi': "'free'", 'Caters': 'True', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True'}
categories: Barbeque, American (Traditional), Burgers, Restaurants
text: Went to Smokey Bones on 10/7 for a late lunch - was seated quickly in the section to the back right area in a corner booth.  We sat for at least 10+ minutes waiting to see anyone, when the host came by to take our drink orders and explained that our server would be by shortly.  Drinks arrived before we saw her, and we were ready to order immediately when she arrived, at which point she told us that she had only been on the job for a week and was juggling 5 tables.  She seemed on top of it, so I didn't worry too much - we gave her our order - my mom ordered off the menu and I did the "build a burger" thing with my own slip indicating what I wanted - couldn't be easier, right?? Well, we waited no less than 50 minutes from our order till the final result.  Along the way, the server brought refills of our drinks, and twice explained that my burger was the holdup - I was ready to tell her to go ahead and bring my mom's food before my burger and then when we finally questioned her about why my burger was taking so long, she finally said that the kitchen just told her that they didn't even receive our entire order.  We decided to leave, as there was no offer to resubmit our order - the server did say that she was sending over a manager to apologize - we thought perhaps we would be offered something for our inconvenience - we waited over 10 minutes for a manager to arrive and one never did so we left.  My parents have, in the past frequented this restaurant not only with me, but with other people and I can guarantee that they and I will never be back.  What a disappointment.

name: Joseph Carroll - Coldwell Banker Brown Realtors
categories: Real Estate Agents, Real Estate Services, Home Services, Real Estate
text: My family and I had just bought a home and Joe has made our home buying experience transition go smoothly. He is very knowledgeable and frank with questions and answers.  Would highly recommend him when looking for purchasing a new home.

name: Ace Hardware
categories: Shopping, Hardware Stores, Home & Garden
text:
Had an issue regarding switching out from a European/Asian type plug to the US Standard for several devices.  Was greeted warmly by the Store Manager - Matt Paul, who immediately had a most cost effective solution, in addition to having the means to change out plugs in store.  He brought in one of his associates named Terry who was proficient in this type of work.  Left what needed done and work was completed in short time. (They would have completed it all right then, but delivery truck just arrived and needed to help with that).  

A most clean store, well lit, good energy, and friendly and sincere service with all of the employees. They made what was a very stressful situation (timeline), for me and handled it with ease.  Made my day!  

Ace is the place for me!   My new "Go-To" spot for any and all hardware needs!   

Thanks,, Gentleman!

name: Dean's Liquor
categories: Beer, Wine & Spirits, Food
text: Was in buying liquor for a get together and the man working was extremely helpful.  If we lived there we would be regulars.

name: Concept Shoe Repair
categories: Shoe Stores, Shopping, Local Services, Shoe Repair, Fashion
text: Bottom line if you value your fine leather goods don't take them here.  I took in my fossil purse.  Its a very expensive purse.  My only expensive purse and I value it.  I took it in for a zipper repair and reconditioning of leather.  It was suppose to be done in a week and then another week and then another week.  Each time they told me to come in they would put me off again with smart alec jokes.  Finally a month later it was done.  They sewed the rip in the zipper, with threads all rubbing the zipper you couldn't get it open with out it catching.  I complained that the zipper didn't work right the man rubbed the zipper with the tip of a pencil where the bad sewing job was catching.  "look all better now" the guy says.  You got to be kidding me!  Zipper still doesn't open right eventually it's gonna rip again with some more wear.  The color they applied wasn't even applied evenly and the purse doesn't even feel nice anymore.  This is a $200 purse something I saved for and they ruined it.  Charged me $85  Don't go here!

name: Oregon Trail Roasting Co
categories: Coffee & Tea, Food, Internet Cafes, Restaurants
text:
I've been here twice and both times had such excellent coffee! We're talking the type where you say to your friend "now I know that I asked for skim milk, but this tastes WAAAY too good to be nonfat!!" I love it when that happens :D (side note: I used to say that about Panera's Carmel Latte until I realized the reason it was so amazing even with skim milk was because the syrup is creamy and buttery... thus entering the yummy fat count...) 

Nice little coffee shop. Comfy spots to sit with your friends and have a chat. Seemed clean. Lots of syrups and bakery goods to choose from. My friend had the cinnamon bun and yes it was huge! I expected it to be hard and not very good, but it was great! I had one bite and I secretly wanted to steal the rest from her plate. I had the zucchini bread and the banana nut bread. Tasty! Though for the first time in my life, I think I liked banana nut bread better. I think the crispy crust on the zucchini bread was throwing me for a loop. I'm used to it being very soft. 

I had lattes both times. First time was a nonfat latte: I felt like I tasted a little bit of nuttiness to it. I'm a fan of that, so I was impressed. Second time I had a nonfat latte with toasted marshmallow syrup: Now... is there cream in that? because my nonfat latte tasted too good to be true. I tell you what, next time I'm going to stand there and WATCH the person and see what milk they use. I must know. 

I like that they had so many cookies, pastries and wrapped caramels to choose from. I love options. 

Was a little sad that they close at 8pm on a weekday... but I suppose it makes sense for the area. It's in a business district where all the other shops and businesses have closed. Well, minus any bars that happen to be around.

name: Weekends Only Furniture & Mattress
categories: Mattresses, Shopping, Home Decor, Furniture Stores, Home & Garden
text: One star is too much and a negative star would be more appropriate.  Buying the stuff is super easy but getting it loaded is a completely different story. It just takes forever to get the stuff it takes 10 minutes to buy over an hour to get it loaded. Quality of products are very low as most furniture is pressboard/particle board and less expensive elsewhere. Mattresses are a decent deal though compared to the other stores.  I would love to get a job in the loading dock,  where else can one get $10 hr to BS,  smoke and stand around?

name: Imos Pizza
categories: Restaurants, Pizza
text: OK experience. I went here for lunch when I was traveling around the area for work. The inside is mediocre and food is ok. Staff was freidnly and food came out fast.

categories: Restaurants, Breakfast & Brunch, American (Traditional)
text: This is the perfect small town restaurant. You go here to people watch and get lots of food for very cheap. It's fun to just pick up the local Freeburg Tribune, grab a cup of coffee and relax for a little bit. If you want to do work as well, they offer free wifi for everyone. I usually get Eric's Special. Don't expect a Michelin Star experience, but expect a small town experience.

name: Johnsons Corner
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'loud'", 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'Caters': 'True', 'Ambience': "{u'divey': True, u'hipster': False, u'casual': None, u'touristy': None, u'trendy': False, u'intimate': False, u'romantic': False, u'classy': False, u'upscale': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{u'breakfast': None, u'brunch': None, u'lunch': True, u'dinner': True, u'latenight': None, u'dessert': None}", 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': True, u'lot': None, u'validated': False}"}
categories: Pizza, Restaurants, American (Traditional)
text:
Yes - it is cold/cooler than your normal restaurant. Everybody is right on about that.

Stopped in one night for a late dinner - ordered salad, cheese fries & zucchini to share. My salad came out DRENCHED in ranch dressing. It was literally spilling over the sides and dressing plopped into my water cup as the waitress handed the plate to me. Both her & I had to wipe off our hands after we handled the plate. I didn't finish the salad because I felt like all I was eating was ranch. The other items I got were good! Crispy zucchini sticks & fries can't really mess those up.

Will definitely try this place out if I'm in the area again looking for a meal. But this time I'm asking for my dressing on the side.

They have a wise variety of items on the menu - sure to please anyone. Lots of fish options in addition to usual bar/traditional American restaurant fare. Very friendly owned or manager at the door/hostess area. Give them a try!

name: Ashley HomeStore
categories: Shopping, Mattresses, Furniture Stores, Home & Garden, Home Decor
text: Amazing service you guys provide here. Thanks for allowing me to be a part of all the rudeness, wasted time, lost wages, and damaged home. This is so much more fun than simply taking back the damaged items and letting my wife and I move on.

name: Morrison Plumbing, Heating and Air
categories: Plumbing, Contractors, Heating & Air Conditioning/HVAC, Home Services, Flooring
text: This is a family owned business that has top notch service. They installed our new central air system complete with a Nest thermostat. I highly recommend them.

name: Pizza Hut
attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False'}
categories: Restaurants, Fast Food, Italian, Pizza, Chicken Wings
text: If your hungry for pizza and salad for lunch, this Pizza Hut is the stop. I have constantly ate lunch here many time before I wrote this review. I will say measuring up to all the Pizza Hut lunches and locations this is the best Pizza Hut for lunch. The salad bar is well kept and the veggies are chopped small enough to pick up and you don't have to cut them or bite one end to get them in your mouth. The pizza is fresh, well made with a bigger assortment than any other Pizza Hut I have been to. Good crowd which keeps the hot food flowing. Sometimes they come up a little short and you end up waiting, but it's worth it. looking for a lunch less than $10 with a soda, less than $8 with water; can't beat it.

attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "'full_bar'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'None'}

text: The Ranch is exclusively a late night bar. I've never been there before 1am. Once the Regal Beagle closes down most of the customers transition to the Ranch. They offer free popcorn, which is nice, but the bar is kind of gross. The late night clientele is a bit sloppy with their free popcorn and it ends up carpeting the floor.

name: Leap & Bounce 4 Fun
categories: Party Equipment Rentals, Party Supplies, Event Planning & Services, Popcorn Shops, Face Painting, Food, Party Characters, Specialty Food
text: Marlon and his team are tops!  We rented one of his wet slides and it was the perfect way to cool off on a hot summer day.  They set up was on time and he made sure everything was perfect for our party.  Thanks again!

name: Speed Lube
categories: Automotive, Oil Change Stations
text: Bad, real bad. Always try to up sell any unsuspecting customers. The last straw was when they asked if my wife could go get cash instead of using a debit/credit card. The tech gave some lame excuse about changing suppliers and having to get oil at O'reilly's. Not my problem and just lost 3 customers. They also are supposed to vacuum out the drivers side of the car and yet again always find some lame excuse not to do it. I even seen them drain a transmission instead of a engine one day. Seriously think about changing your own oil before letting these jokers mess with your auto. BAD.

name: Pie Hard Pizza
categories: Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Pizza, Restaurants, Food, Desserts
text: Amazing pizza, we had (the mcclain/ darkwing duck / the island / the tribianni) and each one was delicious!! Mike and his crew do a phenomenal job and this place is a must stop for any pizza lovers

name: Annie's Frozen Custard
categories: Food, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt
text:
I've been eating frozen custard for a long time. Some of the best I have had has been in Utah (St. George) and in Springfield, MO (Andy's!) And St. Louis has a long tradition of good custard shops.

Annie's is as good as it gets. Great chocolate custard. Pretty much perfect.

They have a great retro location -- vintage 1960 or so -- kept up really well. Staff was VERY friendly. They have added great outdoor seating, flower planters, even heater lamps.  Impressive.

text:
Firstly, this place is terrible because I don't want to wait in line. Secondly, I love this place. The food is fantastic. I spoke to the owner, and though he associated with the prior owner, I forgive him. Even the ribs are competitive with barbecue joints in the area. Most importantly, the music isn't Disney-based. Very happy with my experience so far. 
Everything I have tried so far is really great, and priced very well. Working through the menu has been a treat. I stand by my 5 stars.

attributes: {'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'WiFi': "'free'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BYOB': 'True', 'HappyHour': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'Corkage': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True'}
categories: Restaurants, Thai
text: Wow, what great tasting Thai food right here in Edwardsville! I remember hearing about their opening back in the fall, but never had a chance to visit until tonight. Well, it was worth the wait...or more like, I shouldn't have waited so long to come here!! We walked in on a fairly busy Friday night, and were seated promptly. It took awhile for our server to take our order, but we received our food in fairly good time. It was robust, loaded with flavor, and served piping hot. I had the pho and my wife had the pad see ew. Both dishes were fantastic! Our server talked to us about other items on the menu that he liked, and we agree. There's plenty more on the menu that we'd love to try someday. We'll be back! Check this place out for yourself!

text: My wife and I had Reuben sandwiches and home made chips. Awesome! My wife could only eat half her sandwich.  It was a lot of food.                                                              If you want a great sandwich for lunch. This is the place to go!

name: JCPenney
categories: Shopping, Men's Clothing, Children's Clothing, Appliances, Eyewear & Opticians, Women's Clothing, Baby Gear & Furniture, Department Stores, Fashion, Home & Garden
text:
I believe that JCPENNY overall is a few bad earnings cycles away from the fate of Sears.  This location specifically is already even worse than the first few times we shopped there, in August 2017. 

We hadn't been back except to pick up orders. We went in today and egads it is even worse than a flea market on the bad side of a town. There is too much merchandise scattered all over the place, you can barely navigate the aisles for all the badly jumbled clothing. The music is too loud and it is the worst versions of songs that were pretty bad to begin with.

Today's insult was an abandoned pick-up desk. After standing there for 15 minutes a sullen, spoiled entitled teenager came over.  She was rude and "put upon", basically treated me, an adult paying customer-like a kid at school she didn't need to pay attention to. 

I tried to contact the store to express my concerns, no answer.  I tried to reach corporate- no way to do so.  The store clearing only cares about sales and though their webpage professes customer service as a core value-nothing I saw today puts that on the list at all. 

This location is doomed. We likely leave the area by 2020.  I'm not sure this one will still be open by then. I guess I will pay for delivery to the house, rather than deal with spoiled teens who don't appreciate that they have a job.  If she doesn't change her attitude, she might not achieve much more than where she is now.

name: Mama Mia's Italian Restaurant
categories: Restaurants, Italian
text: We are from out of town and stopped here. The people are very friendly! We came for takeout but ended up staying for the service. The food is cheap and they give you a lot. It was also very clean and professional!

text:
Melissa and all the staff were wonderful.   We ordered and old fashion (yum) and a glass of wine. Drink prices are perfect for the portions. 

We ordered the "Handcrafted Charcuterie" which should be named "Chefs Selection" it was tasty but not a wow moment. Of all the items on the menu this is the time for the chef to truly show off their creativity. Unfortunately I must agree with the other post what is signature about them?  But if I'm in the area again. I would try again.

name: Auffenberg Kia
categories: Oil Change Stations, Car Dealers, Automotive, Auto Repair
text: I'm taking my 2012 Kia Soul in for the THIRD time to get my drivers side window fixed. Why on earth it can't be fixed the first time is totally unbelievable. I've never had an issue like this in any other brand I've ever owned. Ever.

text:
I have went to this Dairy Queen for the last time. The last time I was there I got a BBQ sandwich which was cold when I got it out.  This time I get an orange Julius and take the first drink and it was like picking up a milky drink that had sat in a warm room for hours.  Not refreshing at the least.

SAI

name: Garden Gate Tea Room
categories: Food, Restaurants, Tea Rooms
text:
One of my favorite restaurants hands down, and it's in my own city. Brenda is a wonderful person; she gets to know her regulars and her new guests. Deana is darling! 
As far as food it's a wonderful stop for light but filling fare. My favorite to start with is the lobster bisque or chicken and dumpling soup. Curried egg salad, French dip and the pilgrim are all great sandwich choices. Wraps and salads are always fresh, desserts always perfect. The broccoli salad is to die for. 
I have many friends that have hosted showers here and we always enjoy the spread. I miss Sunday brunches! Wish I could make it here more often!

name: Edwardsville Pet Hospital
categories: Pets, Pet Services, Veterinarians
text:
How did I miss this gem for ten years? This is one pet place that doesn't overcharge. The prices are very fair and the care is top notch. The doctors are very attentive and caring. They make you feel that they are there for your animal's care and not for your pocket book.

As I came back to give an update, I must say hats off to this place. They worked hard to help us save our dog, going the extra mile in so many ways. I really appreciated the many, many weeks they spent trying to do so many things to help-but, with age, she couldn't fight any longer (and they were surprised she made it that long). But, the emotional support we had, and the extra mile of help over the phone, with the various options, this place deserves better than five stars.

name: Home Towne Suites
categories: Hotels, Event Planning & Services, Hotels & Travel
text: Room clean. Room service moved suitcase on bed to avoid making it. No plate, cup or fork in room. Could purchase a set, though! No breakfast.  Took our towels and didn't replace them. Beds awful. Never slept on a queen sized cot before! Definitely sleep elsewhere.

name: Pizza Hut
categories: Chicken Wings, Italian, Fast Food, Pizza, Restaurants
text: Scared little pussies WOULD NOT COME OUT AT 1.30PM TO LOVE'S TRUCK STOP. "It's unsafe. If our driver is raped, we'd have to find you. It's not a permanent address - you don't live there." said the woman who answered the phone. Just some bullshit excuse. Called Domino's Pizza - they came out, NO PROBLEM.

Out-FING-standing!!!  Do you know ho hard it is to fine a truly farm raised bone in Ham Steak now a days?   My quest is complete!!  I can. Or recommend this establishment enough. 

If you are traveling North of St. Louis on the great River Road(Illinois side) definitely worth the 1 mile divergence from your travels.

Now all I need is to find a soft bed for a nap.

text: We were looking for a Bed and Breakfast in the area and found Dr. Jazz. The B and B is above a very nice old fashioned soda fountain. Two large bedrooms, living room , two bathrooms and kitchen area (no stove). Very clean and the owner is a great guy. Would definitely stay again!

name: Tim & Joe's Tavern
categories: American (Traditional), Restaurants
text:
A Chrsitmas eve tradition with good pub food.  Had a straightforward cheese burger and fries with a couple beverages and had no complaints.

Staff was not cuper friendly but they were prompt and attentive.  So try it out if you are nearby and want some simple pub food.

text: Lunch visit to one of my favorite local Mexican restaurants. Had the carne asada tacos and they were outstanding.  Tacos come wrapped in flour tortillas and folded in aluminum foil. The carne asada portion size within the taco is not extremely large, but it is just right for me. I added in some pico, salsa and beans to the carne asada and it was excellent. Chips and salsa prior the meal were free. Customer service was outstanding.

name: Ayurvedic Center of Health & Healing
categories: Massage Therapy, Massage, Beauty & Spas, Health & Medical, Ayurveda
text: Best massage I have ever had!!! I haven't been able to disconnect from ever day life until I visited the BRAT House Day Spa!!

name: Neruda Restaurant
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'dressy'", 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '4', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
categories: Restaurants, American (New)
text:
Yes, Neruda is nice. It's one of the nicer restaurants in E'ville. It may be a little overpriced compared to the other restaurants in the area. Also what I noticed is that it is way too dark inside, I am not sure if that is done on purpose, but it's way too dark. The decor is pleasant, the food is really good. The only thing I didn't appreciate when we were there... - when we ordered entrees the waiter asked "Would you like a salad with that or soup"... and I understood as if the entree comes with either one and we ordered salads only to find out that we were charged for them and they weren't cheap. Granted the salads were good (the tomato, mozzarella and basil salad), but still, I didn't appreciate how he asked us making it sound like it comes with salad. Anyway, you live and learn! 

If I lived in St. Louis, I wouldn't necessarily drive all the way to Neruda, there are so many great places in STL to be driving 20 miles.

name: The Ultrasound Zone
categories: Diagnostic Services, Health & Medical, Diagnostic Imaging
text: My husband, parents, and in-laws all had a wonderful experience at The Ultrasound Zone. Leslie was very nice and welcoming when we arrived, and Regina was especially patient with us when our baby wouldn't show his face. She tried everything she could to get us a good shot of him and even did a redo session with us. They were so nice. I would definitely recommend them!

name: Steak ’n Shake

text: I always look forward to Steak N Shake when I'm visiting STL/IL but this one was terrible. My burger had mustard ALL over the outside of the bun and the inside was filled with so much mustard it was pretty much all I could taste. Seriously, see my picture. It's one thing to make a mistake and forget to hold the pickles or whatever, but there's no way the employee wrapping this order didn't notice this mess. Gross.

name: Luxury Nails Salon
categories: Nail Salons, Beauty & Spas
text: The owner is great at doing nails here, it's defiantly my favorite nail salon in O'Fallon! And I've tried them ALL! LOL

name: Burgers STL
categories: Food, Food Trucks
text: This is the best burger I have ever had in my life.  Yes, In N Out and Shake Shack, I am talking to you!  Matt Foley cooks his heart out for these bad boys and it shows.  And the fresh cut french fries are out of this world!  There was quite a line, but we were served with a smile!  Don't miss your opportunity to try the best burger of your life, you won't regret it!

name: Alton Room Escape
categories: Escape Games, Event Planning & Services, Team Building Activities, Active Life
text: Great fun at this well organized and decorated escape room.  They were accommodating early afternoon hours, family friendly, allow smaller groups.  You should check them out.

name: Vallow Floor Covering
categories: Home Services, Heating & Air Conditioning/HVAC, Carpeting, Shopping, Carpet Installation, Rugs, Home & Garden, Flooring, Contractors
text: Vallow did a terrific job for us.  Their prices were more than competitive and the quality of work was extremely high --- AND --- there was one issue and the owner came out and personally fixed it.  I couldn't recommend this company higher!

name: Big Daddy's 618
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Caters': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}"}
categories: Nightlife, Restaurants, American (Traditional), Bars
text:
So shaved and crazy Jesus is gone.  Still can't say this is my favorite place to go.  I have been to Big Daddys in St. Louis, they have crowds, and literate people who speak in complete sentences.   

Walking in at 10pm, I notice not 1, not 2, but 3 police cars out front.  For a sleepy little Mayberry-esque town like Belleville that seems excessive!  One asshat cop was waiting parked outside looking to give DUIs.  They must have stiffed him his bribe (er....... on duty adult libation ;-) ),  

I got here kinda late to meet some friends.  They insisted on the place.  I let them know there are literally a dozen better places within walking distance!  Like places where people have real teeth?

I think this bar supports AA meetings, because this is a good place to sober up.  Despite a very small crowd for a Saturday night, it took forever to get served.  I was waiting for these two lawn gnomes to finish debating in Latin the merits of various alcoholic additions to their Red Bull, when I decided it would be rude to reach over them and order a bottle of Bud.  Although I was tempted.  

After reviewing the inhabitants at Big Daddy's I came to the conclusion that this is the closest I will come to the cantina scene in Star Wars.  

I drank beer, because I was afraid of the local water supply!

The only positive about the place was the DJ, and he wasn't really all that, he just had a great team to make him look good!

name: Savers
categories: Thrift Stores, Shopping, Local Services, Donation Center
text: Very clean and well organized thrift shop.  I thought the houseware prices were a little high by about one or two dollars each. Their display of pictures is really nice.

name: Lowe's Home Improvement
categories: Building Supplies, Shopping, Home Services, Paint Stores, Home & Garden, Hardware Stores, Appliances, Nurseries & Gardening
text: I ordered some flooring for my home from Bruce in the flooring dept & he was excellent with his customer service. He had customers calling, asking question, trying to place orders & he was being paged. He stayed professional & calm. Also he took care everyone he was capable of taking care of.  With my order it took a long time because he had to contact the flooring company (Cali Bamboo) & it was a long process. They gave me a incredible deal for the floors that I ordered. Bruce was very apologetic for the time it took.  I TRULY thank Bruce &  Amy Dow from Cali bamboo for their Excellent customer service!

name: Garden Salon & Spa
categories: Beauty & Spas, Hair Salons, Massage, Nail Salons, Skin Care, Day Spas
text: My favorite salon!! Katie always does a fantastic job on my hair, she always gives me exactly what I want. :) don't even get me started on her nails! Perfection! She did my nails, and three weeks later they're still chip free and no lifting!

text: Nice little cafe place off the beaten path in a quaint little town of Lebanon, IL. They specialize is craft sodas which are very tasty and also a variety of danishes and coffee types. Friendly place as well and an outside area for relaxing on the street front.

name: Cecena's Jewelry
categories: Jewelry, Shopping
text: Stopped by off the recommendation of Yelp and definitely wasn't disappointed. I brought in 6 watches for them to replace batteries, etc. I recommend them for their quick turnaround, affordable cost on repairs and easy access off of the highway 64/40.

name: AT&T Store
categories: Mobile Phones, Mobile Phone Accessories, Internet Service Providers, Shopping, Professional Services, Home Services, Telecommunications, Local Services, IT Services & Computer Repair
text: I've gone in there for years because it is a company store, not one of the franchise stores (which charge extra for everything).  Usually it is bustling and there is a wait.  But this time it was 7:20 on a Friday and they should have been packed, but not a single customer and about 5 reps standing around trying to figure out what to do.  Odd.  But now I know why.  I need a SIM card for a new phone I got off eBay.  They wanted to charge me $5 for the sim card.  It has never happened before, but supposedly it was a new policy if you did not buy one of their over priced products.  I objected, the manager came out (very detached) and said that was the policy period.  I said without a sim, their service was useless, he shrugged. I said I would take my 220/mo account elsewhere and his reaction was "if that is what you need to do".  Over $5 my gosh.  I got home, called 611 and that rep was appalled, sent me a sim overnight without charge as customer service should be.  I'll be going to a different company store in the future.

name: Smile For Life Dentistry
categories: Health & Medical, General Dentistry, Dentists, Orthodontists, Endodontists
text: I have never liked going to the Dentist until I started going to Smile For Life. The Staff is amazing everyone has a smiles with great energy. I have to say Ashley is amazing! I like going just to hang with her. My daughter loves going too. They make the painful visit not so scary for the kids. The best part....they allow you to stay with your kids the whole time.

name: Rocket Bowls

text: Love this place! Their sesame chicken and sweet potato fries are to die for! Will be returning :)

name: Beautiful Nails
categories: Nail Salons, Beauty & Spas
text: I have been coming here for years and never been more disappointed than now. I went in for a pedicure and the lady that did mine was on her phone more than anything. Glad I'm not on a time crunch today.

text:
1) walk in. no one at counter.
2) counter help sees you, ignores you.
3) same person comes back 45 seconds later
4) no "hi" or 'hello", just that "dead fish eye look"
5) she takes order. gives change. doesn't say amount, just dumps receipt and change in hand. no "thank you. turns and walks away and starts chatting with drive thru clerk.
6) fries put on tray on counter. fries sit on tray on counter for no less than 5 minutes.
7) burgers come. placed on tray.
8) order sits on counter for another 3 minutes before being "called out"/announced.

sucks out loud. just close already. this during "lunch rush".

name: Embrich Plumbing Company
categories: Contractors, Shopping, Kitchen & Bath, Home & Garden, Local Services, Plumbing, Building Supplies, Septic Services, Water Heater Installation/Repair, Heating & Air Conditioning/HVAC, Home Services
text: Embrich is the best!  The repairman came out and diagnosed the problem with my water heater the same day I called. He explained everything thoroughly and was very professional. The part had to be ordered, no fault of theirs. Then the owner came back at a time that accommodated our schedule and replaced the part. Thank you!!  A+

name: Maeva's
categories: Bakeries, Food, Coffee & Tea
text:
Okay, I have been going here a few years... 

Now what I don't understand is how a restaurant/ coffee house not run AC while it's 94degrees outside.

I went up to ask the server when they would get it fixed and he plays dumb that there was AC and that I was hot bc there were too many people.

Now are you calling me dumb? I and my friend are over here sweating. You even have a floor fan blowing on the customers bc of your lack of AC. I mean come on.

Maevas used to be cool but how am I supposed to enjoy a delicious hot beverage while sweating and a sarcastic server telling me I am imagining things?

name: Red Shed Storage
categories: Home Services, Movers
text: They do not have customer service at all and they will just throw your stuff on a truck with no care at all and if you call the owner he will just say he doesn't care because he's already got his money and could care less about anyone else's stuff. And will tell you to call the BBB "Better business" and the law and who ever may care.. I will never waist my time again with them

name: Tipsy Nails&Spa
categories: Beauty & Spas, Nail Salons
text: This salon is AMAZING. The space is beautifully decorated. The staff is amazing and so nice. We had four people and they were quickly able to get us in for pedicures on a Saturday. The services were all excellent, everyone was very professional, and it was all for a great price! They have plenty of space for large parties for birthdays or bachelorette parties. This will definitely be my new place - definitely worth the drive from St. Louis. It is a little hard to find in front of walmart but so worth the search.

name: Schaefer Automotive
categories: Tires, Auto Repair, Oil Change Stations, Automotive
text: 5 stars for sure!!!! Thank you to Ben and the entire team at Schaefer Automotive for getting my 1941 Plymouth PT-125 pickup back on the road. The truck is running better than it ever has since I've owned it.

name: Dodge Moving & Storage
categories: Movers, Home Services
text:
I moved from St.Louis Missouri to San Antonio Texas 1 month ago and the two delivers in for Packers were amazing.. I have moved all over the country..95 times 15 states and now my parents and I even though we live separately we take Mayflower until we witnessed something where we will not take them.. it cost $2,900 to move from St Louis to San Antonio and the driver out here was a little iffy one of the days because there was a 13 day time frame and I couldn't be able to move in on the complete 13 days anytime they wanted to because I was moving to a brand new complex in a brand new apartment.. after a little talking and relaxing we both found a conclusion and I moved in
. It was a great experience thank you... I was in a hotel in between the hotel dates and the brand new apartment opening date we had a little anxiety and we got over it and we moved in and nothing was broken and nothing was demolished in the residence..

name: Republic Services
categories: Contractors, Junk Removal & Hauling, Local Services, Recycling Center, Home Services
text:
Republic are liars and unreliable.  They told us that they were our only choice for trash service and that we had to recycle.  Then they didn't pick up our recycling on the designated days and weren't reliable to pick up the trash at all. 

We contacted other trash services that served the nearest town  (we live just outside of town) and they do service us and recycling is NOT mandatory for our county. 

We cancelled service with republic and told them to get their bins. Which weeks later are still sitting in out drive. Surprise! 

Don't believe what they say. Call around and ask.

name: Corral Liquors
categories: Food, Beer, Wine & Spirits
text: Great selection, reasonable prices, plus they do the occasional free sample. It's good to have such a nice place in my own back yard!

name: The Tye-Dyed Iguana
categories: Reptile Shops, Pet Stores, Pets
text: Excellent shop! Top notch customer service by Matt and his staff. We bought a crested gecko and supplies. They even offer pet sitting when you go out of town. We also considered hermit crabs and snakes. Came in twice to look for a good starter pet and price supplies. Received great advice. My kids love to come and get crickets and look around to see what's new. Fantastic store.

name: Pitchers Sports Pub & Pizzaria

text:
I love the wooden oak bar in this place. It is hand made and has all kinds of stains and marks which just adds to the character of the place. The food was kinda of disappointing. The toasted ravioli and wings were good, but they served brats that were so burnt and charcoaled, there was not enough mustard, ketchup, horseradish or sauerkraut to cover the charred meat. 

This place does cater to a certain clientele and I guess they don't come for the food.

text: I thought the crabs were fresh and tasty as well as the sausage. The garlic was a little strong but not horrible. The place was clean but sure what the other people saw. The menu was a bit limited.

name: Sparkle Express Car Wash
categories: Car Wash, Automotive
text: Huge car wash place and free vacuum that I never use. The machines here do as gold as others I've been to. I guess I'm spoiled by hand wash prior to going through the machine. I think it's a little pricy compared to others. But that possibly makes up for the free vacuum.

name: Lottie's Cafe
categories: Nightlife, Bars, Breakfast & Brunch, Restaurants, Italian, Cocktail Bars, Salad, Eatertainment, Arts & Entertainment
text: Love the decor.  Food was very good but find it annoying to have to listen to the gaming machines while trying the enjoy the atmosphere of what would otherwise be a pleasant experience.  Maybe the sound on this machines could be turned off if these are a must.

name: LensCrafters
categories: Ophthalmologists, Doctors, Optometrists, Shopping, Eyewear & Opticians, Health & Medical
text:
My wife purchased a pair of Versace frames and lenses from lenscrafters in the mall end of 2013.  
The paint has been slowly peeling off since may.
I called the manager and he refused to help in any way.  So sad...  People who wear glasses are repeat customers if you stand behind your product and offer assistance.  We will be going somewhere else for our family eyewear. Be warned, they do not stand behind their eye wear.  We recently went to Sam's Club and they were very helpful and stand behind their product.  The frames they offered were all a lot less expensive that lenscrafters as well.

name: Rent Solutions
categories: Apartments, Real Estate Services, Property Management, Home Services, Real Estate, University Housing
text:
Everybody needs to know what a great experience I had at Rent Solutions! The service was incredible and they went above and beyond in every way!!!  

If you need assistance in finding a rental house/apartment, this is the place!

Rent Solutions worked well around my schedule and the communication was excellent! 

Do yourself a favor and call them today.

name: L A Nails
categories: Hair Removal, Eyelash Service, Beauty & Spas, Nail Salons, Waxing
text: Phenomenal job on my pedicure. It was one of the best pedicures I've had in awhile. He also listened to what I wanted for my gel manicure. I would highly recommend.

name: CVS Pharmacy
categories: Drugstores, Food, Health & Medical, Pharmacy, Shopping, Convenience Stores
text: Typical CVS. Organization is good, you can find what you are looking for easily. Have not used the pharmacy, so refer to other reviewers. Customer service was friendly and quick.

name: Memorial Hospital-Belleville
categories: Home Health Care, Diagnostic Services, Health & Medical, Doctors, Hospitals, Radiologists
text:
Had outpatient surgery. Was kept overnight for observation after. Very nice staff at my pre-op, surgery unit and on my floor overnight. Kept me informed and comfortable. 
The only reason for not having the 5th star was that previously I had taken a friend to the ER on several
occasions. As in other reviews I too was unimpressed by the care that he received in ER. 
So avoid the ER if possible. Everything else was first rate.

name: Hardee's
attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}

This would have gotten 5 stars from the service I received from another employee, but because of the manager's lying and bad attitude, this is being dropped to its lowest of 1 star. I don't recommend!

text: Meh, food is okay. Drinks come with the price, but it is just okay. Nothing special, but if you are in the area, it will do.

name: Meurer Brothers
categories: Tree Services, Home Services
text: They did a great job cutting down my big maple tree that was rotting, and then grinding down the stump. They also cleaned out my gutters while they were on the roof which was a very pleasant surprise. I had them trim the same tree a couple years ago. I've never met anyone either time, because I was always at work when they came, but everyone I've talked to has been very nice. I would hire them again, but I have no trees left except one that's just four feet tall, so someday .....

name: Pizza Hut
categories: Pizza, Restaurants, Italian, Fast Food, Chicken Wings
text: Strike 3. 3 times our work group had went here for lunch buffet.3 times the restaurant is almost empty but despite even calling ahead delay in getting a table,  forever to get drinks & salads h buffet was close to empty entire 50 minutes we were at restaurant. Our group of 7 each had 1-2 pieces of pizza Mac because that's all there wad.....

name: Ruby Tuesday

categories: Restaurants, Burgers, American (Traditional)
text: Ruby is not really one of my go to places. It really is good though. The salad bar is always fresh, and the food is good. It is a bit pricey. I think maybe I should add it to my go to places.

name: Hanley's Grille & Tap
categories: Restaurants, American (Traditional), American (New)
text:
First went to Hanley's because I had a Groupn.  I wasn't really a fan of the previos J.Bucks.  I like Hanley's better. The buffalo wings are great anf the thin fries are great if they are fresh.

Because of the atmosphere, I recently had a bookclub meeting there and we had a great time.  Our waiter was hilarious and very helpful. 

I just convinced the peple in my office to order take out that my boss is paying for.  I will comeback and let you know how that goes.

name: F-M Exteriors
categories: Home Services, Roofing, Damage Restoration
text: Don't know how this company is still in business.  They took 30 grand from my insurance company to fix repairs on my home from a big hail storm in 2012.  This past December (2015),  the roof began leaking and damaged the interior ceiling in my daughters room.  It was warranty work, and it's been a nightmare to get them over to fix it.  It's now May 2016 and it's still not finished.  Do NOT use this business.  You'll just get F'd by them.

name: Jared Galleria of Jewelery
categories: Jewelry, Shopping
text: Bought engagement and wedding rings at this location, everything was fantastic. The only reason for the two stars is due to the rings look great.  The great customer service pretty much  ends once they have your money. Good luck having their staff wait on you if you bring in your rings for a cleaning. My wife has her rings cleaned and inspected twice a year, and out of the 10 times we drop them off to have them cleaned/inspected eight of the visits we wait over 15 minutes to be even acknowledged, much less helped. Do yourself a favor if you need to drop off your jewelry, don't bring it in a bag/case or have any Jared paperwork visible, otherwise you will not be helped. Currently writing this review as my wife waits yet again to drop off her rings because they're understaffed as well. 20 minutes and counting...

name: O'Brien Tire & Service Center,Inc
categories: Oil Change Stations, Auto Repair, Automotive, Tires
text: This is my second review for this tire store. I took the time to write it because they continue to exceed my expectations. I had a nail in my tire. Brought it in around 1 pm. Out at 1:20 pm with it good as new. Do yourself a favor and send your business to them.

name: Valvoline Instant Oil Change
categories: Auto Repair, Oil Change Stations, Automotive
text: Best experience I've had getting an oil change!  Extremely nice and they educate you on what you should do next with your vehicle.  Also the military discount is s plus!

name: Federico Kia
categories: Automotive, Auto Parts & Supplies, Car Dealers
text:
WARNINING - Dishonest

We recently purchased a used car from Federico KIA.  When we picked up the car there was only one key.  We asked for, and were promised a second key.  They now refuse to produce the key.  We have escalated through their management and are currently working through the Better Business Bureau, but still the resist.

Background - The car purchased is a Smart car.  The salesperson requested we return to Federico KIA, a 70 mile trip, on a Friday when their key vendor is available.  We agreed, with the stipulation, agreed to by the salesperson, that if their vendor could not produce the key, Federico KIA would pay for a key made by a Smart dealer.  Their vendor was unable to make the key and Federico KIA now refuses to pay for a key from the Smart dealer.

Buyer beware!

Is there a rating lower than one star?  They deserve it...

name: Fezziwig's Marketplace
categories: Home Decor, Food, Cooking Classes, Arts & Crafts, Home & Garden, Specialty Food, Shopping, Wineries, Arts & Entertainment, Coffee & Tea, Wine Tasting Room, Grocery
text: Upscale shop. Friendly and helpful staff. Especially darling to visit during the holidays.

Good pizzas, decent burgers, more of an older crowd...and I mean older, like 70s lol.
Sketchy neighborhood

name: Smoothie King
categories: Specialty Food, Juice Bars & Smoothies, Food, Health Markets
text: Not all smoothies are created equally and not all Smoothie King's are equal either. This is a brand new location in Edwardsville and it has some of the friendliest staff in the area. The feature a drive thru if you're in a rush. I haven't tried it yet but if it is anything like the atmosphere inside it won't disappoint. I have been here twice since they opened and each time they are busy but they move the line quickly and each person in like with care and respect. I tend to get the Gladiator or Veggie Slim and Trim. Yesterday I had the Hulk with coffee 20 oz. The Hulk had a taste of a moca so if your a fan of coffee moca you will love this. An added bonus is Every Friday the 32 oz size is only $6.

name: Bridgette Kelly Photography
categories: Photographers, Session Photography, Event Planning & Services, Arts & Entertainment, Event Photography
text: Not impresed with the quality of her prints or the final outcome. I left my prints sitting out 24 hours after getting them in the mail and they curled. Additionally many of my photos were taken in an alley and all I see when I look at them is a dumpster. I feel like she should have been able to photoshop the dumpster out or do a better job of focusing the image. Her prices are extremely high for the quality of photos you recieve.

name: CVS Pharmacy
categories: Drugstores, Pharmacy, Health & Medical, Convenience Stores, Food, Shopping
text: This cvs consistently has the rudest pharmacy staff. Many visits and never a decent experience. We do our best to go drive miles out of the way to use a different cvs.

categories: Bars, Wine Bars, Restaurants, Italian, Pizza, American (Traditional), Nightlife
text:
If you told me about a place where 4 people can eat huge lunches for a total of $30, I'd slap you and call you crazy. Unfortunately, slapping myself doesn't have the same effect. Either way... holy crap is this place inexpensive for what you get. I had the 1/2 fried chicken dinner (HALF! for $4.99!), it comes with a baked potato, salad & bread. Am I at KFC with these prices? Thankfully, no! 

The chicken was really delicious, but I was so full of salad & bread that I could only eat a little bit of the chicken when it arrived. Since I was hopping on a plane in an hour, I sent my leftovers home with my mom to enjoy. Their menu has a great selection, the dining area is nice, and the service was great. Two thumbs up.

name: Dairy Queen Grill & Chill
categories: Food, Fast Food, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Restaurants, Burgers
text: Impressed with customer service.  I just called asking about a particular ice cream cake and the man told me they keep them in stock and answered all my questions.  A few minutes later he called me back, apparently using a re-dial last number function (I hadn't given him any information) to tell me he double checked the supply after I called and there weren't any of that type ready.  He then checked if they had a back-up, which they did, but it needed to be decorated.  Then he even customized the toppings.  I'm alway happy to patronize a restaurant that takes that little extra step to make sure the customer is happy.

name: Walgreens
categories: Food, Shopping, Cosmetics & Beauty Supply, Photography Stores & Services, Convenience Stores, Beauty & Spas, Drugstores
text: Had to stop in on the way home from a road trip. My girlfriend was super sick and throwing up in the passenger seat. I got some Dramamine, plastic bags, water and some paper towels. I'm thankful that this location was easy to get to and they had trash cans outside.

text: Fantastic food and service with a smile! My friend and I had a wonderful quiche with salad for lunch last Saturday. We shared a delicious piece of tiramisu that was created in the bakery next door. The restaurant has a nice outdoor seating area, too. Highly recommend!

name: Wendy's
categories: Burgers, Fast Food, Restaurants
text: Great burgers and fries. Wendy's is on its way up and this particular location is nice and clean.

name: Cahokia Mounds
categories: Arts & Entertainment, Landmarks & Historical Buildings, Public Services & Government, Museums, Parks, Active Life
text: Great Historic Site. After taking a Native American Studies class my outlook on the natives lives has changed and I wish we were more open and honest about their existence. I encourage everyone to check this place out in addition to more research. They are called Native Americans for a reason and their culture is amazing and beautiful.

name: Golden Oak Pancake House
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': None, u'street': False, u'lot': None, u'validated': None}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True'}
categories: Burgers, American (New), Restaurants, Pancakes, Breakfast & Brunch
text: I've eaten here several times and like the previous review I was surprised I hadn't left one yet. Oh I absolutely love this place I wish I could eat breakfast here every morning. The people are so nice and friendly and they're just college kids who all get along and work really hard. Apparently during COVID nobody can hire a good employees but Golden Oak is doing something right! I think their employees are fabulous. Every time I walk in everybody is happy both customers and employees regardless if it's busy or slow. Note: It was only slow ones on the holiday weekend. The food is incredible I've never had anything bad. The French toast is probably one of the best I've ever had and I highly suggest you order it without sugar and blueberries because the flavor of the toast is phenomenal. My favorite is the sausage and cheese omelette it is huge it is cooked to order and it's served perfect. They also do their hashbrowns right I like need a double order I think every time I go because they cook them to perfection. These people deserve our business. It's always clean happy and tasty

name: Ruler Foods
categories: Grocery, Shopping, Food, Discount Store
text: Not the greatest selection, mainly stocked with Kroger store brands. Savings seems great! But you have to pay a quarter to use their shopping carts, 10 cents for their grocery bags or bring your own and you have to bag your groceries yourself. So if it's worth it to you, it's a great way to save a little $.

name: Karl R Gundersen, MD
categories: Health & Medical, Pediatricians, Counseling & Mental Health, Doctors, Psychiatrists
text:
Seriously confused by these other reviews. Finding Dr. Gundersen was one of the best things I've done for myself. Dr. Gundersen is right there beside you every step of your path-- whatever path you're on. He's one of those doctors that actually listens to you, and what's more-- he hears you; he's always asking how you are, how you feel, what you want to do. And he supports you, advises you, moves WITH you. Here, you are cared for. And you know it. This is not an office where you're an anonymous number on a long roster of clientele. It feels like every single person on the team is working for YOU, making sure you feel comfortable, making sure you are okay. 

So from the above and beyond customer service reps, to the call center (who address me personally), to the layout of the actual building and energy/ambience of the offices, and most importantly, to Dr. Gundersen himself--this place dedicates an exceptional amount of attention to the PATIENT'S comfort and satisfaction. You feel taken care of to a level that you can't find at every office or with every doctor.

With Dr. Gundersen, you just know that you're not alone. You've found someone who is just as concerned with your mental health as you are. And that is seriously rare. The first time I walked out of this office, I knew I had someone on MY team who made sure I was confident in every step of my own mental health treatment and journey. You are in good hands here; and they make sure that you feel that.

name: Gordmans
categories: Shopping, Department Stores, Home Decor, Fashion, Furniture Stores, Women's Clothing, Home & Garden
text: I'm such a Gordman's fan. I always buy my basic tanks here becaus you simply can't beat $4.99. This store is a bit cramped but not terribly so. You can still maneuver with a cart, and if you're like me, you need a cart to carry out all the goodies. I love that they have huge departments, and there is always clearance. For me, that department just so happens to be located near the shoes. God must really love me! Their shoe department is pretty great. Their shoes are a great price to begin with but once they go on clearance, you can get up to an additional 30-50% off. Steve Maddens for $25? Heck, yes! I can usually do 75-90% of my shopping for Christmas at one store because of Gordman's and their selection. They even carry some hard to find colognes and perfumes. Amazing deals on Kathy VanZealand bags, and very neat home decor items. I'm not a fan of paying full price, so Gordman's is my go-to. If you hit it regularly, you can find some fantastic finds. Name brand jeans, close outs, etc.

name: Peachy Yogurt Bar
categories: Restaurants, Food, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt
text:
I'm going as much in the middle as I can on this review as it wasn't great but I don't think it was terrible. There is a lot of room for improvement so maybe they can make it work. 

The place looked as clean as it gets but didn't seem the most inviting, very dull interior. The service wasn't great, the kid working there barely spoke a word and didn't even tell me he was setting the "iced coffee" out with half and half and milk to make myself, I just had to assume that was for me to make myself. Had I known that I wouldn't have ordered it.

Now onto the important part, the yogurt, the flavors I thought had an ok variety depending on what your looking for. The cake batter and the cookies and cream weren't bad. Most of the flavors seemed to be for those less adventurous. The mint was terrible, it tasted like I was eating tooth paste. They had a decent selection of toppings comparable to anywhere else and they all seemed fresh.

This place wasn't bad but not something I would drive out of my way to but if I happen to be strolling down Main St. in downtown Belleville and feel like frozen yogurt I might think about popping my head in to see what they have....I would say 2 and a half stars to be right down the middle but since I can't do that, I will give it 3.

name: X-Treme Carpet & Upholstery-Floor Cleaning Specialist
categories: Local Services, Grout Services, Damage Restoration, Flooring, Home Services, Air Duct Cleaning, Carpet Installation, Carpet Cleaning
text:
Based on prior reviews I thought this was a great option. However, I was not entirely satisfied with the job. Felt the tech rushed through the job, in and out in an hour, and didn't really work on the stains and high traffic areas. Also he didn't spend any time working the carpet up. He didn't walk me through at the end. Seemed to want to pack up and go as fast as possible. Definitely Not worth the $200 spent.  

They did offer to return and clean again but I was already moved out.  Also, told that David the owner would reach out to me to discuss, but still have not heard from him.  Probably will not use them again, nor will I recommend them to anyone.

this is a REAL tavern, the kind where the grandpa takes the grandkid for lunch. solid, wholesome atmosphere in a historical building. lunch and dinner specials. closes early (9-ish) if there aren't any customers. if you ever wonder what "the good old days" would look like if they had survived until today look no further.

no jukebox. no neon signs. just beer and food and no-hassle good company.

name: Triple R's Smokehouse
categories: Seafood, Restaurants, Barbeque, Caterers, Event Planning & Services, American (Traditional)
text: According to the local newspaper, Triple RRR has recently moved here from the other side of base. I had the brisket plate with beans and coleslaw, the wife had a pulled pork sandwich and fries. The brisket was very good, great smoke flavor, tender. The beans were good, but to sweet for me to get again. The coleslaw was creamy and I enjoyed it. The reduction in stars is based on the wait between order and food served. This location is just outside the base gate, so if you are here, its because you are looking for a quick lunch. Our 2 plates took 21 mins. Completely unacceptable, especially when there were only 4 other people in there. I wish them success, but if they can't fix that time piece, the building will be looking for another new occupant.

categories: Hotels & Travel, Event Planning & Services, Hotels
text:
i would rate it a no star. fyi to one and all, clint at the front desk told me they openly share your info with the local pd so they can run background checks on you when you stay here. VIOLATION OF PRIVACY! claiming its condoned by the city. the local pd must have little action around here and need to justify their salaries to the treasurer. 
he typed in my info, then went to make a copy of my id. i asked to have it returned when i check out and was told "no". no reason as to why the copy could not be handed over AFTER i check out.
they put a $50 hold on your credit card for "incidentals" which is more or less their way of profiling all their customers as theives. 
i travel a lot for work. 100% travel. im in & out of hotels every night. never seen such a practice. the 1 and only reason i went through with any of this is the room was paid for by my company in advance. be warned about this place. I'll sleep in my car if theres no other option before i come back here.

text:
Feel good food and funnel cakes, what else do you need? 
I had the steak&shrimp philly and it was better than I anticipated. You can't go wrong with a cheesesteak usually, but the seasoned shrimp on this sandwich made it worth it alone. The fried were seasoned, and there was plenty of them. 

The funnel cake didn't disappoint either, they are worth the trip alone. 

All in all a great LOCALLY OWNED&OPERATED small business with a kind owner who is clearly proud of his food.

name: Starbucks
categories: Coffee & Tea, Food
text:
If your moving like I am right now then there's no place on earth to chill with the free WiFi then this Starbucks. 

It's big, clean, nice, and awesome. Did I mention the free WiFi.

text:
This place is great!
They have a fantastic beer selection, great music and the food can't be beat!

name: 1 Nail Spa
categories: Nail Salons, Beauty & Spas
text: Friendly staff and helped us right away. Had plenty of time to browse colors never rushed.  The pedicure was amazing and they did a great job! My tech was very friendly.   Prices are good too. I would come back here again.

name: ALDI
categories: Grocery, Beer, Wine & Spirits, Organic Stores, Meat Shops, Food, Discount Store, Shopping, Specialty Food, Fruits & Veggies
text:
My favorite grocery store. The food is high quality and it's cheap.
I buy almost everything here. Especially meat, as they usually have some fabulous specials. 
Some of my favorite items: single serving guacamole, milk for around $1.00, chocolate cake, and mac and cheese cups.
Their ability to match name brands has improved and they seem to be making advances every day. I could do without the two aisles of household junk, but it changes over quickly and I occasionally find something I like.
The staff is great and they are quick on the checkouts. Worth the trip!

name: Distinctive Dermatology
categories: Family Practice, Health & Medical, Doctors, Dermatologists
text: I am not happy at all about having to come here.   Let me start by saying this is my second visit.  My first visit i was 20 minutes early and I waited an hour and half to even be brought back to be seen by the doctor.   While the doctor was very nice and thorough, i was aggravated having to wait so long.   This time the visit is a nightmare.  I was 5 minutes late due to road construction and even called them on my way to let them know.   However when I got here, the un-friendly lady at the reception window told me to hang on and walked to the back.  When she came back up she informed me that they are running an hour behind and they could fit me in as the last patient since I arrived late....are you kidding me??? She then said did you want to wait that long?  I told her I really didn't have a choice since I took off work for this appointment and then just drove 45 minutes to get here..  she then SHRUGGED HER SHOULDERS and "well you were late you know"...not one time did she apologize for the inconvenience or have any customer relation skills whatsoever.  This woman should  NOT be greeting or dealing with any patients.  Im currently sitting in the waiting room with 8 other people, and 2 of them are falling asleep in their chairs.  This is ridiculous.  Aside from the fact I was 5 minutes late, they were already running behind an hour.

name: O'Fallon Shiloh Towing
categories: Automotive, Towing
text: Great customer service!  My battery was dead and within 2 hours I was on my way.  I was expecting a longer delay and was shocked at how soon they got there. They are the only towing company I will call.

text: This was THEE worst service I've ever had. My boyfriend and I went out for valentines day, we waited 45 minutes for someone to come to our table to get drink orders after telling the manager. Because of that we received free appetizers with still no drinks. after an hour we finally got our soups and salads and couldn't get drink refill.s An hour and a half of waiting, our chef comes to the table and drops an egg at my feet and was very sloppy, and didn't do any of the fancy tricks they normally do. There were about 7 waitresses there but only one girl was covering the entire place while everyone stood around and watched her. I will never go back because of this terrible experience.

name: Plaza Wine & Liquors
categories: Beer, Wine & Spirits, Food
text: Great liquor store.  You name it they got it.  The people are exceptionally nice.  They are even open on Thanksgiving.

text: Topshooters is a great place to hang out..I love it! There's always a friendly atmosphere, darts, pool tables, and video gambling machines.  The  menu has a wide variety of choices to choose from, and is very reasonably priced.  My favorite is the buffalo chicken pizza. The lovely ladies that work there always greet you with a smile, and provide excellent service. I highly recommend checking this place out.

name: National Brake & Automotive
categories: Tires, Automotive, Auto Repair
text: Had some brake issues and Lou was able to get me in quick for evaluation and repair. Great service, friendly and competitive prices that were given up front and maintained.  I would definitely recommend!

name: Roxy's Night Club
categories: Nightlife, Adult Entertainment
text: Will really take advantage of inexperienced people. $40 for a 5 minute private dance and another $10 to go into private rooms. Other than that, really good. Can't get over the fact that I spent $40 for less than 5min, when girls were giving longer dances to people throwing dollar bills. One only spent $3 and got a longer dance. Ruined my experience.

text: If I could give this half a star I would.. this McDonald's always has problems when it comes to service. No matter what time I come it's always busy or closed before quoted hours online and on the doors. It's 8:30pm and lobby closes at 11pm but was told to go through the drive thru because they locked lobby doors. Only come to this one because it's the closest but I guess I'll have to drive further down the way to get better service than this one provides.

name: Waterloo Cinema
categories: Arts & Entertainment, Cinema
text: While this theater may be cheaper than most of its competitors it lacks in comfort and customer service. The theaters are in serious need of renovation with broken seats, badly stained carpets and what looks like storage just beneath the screen that gives the impression that providing an environment conducive to enjoying a movie is far from the minds of the owners. When there is problems with the projectors or other equipment, management does not refund, or discount the movie tickets, they just move you to another theatre that has already started the movie.

name: Dairy Queen Grill & Chill
categories: Burgers, Fast Food, Restaurants, Food, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt
text: My daughter loves the grilled cheese and that is the ONLY reason I visit this location. The drive thru staff is so unprofessional and unfriendly. I once waited at the window for SIX minutes until I was acknowledged. They saw me and I was just ignored. Something serious needs to change at this location or they are about to loose a loyal customer.

name: Valvoline Instant Oil Change
categories: Automotive, Auto Repair, Oil Change Stations
text: I LOVE this place. I won't get my oil changed anywhere else. When I purchased my car they gave me 5 free oil changes and I have only used one. I would rather pay to get my oil changed here! Every person that has ever helped me has gone above and beyond and I recommend this location to everyone I know!

name: World's Tallest Man Statue
categories: Local Flavor
text:
It's fun, it's free, and best of all, you learn a lot about Robert Wadlow - who was the tallest man in recorded history. In fact, he is currently in the Guinness World Records book. You can see and sit in his chair, as well as compare sizes with the man. I remember my family had friends from Florida recently visit and they chose to come here over many local attractions. Point is, I find it a bit sad this isn't so much of a big deal as it should be. Wadlow was more famous than for his height, he was a Goodwill ambassador who made several public appearances during his short lifetime. 

I highly recommend turning on Seminary Street and using the back parking lot.

name: So'Pasta
categories: Italian, Salad, Restaurants
text:
So' - So' - Soooo' DISAPPOINTING. and a culinarily confused restaurant. 

You would think that with Pasta in the name that their Pasta would be a signature dish but that couldn't be any farther from the truth. We got the spaghetti  and meatball and the sauce had the consistency of tomato juice and a complete lack of flavor. As for their so called "killer" meatballs the chef bypassed the spice rack on what we were served. Our other dish was their fried chicken which was dry, overcooked, (or refried) and had more breading then chicken. The only bright spot of the meal was the small side salad because the cook didn't get his or her hands on it. We also ordered Tiramisu and would have reviewed it here but the server forgot to include it in our to go bag. We were so disappointed in our entire meal that we took everything back and were given our money back. Take it from us...this place is culinary train wreck.

text: Best wings in life. Great customer service. The food is fantastic. Everytime I come here I attempt to to something different however I usually end up getting a 10 PC wings or chicken and shrimp quesadillas. The wings are delicious. Different flavors include lemon pepper, sweet and spicy, Peach Wings (yes I said peach) and a few other ones. You can throw a dart at the menu blindfolded and what ever it lands in you will not be disappointed. The food is that good. I guarantee it.
