I called the main number to the store three times to have an employee come back ten minutes later the employee finally showed up I asked to have a manager come back he come back acting cocky and like he didn't care said the song and dance and said the employee had to go all the way up front to get some key for the department and I said well why couldn't the manager which is you bring the keys back to the employee.  NOONE IN THIS LOCATION GIVES A DAMN ABOUT GOOD CUSTOMER SERVICE AND APPARENTLY NEITHER DOES THE CORPORATE OFFICE.  I go out of my way to go to another WALMART location to buy anything and I know i'm not alone in doing so AVOID THIS STORE AT ALL COST!!!! MAYBE WHEN PEOPLE QUIT COMING THE MANAGEMENT TEAM HERE WILL PULL THE HEAD OUT OF THE SAND AND REACT.

categories: Restaurants, Tex-Mex, Mexican, Bars, Nightlife
text:
Haven't been to a Chevy's in a long time. I was never really a big fan, but because of power outages, we settled on this one. There was a decent wait, also due to the outages I'm sure, but they seated us a little quicker than expected.

You could tell they were rushed, and were very apologetic about the slight messiness and the wait time. The waitress was very nice and kept up with us even though she was clearly stressed.

The food was good, if not a bit pricey for typical Tex-Mex. I got a combo pork verde enchilada and mini chimichanga. Both were pretty good. I wish the verde had a little more bite, but I like it on the spicy side. Girlfriend had the chicken fajita. Unfortunately the meat was a little dry/tasteless. The standout, surprisingly, were the beans that came as a side. They weren't the typical goopy mess, but had very good flavor and some tasty meat mixed in.

It was solid. Definitely better than I remember it being so I was impressed. Would go back.

name: American Fitness
categories: Fitness & Instruction, Gyms, Active Life
text: American Fitness is a good gym for those that live in Troy, IL. It is nothing fancy but it absolutely serves its purpose. No pool or sauna. I've been a member for more than a year and have only had to wait for a treadmill once. The gym is typically clean with plenty of machines. It has a separate free weight room that is pretty sizable. The staff are always friendly. Mark Beasley is the absolute best trainer on staff. I would give him 5 stars if he were on Yelp independently.

name: Motel 6
categories: Hotels & Travel, Hotels, Event Planning & Services
text:
"SLAMMIN' MOTEL 6" -- My nickname for this place...

Staff was nice. Our original room was facing the highway and we heard the whoosh of the passing cars, so the staff was helpful in that they moved us and were quick and accommodating. Our new room was okay, but THE DOORS ARE SO LOUD WHEN PEOPLE CLOSE THEM.  They would make large BOOM sounds when people would close them, so imagine trying to sleep in the morning with that. 

WiFi was $2.99 per device for a day, so no free WiFi here...

Also, we heard noise from the room above us and random sounds at night (which weren't amorous, thank God).  I understand that the price of less than $50 per night (at least for us when we stayed) should be considered when writing a review, but when a person is awoken by slamming doors, that's a problem.  I did my own test and let our room door shut "normally", and I was treated to another loud sound. 

Long story short, this hotel looks nice and modern, but it's just too noisy here in terms of the rooms and slamming doors, IMO.  

I wouldn't return here.

name: Ascend Collinsville Dispensary
categories: Cannabis Clinics, Health & Medical, Shopping, Tobacco Shops
text:
Talked to some tall burly security-type guy. He was so incredibly rude!! I had tried to call ahead three times and no one picked up. 
When I pulled into the lot he asked me if I was recreation or medical. I told him recreational to which he shook his head and said "you're not even supposed to pull in this parking lot. You're supposed to park in the back lot. This lot is only for Medical use." He then asked " did you make an order?" I said I had not because I had questions but I need an answer before I made a decision and he rolled his eyes " you don't know nothing about these products??" And I said "No, it's not been legal until recently". He told me to go online and educate myself. I told him "I have been reading online but still had questions" he kept interrupting me when I was trying to tell him the problems I had attempting to call the store. He sounded disgusted that I had the audacity to call " well we're really busy and we don't have time to have someone answer the phone". I asked him "what about people who drive really far to come here?" He just rolled his eyes and shook his head again. 

This guy He also informed me that the store was totally out of everything recreational and I could try ordering something now then coming back in the afternoon but I probably wouldn't be able to get a slot or any products. He also told me that if I want to find out about the products, I should just buy something small to try. I know this was probably rude of me but I replied "Or I'll just go somewhere else"

I don't think I'll be back. This was really unpleasant

name: Auffenberg Pre-Owned Super Store
categories: Automotive, Auto Repair, Car Dealers, Used Car Dealers, Auto Parts & Supplies
text: Bought a 2011 Altima, nice car, 38 k still had remaining drive train warranty, AC quit working after 5 weeks. Bad compressor, not a drive train item.  they would be happy to fix for $1200. and made it a point to tell me I should have purchased the extended warranty.  Not a single offer to comp, or even split the cost, just sorry, out of luck . The normal, bumper to bumper warranty is 36,000, so at 2 k over a major part fails, and it is to bad , so sad.  They said they checked with Nissan, for some kind of special circumstance thing, but no go. So I found an independent shop, ASE etc, who will repair for 800, I did still have to pay $100.00 for the privilege of knowing they could not help us.  They were very patronizing to my wife.  Quote "Mam, you know when it is hot outside and the humidity is high it takes a while for the ac to cool the car". Are you kidding me!  I have only been driving a car for 40 years, I didn't know that when you get in a car and it is 95 outside, 160 inside that as soon as I turn the car on it will not immediately become a cool 72.  What a jerk! I did remove the free license plate guard and give back to the service manage and told him I didn't want anyone to know I was dumb enough to buy a car from Auffenberg!

name: Club Fitness - Belleville
categories: Gyms, Cardio Classes, Fitness & Instruction, Trainers, Active Life
text: The newest addition to the club franchise features a small cross fit section as they call it.  At best it's just a "turf" area with a half tire next to pull up machines and ropes.  A wide variety of free weights are located next to its resistant machines.  As well as a large area of treadmills and cardio machines next to the tanning area.  Like all other areas, they offer free kids clubs but not like many others they have a smoothie bar that has a friendly staff.  In the far back, they have a spin class room next to the massage room and the cardio theater.  All in all, this club fitness is right up there with their Florissant location as their best gym.  Minus the whole smell of month old vomit.

categories: Event Photography, Session Photography, Real Estate Services, Event Planning & Services, Real Estate Photography, Real Estate, Photographers, Home Services
text: This is the best photographer in the area!  I have gone to them a few times now and each time I am thrilled with my photos and prints. Since I don't splurge on professional photographs often, it is important to me that I love what I am purchasing.  I will definately go back!

name: Fantastic Sams
categories: Barbers, Beauty & Spas, Hair Salons
text: I was visiting relatives in the area and asked where they would recommend to get my haircut and styled.  They said they take the whole family to Fantastic Sams.  They have been going here for the last three years and love being to just pop in with no appointment and get a great haircut.  So, with that recommendation, I was off to give them a try.  Boy, was I glad I did, I received a perfect inverted bob that normally costs $50 plus, but instead $10! Are you kidding me, really, $10, I wish i could move this Fantastic Sams close by me,  Whenever I am town, you can bet I will be back, thank you Fantastic Sams!

name: Mystic Oak Golf Course
categories: Active Life, Golf, Arts & Entertainment, Country Clubs, Restaurants
text:
The Ridge, offers golfers a fairly memorable 18 hole golf outing at a decent price ($24 all you can play after 3 w/ cart). The course is kept up very nicely on the fairways and greens, but the tee boxes can be taken for granted by the grounds crew. 
The actual golf course set up is pretty good for a public golf club. Doglegs on most longer holes, hills and valleys throughout the course. It has water on several holes that make for risky shots, and demands club selection a little bit harder. The scenery is also pretty simplistic, but most of the course is wooded and seems natural. 
The club house is fairly small, but the food is better than expected, and the beer is cold and cheap. If in the area and are looking for a decent place to play, definitely worth checking out.

name: Gateway Motorsports Park
categories: Arts & Entertainment, Races & Competitions, Automotive, Active Life, Race Tracks
text:
My husband and I came to Gateway Motorsports Park for a non-NHRA event.  The TV show "Roadkill" was having their "Zip-Tie Drags" event there Friday-Saturday.  We got to camp out on the grass behind the raceway Friday night, and enjoy the drag races and festivities Friday night, and all day on Saturday.  The facility was clean.  The food was OK.  But we had a great time.  I just wish it wasn't 93 and humid on the 2 days we were there!  There's not much shade in the park...unless you stand under the bleachers for a bit.  

We'd been to the park a couple of months prior to this event, for a separate event put on by Hot Rod Magazine, called the "Hot Rod Power Tour."  You could enter to have your hot rod or muscle car in the Power Tour, or you could be a spectator.  Either way, you get to park your car inside the drag strip for a car show.  People come from all over to show off the hard work they did on their vintage vehicles, and then many follow the tour from town to town through a few different states.  It's usually a week long event, but we only came for the one day.

I never imagined being in this area of IL twice times within the same year, but we were, and had a great time. 

P.S. - If you're staying in the area, there's a delicious pizza place in Edwardsville called Peel Wood Fired Pizza.  And there's a delicious burger place called Swingers in Normal, IL.  The best burgers I've ever had, seriously.  They're about 20-30 mins from the motorsports park though.  We couldn't find any good food in the area of Madison without going into St. Louis.

name: Club Whisker Bones
categories: Pet Boarding, Pet Services, Pet Groomers, Pets, Pet Training, Pet Sitting
text: I wish I could give them 10 stars.  We started taking our puppy to daycare and he's loved it. He comes home exhausted and gets excited when we pull into the parking lot. From the start I've told my husband you can tell how much they truly love the dogs there and how nice the staff is.  They have gone above and beyond in talking to us about our puppy, loving him and making us feel like we are part of the whisker bones family.  They also send report cards with pictures and videos which is nice to see the little guy having fun.  We can't give them enough recommendations or stars.  If you're looking for a place that clearly will love your dog and welcome him like family vs just another daycare/boarder then this is the place for you!!

text: Nothing special to say about the Freddy's Frozen Custard.  Stopped in on a Friday afternoon specifically to try the frozen custard.  I had heard people say how good it was and since I consider myself somewhat of a custard connoisseur I had to give it a try.  I ordered a small Reese's PB concrete.  Let's just say 80% of it was plain vanilla custard.  Not mixed well and definitely very cheap on the peanut butter cups put into it.  Not happy.  I wouldn't be that disappointed if the custard was at least sweet and creamy, but that wasn't the case.  It was very, very thick and almost had zero taste.  We may come back to try the food here, but I will not be having any more custard.  I did notice they had a sign that said military receives a 15% discount on Mondays, so I guess we will be back on a Monday.

name: Foley Dental Group
categories: General Dentistry, Health & Medical, Periodontists, Dentists, Oral Surgeons
text:
After 35 years at the same dental practice, unfortunately, for several reasons I had to change. As I had heard good things about Foley & it was close to home, I made an apt with them. One of the worst mistakes of my life.

According to them, I needed a re-do root canal, several crowns replaced, a tooth extracted & bone graft, 2 implants and braces!!!  

I was charged $235.00 for a Periodontist consult.  I was told that if I didn't have the implants, that $180.00 would be refunded.  I decided to wait on the implants, but do the extraction/bone graft. Originally the $180.00 was applied toward the extraction, which was fine & I actually had a balance due me.  The day of the extraction, I was told that not only did I owe an additional $80.00 for anesthesia, that they had forgotten to charge me,  but also the $180.00 because the other $180.00 was for the consult/xray. 

After I said no, I was told that the $180.00 would be refunded if I didn't have the implants, they said fine & that it would be waived.  I paid the additional for the anesthesia and had the procedure.  Three months later, I received a bill for the difference between what they owed me and the $180.00 saying payment was due immediately.

This wasn't the 1st billing issue I'd had with this office either.  They constantly misquoted a price or "forgot" to charge for a service/fee. Every time I walked in the office for an appt. they would tell me I owed more for some reason (never showed me a bill or a reason in writing).  

I terminated my relationship with this practice & have sought the opinions of 2 other reputable practices in the area. Both of these practices did the consults for free, including state of the art xrays, gum evaluations & biopsies for ca. Both practices have said that I do not need any more crowns replaced, that I don't need braces and if I hadn't let Foley's practice extract my tooth, I wouldn't need the implants either.

name: Weber Ford
categories: Automotive, Car Dealers
text: Buyer beware!  Weber Ford must not have much faith in the used cars they sell.  We purchased 2 used cars from Weber Ford (previously we purchased 2 used cars from Koetting Ford and had very good experiences with them).  First car we purchased had trouble with the sale where we were over charged for the extra warranty (?) and we ended up losing money and we said we would never go back but we did and the second car purchase (2016 Explorer) one 1 key fob provided with no key inside it (you would think that they would check such things!!) and the complete undercarriage cover missing which protects the motor and the catalytic converter from water and debris. Hopefully we don't find anything else wrong!! I know that most used cars are sold as is but you would think that buying a used car from a large car dealer such as Weber Ford would be safer than buying a used car from a questionable used car lot. Very, very disappointed and would not recommend Weber Ford.

name: Midwest Twisters
categories: Gymnastics, Active Life, Kids Activities, Party & Event Planning, Sports Clubs, Event Planning & Services
text:
Very mixed reviews on this place. My sons take their Fitness Heroes class and today I took all three of my kids to their Open Gym. The facility is great. Lots of cool things to do. Unfortunately, my boys don't like the class they're in. A lot of time is spent on stretching and warming up....seriously. It's a 55 minute class and they warm up for a solid 35 to 40 minutes of it. My boys want to be on the equipment. Who wouldn't? They get very little time on it.
Also, the coaches seem like they'd benefit from a little background in age appropriate expectations. The day my boys decided they hate the class--a day they left class in tears--was when they were taken to the gymnastics gym as a class and given directions for a 7 or 8 part circuit. My boys are 6 and 9. They, and every other kid, could only hold onto two or three of the instructions. So they started in and when the fourth obstacle came, they did it wrong...because kids that age can't remember that many steps!! And for getting it wrong, they were yelled at and shamed in front of the class. They received this because they were at the start of the line. No one else knew what to do either.
I've noticed they don't go in that gym anymore. Still, that shaming did my boys in. They're very good boys who aren't used to being yelled at by a coach in that angry manner. It ruined the class for them. We're sticking it out to the end of the session, but no more after that.
Also, we went to Open Gym today because they always complain about not getting time on the equipment. I also brought my daughter. They only had the gymnastics side open for a long time. My daughter, who has issues with anxiety among other things, finally tried some equipment. Every time she got up the nerve to try something, she was told she was too old for it (she's 11 and supposedly allowed at Open Gym). The obstacle course, the bars, the trampoline.... Each time she was so embarrassed for being admonished. There were no signs indicating age and they didn't tell us going in, so she couldn't have known. This left her with almost nothing to do in the only gym they had open. With about 50 minutes left in Open Gym, they finally opened up the other gym. She went in and tried some stuff, but after a bit she found herself in trouble for other unknown rules....don't step on a mat, don't walk on that in that direction, don't go on that until you show us you can do x, y, and z. She finally gave up. 
Oh, and she was told she couldn't go on stuff without her hair up (which, if it's a rule, fine), but at least THREE other girls were doing everything with their hair down and yet, my daughter gets spoken to about it twice (the first time they gave her permission with some stipulations).

So, my older son had a great time once they opened the Fitness Heroes gym. My younger son was less than thrilled and my daughter was incredibly discouraged.

So, I cannot recommend their classes and I can recommend their Open Gym with certain stipulations....make sure, before you go, that they'll actually have both gyms open--especially if your child is over 8. And don't bring a kid who get nervous when y

name: Kloss Furniture
categories: Shopping, Furniture Stores, Home & Garden
text: We had a great experience buying a kitchen table with Kloss. Our salesman Kipp was amazing! We walked in  The store and we had already looked at many stores for a kitchen table, but they had just the one we were looking for and Kipp wasn't high pressure or anything. He just asked if we needed any help, and he llet us look by ourselves and didn't keep following us around. We picked out a table and we had it custom built and he text me a several times to make sure that he got it right. He worked with us so well and made sure that I was updated at all times on the delivery and any changes with the order. It's weird because normally I hate buying furniture, but this was a really great experience. Next time I go furniture shopping I'm going to start at Kloss.

name: Mystic Vapes
categories: Vape Shops, Tobacco Shops, Shopping
text: The staff here is super friendly and knowledgeable! We have visited many vape shops and is always a let down when we know more than the workers luck for us that's not the case at mystic vape. Excellent selection of both house blend juices and premium juice.  Plus they carry my favorite line, boosted. highly suggest people that are new to vapping check it out they will teach you how to use your equipment properly and to its full potential.

name: The Home Depot
categories: Home & Garden, Building Supplies, Hardware Stores, Appliances, Home Services, Shopping, Nurseries & Gardening
text: Great staff and the store is clean and Odor free that is always a plus. They didn't have want I wanted at the store :/ but they looked it up on their online store and had it :)  great customer service!

text:
We tried a grilled cheese/pulled pork mix sandwhich and it was phenominal!  The potato salad is fluffy and perfect to me.  The cornbread is so good my two year old had two whole muffins on her own.  The flavor of their sweet & mild sauce is sure to please any bbq fan.  I'm not a big fan of their baked beans they taste like canned pork n beans.

This is a place you can try time and time again as i saw at least 4 different meals i wanted to try just in one seating and have decided I must go back very soon to try another.  

Compared to 17th st and bandanas I prefer here, it is on a bit of a pricier side but worth what you pay for.  It is not as expensive as 17th street and not as cheap as Bandana's so its definitly that middle way.  I have heard thru the server grapevine that their nachos on mondays are to die for.  I will have to try one Monday...

text: We stopped on a trip to pickup a new church van.   The building is very cool.  Beautiful woodwork and incredibly nice people there.   Now for the bbq.  It was FANTASTIC.  I'm a native KC bbq fan and this is just as great.   Make sure you stop in.  You won't be disappointed.

name: Rowan Tire & Auto Service
categories: Oil Change Stations, Auto Repair, Automotive, Tires
text: We needed a new transmission and they did an excellent job. They were wonderful about communicating with us  and I would certainly recommend their work.

name: Walgreens
categories: Food, Beauty & Spas, Cosmetics & Beauty Supply, Convenience Stores, Shopping, Drugstores, Photography Stores & Services
text:
I like Walgreens for one reason, Walgreen Rewards. The discounts can get deep. I have walk in got $60 worth of product and only paid $35-40.  I like that I can usually find As Seen On Tv products. I don't like that this Walgreens seems to me to be hard to get in and out of the parking lot. Everytime I go to leave I end up almost getting creamed by someone not paying attention or try to go to fast to cut through the red lights. 

Needless to say that this is not My Walgreens.

text: A great hometown bar atmosphere with great food and drinks.  Has yummy homemade pizza all the time,  Mexican Tuesdays, fish on Fridays, and homemade fried chicken on the weekend.  The prices for all drinks are fair, not over priced and great people!

name: Schnucks - Collinsville
categories: Drugstores, Food, Bakeries, Flowers & Gifts, Fashion, Department Stores, Grocery, Florists, Shopping
text: Great store. They have a very wide selection of food including an organic food section, which I find amazing. Very good customer service. When I asked where a product was the employee took me directly to it instead of just telling me where to find it.

name: AutoZone Auto Parts
categories: Automotive, Auto Parts & Supplies
text: I want to give a special Thank You to Susie, the Technician who helped me replace my battery. She was very professional, courteous, and patient while working her way through a long line of customers. She helped a younger & newer coworker through several procedural things with the register, jumped outside (on a very cold day) to replace someone's wiper blades, and then helped me replace my battery and get warranty credit for the old one. She had an outstanding personality and stood out among her coworkers (who were not nearly as enthusiastic about Customer Service). I've been coming to this store for many years and it is refreshing to work with people like Susie. Management and other store employees should take note and ask Susie about her approach to making customers feel valuable and promoting the AutoZone brand...........

name: Weber Chevrolet Columbia
categories: Auto Parts & Supplies, Auto Repair, Car Dealers, Body Shops, Automotive
text: My husband and I set up a time with George Weber Chevrolet to look at cars, specifically because they were the only place to contact us and offer to help us find a new car when we started looking. Our experience was at the minimum, exceptional, there is no way to describe in a short note all the moments of customer service, they went way above and beyond to help us as we had not purchased a vehicle in over 7 years. We now have a home for future purchases. Gary and Cori Miller

name: QuikTrip
categories: Food, Automotive, Gas Stations, Fast Food, Convenience Stores, Restaurants
text:
Sells three grades of self service gasoline at reasonable prices.  Coffee & hot drinks, fountain drinks, sandwiches & wraps, donuts & pastries, snacks and a large refrigerated section that makes you think you're at a super market.
It's open 24-7-365, and because of that it's actually really a safe place due to it being a favorite spot for police and ambulance crews to hang out over night.
It's at the corner of IL. Hwy 111 & 140.  Be careful using YELP map illustrations, they have a habit of being wrong most of the time.

name: Wood River Donut Shop
categories: Donuts, Food, Restaurants
text: Everything you could ever want in a donut shop. Great coffee, pastries, apple fritters( the bomb!!) and the most fantastic biscuits and gravy!!!! The regulars in the early morning are a slew of retired guys. Friendly and welcome always glad to chat with you. My new buddy is a 83 yr old retired watch maker whose from nearby Bethalto. I love talking to him and hearing his stories. This place has great service and prices are reasonable. Love this place!!!

text: Horrible place to go to. Service sucked. The food was awful!!!! The sign says real authentic Mexican food. Which was a completely lie. I asked for carne asada tacos and they give me some weird watery meat. And the cheese tasted gross, i got two little pieces of lettuce and my taco was soaked in grease  same goes for my quesadilla. Had the runs for a whole day. Makes my stomach hurt just thinking bout it.  Oh yea. Salsa was just water. Literally tasted like tomato paste.

name: Meineke Car Care Center
categories: Oil Change Stations, Tires, Automotive, Auto Repair
text:
Shopped around... Looked at reviews. Saw that most of the bad reviews were old. 

Decided to give them a chance. 

Dealer had quoted $1500 for the muffler repair. Other similar shops quoted $250.

Went in spoke with Cody and received a $175 quote  and they could have done in 2 hours.

Work is warrantied for a year. Was completed in 1 hour and within quote. 

I wasn't pressured to purchase needless products. And their assessment of the issue was the same as the dealer and other shops. They were just able to replace the muffler without the expense of replacing the entire exhaust.

I will update if any issues arise. But I was satisfied with the service and the experience.

name: Simons Auto Repair
categories: Auto Repair, Automotive
text:
Based on 10+ years of doing business with them I can absolutely say this is the best shop you'll find anywhere.  

It would be ridiculous for me to claim they never make a mistake, but if you want a better picture of their performance over time, I suggest you go to 

https://www.surecritic.com/reviews/simons-auto-repair 

and see what many others are saying about Simons.  Out of 113 reviews (as of 6/2018)  92% are 5-star, and the rest are 4-star--not a negative one in the lot.

As a fellow auto owner and repair consumer, I feel bad for the reviewer who had a poor experience at Simons. I don't doubt his word, but in fairness I don't think that accurately reflects the bigger picture.

BTW, nobody asked me to write this, I don't work with or for Simons, I don't know anyone at Simons, I'm not related to anyone there, and I have not received an incentive from anyone or any agency to submit this review. I've put it here based only on my own personal satisfaction with the service they provide.

name: Scott Credit Union
categories: Home Services, Mortgage Brokers, Real Estate, Banks & Credit Unions, Financial Services
text: I live in O'Fallon & drive into Fairview Heights to do my banking. The tellers I've encountered at the O'Fallon branch are not friendly. There is one that goes out of her way to be rude every single time! I even called the branch manager to complain & I've never done that in my entire life! The drive into FVH location is well worth it!

name: Subway
attributes: {'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
categories: Restaurants, Fast Food, Delis, Sandwiches
text:
I eat at Subways often. I hadn't been to this one but had an appointment nearby, so stopped for lunch. At the time, I actually thought to myself that I like the vibe in there and appreciated the plentiful seating. I even thought to myself that I would be sure to come back to this one. The place was doing a good amount of business.
I ordered an egg white and cheese flatbread. The young man who made it was delayed a bit as he tried to find the eggs. They clearly weren't where he expected in the full (closed) refrigerator....this isn't my first egg white and cheese....I see where they're usually kept. Another employee pointed out to him that the eggs are now kept in a new spot. It was up on the counter near the condiments. Odd spot. He took one and proceeded to make my order.
I wish I'd given more thought to the fact that they've started keeping their eggs out where it's "chilled" a bit and not in a cold fridge.
Nope. Bad move.
I later became violently ill. Vomiting, diarrhea, muscle and joint pain, headache, chills. Food poisoning!!!
That egg was the only possible culprit, as nothing else I'd had at any point was capable of causing food poisoning. And it wasn't a bug, because I can't keep my kids away from me even while sick and they are all perfectly healthy. Plus given the timing, symptoms, and duration....it was the egg.
I actually had to postpone an important medical test scheduled for the following day because of this.
Please consider relocating your eggs to the colder refrigerator.

name: Jack Schmitt Ford
categories: Car Dealers, Automotive
text: I  had a horrible experience with Jack Schmitt Ford in Collinsville, IL.  Especially with the GM and sales rep Chris.  My husband and I went there 2 days ago to look for a convertible that Chris said he had.  Lie #1.  No convertible on lot. I then told him I found one at Pundman Ford in St. Charles and Chris said he could get that car for me at the same price.  Lie #2. Chris called me on Tuesday and left a voice message that said "We have the car." Lie #3. I spoke with Chris and told him what I needed for my trade-in and he said he could do that. Lie #4.  When I showed up to get my nice car I was told it was not on the lot, i was told since they were getting the car from anothr dealer there would be fees, and the GM offered me $2k less than Auffenberg and Pundman! Chris tried to steal a deal from Pundman with lies and false promises and lied to me. The GM also said I could look for another car AFTER I TOLD THEM ABOUT THIS ONE! Chris tried to take the car I found!  SHAME ON YOU CHRIS.

name: Friar Tuck Beverage
categories: Beer, Wine & Spirits, Food
text: Friar Tuck Edwardsville is the best place to buy not only wine, beer and liquor, but various set-ups and bar ware. The employees always go out of their way to be helpful, friendly and professional. Their Saturday taste tests for wine and other items are great, there are always one or more items we enjoy and buy, and the staff is extremely knowledgeable and answer any and all questions. Saturday taste tests are a must if you haven't tried them yet!  Very clean store and great prices!

name: Little Caesars Pizza
attributes: {'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "'quiet'", 'HasTV': 'True'}
categories: Pizza, Restaurants
text:
WOW! I haven't had Little Caesars pizza in a while, but I'm glad I took my friends advice,and gave them another chance. The pizza we get from Little Caesars now is head and shoulders above what they used to serve, and far better than any other chain pizza place in the area (Pizza Hut, Dominoes, Papa John's).

My wife and I started getting little Caesars when they started offering their pretzel crust pizza. If you want a delicious savory pizza with buttery crust, look no further-this stuff is seriously the bomb!

We decided to also give little Caesars deep dish (Detroit style) pizza a try when they came out with that since Pizza Hut's deep dish is not the same as it used to be (and since we liked the pretzel crust so much) and it did not disappoint. The employee said they use olive oil to make the pizza, but I don't know how you can get such a buttery tasting crust with olive oil, and frankly I don't care. The pizzas are always cooked to perfection (crunchy on the bottom without being burnt, and soft in the middle without being doughy). 

Our new favorite (and "cheat day") pizza is the nine dollar "Detroit style" box special [1 pepperoni deep dish,1 garlic cheese deep dish]. You get so much pizza that we have enough left for the next day! For nine bucks! You will have a hard time finding a better pizza for the price, and even many expensive pizza places can't compete with little Caesars new offerings.

The only drawback we have experienced at the Fairview Heights store is that the owners tend to under staff the restaurant. The workers work their behind off, so be patient with them because it's not their fault the owner doesn't want to shell out a couple more bucks to adequately staff the restaurant. Other than that I have no complaints with Fairview Heights Little Caesars.

I'm waiting for my wife to get back from little Caesars right now *stomach growls*as Saturday is cheat day in our house, and little Caesars nine dollar box special is on the menu! Do yourself a favor and treat yourself to one today. I guarantee you won't be sorry!

name: Red'z Rib Shack
categories: Restaurants, Barbeque
text: After hearing all the hype about their good Q I had to take the 20 min drive & was I disappointed! The sauce was average on the vinagery side. Some of the meat on the ribs were chewy but I have to admit some were fall off the bone tender! Their Q is more boiled or baked than cooked on the grill. The baked beans were average & the potato salad was really onion salad,way too much onion in the salad! The meat wasn't seasoned or if it was I couldn't taste it! They don't have ribtips on the menu but when asked they did say they could make some up! Why not have it on the menu that's the number 1 seller in BBQ restaurants! The food is average at best, if you have a taste for Q & is close by then I guess you could patronize them! I will not make the trip again,there are plenty of mediocre BBQ restaurants near me! The lady who waited on me was nice & personable. When I pulled up to the drive thru no other cars were insight and that was around 2:00pm.I spent around $25.00 for a whole rib(extra sauce),small potato salad & a small baked beans.

name: Hilton Garden Inn St. Louis Shiloh/O’Fallon
categories: Hotels & Travel, Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Venues & Event Spaces
text:
Stayed here on one of my many many business trips. Compared to other HGIs, I would say this was right up there! Very impressed with the cleanliness and appearance of the hotel. The room was equally clean and comfy. Even dined here in the mornings for breakfast and the buffet is 4/5 stars. Good selection of tasty items. 

Would stay here again in a heartbeat. Highly recommend.

name: Bandana's Bar-B-Q - Fairview Heights
attributes: {'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'loud'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'beer_and_wine'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
categories: Sandwiches, Food, Barbeque, Restaurants, Desserts
text: This is some seriously good barbecue. Sure, it is a chain but they most certainly got the recipe right. Over the course of several visits, I had the brisket, ribs, and the pulled pork. All of them were very good with such a variety of sauces to choose from that the combinations were endless.  To clarify, the meat was delicious without needing to put any sauce on it. To me, that is always the mark of a good barbecue place.  Are the sauces there as a compliment or because the meat is so terrible that you need to cover it up with something?  The atmosphere of the restaurant definitely left something to be desired. If you can look past the somewhat cheap feel of the restaurant, you will find some really good food.

name: Jack Schmitt Auto World
categories: Tires, Automotive, Car Dealers, Auto Repair, Auto Parts & Supplies
text: Needed quick service yesterday on my mothers car and was quite pleased with the quick response I received. Customer service was happy to help. Thanks Jack  Schmitt team.

name: Hampton Inn Collinsville
categories: Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Hotels & Travel
text: Clean room. The suite is fabulous if you have a child. Extra living space and tv are awesome!!

name: Chicken Salad Chick
categories: Chicken Shop, Sandwiches, Southern, Restaurants
text: Hello  everyone  I came in yesterday I was surprised by the restaurant  how it looked very nice  I missed the  family  event Monday and Tuesday  everyone seemed very nice I saw a girl i worked with at Krabi kingz in O'Fallon il  I guess next time I'll have some lunch  but it was very nice all clean  bathrooms  but I noticed no outside dinning and no bike racks for bikes well there's always summer they will have all that  well anyway every thing was very nice.  Ill be back congratulations  best wishes

name: Academy Sports + Outdoors
categories: Sporting Goods, Fitness/Exercise Equipment, Ski & Snowboard Shops, Swimwear, Fashion, Shopping, Outdoor Gear, Shoe Stores, Sports Wear
text:
Doing last minute gift shopping and stumbled upon this place. This store is fairly new as, I believe, they have only been open a few months. At this time of the year you expect the store to look disorganized and disheveled, but that was not the case here. It was clean and organized! The layout is similar to other sporting goods stores but everything is spread out nicely and the area they have the shoes set up in is spacious which can allow for many people to shop, look and try on shoes without feeling like you're in a mosh pit!

I was able to locate a reasonably priced football for my cousin (they actually had quite a few sales on shoes, clothes, outdoor, and sporting equipment that I rarely saw in other stores like this). That made this lady happy!!  Mission accomplished. I will return the next time I am looking for anything related to sports or athletic gear!

name: Atlantis Pools
categories: Home Services, Pool & Hot Tub Service
text: Customer service is abysmal.  I live in Springfield where they had a store until last November when they changed it to a summer-only store.  I bought a hot tub there 6 years ago and when I went in for service the Springfield manager was cleaning out a near empty store and told me to call the Alton store. So today I called Alton and they told me they will no longer provide service from November through March in Springfield which is pretty much prime season for hot tubs.  This tells me they are only interested in sales and not customer service.  You will do better on chemicals from Amazon and you on your own for service.  I would never buy from people who apparently have no intention of providing support for their customer base.

name: Sever's Market
categories: Grocery, Food
text: Good priced meat per lb, and nice little selection of necessities (paper towels, toilet paper, pasta salads).

name: Walmart
categories: Department Stores, Fashion, Electronics, Grocery, Discount Store, Drugstores, Shopping, Food, Mobile Phones
text: To my dismay this is the closest Walmart to me! I hate every second of having to go in there and try my damnedest not to go there except when absolutely necessary! 30 registers and 5 will be open! Usually a mess in there! Cashiers are most of the time grouchy and act like you are bothering them! Not to say that all of them act that way but alot do! Not unheard of for a line of people to be standing there and one to go on break! Really? If you can find another one...do it!

name: Peace by Piece Company
categories: Shopping, Shoe Stores, Jewelry, Women's Clothing, Fashion
text: I've been here several times but only purchased twice. The other times I was with someone looking for a gift, and we have always left with something. I love that they carry a majority of American made products, and they have beautiful pieces that aren't offered in huge quantities. I like that I may not see someone else with my top on! I bought a gorgeous little studded tee a couple years ago, and it still looks as good as the day I bought it. I also bought my first and only pair of Toms here. Toms aren't really my thing but these happened to be a melon colored open toe wedge. Much more my speed. They were having a sale, and I got them for $30. What a steal! I can say I slightly agree with the review saying staff can be overly helpful. I appreciate an attentive sales person, but at some point, after I've said, "I'm just looking," please back off just a little. Don't go AWOL on me, but give me a little room to breathe. However, I really can't call this a flaw of "charge" them a star for it. There are places I'd give my right arm to find an associate much less have one actually help me. I haven't been into PBP for some time. Guess it's time I venture back. If you haven't stopped in, do yourself a favor and do so.

name: Eckert's Millstadt Fun Farm
categories: Local Flavor, Pumpkin Patches, Shopping, Farms, Pick Your Own Farms, Arts & Entertainment, Home & Garden, Farmers Market, Festivals, Food
text:
Took our group of young teens here this weekend as part of our church group. $10 per person was the admission price, and we went later in the afternoon (and later in the pumpkin patch season) so the crowds were manageable. 

Despite having a group of 13-year-olds, I think everyone had a pleasant time. We took advantage of watching the pig races, the pumpkin cannon, the petting zoo of baby animals, and the jumping bag/pillow thing. The chaperones weren't bored, and I was able to bring my puppy as well. :-)

name: I Think I Can Learning Center
categories: Psychiatrists, Tutoring Centers, Doctors, Education, Health & Medical
text:
I have nothing but contempt for this place.  At the time, it was the only place that we could realistically go to on a regular basis, so we put up with their nonsense for almost a year.  Now before I go into detail, I think it's important to clarify that these people are DOCTORS.  They're tasked with treating a wide variety of mental illnesses; they hold their patients' mental health in their hands.  This is why I am so appalled by the way their business is run.  A kid messes up my sandwich?  No big deal.  A store charges my card twice for one purchase?  It sucks, but it'll get fixed and I'll live.  My wife's mental health suffers due to incompetent staff?  Unbelievable.

First, let's address actually GETTING an appointment here.  You'll want to start by calling...  Just don't call at any time in the middle of the day, as it appears both people at the front desk take lunch at the same time for a 5-hour period.  Don't bother leaving a message, they won't call back.  Just keep calling until you finally get a hold of someone, who will schedule your first visit for next month.  

A month goes by and you go to your appointment, arriving 15 minutes early to take care of any paperwork.  After an hour of waiting with no explanation, you finally meet with your therapist/psychiatrist (in my wife's case, she needed to see both, which doubled the amount of painful visits), who will try their hardest to get you out the door as soon as possible.  Wonderful, isn't it?  I understand that the average psychiatrist appointment is short due to the nature of their job, but they have no right to cut the hour-long therapy sessions we paid for short.  But hey, if anything major comes up that you couldn't cover in your session, "you can call me directly any time"...  Lies.  

First, read up a couple paragraphs and you'll see how difficult it is to get a hold of the office.  The doctor won't answer their cell.  The front desk won't answer their phones.  If they do, they will forward you to a voicemail so you can "leave a message for the doctor", and that message will never be returned.  How can they do this?  Seriously...  How can someone sit there, listen to some crying over the phone begging for help, and just decide to never respond?  What kind of sick individuals would do this?  Okay okay, I exaggerate a bit...  No one is sitting there ignoring cries for help.  They're just ignoring the messages entirely.  My wife tried to call them as instructed whenever something came up, and after a few months the voice mailbox was full, never to be emptied.

So I bet you're thinking, "These doctors must suck!" right?  Well, to be honest, not entirely...  This is actually where it just gets weird.  When we first went there, both the therapist and psychiatrist seemed kind and knowledgeable, but seemed to be struggling to work around ITIC's poor management.   If put in a professional environment in which the staff answered the phones, properly relayed messages, and staggered appointments in a way that prevented significant overlap, I imagine they would do quite well.  Too bad...  But I did say it gets weird, didn't I?  My wife's therapist disappeared...  No, I'm not making this up.  She just disappeared.  When we went to our appointment, they informed us that she simply never came back from vacation and they couldn't make contact with her (note that they didn't call and tell us BEFORE I took time off work to drive down to the office...).  Similarly, my wife's psychiatrist simply up and retired with no prior notice given to the office or his patients.  I think this shows just how little he cared for the people that relied on him.  

The final straw was the replacement psychiatrist...  A patronizing, forgetful woman of dubious intellect.  I don't know how she got the job, but after several visits in which she literally did not remember my wife and was unfamiliar with the medicines she had been taking, we called it quits.

Ultimately, I feel this place did more harm than good to my wife's mental health.  We both agree that since seeking help elsewhere, everything has been so much better.  She actually gets to see people who care and will give her the time she needs in a stress-free environment...  I just don't understand why that's too much to ask of ITIC.

My husband even had partial plates made which match his teeth perfectly! He does comprehensive dental X-rays which helped to identify my husbands major issues! Next year I am having an implant by Dr Bell and I wouldn't consider anyone else! I really like that this practice offers dental insurance too! You would never regret joining this practice!

name: Fairfield Inn & Suites St. Louis Pontoon Beach/Granite City, IL
categories: Hotels, Hotels & Travel, Venues & Event Spaces, Event Planning & Services
text:
This location needs some attention. The building is new and the staff was nice, but otherwise they seem to be struggling with the workload.

The breakfast attendant has trouble keeping up with refilling food and supplies. At one point the plasticware was just sitting in cardboard boxes on the counter because they were too overwhelmed to keep up. Despite being new, everything is a little dirty. Your shoes stick to the floor when you walk. Rotting pizza and chicken had overflowed the outside trash can and was left for two days before being emptied. There is still a soda bottle on the ground right in front of the door.

The ceiling in our bathroom is cracking and falling down and the hardware is rusting already. The finishes are contemporary and new, but there's clearly a quality and upkeep issue.

They also incorrectly told us they allowed pets when they do not. I called and spoke with the front desk before booking to make sure pets were allowed. I even asked about the pet fee and was told $50. I double checked because that is much lower than most hotels and the front desk confirmed that yes dogs are allowed and the fee is only $50.

I then called back after I booked through the Marriott app to confirm and have the reservation noted so we would be charged the pet fee. The woman said she noted the reservation and never mentioned pets weren't allowed. At check in no one said anything despite the fact that we carried dog beds and walked two dogs down the hallway.

When the staff did eventually address the dogs they locked us out of our room instead of simply calling us. They had both our cell phones and our room number to call. At anytime they could have easily called and talked to us. Instead they locked us out of our room and said they "caught us" with dogs on the security camera, as if we did something wrong.

They agreed to let us stay, but only as a courtesy because we were Marriott members and not because they made a mistake. The tone was as if we did something wrong but they were being kind in overlooking it. No one cared we were 1,000 miles from home and worried about a place to sleep because they gave us wrong information. No one attempted to apologize or take responsibility. The manager wouldn't even speak to us. All the information was relayed through the front desk.

The remainder of the stay has been strained and stressful. The staff hasn't so much as nodded our way, apolized, or checked on us. This whole ordeal has turned what should have been a nice family trip into a really uncomfortable situation.

categories: American (New), Restaurants, Bars, Chicken Wings, Burgers, Steakhouses, Sports Bars, American (Traditional), Nightlife
text: This place never fails to screw up an order. I usually do the car side to go. I order my steak medium rare. However, since they always overcook it I suppose I should order it rare. I always order sautéed onions and mushrooms. There's always onions and hardly any mushrooms. Tonight I got 3 slices of mushrooms. So ridiculous. The last 2 times they didn't even give me the right food and so I called them. Both times I was told they would mail me a dinner since they screwed it up. Neither time did I receive anything in the mail, even though I called back to tell them I hadn't received it. Still nothing. Tonight I'm not even going to call them. I also will never eat there again. Come on people! Just get it right!!!

name: Backtothe80sarcade
categories: Arcades, Arts & Entertainment
text:
Wow, this place is a hidden gem in the Metro St. Louis area. The place is nestled just off Route 3 in an industrial park. Plenty of parking.
 
$15 per person gets you unlimited play, or $10 for two hours.

They have just about every top classic arcade game in their 50+ game collection, and my two favorites, The Simpsons and Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles. Finally beat them for the first time in 25 years without spending over $20 in quarters per game. 

They also have a pretty extensive snack bar, plus an assortment of beer, a hard cider, and Bud Margaritas. All reasonably priced.

The owner was great and very glad to have us. Can't wait to come back. Highly recommended for a slice of nostalgia and fantastic games.

name: Petco
categories: Pet Groomers, Pet Services, Pet Training, Pet Stores, Pets
text: The fact that they collect food for Bi-State Pet Food Pantry gets them 4 stars in my book.  We are huge supporters of the pet food pantry and all of the St. Louis area Petcos have a collection bin.  The staff are always friendly and they always have what we need in stock.  The store is always well kept and clean.

name: Perfect Finish Auto Center
categories: Shopping, Hardware Stores, Home & Garden, Automotive, Body Shops, Auto Repair
text: Perfect Finish did a great job repairing my Sons car and finished ahead of schedule! Steve kept me up to speed on the progress of my car and it looked like new when they were done. I would highly recommend them to everyone. Thank you so much!

name: Social Security
categories: Public Services & Government
text:
Wow. No wait at 3 pm on Tuesday. 
Niceish people. 
Apparently you can make appointments and I didn't know that. Will do so in the future. 
Twilight zone at the SS Admin.

name: The National Shrine of Our Lady of the Snows

text: Well the drive thru was nice this 2015 season but they really screwed the pooch for kids this year. No inside crafts just a puppet show and things that cost money . which we all don't have a lot of . And at the end a book no stuffed animal. And to eat in buffet is to costly for family. Will I be back just to give dioceses more money.Doubt if this Catholic man will.

name: Barber Shop
categories: Hair Salons, Beauty & Spas, Barbers
text: Great place to get your haircut!! I've tried others in town as well and not pleased! Friendly two ladies who do a great job! Simple! $16 bucks!

name: Monkey Joe's of Fairview Heights
categories: Party Supplies, Kids Activities, Amusement Parks, Event Planning & Services, Active Life
text:
I can't help but think every time I walk into this place that it would be a blast if I could run around with the reckless abandon that all of the kids that love this place do.  This is a place any child will love.  Monkey Joe's is filled with inflatable bounce house like structures.  There are slides, obstacle course like structures and so many more that just look like so much fun.  When just about every child you see is red faced and sweating you know that they are having a blast.  Cost wise it is cheaper than going to the movies and much more worth your money.  After taking your child to Monkey Joe's they will be exhausted and will sleep soundly that night.  

Unlike places like Chuck E Cheese, food is more an after thought at Monkey Joe's.  There is a concession stand, but it's not a center piece of what the place is about.  They host birthday parties and do a good job with those.  Monkey Joe's is a great place to take your child so they can burn off some of that energy that they have an abundant supply of.  

I will definitely be returning to Monkey Joe's in the near future to help my son burn off some of that energy he has so much of.

name: Diamond Nail Shop
categories: Nail Salons, Beauty & Spas
text: I used to go here with my mother, and went here to get my wedding nails.  The girl who did my manicure watched a portable DVD player that was placed under her desk the whole time, and clipped into my cuticles several times, leaving a gash on my right hand's middle finger.  DO NOT GO HERE, simple enough.

name: Bowley Cleaning
categories: Home Cleaning, Home Services, Professional Services, Office Cleaning
text: This is a bizarre company.  I had scheduled a move out/deep clean weeks in advance with Erica's company.  She arrived yesterday with her team comprised of young children.  She said she would need to come back the next day with a larger crew and ladders.  Instead, she stood me up today, has not answered the phone or returned messages, and has blocked me on Messenger where we have all of our previous correspondence.  It seems strange that she wouldn't just communicate that they did not want the work.  Luckily, I have time before the new tenant moves in and was able to reschedule with another company I've used in the past!

name: CT Hair & Nail Salon
categories: Hair Salons, Beauty & Spas, Nail Salons, Eyelash Service
text: This was the absolute worst pedicure I've ever gotten. I get a pedicure every two weeks because it's my treat to myself. So I tried them based upon a recommendation from my co-workers and they're close to home. It was a half done job and the pricing said one thing and I was charged a higher amount. Won't ever go there again

name: Burger King
categories: Restaurants, Burgers, Fast Food
text: I stop here in the mornings on my way back from dropping my Granddaughter to school.  They are SUPER NICE!!  Not a long line, which is awesome for me also.  The food looks like the food in commercials too, which is unusual, but really nice as well...  I will continue going there... great people and great food...

name: Schneider Quality Meats
categories: Grocery, Meat Shops, Specialty Food, Food
text: The only place to get brats.  They are hands down the best brats around and I have tried many other meat markets.  I can't say that I have had anything bad from here, but they are a little pricey.  I still keep coming back for the brats.  They do know that they have something special going on with their brats.  5 stars would have been granted if their prices were a little more friendly.

name: Amazing Smiles Orthodontics
address: 4905 Stone Falls Center Dr, Ste A
categories: Dentists, Health & Medical, Orthodontists
text:
They are a very busy practice.  They have all of these electronic bells and whistles.  Others may be impressed as a single working professional parent I see this as more crap to keep straight. 

Also if you have a busy professional schedule it can be a real challenge to reschedule appointments.  Between my calendar, his calendar and 2 separate offices.  This is a crucially important metric when choosing an orthodontist.

text: Very rude. Tried to order a delivery within an hour of closing anhad an extremely rude employee ask 4 times "can't you just come pick it up?" If you can't deliver until closing hours just post that.

name: Annbriar Golf Course
categories: Active Life, Golf, Restaurants
text:
This is THE BEST golf course anywhere within an hour of St Louis - SERIOUSLY!

Course conditions couldn't be better - lush fairways, smooth challenging greens, and a gorgeous layout. Designer obviously knew what they were doing, and the grounds crew deserves a lot of praise for keeping this gem looking so good. There's a lot to look at here and I always enjoy coming back.

Golfers - FIX YOUR BALL MARKS ON THR GREENS!!

name: Vern's Auto Repair
categories: Oil Change Stations, Auto Repair, Tires, Automotive
text: Had a great experience with Russ and the shop when I had to stop in for repairs on my Honda.  He went the extra mile to diagnose and help me out. I found an excellent mechanic who's reasonably priced and a fantastic guy to work with.  If you like to support small business, get a good value and quality work - make your next appointment at Vern's.

text: It's your typical jack in the box. Restaurant is clean, food is good. They seem pretty busy most of the time especially with drive thru. However, my issue is the short supply they have for anything in the dining area. All sodas are out on the coca-cola machine, water and fruit drinks are still there. Most of the dipping sauces are out, too. They said they're having delivery problems, but do have a supply in the back for drive-thru customers.

name: Wasabi Sushi Bar
attributes: {'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'HappyHour': 'True', 'DogsAllowed': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': True, 'upscale': False, 'classy': None, 'casual': True}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}"}
categories: Restaurants, Sushi Bars, Japanese
text:
This used to be one of our favorite haunts, but we moved from the area and haven't been back for a year. In that year, several things have changed:

The music is too, for want of a better term, urban nightclub. Not conducive for conversation or for enjoying a leisurely meal.

The service used to be amateur but friendly. Now it's gothy and terse.

The prices have gone way up. Rolls that were $10.50 are now $12, old price $7 now $9. But the nigiri-style has literally doubled - the price that used to get you two pieces now gets you one. So $63 later, we were still a little hungry. Everything was plenty tasty, just not much of it for the dollars.

The homey touches like actual Kikkoman bottles, Kirin beer glasses and unique little earthenware dishes have been replaced with confusing salad dressing bottles (seriously, the staff was even annoyed by them), standard glassware and sterile white ceramic squares.

Kinda like the place went a little bit upscale emo.

So I don't know that we'll be back. Maybe we'll win the lotto and then order take-out so we can take our time without the annoying music and hurried service.

text: Pizza was good, two stars due to poor quality of customer service at this location on a busy friday night. Phoned in my order, arrived at the appropriate time, no pizza. The order was lost, staff prepared another one and twenty minutes later I was handed my pizza. Understandably mistakes happen, however a simple apology would have been nice and appropriate given the circumstances. Plenty of choices for pizza, I will look elsewhere on a busy night.

text: Delicious and fast! Great service! Nice and clean newer location. Ate here for breakfast with no issues!

name: Mid America Cab Company
categories: Hotels & Travel, Transportation, Taxis
text: Horrible.  1st time 1/29, needed to get to Dr., no problem, trip cost $7.50. 2nd time, return trip, cab was a no show, multiple calls all went to recording to call back later (@4:00 pm), had to wait for family to get off work for ride home. 3rd time 2/1, needed to get back to same Dr. Office, cab again no show, finally got call through, was an hr late, and fare was almost TWICE $$, $13.50, same locations, same time of day!  Belleville needs a better service - feeling hostage to bad service -- only service I could find, shouldn't be allowed to do this to anyone.

name: Oral Surgeons of Southern Illinois
categories: Oral Surgeons, Health & Medical, Surgeons, Doctors, Dentists
text: 5 stars for an oral surgeon... must be some place huh? You know we all hate going to the dentist or having oral surgery. I had oral surgery yesterday with Dr. John Leib and he was so good at explaining everything, being supportive and careful. His staff was pleasant, especially Joly his dental assistant. Dr. Leib even called after hours last night to check on me. (Not an assistant but the dr. himself.) That's great customer service. My husband had oral surgery with his partner Dr. Schulte back in November and had the same service. They do take Tricare too and were both previous Air Force service members. I would recommend them to anyone.

name: Brite Worx Car Washery
categories: Car Wash, Automotive
text: Didn't get the bugs off the windshield and leaves a weird film all over the car and windows. Signed up for the monthly washes which turns out is not a good deal at all and requested cancellation. I never received a confirmation email so I'm hoping it cancels when requested.

name: A Plus Glass Tinting
categories: Glass & Mirrors, Auto Glass Services, Home Services, Automotive, Home Window Tinting
text: I'm shipping my car to Germany and needed it detailed. They did an amazing job! I think it was cleaner than when I bought it! I passed the inspection no problem, Thank you!

name: To-Do's
categories: Party Supplies, Event Planning & Services
text:
What can I say?  I just love To-Do's.  I shop there for every birthday, holiday and even Halloween!  I also use their streamers, balloons and window paint to decorate my car each year as I pick up my son from school (painting the car with:  2nd Grade, Here I Come!, etc.)

The staff is friendly, the selection is incredible and they always have what I'm looking for.  I heart To-Do's!  :)

name: Holiday Inn St. Louis-Fairview Heights
categories: Event Planning & Services, Venues & Event Spaces, Hotels & Travel, Resorts, Hotels
text: Best Holiday Inn in the Midwest.  Great food and atmosphere at Kems Resturaunt!  Hospitality and warm welcomes are plentiful here!  Thanks to everyone here for your hard work and dedication in making every stay excellent!

name: Edwardsville Frozen Foods
categories: Specialty Food, Food, Meat Shops
text: This weekend I found out that the beef is raised in Jerseyville, IL and the pork is raised in Trenton, IL.  So happy that what I buy here is locally sourced.

text: The food and service were great. Nothing fancy about the food, just great taste and everything appeared to be frresh.

name: Frew's Bridal
categories: Formal Wear, Bridal, Fashion, Shopping
text: If I could give negative stars I would. I ordered my wedding dress well in advance and once it arrived it was not the correct size. The general manager seemed very careless about the situation of getting the correct dress in time for my wedding. Then she told me the dress I ordered didn't look good and wasn't the correct size I explained they were the experts and they sized me all she could say was the person who helped me was no longer there.... No consideration past that. The store manager Angie was very kind and seemed to care more than her boss did. She attempted to make me happy but we came to the point where I left unsatisfied and felt as though I was treated so poorly I can't image how they stay in business when this is the biggest day of a woman's life. I live 45 minutes and made multiple trips in attempt to pick up my dress from size to alterations nothing was correct each time I went in. The facility is very nice but beyond that I recommend no one purchase from them.  Also a heads up multiple brides around me at my fittings had complaints and issues as well.... I took the dress home in a plastic bag that was tied in a knot at the bottom which the dress fell out of and drug on the asphalt on the walk to my car, not what I expected for a $1,400 purchase, Nordstrom takes better care of me when I spend $100.  Extremely disappointed and a ton of stress prior to wedding and I felt like it could have all been avoided.

name: McDonald's
categories: Coffee & Tea, Burgers, Food, Fast Food, Restaurants
text: I stopped by this place Monday 4/25/16 and ordered a breakfast sandwich. There were so many pieces of egg shell in it that I think it was done deliberately. If not, someone is very incompetent. A restaurant relies on the trust of their customers. This place lost mine.

name: Master Auto Repair
categories: Automotive, Oil Change Stations, Auto Repair, Tires
text: This has got to be the BEST mechanic ever!!!!  My husband and I were traveling from Indiana to Arizona when our windshield wiper arm broke.  I called and spoke to the owner, Ed Starns and told him my issue.  Knowing we were traveling, he worked us in and he was able to get us back on the road again for a very reasonable price.  I wish he was in Arizona as he would be my mechanic!  I strongly recommend Master Auto Repair!  Amazing customer service.

You enter into the from like you are dropping off mail. Behind the window is the coffee bar. Many coffee specialities are available. They have a bar off to the side. A limited lunch menu is why I gave them three stars. Space is filled with vintage furniture and even an old phone booth. Event space is available to rent.

name: Viva la Fiesta
categories: Nightlife, Restaurants, Mexican, Event Planning & Services, Bars, Caterers, Cocktail Bars
text: Yelp keeps eating this review but welcoming place with fun decor, warm staff and good homey food. Had the moltejeca which was yummy and can feed two. Wife had chiles rellenos, which are hard to do right, and these were just perfect. Margaritas were cheap and fine. This place is in the same place as Katrina's.

text: Ordered two cheeseburgers and got them with no meat. Seriously. No patties in either burger and this is the 2nd time it happened. I didn't notice until I was on the road so I couldn't turn around. Major league FAIL. How do you forget the hamburger patty in a hamburger? This McDonald's always sucks and ruins my food. I don't know why I go to it and probably never will again.

name: Firehouse Subs

categories: Pizza, Restaurants, Italian, Sandwiches
text:
We were staying overnight at the Journey KOA in Granite City. Tired and hungry when we arrived, we asked the KOA desk people who delivered pizza. They gave us an IMO's menu.  We were happy with the variety on the menu so we called and ordered. (6 people). 
Delivery was on time as promised. Food was hot and fresh. The delivery person and the lady who took the order were very friendly (don't forget to tip the person taking the order). 
This was a great choice after spending 14 days on the road. The food was excellent and gobbled up. By the way, we didn't order pizza. :)

name: Here Today
categories: Home Decor, Shopping, Fashion, Home & Garden, Department Stores, Discount Store
text: Here Today is a unique take on a discount store from the local minds behind the former Grandpa's stores. Here today focuses on closeout deals, from anything from food, home goods/furnishing, wine/beer, gifts, and even some appliances/electronics. The store is like Big Lots, however a bit more upscale and less cluttered. Prices are fair, and you can manage to really stock up on some name brand items at a very reasonable value. The selection is not very wide, however it can vary from week to week.  By no means is this a place that will replace Schnucks or even Shop 'N Save, however its worth checking out before to see if you can save on a few items.

name: Sammy Nail
categories: Nail Salons, Beauty & Spas
text: They sat me quickly and I decided to do a deluxe pedi. The guy hardly did his job. It called for a scrub which I didn't not get. Hot oil and it was not hot. Stones that he hardly rubbed. Wax that was left on for second. He hardly massaged and did not buff my heels or cut back cuticles or even file my nails. He only trimmed them because I asked. The mani was just ok. If I went back I would only get a basic pedi and only if I needed one in a rush. They also do eyebrow waxing but I didn't have it done. I saw someone get theirs done and they do it out in the open.

name: Joes Pizza & Pasta
attributes: {'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}"}
categories: Pizza, Restaurants, Italian, Salad
text: This is my 3rd time trying Joe's. I like sweet sauce. Their sauce is super sweet which I don't like.  I know not to order pasta dishes. However, the italian sandwich was awesome!! And this location?? I've already told several friends how nice it was compared to another location.  It's beautiful inside. Waitress was great. Wait time for food was fine... what u normally would wait. I had the moscachli (sp) ... too sweet as I already stated.  The side salad that came with it was huge! This location has a separate bar.. its very nice. They put some $$$ in this and it shows!!

name: Braeutigam Orchards
categories: Specialty Food, Food, Fruits & Veggies, Farmers Market
text: Not organic but the BEST orchard in the area. Very friendly helpful staff. U pick veggies too! Not commercial just a great place to visit. A real farm with a  new bakery.

categories: Mexican, Restaurants, Latin American
text:
There were not many vegetarian options on the menu, so my friend and I requested veggie fajitas. We were expecting a variety of veggies, but unfortunately got a sizzling plate of onions topped w/ steakfries. We also ordered the "flamin" cheese dip w/out meat. Again, we were very disappointed. The cheese was not edible, it was a glob of goo w/ a ring of grease. The only good thing about this place were the margaritas, they were ok. 
I WOULD NOT RECOMMEND THIS PLACE!!

name: Kruz Kennel Services
categories: Pet Sitting, Pet Services, Pets
text: Kruz Kennel is absolutely amazing!!! They are so kind and loving to our pets when we pick them up they smell amazing (as they give them a post kennel bath) and they act like they have spent time at a retreat. When we pick them up they are so full of life and happiness. We had them kenneled there for 10 days because of an extended vacation and the owner text us updates and even doggie selfies! We are so grateful to have such a wonderful place to board our four legged family members!

name: Bluestem Distillery
categories: Distilleries, Medical Supplies, Food, Shopping, Hotels & Travel, Tours
text: One of the best vodkas I've had in a long time.  Their facility is open for tastings along with tours plus they've got some signature cocktails.  I hope it's out in more restaurants/bars soon.  This beats the other 'local' vodka by a mile!

name: Metro Lock & Security
categories: Keys & Locksmiths, Home Services
text: Got us out of a bind over the weekend.  Our front door knob and lock seized up on us when we came home from shopping this afternoon.  We could not lock the door at all.  The technician was at our house within an hour of our call.  He replaced the front door lock and updated the cylinders on two outside doors so the new key would work on all doors.  He also made four key copies and tested them all before leaving.  A job well done.   I will call Metro again if I need additional security services.

Nice friendly staff. The Hawaiian roast beef is great.

Nothing fully special about this place. They have decent fast food and nice people working there.

text: The crab rangoon is amazing!!  Nice affordable buffet and the staff are so nice.  Dave came by to check on us several times, and you get that feeling of a great family atmosphere from everyone there.  I can't say enough how great the crab rangoon was, the best in the city by far.

name: Lucinda's Grill and Cafe
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}"}
categories: Cafes, Restaurants
text: Great American grub.  What's different about this place is that they have pretty darned good Mexican food.  I had the burritos and they were excellent.  There were a lot of customers ordering burgers and they looked really exceptional and when I go back there next week I will road test one.  The owners do the cooking and one of the owner's wives runs the cash register so there is a lot of dedicated, attentive, on-site quality control and management and they are good folks.  The building is pretty small and seating is comfortably tight but you can still talk without anyone eavesdropping.  They also offer a frequent diner program.  Ten purchases gets you $5.00 your next purchase.  They do not serve alcohol at this time.

name: O'Fallon Family Dental Care
categories: General Dentistry, Dentists, Orthodontists, Health & Medical, Cosmetic Dentists
text: Great, friendly staff. Caring and kind. My whole family goes here, and we love it! I would recommend this office to anyone.

name: Domino's Pizza
categories: Chicken Wings, Pizza, Sandwiches, Restaurants
text: We order from this Dominos all the time. They're almost always faster than expected! Only one time did we run into an interesting situation. I stood near the picture window to watch because my fur baby is a bit of a jackass and like to run out the front door. Yes, only the front, so once the tracker said the delivery was on its way, I went to watch. The driver came the wrong way through the cul-de-sac and sat in front of my house for a good 2-3 minutes and left. He didn't come back for another 10-15 minutes. By then our food was lukewarm but we were starving. I can honestly say that this has only occurred once. Every other time, our order has been piping hot--literally right out of the oven. Everything has been delivered accurately and on time (usually early!) Every business can have an off day. It happens. Humans are involved in the process. For me, it's more about how they fix a mistake rather than holding them to a standard of never making them. You won't find constant mistakes here. They're few and far between. I have to say, when I allow myself to order pizza, the Wisconsin Six Cheese is ridiculous!! It's so good. The Mediterranean Veggie sub is so good, and my family loves the Brooklyn crust. The new Parmesan bites are killer. Possibly literally because they're doused in butter, but on an indulgence night...mmm holy delicious!

name: Chinese Dragon
categories: Chinese, Restaurants
text: Clean, friendly, family owned restaurant. The food is delicious. One of the better Chinese restaurants in the area. You can sit and eat there, but the dining area is small. We generally order carry out.

name: Cyclery & Fitness Center
categories: Fitness/Exercise Equipment, Eyewear & Opticians, Shopping, Sporting Goods, Bikes
text: Since moving to the area I decided to purchase a bike. I had a great experience with the staff, they were very helpful and patient. After I decided on a bike, they helped me set up the bike mount in my vehicle. I returned a week later to purchase a burley trailer for my child. There were a few options and I was unsure on which route to go but the employee working with me helped identify the features Evan trailer had. Once I made up my mind, they put it together and helped me to my vehicle to load everything up. After using the trailer twice I did have an issue with one of the tires but they replaced the tube once I returned to the store for assistance.
